Field.Name: Account
Field.Description: Account mnemonic as agreed between buy and sell sides, e.g. broker and institution or investor/intermediary and fund manager.

Field.Name: AdvId
Field.Description: Unique identifier of advertisement message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: AdvRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: AdvSide
Field.Description: Broker's side of advertised trade

Field.Name: AdvTransType
Field.Description: Identifies advertisement message transaction type

Field.Name: AvgPx
Field.Description: Calculated average price of all fills on this order. For Fixed Income trades AvgPx is always expressed as percent-of-par, regardless of the PriceType (423) of LastPx (31). I.e., AvgPx will contain an average of percent-of-par values (see LastParPx (669)) for issues traded in Yield, Spread or Discount.

Field.Name: BeginSeqNo
Field.Description: Message sequence number of first message in range to be resent

Field.Name: BeginString
Field.Description: Identifies beginning of new message and protocol version. ALWAYS FIRST FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted) Valid values: FIXT.1.1

Field.Name: BodyLength
Field.Description: Message length, in bytes, forward to the CheckSum field. ALWAYS SECOND FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

Field.Name: CheckSum
Field.Description: Three byte, simple checksum (see Volume 2: "Checksum Calculation" for description). ALWAYS LAST FIELD IN MESSAGE; i.e. serves, with the trailing <SOH>, as the end-of-message delimiter. Always defined as three characters. (Always unencrypted)

Field.Name: ClOrdID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by the buy-side (institution, broker, intermediary etc.) (identified by SenderCompID (49) or OnBehalfOfCompID (5) as appropriate). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms, particularly those which electronically submit multi-day orders, trade globally or throughout market close periods, should ensure uniqueness across days, for example by embedding a date within the ClOrdID field.

Field.Name: Commission
Field.Description: Commission. Note if CommType (13) is percentage, Commission of 5% should be represented as .05.

Field.Name: CommType
Field.Description: Specifies the basis or unit used to calculate the total commission based on the rate.

Field.Name: CumQty
Field.Description: Total quantity (e.g. number of shares) filled. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: Currency
Field.Description: Identifies currency used for price. Absence of this field is interpreted as the default for the security. It is recommended that systems provide the currency value whenever possible. See "Appendix 6-A: Valid Currency Codes" for information on obtaining valid values.

Field.Name: EndSeqNo
Field.Description: Message sequence number of last message in range to be resent. If request is for a single message BeginSeqNo (7) = EndSeqNo. If request is for all messages subsequent to a particular message, EndSeqNo = "0" (representing infinity).

Field.Name: ExecID
Field.Description: Unique identifier of execution message as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN) (will be 0 (zero) for ExecType (150)=I (Order Status)). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day or the life of a multi-day order. Firms which accept multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ExecID field to assure uniqueness across days. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int).

Field.Name: ExecInst
Field.Description: Instructions for order handling on exchange trading floor. If more than one instruction is applicable to an order, this field can contain multiple instructions separated by space. *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" *** (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

Field.Name: ExecRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier used with Trade, Trade Cancel and Trade Correct execution types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: HandlInst
Field.Description: Instructions for order handling on Broker trading floor

Field.Name: SecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityID(48) value.

Field.Name: IOIID
Field.Description: Unique identifier of IOI message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: IOIQltyInd
Field.Description: Relative quality of indication

Field.Name: IOIRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE, transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: IOIQty
Field.Description: Quantity (e.g. number of shares) in numeric form or relative size.

Field.Name: IOITransType
Field.Description: Identifies IOI message transaction type

Field.Name: LastCapacity
Field.Description: Broker capacity in order execution

Field.Name: LastMkt
Field.Description: Market of execution for last fill, or an indication of the market where an order was routed Valid values: See "Appendix 6-C"
Field.Elaboration: In the context of ESMA RTS 1 Annex I, Table 3, Field 6 "Venue of Execution" it is required that the "venue where the transaction was executed" be identified using ISO 10383 (MIC). Additionally, ESMA requires the use of "MIC code 'XOFF' for financial instruments admitted to trading or traded on a trading venue, where the transaction on that financial instrument is not executed on a trading venue, systematic internaliser or organized trading platform outside of the Union. Use 'SINT' for financial instruments admitted to trading or traded on a trading venue, where the transaction is executed on a systematic internaliser."

Field.Name: LastPx
Field.Description: Price of this (last) fill.

Field.Name: LastQty
Field.Description: Quantity (e.g. shares) bought/sold on this (last) fill. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: NoLinesOfText
Field.Description: Identifies number of lines of text body

Field.Name: MsgSeqNum
Field.Description: Integer message sequence number.

Field.Name: MsgType
Field.Description: Defines message type ALWAYS THIRD FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted) Note: A "U" as the first character in the MsgType field (i.e. U, U2, etc) indicates that the message format is privately defined between the sender and receiver. *** Note the use of lower case letters ***

Field.Name: NewSeqNo
Field.Description: New sequence number

Field.Name: OrderID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which accept multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the OrderID field to assure uniqueness across days.

Field.Name: OrderQty
Field.Description: Quantity ordered. This represents the number of shares for equities or par, face or nominal value for FI instruments. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: OrdStatus
Field.Description: Identifies current status of order. *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" *** (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

Field.Name: OrdType
Field.Description: Order type. *** SOME VALUES ARE NO LONGER USED - See "Deprecated (Phased-out) Features and Supported Approach" *** (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

Field.Name: OrigClOrdID
Field.Description: ClOrdID (11) of the previous order (NOT the initial order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous order in cancel and cancel/replace requests.

Field.Name: OrigTime
Field.Description: Time of message origination (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT"))

Field.Name: PossDupFlag
Field.Description: Indicates possible retransmission of message with this sequence number

Field.Name: Price
Field.Description: Price per unit of quantity (e.g. per share)

Field.Name: RefSeqNum
Field.Description: Reference message sequence number

Field.Name: SecurityID
Field.Description: Security identifier value of SecurityIDSource (22) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires SecurityIDSource.

Field.Name: SenderCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify firm sending message.

Field.Name: SenderSubID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (desk, trader, etc.)

Field.Name: SendingTime
Field.Description: Time of message transmission (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: Quantity
Field.Description: Overall/total quantity (e.g. number of shares) (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: Side
Field.Description: Side of order (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

Field.Name: Symbol
Field.Description: Ticker symbol. Common, "human understood" representation of the security. SecurityID (48) value can be specified if no symbol exists (e.g. non-exchange traded Collective Investment Vehicles) Use "[N/A]" for products which do not have a symbol.

Field.Name: TargetCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify receiving firm.

Field.Name: TargetSubID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific individual or unit intended to receive message. "ADMIN" reserved for administrative messages not intended for a specific user.

Field.Name: Text
Field.Description: Free format text string (Note: this field does not have a specified maximum length)

Field.Name: TimeInForce
Field.Description: Specifies how long the order remains in effect. Absence of this field is interpreted as DAY. NOTE not applicable to CIV Orders.

Field.Name: TransactTime
Field.Description: Timestamp when the business transaction represented by the message occurred.

Field.Name: Urgency
Field.Description: Urgency flag

Field.Name: ValidUntilTime
Field.Description: Indicates expiration time of indication message (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: SettlType
Field.Description: Indicates order settlement period. If present, SettlDate (64) overrides this field. If both SettlType (63) and SettDate (64) are omitted, the default for SettlType (63) is 0 (Regular) Regular is defined as the default settlement period for the particular security on the exchange of execution. In Fixed Income the contents of this field may influence the instrument definition if the SecurityID (48) is ambiguous. In the US an active Treasury offering may be re-opened, and for a time one CUSIP will apply to both the current and "when-issued" securities. Supplying a value of "7" clarifies the instrument description; any other value or the absence of this field should cause the respondent to default to the active issue. Additionally the following patterns may be uses as well as enum values Dx = FX tenor expression for "days", e.g. "D5", where "x" is any integer > 0 Mx = FX tenor expression for "months", e.g. "M3", where "x" is any integer > 0 Wx = FX tenor expression for "weeks", e.g. "W13", where "x" is any integer > 0 Yx = FX tenor expression for "years", e.g. "Y1", where "x" is any integer > 0 Noted that for FX the tenors expressed using Dx, Mx, Wx, and Yx values do not denote business days, but calendar days.

Field.Name: SettlDate
Field.Description: Specific date of trade settlement (SettlementDate) in YYYYMMDD format. If present, this field overrides SettlType (63). This field is required if the value of SettlType (63) is 6 (Future) or 8 (Sellers Option). This field must be omitted if the value of SettlType (63) is 7 (When and If Issued) (expressed in local time at place of settlement)

Field.Name: SymbolSfx
Field.Description: Additional information about the security (e.g. preferred, warrants, etc.). Note also see SecurityType (167). As defined in the NYSE Stock and bond Symbol Directory and in the AMEX Fitch Directory.

Field.Name: ListID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for list as assigned by institution, used to associate multiple individual orders. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which generate multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ListID field to assure uniqueness across days.

Field.Name: ListSeqNo
Field.Description: Sequence of individual order within list (i.e. ListSeqNo of TotNoOrders (68), 2 of 25, 3 of 25, . . . )

Field.Name: TotNoOrders
Field.Description: Total number of list order entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoOrders (73) in each message that has repeating list order entries related to the same ListID (66). Used to support fragmentation. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was named "ListNoOrds")

Field.Name: ListExecInst
Field.Description: Free format text message containing list handling and execution instructions.

Field.Name: AllocID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for allocation message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: AllocTransType
Field.Description: Identifies allocation transaction type *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" ***

Field.Name: RefAllocID
Field.Description: Reference identifier to be used with AllocTransType (71) = Replace or Cancel. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: NoOrders
Field.Description: Indicates number of orders to be combined for average pricing and allocation.

Field.Name: AvgPxPrecision
Field.Description: Indicates number of decimal places to be used for average pricing. Absence of this field indicates that default precision arranged by the broker/institution is to be used.

Field.Name: TradeDate
Field.Description: Indicates date of trading day. Absence of this field indicates current day (expressed in local time at place of trade).

Field.Name: PositionEffect
Field.Description: Indicates whether the resulting position after a trade should be an opening position or closing position. Used for omnibus accounting - where accounts are held on a gross basis instead of being netted together.

Field.Name: NoAllocs
Field.Description: Number of repeating AllocAccount (79)/AllocPrice (366) entries.

Field.Name: AllocAccount
Field.Description: Sub-account mnemonic

Field.Name: AllocQty
Field.Description: Quantity to be allocated to specific sub-account (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: ProcessCode
Field.Description: Processing code for sub-account. Absence of this field in AllocAccount (79) / AllocPrice (366) /AllocQty (80) / ProcessCode instance indicates regular trade.

Field.Name: NoRpts
Field.Description: Total number of reports within series.

Field.Name: RptSeq
Field.Description: Sequence number of message within report series. Used to carry reporting sequence number of the fill as represented on the Trade Report Side.

Field.Name: CxlQty
Field.Description: Total quantity canceled for this order. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: NoDlvyInst
Field.Description: Number of delivery instruction fields in repeating group. Note this field was removed in FIX 4.1 and reinstated in FIX 4.4.

Field.Name: AllocStatus
Field.Description: Identifies status of allocation.

Field.Name: AllocRejCode
Field.Description: Identifies reason for rejection.

Field.Name: Signature
Field.Description: Electronic signature

Field.Name: SecureDataLen
Field.Description: Length of encrypted message

Field.Name: SecureData
Field.Description: Actual encrypted data stream

Field.Name: SignatureLength
Field.Description: Number of bytes in signature field

Field.Name: EmailType
Field.Description: Email message type.

Field.Name: RawDataLength
Field.Description: Number of bytes in raw data field.

Field.Name: RawData
Field.Description: Unformatted raw data, can include bitmaps, word processor documents, etc.

Field.Name: PossResend
Field.Description: Indicates that message may contain information that has been sent under another sequence number.

Field.Name: EncryptMethod
Field.Description: Method of encryption.

Field.Name: StopPx
Field.Description: Price per unit of quantity (e.g. per share)

Field.Name: ExDestination
Field.Description: Execution destination as defined by institution when order is entered. Valid values: See "Appendix 6-C"

Field.Name: CxlRejReason
Field.Description: Code to identify reason for cancel rejection.

Field.Name: OrdRejReason
Field.Description: Code to identify reason for order rejection. Note: Values 3, 4, and 5 will be used when rejecting an order due to pre-allocation information errors.

Field.Name: IOIQualifier
Field.Description: Code to qualify IOI use. (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

Field.Name: Issuer
Field.Description: Name of security issuer (e.g. International Business Machines, GNMA). see also Volume 7: "PRODUCT: FIXED INCOME - Euro Issuer Values"

Field.Name: SecurityDesc
Field.Description: Can be used by the venue or one of the trading parties to provide a non-normative textual description for the financial instrument.

Field.Name: HeartBtInt
Field.Description: Heartbeat interval (seconds)

Field.Name: MinQty
Field.Description: Minimum quantity of an order to be executed. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: MaxFloor
Field.Description: The quantity to be displayed . Required for reserve orders. On orders specifies the qty to be displayed, on execution reports the currently displayed quantity.

Field.Name: TestReqID
Field.Description: Identifier included in Test Request message to be returned in resulting Heartbeat

Field.Name: ReportToExch
Field.Description: Identifies party of trade responsible for exchange reporting.

Field.Name: LocateReqd
Field.Description: Indicates whether the broker is to locate the stock in conjunction with a short sell order.

Field.Name: OnBehalfOfCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify firm originating message if the message was delivered by a third party i.e. the third party firm identifier would be delivered in the SenderCompID field and the firm originating the message in this field.

Field.Name: OnBehalfOfSubID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (i.e. trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

Field.Name: QuoteID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for quote

Field.Name: NetMoney
Field.Description: Total amount due as the result of the transaction (e.g. for Buy order - principal + commission + fees) reported in currency of execution.

Field.Name: SettlCurrAmt
Field.Description: Total amount due expressed in settlement currency (includes the effect of the forex transaction)

Field.Name: SettlCurrency
Field.Description: Currency code of settlement denomination.

Field.Name: ForexReq
Field.Description: Indicates request for forex accommodation trade to be executed along with security transaction.

Field.Name: OrigSendingTime
Field.Description: Original time of message transmission (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT") when transmitting orders as the result of a resend request.

Field.Name: GapFillFlag
Field.Description: Indicates that the Sequence Reset message is replacing administrative or application messages which will not be resent.

Field.Name: NoExecs
Field.Description: Number of executions or trades.

Field.Name: ExpireTime
Field.Description:
Time/Date of order expiration (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")
The meaning of expiration is specific to the context where the field is used.
For orders, this is the expiration time of a Good Til Date TimeInForce.
For Quotes - this is the expiration of the quote.
Expiration time is provided across the quote message dialog to control the length of time of the overall quoting process.
For collateral requests, this is the time by which collateral must be assigned.
For collateral assignments, this is the time by which a response to the assignment is expected.
For credit/risk limit checks, this is the time when the reserved credit limit will expire for the requested transaction.

Field.Name: DKReason
Field.Description: Reason for execution rejection.

Field.Name: DeliverToCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify the firm targeted to receive the message if the message is delivered by a third party i.e. the third party firm identifier would be delivered in the TargetCompID (56) field and the ultimate receiver firm ID in this field.

Field.Name: DeliverToSubID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message recipient (i.e. trader) if the message is delivered by a third party

Field.Name: IOINaturalFlag
Field.Description: Indicates that IOI is the result of an existing agency order or a facilitation position resulting from an agency order, not from principal trading or order solicitation activity.

Field.Name: QuoteReqID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a QuoteRequest(35=R).

Field.Name: BidPx
Field.Description: Bid price/rate

Field.Name: OfferPx
Field.Description: Offer price/rate

Field.Name: BidSize
Field.Description: Quantity of bid (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: OfferSize
Field.Description: Quantity of offer (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: NoMiscFees
Field.Description: Number of repeating groups of miscellaneous fees

Field.Name: MiscFeeAmt
Field.Description: Miscellaneous fee value

Field.Name: MiscFeeCurr
Field.Description: Currency of miscellaneous fee

Field.Name: MiscFeeType
Field.Description: Indicates type of miscellaneous fee.

Field.Name: PrevClosePx
Field.Description: Previous closing price of security.

Field.Name: ResetSeqNumFlag
Field.Description: Indicates that both sides of the FIX session should reset sequence numbers.

Field.Name: SenderLocationID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator's location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader)

Field.Name: TargetLocationID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message destination's location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader)

Field.Name: OnBehalfOfLocationID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator's location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

Field.Name: DeliverToLocationID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message recipient's location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

Field.Name: NoRelatedSym
Field.Description: Specifies the number of repeating symbols specified.

Field.Name: Subject
Field.Description: The subject of an Email message

Field.Name: Headline
Field.Description: The headline of a News message

Field.Name: URLLink
Field.Description: A URI (Uniform Resource Identifier) or URL (Uniform Resource Locator) link to additional information (i.e. http://www.XYZ.com/research.html) See "Appendix 6-B FIX Fields Based Upon Other Standards"

Field.Name: ExecType
Field.Description: Describes the specific ExecutionRpt (e.g. Pending Cancel) while OrdStatus(39) will always identify the current order status (e.g. Partially Filled).

Field.Name: LeavesQty
Field.Description: Quantity open for further execution. If the OrdStatus (39) is Canceled, DoneForTheDay, Expired, Calculated, or Rejected (in which case the order is no longer active) then LeavesQty could be 0, otherwise LeavesQty = OrderQty (38) - CumQty (14). (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: CashOrderQty
Field.Description: Specifies the approximate order quantity desired in total monetary units vs. as tradeable units (e.g. number of shares). The broker or fund manager (for CIV orders) would be responsible for converting and calculating a tradeable unit (e.g. share) quantity (OrderQty (38)) based upon this amount to be used for the actual order and subsequent messages.

Field.Name: AllocAvgPx
Field.Description: AvgPx (6) for a specific AllocAccount (79) For Fixed Income this is always expressed as "percent of par" price type.

Field.Name: AllocNetMoney
Field.Description: NetMoney (8) for a specific AllocAccount (79)

Field.Name: SettlCurrFxRate
Field.Description: Foreign exchange rate used to compute SettlCurrAmt (9) from Currency (5) to SettlCurrency (20)

Field.Name: SettlCurrFxRateCalc
Field.Description: Specifies whether or not SettlCurrFxRate (155) should be multiplied or divided.

Field.Name: NumDaysInterest
Field.Description: Number of Days of Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income. Note value may be negative.

Field.Name: AccruedInterestRate
Field.Description: The amount the buyer compensates the seller for the portion of the next coupon interest payment the seller has earned but will not receive from the issuer because the issuer will send the next coupon payment to the buyer. Accrued Interest Rate is the annualized Accrued Interest amount divided by the purchase price of the bond.

Field.Name: AccruedInterestAmt
Field.Description: Amount of Accrued Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income

Field.Name: SettlInstMode
Field.Description: Indicates mode used for Settlement Instructions message. *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" ***

Field.Name: AllocText
Field.Description: Free format text related to a specific AllocAccount (79).

Field.Name: SettlInstID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Settlement Instruction.

Field.Name: SettlInstTransType
Field.Description: Settlement Instructions message transaction type

Field.Name: EmailThreadID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for an email thread (new and chain of replies)

Field.Name: SettlInstSource
Field.Description: Indicates source of Settlement Instructions

Field.Name: SecurityType
Field.Description: Indicates type of security. Security type enumerations are grouped by Product(460) field value. NOTE: Additional values may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties.

Field.Name: EffectiveTime
Field.Description: Time the details within the message should take effect (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: StandInstDbType
Field.Description: Identifies the Standing Instruction database used

Field.Name: StandInstDbName
Field.Description: Name of the Standing Instruction database represented with StandInstDbType (169) (i.e. the Global Custodian's name).

Field.Name: StandInstDbID
Field.Description: Unique identifier used on the Standing Instructions database for the Standing Instructions to be referenced.

Field.Name: SettlDeliveryType
Field.Description: Identifies type of settlement

Field.Name: BidSpotRate
Field.Description: Bid F/X spot rate.

Field.Name: BidForwardPoints
Field.Description: Bid F/X forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: OfferSpotRate
Field.Description: Offer F/X spot rate.

Field.Name: OfferForwardPoints
Field.Description: Offer F/X forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: OrderQty2
Field.Description: OrderQty (38) of the future part of a F/X swap order.

Field.Name: SettlDate2
Field.Description: SettDate (64) of the future part of a F/X swap order.

Field.Name: LastSpotRate
Field.Description: F/X spot rate.

Field.Name: LastForwardPoints
Field.Description: F/X forward points added to LastSpotRate (94). May be a negative value. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

Field.Name: AllocLinkID
Field.Description: Can be used to link two different Allocation messages (each with unique AllocID (70)) together, i.e. for F/X "Netting" or "Swaps". Should be unique.

Field.Name: AllocLinkType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of Allocation linkage when AllocLinkID (96) is used.

Field.Name: SecondaryOrderID
Field.Description: Assigned by the party which accepts the order. Can be used to provide the OrderID (37) used by an exchange or executing system.

Field.Name: NoIOIQualifiers
Field.Description: Number of repeating groups of IOIQualifiers (04).

Field.Name: MaturityMonthYear
Field.Description: Can be used with standardized derivatives vs. the MaturityDate (54) field. Month and Year of the maturity (used for standardized futures and options). Format: YYYYMM (e.g. 199903) YYYYMMDD (e.g. 20030323) YYYYMMwN (e.g. 200303w) for week A specific date or can be appended to the MaturityMonthYear. For instance, if multiple standard products exist that mature in the same Year and Month, but actually mature at a different time, a value can be appended, such as "w" or "w2" to indicate week as opposed to week 2 expiration. Likewise, the date (0-3) can be appended to indicate a specific expiration (maturity date).

Field.Name: PutOrCall
Field.Description: Indicates whether an option contract is a put, call, chooser or undetermined.

Field.Name: StrikePrice
Field.Description: Strike Price for an Option.

Field.Name: CoveredOrUncovered
Field.Description: Used for derivative products, such as options

Field.Name: OptAttribute
Field.Description: Provided to support versioning of option contracts as a result of corporate actions or events. Use of this field is defined by counterparty agreement or market conventions.

Field.Name: SecurityExchange
Field.Description: Market used to help identify a security. Valid values: See "Appendix 6-C"

Field.Name: NotifyBrokerOfCredit
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not details should be communicated to BrokerOfCredit (i.e. step-in broker).

Field.Name: AllocHandlInst
Field.Description: Indicates how the receiver (i.e. third party) of allocation information should handle/process the account details.

Field.Name: MaxShow
Field.Description: Maximum quantity (e.g. number of shares) within an order to be shown to other customers (i.e. sent via an IOI). (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: PegOffsetValue
Field.Description: Amount (signed) added to the peg for a pegged order in the context of the PegOffsetType (836) (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was of type PriceOffset)

Field.Name: XmlDataLen
Field.Description: Length of the XmlData data block.

Field.Name: XmlData
Field.Description: Actual XML data stream (e.g. FIXML). See approriate XML reference (e.g. FIXML). Note: may contain embedded SOH characters.

Field.Name: SettlInstRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier for the SettlInstID (162) with Cancel and Replace SettlInstTransType (163) transaction types.

Field.Name: NoRoutingIDs
Field.Description: Number of repeating groups of RoutingID (217) and RoutingType (216) values. See Volume 3: "Pre-Trade Message Targeting/Routing"

Field.Name: RoutingType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of RoutingID (217) specified.

Field.Name: RoutingID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify a specific routing destination.

Field.Name: Spread
Field.Description: For Fixed Income. Either Swap Spread or Spread to Benchmark depending upon the order type. Spread to Benchmark: Basis points relative to a benchmark. To be expressed as "count of basis points" (vs. an absolute value). E.g. High Grade Corporate Bonds may express price as basis points relative to benchmark (the BenchmarkCurveName (22) field). Note: Basis points can be negative. Swap Spread: Target spread for a swap.

Field.Name: BenchmarkCurveCurrency
Field.Description: Identifies currency used for benchmark curve. See "Appendix 6-A: Valid Currency Codes" for information on obtaining valid values. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: BenchmarkCurveName
Field.Description: Name of benchmark curve. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: BenchmarkCurvePoint
Field.Description: Point on benchmark curve. Free form values: e.g. "Y", "7Y", "INTERPOLATED". Sample values: M = combination of a number between 1-12 and a "M" for month Y = combination of number between 1-100 and a "Y" for year} 10Y-OLD = see above, then add "-OLD" when appropriate INTERPOLATED = the point is mathematically derived 2/2031 5 3/8 = the point is stated via a combination of maturity month / year and coupon See Fixed Income-specific documentation at http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org for additional values. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: CouponRate
Field.Description: The rate of interest that, when multiplied by the principal, par value, or face value of a bond, provides the currency amount of the periodic interest payment. The coupon is always cited, along with maturity, in any quotation of a bond's price.

Field.Name: CouponPaymentDate
Field.Description: Date interest is to be paid. Used in identifying Corporate Bond issues. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3) (prior to FIX 4.4 field was of type UTCDate)

Field.Name: IssueDate
Field.Description: The date on which a bond or stock offering is issued. It may or may not be the same as the effective date ("Dated Date") or the date on which interest begins to accrue ("Interest Accrual Date") (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3) (prior to FIX 4.4 field was of type UTCDate)

Field.Name: RepurchaseTerm
Field.Description: Number of business days before repurchase of a repo. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: RepurchaseRate
Field.Description: Percent of par at which a Repo will be repaid. Represented as a percent, e.g. .9525 represents 95-/4 percent of par. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: Factor
Field.Description: For Fixed Income: Amorization Factor for deriving Current face from Original face for ABS or MBS securities, note the fraction may be greater than, equal to or less than . In TIPS securities this is the Inflation index. Qty * Factor * Price = Gross Trade Amount For Derivatives: Contract Value Factor by which price must be adjusted to determine the true nominal value of one futures/options contract. (Qty * Price) * Factor = Nominal Value (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: TradeOriginationDate
Field.Description: Used with Fixed Income for Muncipal New Issue Market. Agreement in principal between counter-parties prior to actual trade date. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3) (prior to FIX 4.4 field was of type UTCDate)

Field.Name: ExDate
Field.Description: The date when a distribution of interest is deducted from a securities assets or set aside for payment to bondholders. On the ex-date, the securities price drops by the amount of the distribution (plus or minus any market activity). (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3) (prior to FIX 4.4 field was of type UTCDate)

Field.Name: ContractMultiplier
Field.Description: Specifies the ratio or multiply factor to convert from "nominal" units (e.g. contracts) to total units (e.g. shares) (e.g. 1.0, 100, 1000, etc). Applicable For Fixed Income, Convertible Bonds, Derivatives, etc.
Field.Elaboration: In general quantities for all classes should be expressed in the basic unit of the instrument, e.g. shares for equities, nominal or par amount for bonds, currency for foreign exchange. When quantity is expressed in contracts, e.g. financing transactions and bond trade reporting, ContractMultiplier(231) should contain the number of units in one contract and can be omitted if the multiplier is the default amount for the instrument, i.e. 1,000 par of bonds, 1,000,000 par for financing transactions.

Field.Name: NoStipulations
Field.Description: Number of stipulation entries (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3).

Field.Name: StipulationType
Field.Description: For Fixed Income. Type of Stipulation. Other types may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: StipulationValue
Field.Description: For Fixed Income. Value of stipulation. The expression can be an absolute single value or a combination of values and logical operators: < value > value <= value >= value value value - value2 value OR value2 value AND value2 YES NO Bargain conditions recognized by the London Stock Exchange - to be used when StipulationType is "BGNCON". CD = Special cum Dividend XD = Special ex Dividend CC = Special cum Coupon XC = Special ex Coupon CB = Special cum Bonus XB = Special ex Bonus CR = Special cum Rights XR = Special ex Rights CP = Special cum Capital Repayments XP = Special ex Capital Repayments CS = Cash Settlement SP = Special Price TR = Report for European Equity Market Securities in accordance with Chapter 8 of the Rules. GD = Guaranteed Delivery Values for StipulationType = "PXSOURCE": BB GENERIC BB FAIRVALUE BROKERTEC ESPEED GOVPX HILLIARD FARBER ICAP TRADEWEB TULLETT LIBERTY If a particular side of the market is wanted append /BID /OFFER or /MID. plus appropriate combinations of the above and other expressions by mutual agreement of the counterparties. Examples: ">=60", ".25", "ORANGE OR CONTRACOSTA", etc. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: YieldType
Field.Description: Type of yield. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: Yield
Field.Description: Yield percentage. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: TotalTakedown
Field.Description: The price at which the securities are distributed to the different members of an underwriting group for the primary market in Municipals, total gross underwriter's spread. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: Concession
Field.Description: Provides the reduction in price for the secondary market in Muncipals. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: RepoCollateralSecurityType
Field.Description: Identifies the collateral used in the transaction. Valid values: see SecurityType (167) field (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: RedemptionDate
Field.Description: Return of investor's principal in a security. Bond redemption can occur before maturity date.(Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3) (prior to FIX 4.4 field was of type UTCDate)

Field.Name: UnderlyingCouponPaymentDate
Field.Description: Underlying security's CouponPaymentDate. See CouponPaymentDate (224) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3) (prior to FIX 4.4 field was of type UTCDate)

Field.Name: UnderlyingIssueDate
Field.Description: Underlying security's IssueDate. See IssueDate (225) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3) (prior to FIX 4.4 field was of type UTCDate)

Field.Name: UnderlyingRepoCollateralSecurityType
Field.Description: Underlying security's RepoCollateralSecurityType. See RepoCollateralSecurityType (239) field for description.(Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: UnderlyingRepurchaseTerm
Field.Description: Underlying security's RepurchaseTerm. See RepurchaseTerm (226) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: UnderlyingRepurchaseRate
Field.Description: Underlying security's RepurchaseRate. See RepurchaseRate (227) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: UnderlyingFactor
Field.Description: Underlying security's Factor. See Factor (228) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: UnderlyingRedemptionDate
Field.Description: Underlying security's RedemptionDate. See RedemptionDate (240) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3) (prior to FIX 4.4 field was of type UTCDate)

Field.Name: LegCouponPaymentDate
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's CouponPaymentDate. See CouponPaymentDate (224) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3) (prior to FIX 4.4 field was of type UTCDate)

Field.Name: LegIssueDate
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's IssueDate. See IssueDate (225) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3) (prior to FIX 4.4 field was of type UTCDate)

Field.Name: LegRepoCollateralSecurityType
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's RepoCollateralSecurityType. See RepoCollateralSecurityType (239) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: LegRepurchaseTerm
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's RepurchaseTerm. See RepurchaseTerm (226) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: LegRepurchaseRate
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's RepurchaseRate. See RepurchaseRate (227) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: LegFactor
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's Factor. See Factor (228) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: LegRedemptionDate
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's RedemptionDate. See RedemptionDate (240) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3) (prior to FIX 4.4 field was of type UTCDate)

Field.Name: CreditRating
Field.Description: An evaluation of a company's ability to repay obligations or its likelihood of not defaulting. These evaluation are provided by Credit Rating Agencies, i.e. S&P, Moody's. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: UnderlyingCreditRating
Field.Description: Underlying security's CreditRating. See CreditRating (255) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: LegCreditRating
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's CreditRating. See CreditRating (255) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: TradedFlatSwitch
Field.Description: Driver and part of trade in the event that the Security Master file was wrong at the point of entry(Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: BasisFeatureDate
Field.Description: BasisFeatureDate allows requesting firms within fixed income the ability to request an alternative yield-to-worst, -maturity, -extended or other call. This flows through the confirm process. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3) (prior to FIX 4.4 field was of type UTCDate)

Field.Name: BasisFeaturePrice
Field.Description: Price for BasisFeatureDate. See BasisFeatureDate (259) (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: MDReqID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Market Data Request

Field.Name: SubscriptionRequestType
Field.Description: Subscription Request Type

Field.Name: MarketDepth
Field.Description: Depth of market for Book Snapshot / Incremental updates 0 - full book depth 1 - top of book 2 and above - book depth (number of levels)

Field.Name: MDUpdateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of Market Data update.

Field.Name: AggregatedBook
Field.Description: Specifies whether or not book entries should be aggregated. (Not specified) = broker option

Field.Name: NoMDEntryTypes

Field.Name: NoMDEntries

Field.Name: MDEntryType

Field.Name: MDEntryPx
Field.Description: Price of the Market Data Entry.

Field.Name: MDEntrySize

Field.Name: MDEntryDate

Field.Name: MDEntryTime

Field.Name: TickDirection

Field.Name: MDMkt
Field.Description: Market posting quote / trade. Valid values: See "Appendix 6-C"

Field.Name: QuoteCondition
Field.Description: Space-delimited list of conditions describing a quote.

Field.Name: TradeCondition
Field.Description: Type of market data entry.

Field.Name: MDEntryID
Field.Description: Unique Market Data Entry identifier.

Field.Name: MDUpdateAction

Field.Name: MDEntryRefID

Field.Name: MDReqRejReason
Field.Description: Reason for the rejection of a Market Data request.

Field.Name: MDEntryOriginator
Field.Description: Originator of a Market Data Entry

Field.Name: LocationID

Field.Name: DeskID
Field.Description: Identification of a Market Maker's desk

Field.Name: DeleteReason
Field.Description: Reason for deletion.

Field.Name: OpenCloseSettlFlag
Field.Description: Flag that identifies a market data entry. (Prior to FIX 4.3 this field was of type char)

Field.Name: SellerDays
Field.Description: Specifies the number of days that may elapse before delivery of the security

Field.Name: MDEntryBuyer
Field.Description: Buying party in a trade

Field.Name: MDEntrySeller
Field.Description: Selling party in a trade

Field.Name: MDEntryPositionNo
Field.Description: Display position of a bid or offer, numbered from most competitive to least competitive, per market side, beginning with .

Field.Name: FinancialStatus
Field.Description: Identifies a firm's or a security's financial status

Field.Name: CorporateAction
Field.Description: Identifies the type of Corporate Action.

Field.Name: DefBidSize
Field.Description: Default Bid Size.

Field.Name: DefOfferSize
Field.Description: Default Offer Size.

Field.Name: NoQuoteEntries
Field.Description: The number of quote entries for a QuoteSet.

Field.Name: NoQuoteSets
Field.Description: The number of sets of quotes in the message.

Field.Name: QuoteStatus
Field.Description: Identifies the status of the quote acknowledgement.

Field.Name: QuoteCancelType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of quote cancel.

Field.Name: QuoteEntryID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a quote. The QuoteEntryID stays with the quote as a static identifier even if the quote is updated.

Field.Name: QuoteRejectReason
Field.Description: Reason Quote was rejected:

Field.Name: QuoteResponseLevel
Field.Description: Level of Response requested from receiver of quote messages. A default value should be bilaterally agreed.

Field.Name: QuoteSetID
Field.Description: Unique id for the Quote Set.

Field.Name: QuoteRequestType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of Quote Request being generated

Field.Name: TotNoQuoteEntries
Field.Description: Total number of quotes for the quote set.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Underlying security's SecurityIDSource. Valid values: see SecurityIDSource (22) field

Field.Name: UnderlyingIssuer
Field.Description: Underlying security's Issuer. See Issuer (06) field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityDesc
Field.Description: Description of the underlying security. Can be used by the venue or one of the trading parties to provide an optional non-normative textual description of the financial instrument.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityExchange
Field.Description: Underlying security's SecurityExchange. Can be used to identify the underlying security. Valid values: see SecurityExchange (207)

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityID
Field.Description: Underlying security's SecurityID. See SecurityID (48) field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityType
Field.Description: Underlying security's SecurityType. Valid values: see SecurityType (167) field (see below for details concerning this fields use in conjunction with SecurityType=REPO) The following applies when used in conjunction with SecurityType=REPO Represents the general or specific type of security that underlies a financing agreement Valid values for SecurityType=REPO: If bonds of a particular issuer or country are wanted in an Order or are in the basket of an Execution and the SecurityType is not granular enough, include the UnderlyingIssuer (306), UnderlyingCountryOfIssue (592), UnderlyingProgram, UnderlyingRegType and/or < UnderlyingStipulations > block e.g.:

Field.Name: UnderlyingSymbol
Field.Description: Underlying security's Symbol. See Symbol (55) field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingSymbolSfx
Field.Description: Underlying security's SymbolSfx. See SymbolSfx (65) field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingMaturityMonthYear
Field.Description: Underlying security's MaturityMonthYear. Can be used with standardized derivatives vs. the UnderlyingMaturityDate (542) field. See MaturityMonthYear (200) field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingPutOrCall
Field.Description: Indicates whether an underlying option contract is a put, call, chooser or undetermined.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStrikePrice
Field.Description: Underlying security's StrikePrice. See StrikePrice (202) field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptAttribute
Field.Description: Underlying security's OptAttribute. See OptAttribute (206) field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingCurrency
Field.Description: Underlying security's Currency. See Currency (5) field for description and valid values

Field.Name: SecurityReqID
Field.Description: Unique ID of a Security Definition Request.

Field.Name: SecurityRequestType
Field.Description: Type of Security Definition Request.

Field.Name: SecurityResponseID
Field.Description: Unique ID of a Security Definition message.

Field.Name: SecurityResponseType
Field.Description: Type of Security Definition message response.

Field.Name: SecurityStatusReqID
Field.Description: Unique ID of a Security Status Request or a Security Mass Status Request message.

Field.Name: UnsolicitedIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not message is being sent as a result of a subscription request or not.

Field.Name: SecurityTradingStatus

Field.Name: HaltReason

Field.Name: InViewOfCommon
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not the halt was due to Common Stock trading being halted.

Field.Name: DueToRelated
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not the halt was due to the Related Security being halted.

Field.Name: BuyVolume
Field.Description: Quantity bought.

Field.Name: SellVolume
Field.Description: Quantity sold.

Field.Name: HighPx
Field.Description: Represents an indication of the high end of the price range for a security prior to the open or reopen

Field.Name: LowPx
Field.Description: Represents an indication of the low end of the price range for a security prior to the open or reopen

Field.Name: Adjustment
Field.Description: Identifies the type of adjustment.

Field.Name: TradSesReqID
Field.Description: Unique ID of a Trading Session Status message.

Field.Name: TradingSessionID
Field.Description: Identifier for a trading session. A trading session spans an extended period of time that can also be expressed informally in terms of the trading day. Usage is determined by market or counterparties. To specify good for session where session spans more than one calendar day, use TimeInForce = 0 (Day) in conjunction with TradingSessionID(336). Bilaterally agreed values of data type "String" that start with a character can be used for backward compatibility.

Field.Name: ContraTrader
Field.Description: Identifies the trader (e.g. "badge number") of the ContraBroker.

Field.Name: TradSesMethod
Field.Description: Method of trading

Field.Name: TradSesMode
Field.Description: Trading Session Mode

Field.Name: TradSesStatus
Field.Description: State of the trading session.

Field.Name: TradSesStartTime
Field.Description: Starting time of the trading session

Field.Name: TradSesOpenTime

Field.Name: TradSesPreCloseTime

Field.Name: TradSesCloseTime

Field.Name: TradSesEndTime
Field.Description: End time of the trading session

Field.Name: NumberOfOrders
Field.Description: Number of orders in the market.
