Field.Description: Upper liquidity indicator if TotalNumSecurities (393) > 1. Represented as a percentage.

Field.Name: LiquidityValue
Field.Description: Value between LiquidityPctLow (402) and LiquidityPctHigh (403) in Currency

Field.Name: EFPTrackingError
Field.Description: Eg Used in EFP trades 2% (EFP - Exchange for Physical ). Represented as a percentage.

Field.Name: FairValue
Field.Description: Used in EFP trades

Field.Name: OutsideIndexPct
Field.Description: Used in EFP trades. Represented as a percentage.

Field.Name: ValueOfFutures
Field.Description: Used in EFP trades

Field.Name: LiquidityIndType
Field.Description: Code to identify the type of liquidity indicator.

Field.Name: WtAverageLiquidity
Field.Description: Overall weighted average liquidity expressed as a % of average daily volume. Represented as a percentage.

Field.Name: ExchangeForPhysical
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not to exchange for phsyical.

Field.Name: OutMainCntryUIndex
Field.Description: Value of stocks in Currency

Field.Name: CrossPercent
Field.Description: Percentage of program that crosses in Currency. Represented as a percentage.

Field.Name: ProgRptReqs
Field.Description: Code to identify the desired frequency of progress reports.

Field.Name: ProgPeriodInterval
Field.Description: Time in minutes between each ListStatus report sent by SellSide. Zero means don't send status.

Field.Name: IncTaxInd
Field.Description: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross.

Field.Name: NumBidders
Field.Description: Indicates the total number of bidders on the list

Field.Name: BidTradeType
Field.Description: Code to represent the type of trade. (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was named "TradeType")

Field.Name: BasisPxType
Field.Description: Code to represent the basis price type.

Field.Name: NoBidComponents
Field.Description: Indicates the number of list entries.

Field.Name: Country
Field.Description: ISO Country Code in field

Field.Name: TotNoStrikes
Field.Description: Total number of strike price entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoStrikes (428) in each message that has repeating strike price entries related to the same ListID (66). Used to support fragmentation.

Field.Name: PriceType
Field.Description: Code to represent the price type.
Field.Elaboration: For Financing transactions PriceType(423) implies the "repo type" - Fixed or Floating - 9 (Yield) or 6 (Spread) respectively - and Price(44) gives the corresponding "repo rate". See Volume 1 "Glossary" for further value definitions.

Field.Name: DayOrderQty
Field.Description: For GT orders, the OrderQty (38) less all quantity (adjusted for stock splits) that traded on previous days. DayOrderQty (424) = OrderQty - (CumQty (14) - DayCumQty (425))

Field.Name: DayCumQty
Field.Description: Quantity on a GT order that has traded today.

Field.Name: DayAvgPx
Field.Description: The average price for quantity on a GT order that has traded today.

Field.Name: GTBookingInst
Field.Description: Code to identify whether to book out executions on a part-filled GT order on the day of execution or to accumulate.

Field.Name: NoStrikes
Field.Description: Number of list strike price entries.

Field.Name: ListStatusType
Field.Description: Code to represent the status type.

Field.Name: NetGrossInd
Field.Description: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross.

Field.Name: ListOrderStatus
Field.Description: Code to represent the status of a list order.

Field.Name: ExpireDate
Field.Description: Date of order expiration (last day the order can trade), always expressed in terms of the local market date. The time at which the order expires is determined by the local market's business practices

Field.Name: ListExecInstType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of ListExecInst (69).

Field.Name: CxlRejResponseTo
Field.Description: Identifies the type of request that a Cancel Reject is in response to.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCouponRate
Field.Description: Underlying security's CouponRate. See CouponRate (223) field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingContractMultiplier
Field.Description: Underlying security's ContractMultiplier. See ContractMultiplier (231) field for description

Field.Name: ContraTradeQty
Field.Description: Quantity traded with the ContraBroker (375).

Field.Name: ContraTradeTime
Field.Description: Identifes the time of the trade with the ContraBroker (375). (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: LiquidityNumSecurities
Field.Description: Number of Securites between LiquidityPctLow (402) and LiquidityPctHigh (403) in Currency.

Field.Name: MultiLegReportingType
Field.Description: Used to indicate how the multi-legged security (e.g. option strategies, spreads, etc.) is being reported.

Field.Name: StrikeTime
Field.Description: The time at which current market prices are used to determine the value of a basket. In negotiation workflows where a spread-to-benchmark price is negotiated, this is the pre-determined time at which the benchmark is to be spotted.

Field.Name: ListStatusText
Field.Description: Free format text string related to List Status.

Field.Name: EncodedListStatusTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedListStatusText (446) field.

Field.Name: EncodedListStatusText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ListStatusText (444) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ListStatusText field.

Field.Name: PartyIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies class or source of the PartyID (448) value. Required if PartyID is specified. Note: applicable values depend upon PartyRole (452) specified. See "Appendix 6-G - Use of <Parties> Component Block"

Field.Name: PartyID
Field.Description: Party identifier/code. See PartyIDSource (447) and PartyRole (452). See "Appendix 6-G - Use of <Parties> Component Block"

Field.Name: NetChgPrevDay
Field.Description: Net change from previous day's closing price vs. last traded price.

Field.Name: PartyRole
Field.Description: Identifies the type or role of the PartyID (448) specified. See "Appendix 6-G - Use of <Parties> Component Block" (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

Field.Name: NoPartyIDs
Field.Description: Number of PartyID (448), PartyIDSource (447), and PartyRole (452) entries

Field.Name: NoSecurityAltID
Field.Description: Number of SecurityAltID (455) entries.

Field.Name: SecurityAltID
Field.Description: Alternate Security identifier value for this security of SecurityAltIDSource (456) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires SecurityAltIDSource.

Field.Name: SecurityAltIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityAltID (455) value. Required if SecurityAltID is specified. Valid values: Same valid values as the SecurityIDSource (22) field

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingSecurityAltID
Field.Description: Number of UnderlyingSecurityAltID (458) entries.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityAltID
Field.Description: Alternate Security identifier value for this underlying security of UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource (459) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies class or source of the UnderlyingSecurityAltID (458) value. Required if UnderlyingSecurityAltID is specified. Valid values: Same valid values as the SecurityIDSource (22) field

Field.Name: Product
Field.Description: Indicates the type of product the security is associated with. See also the CFICode (461) and SecurityType (167) fields.

Field.Name: CFICode
Field.Description: Indicates the type of security using ISO 10962 standard, Classification of Financial Instruments (CFI code) values. ISO 10962 is maintained by ANNA (Association of National Numbering Agencies) acting as Registration Authority. See "Appendix 6-B FIX Fields Based Upon Other Standards". See also the Product (460) and SecurityType (167) fields. It is recommended that CFICode be used instead of SecurityType (167) for non-Fixed Income instruments. A subset of possible values applicable to FIX usage are identified in "Appendix 6-D CFICode Usage - ISO 10962 Classification of Financial Instruments (CFI code)"

Field.Name: UnderlyingProduct
Field.Description: Underlying security's Product. Valid values: see Product(460) field

Field.Name: UnderlyingCFICode
Field.Description: Underlying security's CFICode. Valid values: see CFICode (461) field

Field.Name: TestMessageIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not this FIX Session is a "test" vs. "production" connection. Useful for preventing "accidents".

Field.Name: BookingRefID
Field.Description: Common reference passed to a post-trade booking process (e.g. industry matching utility).

Field.Name: IndividualAllocID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a specific NoAllocs (78) repeating group instance (e.g. for an AllocAccount).

Field.Name: RoundingDirection
Field.Description: Specifies which direction to round For CIV - indicates whether or not the quantity of shares/units is to be rounded and in which direction where CashOrdQty (152) or (for CIV only) OrderPercent (516) are specified on an order. The default is for rounding to be at the discretion of the executing broker or fund manager. e.g. for an order specifying CashOrdQty or OrderPercent if the calculated number of shares/units was 325.76 and RoundingModulus (469) was 0 - "round down" would give 320 units, 1 - "round up" would give 330 units and "round to nearest" would give 320 units.

Field.Name: RoundingModulus
Field.Description: For CIV - a float value indicating the value to which rounding is required. i.e. 0 means round to a multiple of 0 units/shares; 0.5 means round to a multiple of 0.5 units/shares. The default, if RoundingDirection (468) is specified without RoundingModulus, is to round to a whole unit/share.

Field.Name: CountryOfIssue
Field.Description: ISO Country code of instrument issue (e.g. the country portion typically used in ISIN). Can be used in conjunction with non-ISIN SecurityID (48) (e.g. CUSIP for Municipal Bonds without ISIN) to provide uniqueness.

Field.Name: StateOrProvinceOfIssue
Field.Description: A two-character state or province abbreviation.

Field.Name: LocaleOfIssue
Field.Description: Identifies the locale or region of issue.
Field.Elaboration: For Municipal Security Issuers other than state or province. Refer to http://www.atmos.albany.edu/cgi/stagrep-cgi. Reference the IATA city codes for values. Note IATA (International Air Transport Association) maintains the codes at www.iata.org. For other securities the value may be a region of the issuer, e.g. North America.

Field.Name: NoRegistDtls
Field.Description: The number of registration details on a Registration Instructions message

Field.Name: MailingDtls
Field.Description: Set of Correspondence address details, possibly including phone, fax, etc.

Field.Name: InvestorCountryOfResidence
Field.Description: The ISO 366 Country code (2 character) identifying which country the beneficial investor is resident for tax purposes.

Field.Name: PaymentRef
Field.Description: "Settlement Payment Reference" - A free format Payment reference to assist with reconciliation, e.g. a Client and/or Order ID number.

Field.Name: DistribPaymentMethod
Field.Description: A code identifying the payment method for a (fractional) distribution. 13 through 998 are reserved for future use Values above 1000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

Field.Name: CashDistribCurr
Field.Description: Specifies currency to be used for Cash Distributions see "Appendix 6-A Valid Currency Codes".

Field.Name: CommCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies currency to be use for Commission (12) if the Commission currency is different from the Deal Currency - see "Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes".

Field.Name: CancellationRights
Field.Description: For CIV - A one character code identifying whether Cancellation rights/Cooling off period applies.

Field.Name: MoneyLaunderingStatus
Field.Description: A one character code identifying Money laundering status.

Field.Name: MailingInst
Field.Description: Free format text to specify mailing instruction requirements, e.g. "no third party mailings".

Field.Name: TransBkdTime
Field.Description: For CIV A date and time stamp to indicate the time a CIV order was booked by the fund manager. For derivatives a date and time stamp to indicate when this order was booked with the agent prior to submission to the VMU. Indicates the time at which the order was finalized between the buyer and seller prior to submission.

Field.Name: ExecPriceType
Field.Description: For CIV - Identifies how the execution price LastPx (31) was calculated from the fund unit/share price(s) calculated at the fund valuation point.

Field.Name: ExecPriceAdjustment
Field.Description: For CIV the amount or percentage by which the fund unit/share price was adjusted, as indicated by ExecPriceType (484)

Field.Name: DateOfBirth
Field.Description: The date of birth applicable to the individual, e.g. required to open some types of tax-exempt account.

Field.Name: TradeReportTransType
Field.Description: Identifies Trade Report message transaction type (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was of type char)

Field.Name: CardHolderName
Field.Description: The name of the payment card holder as specified on the card being used for payment.

Field.Name: CardNumber
Field.Description: The number of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment.

Field.Name: CardExpDate
Field.Description: The expiry date of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment.

Field.Name: CardIssNum
Field.Description: The issue number of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment. This is only applicable to certain types of card.

Field.Name: PaymentMethod
Field.Description: A code identifying the Settlement payment method. 16 through 998 are reserved for future use Values above 1000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

Field.Name: RegistAcctType
Field.Description: For CIV - a fund manager-defined code identifying which of the fund manager's account types is required.

Field.Name: Designation
Field.Description: Free format text defining the designation to be associated with a holding on the register. Used to identify assets of a specific underlying investor using a common registration, e.g. a broker's nominee or street name.

Field.Name: TaxAdvantageType
Field.Description: For CIV - a code identifying the type of tax exempt account in which purchased shares/units are to be held. 30 - 998 are reserved for future use by recognized taxation authorities 999=Other values above 1000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

Field.Name: RegistRejReasonText
Field.Description: Text indicating reason(s) why a Registration Instruction has been rejected.

Field.Name: FundRenewWaiv
Field.Description: A one character code identifying whether the Fund based renewal commission is to be waived.

Field.Name: CashDistribAgentName
Field.Description: Name of local agent bank if for cash distributions

Field.Name: CashDistribAgentCode
Field.Description: BIC (Bank Identification Code--Swift managed) code of agent bank for cash distributions

Field.Name: CashDistribAgentAcctNumber
Field.Description: Account number at agent bank for distributions.

Field.Name: CashDistribPayRef
Field.Description: Free format Payment reference to assist with reconciliation of distributions.

Field.Name: CashDistribAgentAcctName
Field.Description: Name of account at agent bank for distributions.

Field.Name: CardStartDate
Field.Description: The start date of the card as specified on the card being used for payment.

Field.Name: PaymentDate
Field.Description: The date written on a cheque or date payment should be submitted to the relevant clearing system.

Field.Name: PaymentRemitterID
Field.Description: Identifies sender of a payment, e.g. the payment remitter or a customer reference number.

Field.Name: RegistStatus
Field.Description: Registration status as returned by the broker or (for CIV) the fund manager:

Field.Name: RegistRejReasonCode
Field.Description: Reason(s) why Registration Instructions has been rejected. The reason may be further amplified in the RegistRejReasonCode field. Possible values of reason code include:

Field.Name: RegistRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier for the RegistID (53) with Cancel and Replace RegistTransType (54) transaction types.

Field.Name: RegistDtls
Field.Description: Set of Registration name and address details, possibly including phone, fax etc.

Field.Name: NoDistribInsts
Field.Description: The number of Distribution Instructions on a Registration Instructions message

Field.Name: RegistEmail
Field.Description: Email address relating to Registration name and address details

Field.Name: DistribPercentage
Field.Description: The amount of each distribution to go to this beneficiary, expressed as a percentage

Field.Name: RegistID
Field.Description: Unique identifier of the registration details as assigned by institution or intermediary.

Field.Name: RegistTransType
Field.Description: Identifies Registration Instructions transaction type

Field.Name: ExecValuationPoint
Field.Description: For CIV - a date and time stamp to indicate the fund valuation point with respect to which a order was priced by the fund manager.

Field.Name: OrderPercent
Field.Description: For CIV specifies the approximate order quantity desired. For a CIV Sale it specifies percentage of investor's total holding to be sold. For a CIV switch/exchange it specifies percentage of investor's cash realised from sales to be re-invested. The executing broker, intermediary or fund manager is responsible for converting and calculating OrderQty (38) in shares/units for subsequent messages.

Field.Name: OwnershipType
Field.Description: The relationship between Registration parties.

Field.Name: NoContAmts
Field.Description: The number of Contract Amount details on an Execution Report message

Field.Name: ContAmtType
Field.Description: Type of ContAmtValue (520). NOTE That Commission Amount / % in Contract Amounts is the commission actually charged, rather than the commission instructions given in Fields 2/3.

Field.Name: ContAmtValue
Field.Description: Value of Contract Amount, e.g. a financial amount or percentage as indicated by ContAmtType (519).

Field.Name: ContAmtCurr
Field.Description: Specifies currency for the Contract amount if different from the Deal Currency - see "Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes".

Field.Name: OwnerType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of owner.

Field.Name: PartySubID
Field.Description: Sub-identifier (e.g. Clearing Account for PartyRole (452)=Clearing Firm, Locate ID # for PartyRole=Locate/Lending Firm, etc). Not required when using PartyID (448), PartyIDSource (447), and PartyRole.

Field.Name: NestedPartyID
Field.Description: PartyID value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyID (448)

Field.Name: NestedPartyIDSource
Field.Description: PartyIDSource value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

Field.Name: SecondaryClOrdID
Field.Description: Assigned by the party which originates the order. Can be used to provide the ClOrdID (11) used by an exchange or executing system.

Field.Name: SecondaryExecID
Field.Description: Assigned by the party which accepts the order. Can be used to provide the ExecID (17) used by an exchange or executing system.

Field.Name: OrderCapacity
Field.Description: Designates the capacity of the firm placing the order. (as of FIX 4.3, this field replaced Rule80A (tag 47) --used in conjunction with OrderRestrictions (529) field) (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

Field.Name: OrderRestrictions
Field.Description: Restrictions associated with an order. If more than one restriction is applicable to an order, this field can contain multiple instructions separated by space.

Field.Name: MassCancelRequestType
Field.Description: Specifies scope of Order Mass Cancel Request.

Field.Name: MassCancelResponse
Field.Description: Specifies the action taken by counterparty order handling system as a result of the Order Mass Cancel Request

Field.Name: MassCancelRejectReason
Field.Description: Reason Order Mass Cancel Request was rejected

Field.Name: TotalAffectedOrders
Field.Description: Total number of orders affected by either the OrderMassActionRequest(MsgType=CA) or OrderMassCancelRequest(MsgType=Q).

Field.Name: NoAffectedOrders
Field.Description: Number of affected orders in the repeating group of order ids.

Field.Name: AffectedOrderID
Field.Description: OrderID(37) of an order affected by a mass cancel or mass action request.

Field.Name: AffectedSecondaryOrderID
Field.Description: SecondaryOrderID(198) of an order affected by a mass cancel or mass action request.

Field.Name: QuoteType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of quote. An indicative quote is used to inform a counterparty of a market. An indicative quote does not result directly in a trade. A tradeable quote is submitted to a market and will result directly in a trade against other orders and quotes in a market. A restricted tradeable quote is submitted to a market and within a certain restriction (possibly based upon price or quantity) will automatically trade against orders. Order that do not comply with restrictions are sent to the quote issuer who can choose to accept or decline the order. A counter quote is used in the negotiation model. See Volume 7 - Product: Fixed Income for example usage.

Field.Name: NestedPartyRole
Field.Description: PartyRole value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyRole (452)

Field.Name: NoNestedPartyIDs
Field.Description: Number of NestedPartyID (524), NestedPartyIDSource (525), and NestedPartyRole (538) entries

Field.Name: TotalAccruedInterestAmt
Field.Description: Total Amount of Accrued Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income

Field.Name: MaturityDate
Field.Description: Date of maturity.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMaturityDate
Field.Description: Underlying security's maturity date. See MaturityDate (541) field for description

Field.Name: InstrRegistry
Field.Description: Values may include BIC for the depository or custodian who maintain ownership records, the ISO country code for the location of the record, or the value "ZZ" to specify physical ownership of the security (e.g. stock certificate).

Field.Name: CashMargin
Field.Description: Identifies whether an order is a margin order or a non-margin order. This is primarily used when sending orders to Japanese exchanges to indicate sell margin or buy to cover. The same tag could be assigned also by buy-side to indicate the intent to sell or buy margin and the sell-side to accept or reject (base on some validation criteria) the margin request.

Field.Name: NestedPartySubID
Field.Description: PartySubID value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartySubID (523)

Field.Name: Scope
Field.Description: Specifies the market scope of the market data.

Field.Name: MDImplicitDelete
Field.Description: Defines how a server handles distribution of a truncated book. Defaults to broker option.

Field.Name: CrossID
Field.Description: Identifier for a cross order. Must be unique during a given trading day. Recommend that firms use the order date as part of the CrossID for Good Till Cancel (GT) orders.

Field.Name: CrossType
Field.Description: Type of cross being submitted to a market

Field.Name: CrossPrioritization
Field.Description: Indicates if one side or the other of a cross order should be prioritized. The definition of prioritization is left to the market. In some markets prioritization means which side of the cross order is applied to the market first. In other markets - prioritization may mean that the prioritized side is fully executed (sometimes referred to as the side being protected).

Field.Name: OrigCrossID
Field.Description: CrossID of the previous cross order (NOT the initial cross order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous cross order in Cross Cancel and Cross Cancel/Replace Requests.

Field.Name: NoSides
Field.Description: Number of Side repeating group instances.

Field.Name: Username
Field.Description: Userid or username.

Field.Name: Password
Field.Description: Password or passphrase.

Field.Name: NoLegs
Field.Description: Number of InstrumentLeg repeating group instances.

Field.Name: LegCurrency
Field.Description: Currency associated with a particular Leg's quantity

Field.Name: TotNoSecurityTypes
Field.Description: Used to support fragmentation. Indicates total number of security types when multiple Security Type messages are used to return results.

Field.Name: NoSecurityTypes
Field.Description: Number of Security Type repeating group instances.

Field.Name: SecurityListRequestType
Field.Description: Identifies the type/criteria of Security List Request

Field.Name: SecurityRequestResult
Field.Description: The results returned to a Security Request message

Field.Name: RoundLot
Field.Description: The trading lot size of a security

Field.Name: MinTradeVol
Field.Description: The minimum order quantity (as expressed by TradeVolType(1786)) that can be submitted for a security.

Field.Name: MultiLegRptTypeReq
Field.Description: Indicates the method of execution reporting requested by issuer of the order.

Field.Name: LegPositionEffect
Field.Description: PositionEffect for leg of a multileg See PositionEffect (77) field for description

Field.Name: LegCoveredOrUncovered
Field.Description: CoveredOrUncovered for leg of a multileg See CoveredOrUncovered (203) field for description

Field.Name: LegPrice
Field.Description: Price for leg of a multileg See Price (44) field for description

Field.Name: TradSesStatusRejReason
Field.Description: Indicates the reason a Trading Session Status Request was rejected.

Field.Name: TradeRequestID
Field.Description: Trade Capture Report Request ID

Field.Name: TradeRequestType
Field.Description: Type of Trade Capture Report.

Field.Name: PreviouslyReported
Field.Description: Indicates if the transaction was previously reported to the counterparty or market.

Field.Name: TradeReportID
Field.Description: Unique identifier of trade capture report

Field.Name: TradeReportRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE transaction types.

Field.Name: MatchStatus
Field.Description: The status of this trade with respect to matching or comparison.

Field.Name: MatchType
Field.Description: The point in the matching process at which this trade was matched.

Field.Name: OddLot
Field.Description: This trade is to be treated as an odd lot If this field is not specified, the default will be "N"

Field.Name: NoClearingInstructions
Field.Description: Number of clearing instructions

Field.Name: ClearingInstruction
Field.Description: Eligibility of this trade for clearing and central counterparty processing.

Field.Name: TradeInputSource
Field.Description: Type of input device or system from which the trade was entered.

Field.Name: TradeInputDevice
Field.Description: Specific device number, terminal number or station where trade was entered

Field.Name: NoDates
Field.Description: Number of Date fields provided in date range

Field.Name: AccountType
Field.Description: Type of account associated with an order

Field.Name: CustOrderCapacity
Field.Description: Capacity of customer placing the order.
Field.Elaboration: Used by futures exchanges to indicate the CTICode (customer type indicator) as required by the US CFTC (Commodity Futures Trading Commission). May be used as required by other regulatory commissions for similar purposes.

Field.Name: ClOrdLinkID
Field.Description: Permits order originators to tie together groups of orders in which trades resulting from orders are associated for a specific purpose, for example the calculation of average execution price for a customer or to associate lists submitted to a broker as waves of a larger program trade.

Field.Name: MassStatusReqID
Field.Description: Value assigned by issuer of Mass Status Request to uniquely identify the request

Field.Name: MassStatusReqType
Field.Description: Mass Status Request Type

Field.Name: OrigOrdModTime
Field.Description: The most recent (or current) modification TransactTime (tag 60) reported on an Execution Report for the order. The OrigOrdModTime is provided as an optional field on Order Cancel Request and Order Cancel Replace Requests to identify that the state of the order has not changed since the request was issued. The use of this approach is not recommended.

Field.Name: LegSettlType
Field.Description: Indicates order settlement period. If present, LegSettlDate (588) overrides this field. If both LegSettlType (587) and LegSettDate (588) are omitted, the default for LegSettlType (587) is 0 (Regular) Regular is defined as the default settlement period for the particular security on the exchange of execution. In Fixed Income the contents of this field may influence the instrument definition if the LegSecurityID (602) is ambiguous. In the US an active Treasury offering may be re-opened, and for a time one CUSIP will apply to both the current and "when-issued" securities. Supplying a value of "7" clarifies the instrument description; any other value or the absence of this field should cause the respondent to default to the active issue. Additionally the following patterns may be uses as well as enum values Dx = FX tenor expression for "days", e.g. "D5", where "x" is any integer > 0 Mx = FX tenor expression for "months", e.g. "M3", where "x" is any integer > 0 Wx = FX tenor expression for "weeks", e.g. "W13", where "x" is any integer > 0 Yx = FX tenor expression for "years", e.g. "Y1", where "x" is any integer > 0. Note that for FX the tenors expressed using Dx, Mx, Wx, and Yx values do not denote business days, but calendar days.

Field.Name: LegSettlDate
Field.Description: Refer to description for SettlDate[64]

Field.Name: DayBookingInst
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not automatic booking can occur.

Field.Name: BookingUnit
Field.Description: Indicates what constitutes a bookable unit.

Field.Name: PreallocMethod
Field.Description: Indicates the method of preallocation.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCountryOfIssue
Field.Description: Underlying security's CountryOfIssue. See CountryOfIssue (470) field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingStateOrProvinceOfIssue
Field.Description: Underlying security's StateOrProvinceOfIssue. See StateOrProvinceOfIssue (471) field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingLocaleOfIssue
Field.Description: Underlying security's LocaleOfIssue. See LocaleOfIssue (472) field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingInstrRegistry
Field.Description: Underlying security's InstrRegistry. See InstrRegistry (543) field for description

Field.Name: LegCountryOfIssue
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's CountryOfIssue. See CountryOfIssue (470) field for description

Field.Name: LegStateOrProvinceOfIssue
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's StateOrProvinceOfIssue. See StateOrProvinceOfIssue (471) field for description

Field.Name: LegLocaleOfIssue
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's LocaleOfIssue. See LocaleOfIssue (472) field for description

Field.Name: LegInstrRegistry
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's InstrRegistry. See InstrRegistry (543) field for description

Field.Name: LegSymbol
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's Symbol. See Symbol (55) field for description

Field.Name: LegSymbolSfx
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's SymbolSfx. See SymbolSfx (65) field for description

Field.Name: LegSecurityID
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's SecurityID. See SecurityID (48) field for description

Field.Name: LegSecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's SecurityIDSource. See SecurityIDSource (22) field for description

Field.Name: NoLegSecurityAltID
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's NoSecurityAltID. See NoSecurityAltID (454) field for description

Field.Name: LegSecurityAltID
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's SecurityAltID. See SecurityAltID (455) field for description

Field.Name: LegSecurityAltIDSource
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's SecurityAltIDSource. See SecurityAltIDSource (456) field for description

Field.Name: LegProduct
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's Product. See Product (460) field for description

Field.Name: LegCFICode
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's CFICode. See CFICode (461) field for description

Field.Name: LegSecurityType
Field.Description: Refer to definition of SecurityType(167)

Field.Name: LegMaturityMonthYear
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's MaturityMonthYear. See MaturityMonthYear (200) field for description

Field.Name: LegMaturityDate
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's MaturityDate. See MaturityDate (54) field for description

Field.Name: LegStrikePrice
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's StrikePrice. See StrikePrice (202) field for description

Field.Name: LegOptAttribute
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's OptAttribute. See OptAttribute (206) field for description

Field.Name: LegContractMultiplier
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's ContractMultiplier. See ContractMultiplier (23) field for description

Field.Name: LegCouponRate
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's CouponRate. See CouponRate (223) field for description

Field.Name: LegSecurityExchange
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's SecurityExchange. See SecurityExchange (207) field for description

Field.Name: LegIssuer
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's Issuer. See Issuer (106) field for description

Field.Name: EncodedLegIssuerLen
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's EncodedIssuerLen. See EncodedIssuerLen (348) field for description

Field.Name: EncodedLegIssuer
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's EncodedIssuer. See EncodedIssuer (349) field for description

Field.Name: LegSecurityDesc
Field.Description: Description of a multileg instrument. Can be used by the venue or one of the trading parties to provide an optional non-normative textual description of the financial instrument.

Field.Name: EncodedLegSecurityDescLen
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's EncodedSecurityDescLen. See EncodedSecurityDescLen (350) field for description

Field.Name: EncodedLegSecurityDesc
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security's EncodedSecurityDesc. See EncodedSecurityDesc (35) field for description

Field.Name: LegRatioQty
Field.Description: The ratio of quantity for this individual leg relative to the entire multileg security.

Field.Name: LegSide
Field.Description: The side of this individual leg (multileg security). See Side (54) field for description and values

Field.Name: TradingSessionSubID
Field.Description: Optional market assigned sub identifier for a trading phase within a trading session. Usage is determined by market or counterparties. Used by US based futures markets to identify exchange specific execution time bracket codes as required by US market regulations. Bilaterally agreed values of data type "String" that start with a character can be used for backward compatibility

Field.Name: AllocType
Field.Description: Describes the specific type or purpose of an Allocation message (i.e. "Buyside Calculated") (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions) *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" ***

Field.Name: NoHops
Field.Description: Number of HopCompID entries in repeating group.

Field.Name: HopCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify the third party firm which delivered a specific message either from the firm which originated the message or from another third party (if multiple "hops" are performed). It is recommended that this value be the SenderCompID (49) of the third party. Applicable when messages are communicated/re-distributed via third parties which function as service bureaus or "hubs". Only applicable if OnBehalfOfCompID (115) is being used.

Field.Name: HopSendingTime
Field.Description: Time that HopCompID (628) sent the message. It is recommended that this value be the SendingTime (52) of the message sent by the third party. Applicable when messages are communicated/re-distributed via third parties which function as service bureaus or "hubs". Only applicable if OnBehalfOfCompID (115) is being used.

Field.Name: HopRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier assigned by HopCompID (628) associated with the message sent. It is recommended that this value be the MsgSeqNum (34) of the message sent by the third party. Applicable when messages are communicated/re-distributed via third parties which function as service bureaus or "hubs". Only applicable if OnBehalfOfCompID (115) is being used.

Field.Name: MidPx
Field.Description: Mid price/rate. For OTC swaps this is the mid-market mark (for example, as defined by CFTC). For uncleared OTC swaps, LegMidPx(2346) and the MidPx(631) fields are mutually exclusive.

Field.Name: BidYield
Field.Description: Bid yield

Field.Name: MidYield
Field.Description: Mid yield

Field.Name: OfferYield
Field.Description: Offer yield

Field.Name: ClearingFeeIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates type of fee being assessed of the customer for trade executions at an exchange. Applicable for futures markets only at this time. (Values source CBOT, CME, NYBOT, and NYMEX):

Field.Name: WorkingIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates if the order is currently being worked. Applicable only for OrdStatus = "New". For open outcry markets this indicates that the order is being worked in the crowd. For electronic markets it indicates that the order has transitioned from a contingent order to a market order.

Field.Name: LegLastPx
Field.Description: Execution price assigned to a leg of a multileg instrument. See LastPx (31) field for description and values

Field.Name: PriorityIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates if a Cancel/Replace has caused an order to lose book priority.

Field.Name: PriceImprovement
Field.Description: Amount of price improvement.

Field.Name: Price2
Field.Description: Price of the future part of a F/X swap order. See Price (44) for description.

Field.Name: LastForwardPoints2
Field.Description: F/X forward points of the future part of a F/X swap order added to LastSpotRate (94). May be a negative value.

Field.Name: BidForwardPoints2
Field.Description: Bid F/X forward points of the future portion of a F/X swap quote added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: OfferForwardPoints2
Field.Description: Offer F/X forward points of the future portion of a F/X swap quote added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: RFQReqID
Field.Description: RFQ Request ID - used to identify an RFQ Request.

Field.Name: MktBidPx
Field.Description: Used to indicate the best bid in a market

Field.Name: MktOfferPx
Field.Description: Used to indicate the best offer in a market

Field.Name: MinBidSize
Field.Description: Used to indicate a minimum quantity for a bid.

Field.Name: MinOfferSize
Field.Description: Used to indicate a minimum quantity for an offer. If this field is used the OfferSize (135) field is interpreted as the maximum offer size.

Field.Name: QuoteStatusReqID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Quote Status Request.

Field.Name: LegalConfirm
Field.Description: Indicates that this message is to serve as the final and legal confirmation.

Field.Name: UnderlyingLastPx
Field.Description: The calculated or traded price for the underlying instrument that corresponds to a derivative. Used for transactions that include the cash instrument and the derivative.

Field.Name: UnderlyingLastQty
Field.Description: The calculated or traded quantity for the underlying instrument that corresponds to a derivative. Used for transactions that include the cash instrument and the derivative.

Field.Name: LegRefID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a specific leg (uniqueness not defined as part of the FIX specification). LegRefID(654) be used to reference the value from LegID(1788).

Field.Name: ContraLegRefID
Field.Description: Unique indicator for a specific leg for the ContraBroker (375).

Field.Name: SettlCurrBidFxRate
Field.Description: Foreign exchange rate used to compute the bid "SettlCurrAmt" (119) from Currency (15) to SettlCurrency (120)

Field.Name: SettlCurrOfferFxRate
Field.Description: Foreign exchange rate used to compute the offer "SettlCurrAmt" (119) from Currency (15) to SettlCurrency (120)

Field.Name: QuoteRequestRejectReason
Field.Description: Reason Quote was rejected:

Field.Name: SideComplianceID
Field.Description: ID within repeating group of sides which is used to represent this transaction for compliance purposes (e.g. OATS reporting).

Field.Name: AcctIDSource
Field.Description: Used to identify the source of the Account (1) code. This is especially useful if the account is a new account that the Respondent may not have setup yet in their system.

Field.Name: AllocAcctIDSource
Field.Description: Used to identify the source of the AllocAccount (79) code. See AcctIDSource (660) for valid values.

Field.Name: BenchmarkPrice
Field.Description: Specifies the price of the benchmark.

Field.Name: BenchmarkPriceType
Field.Description: Identifies type of BenchmarkPrice (662). See PriceType (423) for valid values.

Field.Name: ConfirmID
Field.Description: Message reference for Confirmation

Field.Name: ConfirmStatus
Field.Description: Identifies the status of the Confirmation.

Field.Name: ConfirmTransType
Field.Description: Identifies the Confirmation transaction type.

Field.Name: ContractSettlMonth
Field.Description: Specifies when the contract (i.e. MBS/TBA) will settle.

Field.Name: DeliveryForm
Field.Description: Identifies the form of delivery.

Field.Name: LastParPx
Field.Description: Last price expressed in percent-of-par. Conditionally required for Fixed Income trades when LastPx (31) is expressed in Yield, Spread, Discount or any other type. Usage: Execution Report and Allocation Report repeating executions block (from sellside).

Field.Name: NoLegAllocs
Field.Description: Number of Allocations for the leg

Field.Name: LegAllocAccount
Field.Description: Allocation Account for the leg See AllocAccount (79) for description and valid values.

Field.Name: LegIndividualAllocID
Field.Description: Reference for the individual allocation ticket See IndividualAllocID (467) for description and valid values.

Field.Name: LegAllocQty
Field.Description: Leg allocation quantity. See AllocQty (80) for description and valid values.

Field.Name: LegAllocAcctIDSource
Field.Description: The source of the LegAllocAccount (671) See AllocAcctIDSource (661) for description and valid values.

Field.Name: LegSettlCurrency
Field.Description: Identifies settlement currency for the Leg. See SettlCurrency (20) for description and valid values

Field.Name: LegBenchmarkCurveCurrency
Field.Description: LegBenchmarkPrice (679) currency See BenchmarkCurveCurrency (220) for description and valid values.

Field.Name: LegBenchmarkCurveName
Field.Description: Name of the Leg Benchmark Curve. See BenchmarkCurveName (22) for description and valid values.

Field.Name: LegBenchmarkCurvePoint
Field.Description: Identifies the point on the Leg Benchmark Curve. See BenchmarkCurvePoint (222) for description and valid values.

Field.Name: LegBenchmarkPrice
Field.Description: Used to identify the price of the benchmark security. See BenchmarkPrice (662) for description and valid values.

Field.Name: LegBenchmarkPriceType
Field.Description: The price type of the LegBenchmarkPrice(679).

Field.Name: LegBidPx
Field.Description: Bid price of this leg. See BidPx (32) for description and valid values.

Field.Name: LegIOIQty
Field.Description: Leg-specific IOI quantity. See IOIQty (27) for description and valid values

Field.Name: NoLegStipulations
Field.Description: Number of leg stipulation entries

Field.Name: LegOfferPx
Field.Description: Offer price of this leg. See OfferPx (133) for description and valid values

Field.Name: LegOrderQty
Field.Description: Quantity ordered of this leg. See OrderQty (38) for description and valid values

Field.Name: LegPriceType
Field.Description: The price type of the LegBidPx (681) and/or LegOfferPx (684). See PriceType (423) for description and valid values

Field.Name: LegQty
Field.Description: This field is deprecated and has been replaced by LegOrderQty(865). This field will likely be removed from the FIX standard in a future version.

Field.Name: LegStipulationType
Field.Description: For Fixed Income, type of Stipulation for this leg. See StipulationType (233) for description and valid values

Field.Name: LegStipulationValue
Field.Description: For Fixed Income, value of stipulation. See StipulationValue (234) for description and valid values

Field.Name: LegSwapType
Field.Description: For Fixed Income, used instead of LegOrderQty(685) to requests the respondent to calculate the quantity based on the quantity on the opposite side of the swap.

Field.Name: Pool
Field.Description: For Fixed Income, identifies MBS / ABS pool.

Field.Name: QuotePriceType
Field.Description: Code to represent price type requested in Quote. If the Quote Request is for a Swap, values 1-8 apply to all legs.

Field.Name: QuoteRespID
Field.Description: Message reference for Quote Response

Field.Name: QuoteRespType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of Quote Response.

Field.Name: QuoteQualifier
Field.Description: Code to qualify Quote use and other aspects of price negotiation.

Field.Name: YieldRedemptionDate
Field.Description: Date to which the yield has been calculated (i.e. maturity, par call or current call, pre-refunded date).

Field.Name: YieldRedemptionPrice
Field.Description: Price to which the yield has been calculated.

Field.Name: YieldRedemptionPriceType
Field.Description: The price type of the YieldRedemptionPrice (697) See PriceType (423) for description and valid values.

Field.Name: BenchmarkSecurityID
Field.Description: The identifier of the benchmark security, e.g. Treasury against Corporate bond. See SecurityID (tag 48) for description and valid values.

Field.Name: ReversalIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates a trade that reverses a previous trade.

Field.Name: YieldCalcDate
Field.Description: Include as needed to clarify yield irregularities associated with date, e.g. when it falls on a non-business day.

Field.Name: NoPositions
Field.Description: Number of position entries.

Field.Name: PosType
Field.Description: Used to identify the type of quantity that is being returned.

Field.Name: LongQty
Field.Description: Long quantity.

Field.Name: ShortQty
Field.Description: Short quantity.

Field.Name: PosQtyStatus
Field.Description: Status of this position.

Field.Name: PosAmtType
Field.Description: Type of Position amount

Field.Name: PosAmt
Field.Description: Position amount

Field.Name: PosTransType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of position transaction.

Field.Name: PosReqID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for the position maintenance request as assigned by the submitter

Field.Name: NoUnderlyings
Field.Description: Number of underlying legs that make up the security.

Field.Name: PosMaintAction
Field.Description: Maintenance Action to be performed.

Field.Name: OrigPosReqRefID
Field.Description: Reference to the PosReqID (710) of a previous maintenance request that is being replaced or canceled.

Field.Name: PosMaintRptRefID
Field.Description: Reference to a PosMaintRptID (721) from a previous Position Maintenance Report that is being replaced or canceled.

Field.Name: ClearingBusinessDate
Field.Description: The business date for which the trade is expected to be cleared.

Field.Name: SettlSessID
Field.Description: Identifies a specific settlement session

Field.Name: SettlSessSubID
Field.Description: SubID value associated with SettlSessID(716)

Field.Name: AdjustmentType
Field.Description: Type of adjustment to be applied. Used for Position Change Submission (PCS), Position Adjustment (PAJ), and Customer Gross Margin (CGM).

Field.Name: ContraryInstructionIndicator
Field.Description: Used to indicate when a contrary instruction for exercise or abandonment is being submitted

Field.Name: PriorSpreadIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates if requesting a rollover of prior day's spread submissions.

Field.Name: PosMaintRptID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for this position report

Field.Name: PosMaintStatus
Field.Description: Status of Position Maintenance Request

Field.Name: PosMaintResult
Field.Description: Result of Position Maintenance Request.

Field.Name: PosReqType
Field.Description: Used to specify the type of position request being made.

Field.Name: ResponseTransportType
Field.Description: Identifies how the response to the request should be transmitted. Details specified via ResponseDestination (726).

Field.Name: ResponseDestination
Field.Description: URI (Uniform Resource Identifier) for details) or other pre-arranged value. Used in conjunction with ResponseTransportType (725) value of Out-of-Band to identify the out-of-band destination. See "Appendix 6-B FIX Fields Based Upon Other Standards"

Field.Name: TotalNumPosReports
Field.Description: Total number of Position Reports being returned.

Field.Name: PosReqResult
Field.Description: Result of Request for Positions.

Field.Name: PosReqStatus
Field.Description: Status of Request for Positions

Field.Name: SettlPrice
Field.Description: Settlement price

Field.Name: SettlPriceType
Field.Description: Type of settlement price

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlPrice
Field.Description: Underlying security's SettlPrice. See SettlPrice (730) field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlPriceType
Field.Description: Underlying security's SettlPriceType. See SettlPriceType (731) field for description

Field.Name: PriorSettlPrice
Field.Description: Previous settlement price

Field.Name: NoQuoteQualifiers
Field.Description: Number of repeating groups of QuoteQualifiers (695).

Field.Name: AllocSettlCurrency
Field.Description: Currency code of settlement denomination for a specific AllocAccount (79).

Field.Name: AllocSettlCurrAmt
Field.Description: Total amount due expressed in settlement currency (includes the effect of the forex transaction) for a specific AllocAccount (79).

Field.Name: InterestAtMaturity
Field.Description: Amount of interest (i.e. lump-sum) at maturity.

Field.Name: LegDatedDate
Field.Description: The effective date of a new securities issue determined by its underwriters. Often but not always the same as the Issue Date and the Interest Accrual Date

Field.Name: LegPool
Field.Description: For Fixed Income, identifies MBS / ABS pool for a specific leg of a multi-leg instrument. See Pool (691) for description and valid values.

Field.Name: AllocInterestAtMaturity
Field.Description: Amount of interest (i.e. lump-sum) at maturity at the account-level.

Field.Name: AllocAccruedInterestAmt
Field.Description: Amount of Accrued Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income at the allocation-level.

Field.Name: DeliveryDate
Field.Description: Date of delivery.

Field.Name: AssignmentMethod
Field.Description: Method by which short positions are assigned to an exercise notice during exercise and assignment processing

Field.Name: AssignmentUnit
Field.Description: Quantity Increment used in performing assignment.

Field.Name: OpenInterest
Field.Description: Open interest that was eligible for assignment.

Field.Name: ExerciseMethod
Field.Description: Exercise Method used to in performing assignment.

Field.Name: TotNumTradeReports
Field.Description: Total number of trade reports returned.

Field.Name: TradeRequestResult
Field.Description: Result of Trade Request

Field.Name: TradeRequestStatus
Field.Description: Status of Trade Request.

Field.Name: TradeReportRejectReason
Field.Description: Reason Trade Capture Request was rejected. 100+ Reserved and available for bi-laterally agreed upon user-defined values.

Field.Name: SideMultiLegReportingType
Field.Description: Used to indicate if the side being reported on Trade Capture Report represents a leg of a multileg instrument or a single security.

Field.Name: NoPosAmt
Field.Description: Number of position amount entries.

Field.Name: AutoAcceptIndicator
Field.Description: Identifies whether or not an allocation has been automatically accepted on behalf of the Carry Firm by the Clearing House.

Field.Name: AllocReportID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Allocation Report message.

Field.Name: NoNested2PartyIDs
Field.Description: Number of Nested2PartyID (757), Nested2PartyIDSource (758), and Nested2PartyRole (759) entries

Field.Name: Nested2PartyID
Field.Description: PartyID value within a "second instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartyID (448)

Field.Name: Nested2PartyIDSource
Field.Description: PartyIDSource value within a "second instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

Field.Name: Nested2PartyRole
Field.Description: PartyRole value within a "second instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartyRole (452)

Field.Name: Nested2PartySubID
Field.Description: PartySubID value within a "second instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartySubID (523)

Field.Name: BenchmarkSecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies class or source of the BenchmarkSecurityID (699) value. Required if BenchmarkSecurityID is specified. Same values as the SecurityIDSource (22) field

Field.Name: SecuritySubType
Field.Description: Sub-type qualification/identification of the SecurityType. As an example for SecurityType(167)="REPO", the SecuritySubType="General Collateral" can be used to further specify the type of REPO. If SecuritySubType is used, then SecurityType is required. For SecurityType="MLEG" a name of the option or futures strategy name can be specified, such as "Calendar", "Vertical", "Butterfly". For SecurityType(167)="OPT" the subclassification can be specified, such as "Asian". For SecurityType(167)="SWAPTION" a value of "Straddle" is used to identify a straddle swaption. In the context of EU SFTR reporting use the appropriate 4-character code noted in the regulations - "GENE" for general collateral or "SPEC" for specific collateral (without quote marks).

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecuritySubType
Field.Description: Underlying security's SecuritySubType. See SecuritySubType (762) field for description

Field.Name: LegSecuritySubType
Field.Description: SecuritySubType of the leg instrument. See SecuritySubType (762) field for description

Field.Name: AllowableOneSidednessPct
Field.Description: The maximum percentage that execution of one side of a program trade can exceed execution of the other.

Field.Name: AllowableOneSidednessValue
Field.Description: The maximum amount that execution of one side of a program trade can exceed execution of the other.

Field.Name: AllowableOneSidednessCurr
Field.Description: The currency that AllowableOneSidednessValue (766) is expressed in if AllowableOneSidednessValue is used.

Field.Name: NoTrdRegTimestamps
Field.Description: Number of TrdRegTimestamp (769) entries

Field.Name: TrdRegTimestamp
Field.Description: Traded / Regulatory timestamp value. Use to store time information required by government regulators or self regulatory organizations (such as an exchange or clearing house).

Field.Name: TrdRegTimestampType
Field.Description: Trading / Regulatory timestamp type. Note of applicability: Values are required in various regulatory environments: required for US futures markets to support computerized trade reconstruction, required by MiFID II / MiFIR for transaction reporting and publication, and required by FINRA for reporting to the Consolidated Audit Trail (CAT).

Field.Name: TrdRegTimestampOrigin
Field.Description: Text which identifies the "origin" (i.e. system which was used to generate the time stamp) for the Traded / Regulatory timestamp value.

Field.Name: ConfirmRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier to be used with ConfirmTransType (666) = Replace or Cancel

Field.Name: ConfirmType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of Confirmation message being sent.

Field.Name: ConfirmRejReason
Field.Description: Identifies the reason for rejecting a Confirmation.

Field.Name: BookingType
Field.Description: Method for booking out this order. Used when notifying a broker that an order to be settled by that broker is to be booked out as an OTC derivative (e.g. CFD or similar).

Field.Name: IndividualAllocRejCode
Field.Description: Identified reason for rejecting an individual AllocAccount (79) detail. Same values as AllocRejCode (88)

Field.Name: SettlInstMsgID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Settlement Instruction message.

Field.Name: NoSettlInst
Field.Description: Number of settlement instructions within repeating group.

Field.Name: LastUpdateTime
Field.Description: Timestamp of last update to data item (or creation if no updates made since creation).

Field.Name: AllocSettlInstType
Field.Description: Used to indicate whether settlement instructions are provided on an allocation instruction message, and if not, how they are to be derived.

Field.Name: NoSettlPartyIDs
Field.Description: Number of SettlPartyID (782), SettlPartyIDSource (783), and SettlPartyRole (784) entries

Field.Name: SettlPartyID
Field.Description: PartyID value within a settlement parties component. Nested repeating group. Same values as PartyID (448)

Field.Name: SettlPartyIDSource
Field.Description: PartyIDSource value within a settlement parties component. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

Field.Name: SettlPartyRole
Field.Description: PartyRole value within a settlement parties component. Same values as PartyRole (452)

Field.Name: SettlPartySubID
Field.Description: PartySubID value within a settlement parties component. Same values as PartySubID (523)

Field.Name: SettlPartySubIDType
Field.Description: Type of SettlPartySubID (785) value. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

Field.Name: DlvyInstType
Field.Description: Used to indicate whether a delivery instruction is used for securities or cash settlement.

Field.Name: TerminationType
Field.Description: Type of financing termination.

Field.Name: NextExpectedMsgSeqNum
Field.Description: Next expected MsgSeqNum value to be received.

Field.Name: OrdStatusReqID
Field.Description: Can be used to uniquely identify a specific Order Status Request message.

Field.Name: SettlInstReqID
Field.Description: Unique ID of settlement instruction request message

Field.Name: SettlInstReqRejCode
Field.Description: Identifies reason for rejection (of a settlement instruction request message).

Field.Name: SecondaryAllocID
Field.Description: Secondary allocation identifier. Unlike the AllocID (70), this can be shared across a number of allocation instruction or allocation report messages, thereby making it possible to pass an identifier for an original allocation message on multiple messages (e.g. from one party to a second to a third, across cancel and replace messages etc.).

Field.Name: AllocReportType
Field.Description: Describes the specific type or purpose of an Allocation Report message

Field.Name: AllocReportRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier to be used with AllocTransType (7) = Replace or Cancel

Field.Name: AllocCancReplaceReason
Field.Description: Reason for cancelling or replacing an Allocation Instruction or Allocation Report message

Field.Name: CopyMsgIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not this message is a drop copy of another message.

Field.Name: AllocAccountType
Field.Description: Type of account associated with a confirmation or other trade-level message

Field.Name: OrderAvgPx
Field.Description: Average price for a specific order

Field.Name: OrderBookingQty
Field.Description: Quantity of the order that is being booked out as part of an Allocation Instruction or Allocation Report message

Field.Name: NoSettlPartySubIDs
Field.Description: Number of SettlPartySubID (785) and SettlPartySubIDType (786) entries

Field.Name: NoPartySubIDs
Field.Description: Number of PartySubID (523)and PartySubIDType (803) entries

Field.Name: PartySubIDType
Field.Description: Type of PartySubID(523) value.

Field.Name: NoNestedPartySubIDs
Field.Description: Number of NestedPartySubID (545) and NestedPartySubIDType (805) entries

Field.Name: NestedPartySubIDType
Field.Description: Type of NestedPartySubID (545) value. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

Field.Name: NoNested2PartySubIDs
Field.Description: Number of Nested2PartySubID (760) and Nested2PartySubIDType (807) entries. Second instance of <NestedParties>.

Field.Name: Nested2PartySubIDType
Field.Description: Type of Nested2PartySubID (760) value. Second instance of <NestedParties>. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

Field.Name: AllocIntermedReqType
Field.Description: Response to allocation to be communicated to a counterparty through an intermediary, i.e. clearing house. Used in conjunction with AllocType = "Request to Intermediary" and AllocReportType = "Request to Intermediary"

Field.Name: UnderlyingPx
Field.Description: Underlying price associate with a derivative instrument.

Field.Name: PriceDelta
Field.Description: The rate of change in the price of a derivative with respect to the movement in the price of the underlying instrument(s) upon which the derivative instrument price is based. This value is normally between -1.0 and 1.0.

Field.Name: ApplQueueMax
Field.Description: Used to specify the maximum number of application messages that can be queued bedore a corrective action needs to take place to resolve the queuing issue.

Field.Name: ApplQueueDepth
Field.Description: Current number of application messages that were queued at the time that the message was created by the counterparty.

Field.Name: ApplQueueResolution
Field.Description: Resolution taken when ApplQueueDepth (813) exceeds ApplQueueMax (812) or system specified maximum queue size.

Field.Name: ApplQueueAction
Field.Description: Action to take to resolve an application message queue (backlog).

Field.Name: NoAltMDSource
Field.Description: Number of alternative market data sources

Field.Name: AltMDSourceID
Field.Description: Session layer source for market data (For the standard FIX session layer, this would be the TargetCompID (56) where market data can be obtained).

Field.Name: SecondaryTradeReportID

Field.Name: TransferReason

Field.Name: PegLimitType

Field.Name: PegRoundDirection

Field.Name: PeggedPrice

Field.Name: PegScope

Field.Name: DiscretionMoveType

Field.Name: DiscretionOffsetType

Field.Name: DiscretionLimitType

Field.Name: DiscretionRoundDirection

Field.Name: DiscretionPrice

Field.Name: DiscretionScope

Field.Name: TargetStrategy

Field.Name: TargetStrategyParameters

Field.Name: ParticipationRate
Field.Description: For a TargetStrategy=Participate order specifies the target particpation rate. For other order types this is a volume limit (i.e. do not be more than this percent of the market volume)

Field.Name: TargetStrategyPerformance
Field.Description: For communication of the performance of the order versus the target strategy

Field.Name: LastLiquidityInd

Field.Name: PublishTrdIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates if a trade should be reported via a market reporting service.

Field.Name: ShortSaleReason

Field.Name: QtyType
Field.Description: Type of quantity specified in quantity field. ContractMultiplier (tag 231) is required when QtyType = 1 (Contracts). UnitOfMeasure (tag 996) and TimeUnit (tag 997) are required when QtyType = 2 (Units of Measure per Time Unit).

Field.Name: SecondaryTrdType
Field.Description: Additional TrdType(828) assigned to a trade by trade match system.

Field.Name: TradeReportType

Field.Name: AllocNoOrdersType
Field.Description: Indicates how the orders being booked and allocated by an AllocationInstruction or AllocationReport message are identified, e.g. by explicit definition in the OrdAllocGrp or ExecAllocGrp components, or not identified explicitly.

Field.Name: SharedCommission

Field.Name: ConfirmReqID

Field.Name: AvgParPx
Field.Description: Used to express average price as percent of par (used where AvgPx field is expressed in some other way)

Field.Name: ReportedPx
Field.Description: Reported price (used to differentiate from AvgPx on a confirmation of a marked-up or marked-down principal trade)

Field.Name: EventText

Field.Name: PctAtRisk

Field.Name: NoInstrAttrib
Field.Description: Number of repeating InstrAttribType entries.

Field.Name: InstrAttribType
Field.Description: Code to represent the type of instrument attribute

Field.Name: InstrAttribValue
Field.Description: Attribute value appropriate to the InstrAttribType (87) field.

Field.Name: DatedDate
Field.Description: The effective date of a new securities issue determined by its underwriters. Often but not always the same as the Issue Date and the Interest Accrual Date

Field.Name: InterestAccrualDate
Field.Description: The start date used for calculating accrued interest on debt instruments which are being sold between interest payment dates. Often but not always the same as the Issue Date and the Dated Date

Field.Name: CPProgram
Field.Description: The program under which a commercial paper offering is exempt from SEC registration identified by the paragraph number(s) within the US Securities Act of 1933 or as identified below.

Field.Name: CPRegType
Field.Description: The description of commercial paper registration or rule under which exempt commercial paper is offered. For example "144a", "Tax Exempt" or "REG. S".

Field.Name: UnderlyingCPProgram

Field.Name: UnderlyingCPRegType
Field.Description: The registration type of the underlying commercial paper issuance

Field.Name: UnderlyingQty

Field.Name: SecondaryTradeReportRefID

Field.Name: UnderlyingDirtyPrice
Field.Description: Price (percent-of-par or per unit) of the underlying security or basket. "Dirty" means it includes accrued interest

Field.Name: UnderlyingEndPrice
Field.Description: Price (percent-of-par or per unit) of the underlying security or basket at the end of the agreement.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStartValue
Field.Description: Currency value attributed to this collateral at the start of the agreement

Field.Name: UnderlyingCurrentValue
Field.Description: Currency value currently attributed to this collateral

Field.Name: UnderlyingEndValue
Field.Description: Currency value attributed to this collateral at the end of the agreement

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingStips

Field.Name: UnderlyingStipType

Field.Name: UnderlyingStipValue
Field.Description: Value of stipulation. Same values as StipulationValue (234)

Field.Name: MaturityNetMoney
Field.Description: Net Money at maturity if Zero Coupon and maturity value is different from par value

Field.Name: MiscFeeBasis
Field.Description: Defines the unit for a miscellaneous fee.

Field.Name: TotNoAllocs
Field.Description: Total number of NoAlloc entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoAllocs in each message that has repeating NoAlloc entries related to the same AllocID or AllocReportID. Used to support fragmentation.

Field.Name: LastFragment
Field.Description: Indicates whether this message is the last in a sequence of messages for those messages that support fragmentation, such as Allocation Instruction, Mass Quote, Security List, Derivative Security List

Field.Name: CollReqID
Field.Description: Collateral Request Identifier

Field.Name: CollAsgnReason
Field.Description: Reason for Collateral Assignment

Field.Name: CollInquiryQualifier
Field.Description: Collateral inquiry qualifiers:

Field.Name: NoTrades
Field.Description: Number of trades in repeating group.

Field.Name: MarginRatio
Field.Description: The fraction of the cash consideration that must be collateralized, expressed as a percent. A MarginRatio of 02% indicates that the value of the collateral (after deducting for "haircut") must exceed the cash consideration by 2%.

Field.Name: MarginExcess
Field.Description: Excess margin amount (deficit if value is negative)

Field.Name: TotalNetValue
Field.Description: TotalNetValue is determined as follows: At the initial collateral assignment TotalNetValue is the sum of (UnderlyingStartValue * (1-haircut)). In a collateral substitution TotalNetValue is the sum of (UnderlyingCurrentValue * (1-haircut)). For listed derivatives clearing margin management, this is the collateral value which equals (Market value * haircut)

Field.Name: CashOutstanding
Field.Description: Starting consideration less repayments

Field.Name: CollAsgnID
Field.Description: Collateral Assignment Identifier

Field.Name: CollAsgnTransType
Field.Description: Collateral Assignment Transaction Type

Field.Name: CollRespID
Field.Description: Collateral Response Identifier

Field.Name: CollAsgnRespType
Field.Description: Type of collateral assignment response.

Field.Name: CollAsgnRejectReason
Field.Description: Collateral Assignment Reject Reason

Field.Name: CollAsgnRefID
Field.Description: Collateral Assignment Identifier to which a transaction refers

Field.Name: CollInquiryID
Field.Description: Collateral Inquiry Identifier

Field.Name: CollStatus
Field.Description: Collateral Status

Field.Name: TotNumReports

Field.Name: LastRptRequested
Field.Description: Indicates whether this message is the last report message in response to a request message, e.g. OrderMassStatusRequest(35=AF), TradeCaptureReportRequest(35=AD).

Field.Name: AgreementDesc
Field.Description: The full name of the base standard agreement, annexes and amendments in place between the principals applicable to a financing transaction. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/master-agreement-type for derivative values.
Field.Elaboration: For EU SFTR reporting use the appropriate 4-character code noted in the regulations. See SFTR ITS "Commission Implementing Regulation (EU) 2019/363" Annexes 1 to 2 for values. For other agreement type use OTHR and the name of the agreement concatenated with a hyphen, e.g. OTHR-<IndexName>.

Field.Name: AgreementID
Field.Description: A common reference to the applicable standing agreement between the counterparties to a financing transaction.

Field.Name: AgreementDate
Field.Description: A reference to the date the underlying agreement specified by AgreementID and AgreementDesc was executed.

Field.Name: StartDate
Field.Description: Start date of a financing deal, i.e. the date the buyer pays the seller cash and takes control of the collateral

Field.Name: EndDate
Field.Description: End date of a financing deal, i.e. the date the seller reimburses the buyer and takes back control of the collateral

Field.Name: AgreementCurrency
Field.Description: Contractual currency forming the basis of a financing agreement and associated transactions. Usually, but not always, the same as the trade currency.

Field.Name: DeliveryType
Field.Description: Identifies type of settlement

Field.Name: EndAccruedInterestAmt
Field.Description: Accrued Interest Amount applicable to a financing transaction on the End Date.

Field.Name: StartCash
Field.Description: Starting dirty cash consideration of a financing deal, i.e. paid to the seller on the Start Date.

Field.Name: EndCash
Field.Description: Ending dirty cash consideration of a financing deal. i.e. reimbursed to the buyer on the End Date.

Field.Name: UserRequestID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a User Request.

Field.Name: UserRequestType
Field.Description: Indicates the action required by a User Request Message

Field.Name: NewPassword

Field.Name: UserStatus
Field.Description: Indicates the status of a user

Field.Name: UserStatusText

Field.Description: Indicates the status of a network connection

Field.Name: StatusText
Field.Description: A text description associated with a network status.

Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify a firm.

Field.Name: RefSubID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific elements within a firm.

Field.Name: NetworkResponseID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a network response.

Field.Name: NetworkRequestID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a network resquest.

Field.Name: LastNetworkResponseID
Field.Description: Identifier of the previous Network Response message sent to a counterparty, used to allow incremental updates.

Field.Name: NetworkRequestType
Field.Description: Indicates the type and level of details required for a Network Status Request Message Boolean logic applies EG If you want to subscribe for changes to certain id's then UserRequestType =0 (8+2), Snapshot for certain ID's = 9 (8+1)

Field.Name: NoCompIDs
Field.Description: Number of CompID entries in a repeating group.

Field.Name: NetworkStatusResponseType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of Network Response Message.

Field.Name: NoCollInquiryQualifier
Field.Description: Number of CollInquiryQualifier entries in a repeating group.

Field.Name: TrdRptStatus
Field.Description: Trade Report Status

Field.Name: AffirmStatus
Field.Description: Specifies the affirmation status of the confirmation.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStrikeCurrency
Field.Description: Currency in which the strike price of an underlying instrument is denominated

Field.Name: LegStrikeCurrency
Field.Description: Currency in which the strike price of a instrument leg of a multileg instrument is denominated

Field.Name: TimeBracket
Field.Description: A code that represents a time interval in which a fill or trade occurred. Required for US futures markets.

Field.Name: CollAction
Field.Description: Action proposed for an Underlying Instrument instance.

Field.Name: CollInquiryStatus

Field.Name: CollInquiryResult
Field.Description: Result returned in response to Collateral Inquiry 4000+ Reserved and available for bi-laterally agreed upon user-defined values

Field.Description: PartySubIDType value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

Field.Name: LegContractSettlMonth
Field.Description: Specifies when the contract (i.e. MBS/TBA) will settle.

Field.Name: LegInterestAccrualDate
Field.Description: The start date used for calculating accrued interest on debt instruments which are being sold between interest payment dates. Often but not always the same as the Issue Date and the Dated Date

Field.Name: NoStrategyParameters
Field.Description: Indicates number of strategy parameters

Field.Name: StrategyParameterName
Field.Description: Name of parameter

Field.Name: StrategyParameterType
Field.Description: Datatype of the parameter

Field.Name: StrategyParameterValue
Field.Description: Value of the parameter

Field.Name: HostCrossID
Field.Description: Host assigned entity ID that can be used to reference all components of a cross; sides + strategy + legs. Used as the primary key with which to refer to the Cross Order for cancellation and replace. The HostCrossID will also be used to link together components of the Cross Order. For example, each individual Execution Report associated with the order will carry HostCrossID in order to tie back to the original cross order.

Field.Name: SideTimeInForce
Field.Description: Indicates how long the order as specified in the side stays in effect. SideTimeInForce allows a two-sided cross order to specify order behavior separately for each side. Absence of this field indicates that TimeInForce should be referenced. SideTimeInForce will override TimeInForce if both are provided.

Field.Description: Unique identifier for the Market Data Report.

Field.Name: StrikeValue

Field.Name: MinPriceIncrement
Field.Description: Minimum price increase for a given exchange-traded Instrument

Field.Name: PositionLimit
Field.Description: Position Limit for a given exchange-traded product.

Field.Name: NTPositionLimit
Field.Description: Position Limit in the near-term contract for a given exchange-traded product.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAllocationPercent
Field.Description: Percent of the Strike Price that this underlying represents.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashAmount
Field.Description: Cash amount associated with the underlying component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashType
Field.Description: Used for derivatives that deliver into cash underlying.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlementType
Field.Description: Indicates order settlement period for the underlying instrument.

Field.Name: QuantityDate
Field.Description: Date associated to the quantity that is being reported for the position.

Field.Name: ContIntRptID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for the Contrary Intention report

Field.Name: LateIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates if the contrary intention was received after the exchange imposed cutoff time
