Field.Name: ExpirationQtyType
Field.Description: Expiration Quantity type

Field.Name: ExpQty
Field.Description: Expiration Quantity associated with the Expiration Type

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingAmounts
Field.Description: Total number of occurrences of Amount to pay in order to receive the underlying instrument

Field.Name: UnderlyingPayAmount
Field.Description: Amount to pay in order to receive the underlying instrument

Field.Name: UnderlyingCollectAmount
Field.Description: Amount to collect in order to deliver the underlying instrument

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlementDate
Field.Description: Date the underlying instrument will settle. Used for derivatives that deliver into more than one underlying instrument. Settlement dates can vary across underlying instruments.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlementStatus
Field.Description: Settlement status of the underlying instrument. Used for derivatives that deliver into more than one underlying instrument. Settlement can be delayed for an underlying instrument.

Field.Name: SecondaryIndividualAllocID
Field.Description: Will allow the intermediary to specify an allocation ID generated by their system.

Field.Name: LegReportID
Field.Description: Additional attribute to store the Trade ID of the Leg.

Field.Name: RndPx
Field.Description: Specifies average price rounded to quoted precision.

Field.Name: IndividualAllocType
Field.Description: Identifies whether the allocation is to be sub-allocated or allocated to a third party

Field.Name: AllocCustomerCapacity
Field.Description: Capacity of customer in the allocation block.

Field.Name: TierCode
Field.Description: The Tier the trade was matched by the clearing system.

Field.Name: UnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The unit of measure of the underlying commodity upon which the contract is based. Two groups of units of measure enumerations are supported. Fixed Magnitude UOMs are primarily used in energy derivatives and specify a magnitude (such as, MM, Kilo, M, etc.) and the dimension (such as, watt hours, BTU's) to produce standard fixed measures (such as MWh - Megawatt-hours, MMBtu - One million BTUs). The second group, Variable Quantity UOMs, specifies the dimension as a single unit without a magnitude (or more accurately a magnitude of one) and uses the UnitOfMeasureQty(1147) field to define the quantity of units per contract. Variable Quantity UOMs are used for both commodities (such as lbs of lean cattle, bushels of corn, ounces of gold) and financial futures. Examples: For lean cattle futures contracts, a UnitOfMeasure of 'lbs' with a UnitOfMeasureQty(1147) of 40,000, means each lean cattle futures contract represents 40,000 lbs of lean cattle. For Eurodollars futures contracts, a UnitOfMeasure of Ccy with a UnitOfMeasureCurrency(1716) of USD and a UnitOfMeasureQty(1147) of 1,000,000, means a Eurodollar futures contract represents 1,000,000 USD. For gold futures contracts, a UnitOfMeasure is oz_tr (Troy ounce) with a UnitOfMeasureQty(1147) of 1,000, means each gold futures contract represents 1,000 troy ounces of gold.

Field.Name: TimeUnit
Field.Description: Unit of time associated with the contract. NOTE: Additional values may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties

Field.Name: UnderlyingUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Refer to defintion of UnitOfMeasure(996)

Field.Name: LegUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Refer to defintion of UnitOfMeasure(996)

Field.Name: UnderlyingTimeUnit
Field.Description: Same as TimeUnit.

Field.Name: LegTimeUnit
Field.Description: Same as TimeUnit.

Field.Name: AllocMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the method under which a trade quantity was allocated.

Field.Name: TradeID
Field.Description: The unique ID assigned to the trade entity once it is received or matched by the exchange or central counterparty.

Field.Name: SideTradeReportID
Field.Description: Used on a multi-sided trade to designate the ReportID

Field.Name: SideFillStationCd
Field.Description: Used on a multi-sided trade to convey order routing information

Field.Name: SideReasonCd
Field.Description: Used on a multi-sided trade to convey reason for execution

Field.Name: SideTrdSubTyp
Field.Description: Used on a multi-sided trade to specify the type of trade for a given side. Same values as TrdSubType (829).

Field.Name: SideLastQty
Field.Description: Used to indicate the quantity on one side of a multi-sided trade.

Field.Name: MessageEventSource
Field.Description: Used to identify the event or source which gave rise to a message. Valid values will be based on an exchange's implementation. Example values are: "MQM" (originated at Firm Back Office) "Clear" (originated in Clearing System) "Reg" (static data generated via Register request)

Field.Name: SideTrdRegTimestamp
Field.Description: Will be used in a multi-sided message. Traded Regulatory timestamp value Use to store time information required by government regulators or self regulatory organizations such as an exchange or clearing house

Field.Name: SideTrdRegTimestampType
Field.Description: Same as TrdRegTimeStampType

Field.Name: SideTrdRegTimestampSrc
Field.Description: Same as TrdRegTimestampOrigin Text which identifies the origin i.e. system which was used to generate the time stamp for the Traded Regulatory timestamp value

Field.Name: AsOfIndicator
Field.Description: A trade that is being submitted for a trade date prior to the current trade or clearing date, e.g. in an open outcry market an out trade being submitted for the previous trading session or trading day.

Field.Name: NoSideTrdRegTS
Field.Description: Indicates number of SideTimestamps contained in group

Field.Name: LegOptionRatio
Field.Description: Expresses the risk of an option leg Value must be between -1 and 1. A Call Option will require a ratio value between 0 and 1 A Put Option will require a ratio value between -1 and 0

Field.Name: NoInstrumentParties
Field.Description: Identifies the number of parties identified with an instrument

Field.Name: InstrumentPartyID
Field.Description: PartyID value within an instrument party repeating group. Same values as PartyID (448)

Field.Name: TradeVolume
Field.Description: Used to report volume with a trade

Field.Name: MDBookType
Field.Description: Describes the type of book for which the feed is intended. Used when multiple feeds are provided over the same connection

Field.Name: MDFeedType
Field.Description: Describes a class of service for a given data feed, ie Regular and Market Maker, Bandwidth Intensive or Bandwidth Conservative

Field.Name: MDPriceLevel
Field.Description: Integer to convey the level of a bid or offer at a given price level. This is in contrast to MDEntryPositionNo which is used to convey the position of an order within a Price level

Field.Name: MDOriginType
Field.Description: Used to describe the origin of the market data entry.

Field.Name: FirstPx
Field.Description: Indicates the first trade price of the day/session

Field.Name: MDEntrySpotRate
Field.Description: The spot rate for an FX entry

Field.Name: MDEntryForwardPoints
Field.Description: Used for an F/X entry. The forward points to be added to or subtracted from the spot rate to get the "all-in" rate in MDEntryPx. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

Field.Name: ManualOrderIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates if the order was initially received manually (as opposed to electronically) or if it was entered manually (as opposed to entered by automated trading software).

Field.Name: CustDirectedOrder
Field.Description: Indicates if the customer directed this order to a specific execution venue "Y" or not "N". A default of "N" customer did not direct this order should be used in the case where the information is both missing and essential.

Field.Name: ReceivedDeptID
Field.Description: Identifies the broker-dealer department that first took the order.

Field.Name: CustOrderHandlingInst
Field.Description:
Codes that apply special information that the Broker / Dealer needs to report, as specified by the customer. NOTE: This field and its values have no bearing on the ExecInst and TimeInForce fields. These values should not be used instead of ExecInst or TimeInForce. This field and its values are intended for compliance reporting and/or billing purposes only.
For OrderHandlingInstSrc(1032) = 1 (FINRA OATS), valid values are (as of OATS Phase 3 as provided by FINRA. See also http://www.finra.org/Industry/Compliance/MarketTransparency/OATS/PhaseIII/index.htm for a complete list.
For OrderHandlingInstSrc(1032) = 2 (FIA Execution Source Code), only one enumeration value may be specified.

Field.Name: OrderHandlingInstSource
Field.Description: Identifies the class or source of the order handling instruction values. Scope of this will apply to both CustOrderHandlingInst(1031) and DeskOrderHandlingInst(1035). Conditionally required when CustOrderHandlingInst(1031) or DeskOrderHandlingInst(1035) is specified.

Field.Name: DeskType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of Trading Desk. Conditionally required when InformationBarrierID(1727) is specified for OATS.

Field.Name: DeskTypeSource
Field.Description: Identifies the class or source of DeskType(1033) values. Conditionally required when DeskType(1033) is specified.

Field.Name: DeskOrderHandlingInst
Field.Description: Codes that apply special information that the broker-dealer needs to report.

Field.Name: ExecAckStatus
Field.Description: The status of this execution acknowledgement message.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryAmount
Field.Description: Indicates the underlying position amount to be delivered

Field.Name: UnderlyingCapValue
Field.Description: Maximum notional value for a capped financial instrument

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlMethod
Field.Description: Settlement method for a contract or instrument. Additional values may be used with bilateral agreement.

Field.Name: SecondaryTradeID
Field.Description: Used to carry an internal trade entity ID which may or may not be reported to the firm

Field.Name: FirmTradeID
Field.Description: The ID assigned to a trade by the Firm to track a trade within the Firm system. This ID can be assigned either before or after submission to the exchange or central counterpary

Field.Name: SecondaryFirmTradeID
Field.Description: Used to carry an internal firm assigned ID which may or may not be reported to the exchange or central counterpary

Field.Name: CollApplType
Field.Description: conveys how the collateral should be/has been applied

Field.Name: UnderlyingAdjustedQuantity
Field.Description: Unit amount of the underlying security (shares) adjusted for pending corporate action not yet allocated.

Field.Name: UnderlyingFXRate

Field.Description: Specifies whether the UnderlyingFxRate(1045) should be multiplied or divided.

Field.Name: AllocPositionEffect
Field.Description: Indicates whether the resulting position after a trade should be an opening position or closing position. Used for omnibus accounting - where accounts are held on a gross basis instead of being netted together.

Field.Name: DealingCapacity
Field.Description: Identifies role of dealer; Agent, Principal, RisklessPrincipal

Field.Name: InstrmtAssignmentMethod
Field.Description: Method under which assignment was conducted

Field.Name: InstrumentPartyIDSource
Field.Description: PartyIDSource value within an instrument partyrepeating group. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

Field.Name: InstrumentPartyRole
Field.Description: PartyRole value within an instrument partyepeating group. Same values as PartyRole (452)

Field.Name: NoInstrumentPartySubIDs
Field.Description: Number of InstrumentPartySubID (1053) and InstrumentPartySubIDType (1054) entries

Field.Name: InstrumentPartySubID
Field.Description: PartySubID value within an instrument party repeating group. Same values as PartySubID (523)

Field.Name: InstrumentPartySubIDType
Field.Description: Type of InstrumentPartySubID (1053) value. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

Field.Name: PositionCurrency
Field.Description: The Currency in which the position Amount is denominated

Field.Name: CalculatedCcyLastQty
Field.Description: Used for the calculated quantity of the other side of the currency trade. Can be derived from LastQty and LastPx.

Field.Name: AggressorIndicator
Field.Description: Used to identify whether the order initiator is an aggressor or not in the trade.

Field.Name: NoUndlyInstrumentParties
Field.Description: Identifies the number of parties identified with an underlying instrument

Field.Name: UnderlyingInstrumentPartyID
Field.Description: PartyID value within an underlying instrument party repeating group. Same values as PartyID (448)

Field.Name: UnderlyingInstrumentPartyIDSource
Field.Description: PartyIDSource value within an underlying instrument partyrepeating group. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

Field.Name: UnderlyingInstrumentPartyRole
Field.Description: PartyRole value within an underlying instrument partyepeating group. Same values as PartyRole (452)

Field.Name: NoUndlyInstrumentPartySubIDs
Field.Description: Number of Underlying InstrumentPartySubID (1053) and InstrumentPartySubIDType (1054) entries

Field.Name: UnderlyingInstrumentPartySubID
Field.Description: PartySubID value within an underlying instrument party repeating group. Same values as PartySubID (523)

Field.Name: UnderlyingInstrumentPartySubIDType
Field.Description: Type of underlying InstrumentPartySubID (1053) value. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

Field.Name: BidSwapPoints
Field.Description: The bid FX Swap points for an FX Swap. It is the "far bid forward points - near offer forward point". Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

Field.Name: OfferSwapPoints
Field.Description: The offer FX Swap points for an FX Swap. It is the "far offer forward points - near bid forward points". Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

Field.Name: LegBidForwardPoints
Field.Description: The bid FX forward points for the leg of an FX Swap. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

Field.Name: LegOfferForwardPoints
Field.Description: The offer FX forward points for the leg of an FX Swap. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

Field.Name: SwapPoints
Field.Description: For FX Swap, this is used to express the differential between the far leg's bid/offer and the near leg's bid/offer. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

Field.Name: MDQuoteType
Field.Description: Identifies market data quote type.

Field.Name: LastSwapPoints
Field.Description: For FX Swap, this is used to express the last market event for the differential between the far leg's bid/offer and the near leg's bid/offer in a fill or partial fill. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

Field.Name: SideGrossTradeAmt
Field.Description: The gross trade amount for this side of the trade. See also GrossTradeAmt (381) for additional definition.

Field.Name: LegLastForwardPoints
Field.Description: The forward points for this leg's fill event. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

Field.Name: LegCalculatedCcyLastQty
Field.Description: Used for the calculated quantity of the other side of the currency for this leg. Can be derived from LegQty and LegLastPx.

Field.Name: LegGrossTradeAmt
Field.Description: The gross trade amount of the leg. For FX Futures this is used to express the notional value of a fill when LegLastQty and other quantity fields are express in terms of contract size.

Field.Name: MaturityTime
Field.Description: Time of security's maturity expressed in local time with offset to UTC specified

Field.Name: RefOrderID
Field.Description:
The ID reference to the order being hit or taken.
For pre-trade credit/risk limit check process, this is the reference to the placed order, quote request or quote for the credit/risk limit check.

Field.Name: RefOrderIDSource
Field.Description: Used to specify the source for the identifier in RefOrderID(1080). This can be an identifier provided in order depth market data when hitting (taking) a specific order or to identify what type of order or quote reference is being provided when seeking credit limit check. In the context of US CAT this can be used to identify related orders and quotes which are parent, previous, or manual orders or quotes. Previous relates to orders changing their unique system assigned order identifier.

Field.Name: SecondaryDisplayQty
Field.Description: Used for reserve orders when DisplayQty applies to the primary execution market (e.g.an ECN) and another quantity is to be shown at other markets (e.g. the exchange). On orders specifies the qty to be displayed, on execution reports the currently displayed quantity.

Field.Name: DisplayWhen
Field.Description: Instructs when to refresh DisplayQty (1138).

Field.Name: DisplayMethod
Field.Description: Defines what value to use in DisplayQty (1138). If not specified the default DisplayMethod is "1"

Field.Name: DisplayLowQty
Field.Description: Defines the lower quantity limit to a randomized refresh of DisplayQty.

Field.Name: DisplayHighQty
Field.Description: Defines the upper quantity limit to a randomized refresh of DisplayQty.

Field.Name: DisplayMinIncr
Field.Description: Defines the minimum increment to be used when calculating a random refresh of DisplayQty. A user specifies this when he wants a larger increment than the standard provided by the market (e.g. the round lot size).

Field.Name: RefreshQty
Field.Description: Defines the quantity used to refresh DisplayQty.

Field.Name: MatchIncrement
Field.Description: Allows orders to specify a minimum quantity that applies to every execution (one execution could be for multiple counter-orders). The order may still fill against smaller orders, but the cumulative quantity of the execution must be in multiples of the MatchIncrement.

Field.Name: MaxPriceLevels
Field.Description: Allows an order to specify a maximum number of price levels to trade through. Only valid for aggressive orders and during continuous (autoexecution) trading sessions. Property lost when order is put on book. A partially filled order is assigned last trade price as limit price. Non-filled order behaves as ordinary Market or Limit.

Field.Name: PreTradeAnonymity
Field.Description: Allows trader to explicitly request anonymity or disclosure in pre-trade market data feeds. Anonymity is relevant in markets where counterparties are regularly disclosed in order depth feeds. Disclosure is relevant when counterparties are not normally visible.

Field.Name: PriceProtectionScope
Field.Description: Defines the type of price protection the customer requires on their order.

Field.Name: LotType
Field.Description: Defines the lot type assigned to the order.

Field.Name: PegPriceType
Field.Description: Defines the type of peg.

Field.Name: PeggedRefPrice
Field.Description: The value of the reference price that the order is pegged to. PeggedRefPrice + PegOffsetValue (211) = PeggedPrice (839) unless the limit price (44, Price) is breached. The values may not be exact due to rounding.

Field.Name: PegSecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Defines the identity of the security off whose prices the order will peg. Same values as SecurityIDSource (22)

Field.Name: PegSecurityID
Field.Description: Defines the identity of the security off whose prices the order will peg.

Field.Name: PegSymbol
Field.Description: Defines the common, 'human understood' representation of the security off whose prices the order will Peg.

Field.Name: PegSecurityDesc
Field.Description: Security description of the security off whose prices the order will Peg.

Field.Name: TriggerType
Field.Description: Defines when the trigger will hit, i.e. the action specified by the trigger instructions will come into effect.

Field.Name: TriggerAction
Field.Description: Defines the type of action to take when the trigger hits.

Field.Name: TriggerPrice
Field.Description: The price at which the trigger should hit.

Field.Name: TriggerSymbol
Field.Description: Defines the common, 'human understood' representation of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic.

Field.Name: TriggerSecurityID
Field.Description: Defines the identity of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic.

Field.Name: TriggerSecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Defines the identity of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic. Same values as SecurityIDSource (22).

Field.Name: TriggerSecurityDesc
Field.Description: Defines the security description of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic.

Field.Name: TriggerPriceType
Field.Description: The type of price that the trigger is compared to.

Field.Name: TriggerPriceTypeScope
Field.Description: Defines the type of price protection the customer requires on their order.

Field.Name: TriggerPriceDirection
Field.Description: The side from which the trigger price is reached.

Field.Name: TriggerNewPrice
Field.Description: The Price that the order should have after the trigger has hit. Could be applicable for any trigger type, but must be specified for Trigger Type 1.

Field.Name: TriggerOrderType
Field.Description: The OrdType the order should have after the trigger has hit. Required to express orders that change from Limit to Market. Other values from OrdType (40) may be used if appropriate and bilaterally agreed upon.

Field.Name: TriggerNewQty
Field.Description: The Quantity the order should have after the trigger has hit.

Field.Name: TriggerTradingSessionID
Field.Description: Defines the trading session at which the order will be activated.

Field.Name: TriggerTradingSessionSubID
Field.Description: Defines the subordinate trading session at which the order will be activated.

Field.Name: OrderCategory
Field.Description: Defines the type of interest behind a trade (fill or partial fill).

Field.Name: NoRootPartyIDs
Field.Description: Number of RootPartyID (1117), RootPartyIDSource (1118), and RootPartyRole (1119) entries

Field.Name: RootPartyID
Field.Description: PartyID value within a root parties component. Same values as PartyID (448)

Field.Name: RootPartyIDSource
Field.Description: PartyIDSource value within a root parties component. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

Field.Name: RootPartyRole
Field.Description: PartyRole value within a root parties component. Same values as PartyRole (452)

Field.Name: NoRootPartySubIDs
Field.Description: Number of RootPartySubID (1121) and RootPartySubIDType (1122) entries

Field.Name: RootPartySubID
Field.Description: PartySubID value within a root parties component. Same values as PartySubID (523)

Field.Name: RootPartySubIDType
Field.Description: Type of RootPartySubID (1121) value. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

Field.Name: TradeHandlingInstr
Field.Description: Specified how the TradeCaptureReport(35=AE) should be handled by the respondent.

Field.Name: OrigTradeHandlingInstr
Field.Description: Optionally used with TradeHandlingInstr = 0 to relay the trade handling instruction used when reporting the trade to the marketplace. Same values as TradeHandlingInstr (1123)

Field.Name: OrigTradeDate
Field.Description: Used to preserve original trade date when original trade is being referenced in a subsequent trade transaction such as a transfer

Field.Name: OrigTradeID
Field.Description: Used to preserve original trade id when original trade is being referenced in a subsequent trade transaction such as a transfer

Field.Name: OrigSecondaryTradeID
Field.Description: Used to preserve original secondary trade id when original trade is being referenced in a subsequent trade transaction such as a transfer

Field.Name: ApplVerID
Field.Description: Specifies the service pack release being applied at message level. Enumerated field with values assigned at time of service pack release

Field.Name: CstmApplVerID
Field.Description: Specifies a custom extension to a message being applied at the message level. Enumerated field

Field.Name: RefApplVerID
Field.Description: Specifies the service pack release being applied to a message at the session level. Enumerated field with values assigned at time of service pack release. Uses same values as ApplVerID

Field.Name: RefCstmApplVerID
Field.Description: Specifies a custom extension to a message being applied at the session level.

Field.Name: TZTransactTime
Field.Description: Transact time in the local date-time stamp with a TZ offset to UTC identified

Field.Name: ExDestinationIDSource
Field.Description: The ID source of ExDestination

Field.Name: ReportedPxDiff
Field.Description: Indicates that the reported price that is different from the market price. The price difference should be stated by using field 828 TrdType and, if required, field 829 TrdSubType

Field.Name: RptSys
Field.Description: Indicates the system or medium on which the report has been published

Field.Name: AllocClearingFeeIndicator
Field.Description: ClearingFeeIndicator(635) for Allocation, see ClearingFeeIndicator(635) for permitted values.

Field.Name: DefaultApplVerID
Field.Description: Specifies the service pack release being applied, by default, to message at the session level. Enumerated field with values assigned at time of service pack release. Uses same values as ApplVerID

Field.Name: DisplayQty
Field.Description: The quantity to be displayed . Required for reserve orders. On orders specifies the qty to be displayed, on execution reports the currently displayed quantity.

Field.Name: ExchangeSpecialInstructions
Field.Description: Free format text string related to exchange.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMaturityTime
Field.Description: Time of security's maturity expressed in local time with offset to UTC specified

Field.Name: LegMaturityTime
Field.Description: Time of security's maturity expressed in local time with offset to UTC specified

Field.Name: MaxTradeVol
Field.Description: The maximum order quantity (as expressed by TradeVolType(1786)) that can be submitted for a security.

Field.Name: NoMDFeedTypes
Field.Description: The number of feed types and corresponding book depths associated with a security

Field.Name: MatchAlgorithm
Field.Description: The types of algorithm used to match orders in a specific security. Possilbe value types are FIFO, Allocation, Pro-rata, Lead Market Maker, Currency Calender.

Field.Name: MaxPriceVariation
Field.Description: The maximum price variation of an execution from one event to the next for a given security. Expressed in absolute price terms.

Field.Name: ImpliedMarketIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates that an implied market should be created for either the legs of a multi-leg instrument (Implied-in) or for the multi-leg instrument based on the existence of the legs (Implied-out). Determination as to whether implied markets should be created is generally done at the level of the multi-leg instrument. Commonly used in listed derivatives.

Field.Name: EventTime
Field.Description: Specific time of event. To be used in combination with EventDate [866]

Field.Name: MinPriceIncrementAmount
Field.Description: Minimum price increment amount associated with the MinPriceIncrement ( tag 969). For listed derivatives, the value can be calculated by multiplying MinPriceIncrement by ContractValueFactor(231).

Field.Name: UnitOfMeasureQty
Field.Description: Used to indicate the quantity of the underlying commodity unit of measure on which the contract is based, such as, 2500 lbs of lean cattle, 1000 barrels of crude oil, 1000 bushels of corn, etc. UnitOfMeasureQty is required for UnitOfMeasure(996) Variable Quantity UOMs enumerations. Refer to the definition of UnitOfMeasure(996) for more information on the use of UnitOfMeasureQty.

Field.Name: LowLimitPrice
Field.Description: Allowable low limit price for the trading day. A key parameter in validating order price. Used as the lower band for validating order prices. Orders submitted with prices below the lower limit will be rejected

Field.Name: HighLimitPrice
Field.Description: Allowable high limit price for the trading day. A key parameter in validating order price. Used as the upper band for validating order prices. Orders submitted with prices above the upper limit will be rejected

Field.Name: TradingReferencePrice
Field.Description: Reference price for the current trading price range usually representing the mid price between the HighLimitPrice and LowLimitPrice. The value may be the settlement price or closing price of the prior trading day.

Field.Name: SecurityGroup
Field.Description: An exchange specific name assigned to a group of related securities which may be concurrently affected by market events and actions.

Field.Name: LegNumber
Field.Description: Allow sequencing of Legs for a Strategy to be captured

Field.Name: SettlementCycleNo
Field.Description: Settlement cycle in which the settlement obligation was generated

Field.Name: SideCurrency
Field.Description: Used to identify the trading currency on the Trade Capture Report Side

Field.Name: SideSettlCurrency
Field.Description: Used to identify the settlement currency on the Trade Capture Report Side

Field.Name: CcyAmt
Field.Description: Net flow of Currency 1

Field.Name: NoSettlDetails
Field.Description: Used to group Each Settlement Party

Field.Name: SettlObligMode
Field.Description: Used to identify the reporting mode of the settlement obligation which is either preliminary or final

Field.Name: SettlObligMsgID
Field.Description: Message identifier for Settlement Obligation Report

Field.Name: SettlObligID
Field.Description: Unique ID for this settlement instruction.

Field.Name: SettlObligTransType
Field.Description: Transaction Type - required except where SettlInstMode is 5=Reject SSI request

Field.Name: SettlObligRefID
Field.Description: Required where SettlInstTransType is Cancel or Replace

Field.Name: SettlObligSource
Field.Description: Used to identify whether these delivery instructions are for the buyside or the sellside.

Field.Name: NoSettlOblig
Field.Description: Number of settlement obligations

Field.Name: QuoteMsgID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a quote message.

Field.Name: QuoteEntryStatus
Field.Description: Identifies the status of an individual quote. See also QuoteStatus(297) which is used for single Quotes.

Field.Name: TotNoCxldQuotes
Field.Description: Specifies the number of canceled quotes

Field.Name: TotNoAccQuotes
Field.Description: Specifies the number of accepted quotes

Field.Name: TotNoRejQuotes
Field.Description: Specifies the number of rejected quotes

Field.Name: PrivateQuote
Field.Description: Specifies whether a quote is public, i.e. available to the market, or private, i.e. available to a specified counterparty only.

Field.Name: RespondentType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of respondents requested.

Field.Name: MDSubBookType
Field.Description: Describes a class of sub book, e.g. for the separation of various lot types. The Sub Book Type indicates that the following Market Data Entries belong to a non-integrated Sub Book. Whenever provided the Sub Book must be used together with MDPriceLevel and MDEntryPositionNo in order to sort the order properly. Values are bilaterally agreed.

Field.Name: SecurityTradingEvent
Field.Description: Identifies an event related to a SecurityTradingStatus(326). An event occurs and is gone, it is not a state that applies for a period of time.

Field.Name: NoStatsIndicators
Field.Description: Number of statistics indicator repeating group entries

Field.Name: StatsType
Field.Description: Type of statistics

Field.Name: NoOfSecSizes
Field.Description: The number of secondary sizes specifies in this entry

Field.Name: MDSecSizeType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of secondary size.

Field.Name: MDSecSize
Field.Description: A part of the MDEntrySize(271) that represents secondary interest as specified by MDSecSizeType(1178).

Field.Name: ApplID
Field.Description: Identifies the application with which a message is associated. Used only if application sequencing is in effect.

Field.Name: ApplSeqNum
Field.Description: Data sequence number to be used when FIX session is not in effect

Field.Name: ApplBegSeqNum
Field.Description: Beginning range of application sequence numbers

Field.Name: ApplEndSeqNum
Field.Description: Ending range of application sequence numbers

Field.Name: SecurityXMLLen
Field.Description: The length of the SecurityXML(1185) data block.

Field.Name: SecurityXML
Field.Description: XML definition for the security.

Field.Name: SecurityXMLSchema
Field.Description: The schema used to validate the contents of SecurityXML(1185).

Field.Name: RefreshIndicator
Field.Description: Set by the sender to tell the receiver to perform an immediate refresh of the book due to disruptions in the accompanying real-time feed 'Y' - Mandatory refresh by all participants 'N' - Process as required

Field.Name: Volatility
Field.Description: Annualized volatility for option model calculations

Field.Name: TimeToExpiration
Field.Description: Time to expiration in years calculated as the number of days remaining to expiration divided by 365 days per year.

Field.Name: RiskFreeRate
Field.Description: Interest rate. Usually some form of short term rate.

Field.Name: PriceUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Used to express the UOM of the price if different from the contract. In futures, this can be different for cross-rate products in which the price is quoted in units differently from the contract

Field.Name: PriceUnitOfMeasureQty
Field.Description: Used to express the UOM Quantity of the price if different from the contract. In futures, this can be different for physically delivered products in which price is quoted in a unit size different from the contract, i.e. a Cattle Future contract has a UOMQty of 40,000 and a PriceUOMQty of 100.

Field.Name: SettlMethod
Field.Description: Settlement method for a contract or instrument. Additional values may be used with bilateral agreement.

Field.Name: ExerciseStyle
Field.Description: Type of exercise of a derivatives security

Field.Name: UnderlyingExerciseStyle
Field.Description: Type of exercise of a derivatives security

Field.Name: LegExerciseStyle
Field.Description: Type of exercise of a derivatives security

Field.Name: OptPayoutAmount
Field.Description: Cash amount indicating the pay out associated with an option. For binary options this is a fixed amount.

Field.Name: PriceQuoteMethod
Field.Description: Method for price quotation

Field.Name: ValuationMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the type of valuation method applied.

Field.Name: ListMethod
Field.Description: Indicates whether instruments are pre-listed only or can also be defined via user request

Field.Name: CapPrice
Field.Description: Used to express the ceiling price of a capped call

Field.Name: FloorPrice
Field.Description: Used to express the floor price of a capped put

Field.Name: NoStrikeRules
Field.Description: Number of strike rule entries. This block specifies the rules for determining how new strikes should be listed within the stated price range of the underlying instrument

Field.Name: StartStrikePxRange
Field.Description: Starting price for the range to which the StrikeIncrement applies. Price refers to the price of the underlying

Field.Name: EndStrikePxRange
Field.Description: Ending price of the range to which the StrikeIncrement applies. Price refers to the price of the underlying

Field.Name: StrikeIncrement
Field.Description: Value by which strike price should be incremented within the specified price range.

Field.Name: NoTickRules
Field.Description: Number of tick rules. This block specifies the rules for determining how a security ticks, i.e. the price increments at which it can be quoted and traded, depending on the current price of the security

Field.Name: StartTickPriceRange
Field.Description: Starting price range for specified tick increment

Field.Name: EndTickPriceRange
Field.Description: Ending price range for the specified tick increment

Field.Name: TickIncrement
Field.Description: Tick increment for stated price range. Specifies the valid price increments at which a security can be quoted and traded

Field.Name: TickRuleType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of tick rule which is being described

Field.Name: NestedInstrAttribType
Field.Description: Code to represent the type of instrument attribute

Field.Name: NestedInstrAttribValue
Field.Description: Attribute value appropriate to the NestedInstrAttribType field

Field.Name: DerivativeSymbol
Field.Description: Refer to definition for Symbol(55)

Field.Name: DerivativeSymbolSfx
Field.Description: Refer to definition for SymbolSfx(65)

Field.Name: DerivativeSecurityID
Field.Description: Refer to definition for SecurityID(48)

Field.Name: DerivativeSecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Refer to definition for SecurityIDSoruce(22)

Field.Name: NoDerivativeSecurityAltID
Field.Description: Refer to definition for NoSecurityAltID(454)

Field.Name: DerivativeSecurityAltID
Field.Description: Refer to definition for SecurityAltID(455)

Field.Name: DerivativeSecurityAltIDSource
Field.Description: Refer to definition for SecurityAltIDSource(456)

Field.Name: SecondaryLowLimitPrice
Field.Description: Refer to definition of LowLimitPrice(1148)

Field.Name: SecondaryHighLimitPrice
Field.Description: Refer to definition of HighLimitPrice(1149)

Field.Name: MaturityRuleID
Field.Description: Allows maturity rule to be referenced via an identifier so that rules do not need to be explicitly enumerated

Field.Name: StrikeRuleID
Field.Description: Allows strike rule to be referenced via an identifier so that rules do not need to be explicitly enumerated

Field.Name: DerivativeOptPayAmount
Field.Description: Cash amount indicating the pay out associated with an option. For binary options this is a fixed amount

Field.Name: EndMaturityMonthYear
Field.Description: Ending maturity month year for an option class

Field.Name: ProductComplex
Field.Description: Identifies an entire suite of products for a given market. In Futures this may be "interest rates", "agricultural", "equity indexes", etc.

Field.Name: DerivativeProductComplex
Field.Description: Refer to ProductComplex(1227)

Field.Name: MaturityMonthYearIncrement
Field.Description: Increment between successive maturities for an option class

Field.Name: MinLotSize
Field.Description: Minimum lot size allowed based on lot type specified in LotType(1093)

Field.Name: NoExecInstRules
Field.Description: Number of execution instructions

Field.Name: NoLotTypeRules
Field.Description: Number of Lot Type Rules

Field.Name: NoMatchRules
Field.Description: Number of Match Rules

Field.Name: NoMaturityRules
Field.Description: Number of maturity rules in MarurityRules component block

Field.Name: NoOrdTypeRules
Field.Description: Number of order types

Field.Name: NoTimeInForceRules
Field.Description: Number of time in force techniques

Field.Name: SecondaryTradingReferencePrice
Field.Description: Refer to definition for TradingReferencePrice(1150)

Field.Name: StartMaturityMonthYear
Field.Description: Starting maturity month year for an option class

Field.Name: FlexProductEligibilityIndicator
Field.Description: Used to indicate if a product or group of product supports the creation of flexible securities

Field.Name: DerivFlexProductEligibilityIndicator
Field.Description: Refer to FlexProductEligibilityIndicator(1242)

Field.Name: FlexibleIndicator
Field.Description: Used to indicate a derivatives security that can be defined using flexible terms. The terms commonly permitted to be defined by market participants are expiration date and strike price. FlexibleIndicator is an alternative CFICode(461) Standard/Non-standard attribute.

Field.Name: TradingCurrency
Field.Description: Used when the trading currency can differ from the price currency

Field.Name: DerivativeSecurityXMLLen
Field.Description: Refer to definition SecurityXMLLen(1184)

Field.Name: DerivativeSecurityXML
Field.Description: Refer to definition of SecurityXML(1185)

Field.Name: DerivativeSecurityXMLSchema
Field.Description: Refer to definition of SecurityXMLSchema(1186)

Field.Name: NoDerivativeInstrumentParties
Field.Description: Refer to definition of NoParties(453)

Field.Name: DerivativeInstrumentPartyID
Field.Description: Refer to definition of PartyID(448)

Field.Name: DerivativeInstrumentPartyIDSource
Field.Description: Refer to definition of PartyIDSource(447)

Field.Name: DerivativeInstrumentPartyRole
Field.Description: REfer to definition of PartyRole(452)

Field.Name: NoDerivativeInstrumentPartySubIDs
Field.Description: Refer to definition for NoPartySubIDs(802)

Field.Name: DerivativeInstrumentPartySubID
Field.Description: Refer to definition for PartySubID(523)

Field.Name: DerivativeInstrumentPartySubIDType
Field.Description: Refer to definition for PartySubIDType(803)

Field.Name: DerivativeExerciseStyle
Field.Description: Type of exercise of a derivatives security

Field.Name: MarketSegmentID
Field.Description: Identifies the market segment

Field.Name: MarketID
Field.Description: Identifies the market

Field.Name: MaturityMonthYearIncrementUnits
Field.Description: Unit of measure for the Maturity Month Year Increment

Field.Name: MaturityMonthYearFormat
Field.Description: Format used to generate the MaturityMonthYear for each option

Field.Name: StrikeExerciseStyle
Field.Description: Expiration Style for an option class:

Field.Name: SecondaryPriceLimitType
Field.Description: Describes the how the price limits are expressed

Field.Name: PriceLimitType
Field.Description: Describes the how the price limits are expressed.

Field.Name: ExecInstValue
Field.Description: Indicates execution instructions that are valid for the specified market segment

Field.Name: NoTradingSessionRules
Field.Description: Allows trading rules to be expressed by trading session

Field.Name: NoMarketSegments
Field.Description: Number of Market Segments on which a security may trade.

Field.Name: DerivativeInstrAttribType
Field.Description: Refer to definition of InstrAttribType(871)

Field.Name: DerivativeInstrAttribValue
Field.Description: Refer to definition of InstrAttribValue(872)

Field.Name: DerivativePriceUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Refer to definition for PriceUnitOfMeasure(1191)

Field.Name: DerivativePriceUnitOfMeasureQty
Field.Description: Refer to definition of PriceUnitOfMeasureQty(1192)

Field.Name: DerivativeSettlMethod
Field.Description: Settlement method for a contract or instrument. Additional values may be used with bilateral agreement.

Field.Name: DerivativePriceQuoteMethod
Field.Description: Refer to definition of PriceQuoteMethod(1196)

Field.Description: Identifies settlement currency for the leg level allocation.

Field.Name: TotNoFills
Field.Description: Total number of fill entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoFills(1362) in each message that has repeating list of fill entries related to the same ExecID(17). Used to support fragmentation.

Field.Name: FillExecID
Field.Description: Refer to ExecID(17). Used when multiple partial fills are reported in single Execution Report. ExecID and FillExecID should not overlap,

Field.Name: FillPx
Field.Description: Price of Fill. Refer to LastPx(31).

Field.Name: FillQty
Field.Description: Quantity of Fill. Refer to LastQty(32).

Field.Name: LegAllocID
Field.Description: The AllocID(70) of an individual leg of a multileg order.

Field.Name: TradSesEvent
Field.Description: Identifies an event related to a TradSesStatus(340). An event occurs and is gone, it is not a state that applies for a period of time.

Field.Name: MassActionReportID
Field.Description: Unique identifier of Order Mass Cancel Report or Order Mass Action Report message as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN)

Field.Name: NoNotAffectedOrders
Field.Description: Number of not affected orders in the repeating group of order ids.

Field.Name: NotAffectedOrderID
Field.Description: OrderID(37) of an order not affected by a mass cancel or mass action request.

Field.Name: NotAffOrigClOrdID
Field.Description: ClOrdID(11) of an order not affected by a mass cancel or mass action request.

Field.Name: MassActionType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of action requested

Field.Name: MassActionScope
Field.Description: Specifies scope of Order Mass Action Request.

Field.Name: MassActionResponse
Field.Description: Specifies the action taken by counterparty order handling system as a result of the action type indicated in MassActionType of the Order Mass Action Request.

Field.Name: MassActionRejectReason
Field.Description: Reason Order Mass Action Request was rejected

Field.Name: MultilegModel
Field.Description: Specifies the type of multileg order. Defines whether the security is pre-defined or user-defined. Note that MultilegModel(1377)=2(User-defined, Non-Securitized, Multileg) does not apply for Securities.

Field.Name: MultilegPriceMethod
Field.Description: Code to represent how the multileg price is to be interpreted when applied to the legs. (See Volume : "Glossary" for further value definitions)

Field.Name: LegVolatility
Field.Description: Specifies the volatility of an instrument leg.

Field.Name: DividendYield
Field.Description: The continuously-compounded annualized dividend yield of the underlying(s) of an option. Used as a parameter to theoretical option pricing models.

Field.Name: LegDividendYield
Field.Description: Refer to definition for DividendYield(1380).

Field.Name: CurrencyRatio
Field.Description: Specifies the currency ratio between the currency used for a multileg price and the currency used by the outright book defined by the leg. Example: Multileg quoted in EUR, outright leg in USD and 1 EUR = 0,7 USD then CurrencyRatio = 0.7

Field.Name: LegCurrencyRatio
Field.Description: Specifies the currency ratio between the currency used for a multileg price and the currency used by the outright book defined by the leg. Example: Multileg quoted in EUR, outright leg in USD and 1 EUR = 0,7 USD then LegCurrencyRatio = 0.7

Field.Name: LegExecInst
Field.Description: Refer to ExecInst(18) Same values as ExecInst(18)

Field.Name: ContingencyType
Field.Description: Defines the type of contingency.

Field.Name: ListRejectReason
Field.Description: Identifies the reason for rejection of a New Order List message. Note that OrdRejReason(103) is used if the rejection is based on properties of an individual order part of the List.

Field.Name: NoTrdRepIndicators
Field.Description: Number of trade reporting indicators

Field.Name: TrdRepPartyRole
Field.Description: Identifies the type of party for trade reporting. Same values as PartyRole(452).

Field.Name: TrdRepIndicator
Field.Description: Specifies whether the trade should be reported (or not) to parties of the provided TrdRepPartyRole(1388). Used to override standard reporting behavior by the receiver of the trade report and thereby complements the PublTrdIndicator( tag1390).

Field.Name: TradePublishIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates if a trade should be or has been published via a market publication service. The indicator governs all publication services of the recipient. Replaces PublishTrdIndicator(852).

Field.Name: ApplReqID

Field.Description: Used to indicate that a message is being sent in response to an Application Message Request. It is possible for both ApplResendFlag and PossDupFlag to be set on the same message if the Sender's cache size is greater than zero and the message is being resent due to a session level resend request

Field.Name: ApplResponseID
Field.Description: Identifier for the Applicaton Message Request Ack

Field.Name: ApplResponseError
Field.Description: Used to return an error code or text associated with a response to an Application Request.

Field.Description: Reference to the unique application identifier which corresponds to ApplID(1180) from the Application Sequence Group component

Field.Name: ApplReportID
Field.Description: Identifier for the Application Sequence Reset

Field.Name: RefApplLastSeqNum
Field.Description: Application sequence number of last message in transmission.

Field.Name: ApplNewSeqNum
Field.Description: Used to specify a new application sequence number.

Field.Name: ApplReportType
Field.Description: Type of report

Field.Description: Refer to definition of PartyRole(452)

Field.Name: LegLastQty
Field.Description: Fill quantity for the leg instrument

Field.Name: SideExecID
Field.Description: When reporting trades, used to reference the identifier of the execution (ExecID) being reported if different ExecIDs were assigned to each side of the trade.

Field.Name: OrderDelay
Field.Description: Time lapsed from order entry until match, based on the unit of time specified in OrderDelayUnit. Default is seconds if OrderDelayUnit is not specified. Value = 0, indicates the aggressor (the initiating side of the trade).

Field.Name: OrderDelayUnit
Field.Description: Time unit in which the OrderDelay(1428) is expressed

Field.Name: VenueType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of venue where a trade was executed

Field.Name: RefOrdIDReason
Field.Description: The reason for updating the RefOrdID

Field.Name: OrigCustOrderCapacity
Field.Description: The customer capacity for this trade at the time of the order/execution. Primarily used by futures exchanges to indicate the CTICode (customer type indicator) as required by the US CFTC (Commodity Futures Trading Commission).

Field.Name: RefApplReqID
Field.Description: Used to reference a previously submitted ApplReqID (1346) from within a subsequent ApplicationMessageRequest(MsgType=BW)

Field.Name: ModelType
Field.Description: Type of pricing model used

Field.Name: ContractMultiplierUnit
Field.Description: Indicates the type of multiplier being applied to the contract. Can be optionally used to further define what unit ContractMultiplier(tag 231) is expressed in.

Field.Name: LegContractMultiplierUnit
Field.Description: "Indicates the type of multiplier being applied to the contract. Can be optionally used to further define what unit LegContractMultiplier(tag 614) is expressed in.

Field.Name: UnderlyingContractMultiplierUnit
Field.Description: Indicates the type of multiplier being applied to the contract.
Field.Elaboration: Can be optionally used to further define what unit UnderlyingContractMultiplier(436) is expressed in.

Field.Name: DerivativeContractMultiplierUnit
Field.Description: Indicates the type of multiplier being applied to the contract. Can be optionally used to further define what unit DerivativeContractMultiplier(tag 1266)is expressed in.

Field.Name: FlowScheduleType
Field.Description: The industry standard flow schedule by which electricity or natural gas is traded. Schedules may exist by regions and on-peak and off-peak status, such as "Western Peak".

Field.Name: LegFlowScheduleType
Field.Description: The industry standard flow schedule by which electricity or natural gas is traded. Schedules exist by regions and on-peak and off-peak status, such as "Western Peak".

Field.Name: UnderlyingFlowScheduleType
Field.Description: The industry standard flow schedule by which electricity or natural gas is traded. Schedules exist by regions and on-peak and off-peak status, such as "Western Peak".

Field.Name: DerivativeFlowScheduleType
Field.Description: The industry standard flow schedule by which electricity or natural gas is traded. Schedules exist by regions and on-peak and off-peak status, such as "Western Peak".

Field.Name: FillLiquidityInd
Field.Description: Indicator to identify whether this fill was a result of a liquidity provider providing or liquidity taker taking the liquidity. Applicable only for OrdStatus of Partial or Filled

Field.Name: SideLiquidityInd
Field.Description: Indicator to identify whether this fill was a result of a liquidity provider providing or liquidity taker taking the liquidity. Applicable only for OrdStatus of Partial or Filled.

Field.Name: NoRateSources
Field.Description: Number of rate sources being specified.

Field.Name: RateSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source of rate information. For FX, the reference source to be used for the FX spot rate.

Field.Name: RateSourceType
Field.Description: Indicates whether the rate source specified is a primary or secondary source.

Field.Name: ReferencePage
Field.Description:
Identifies the reference "page" from the rate source. For FX, the reference page to the spot rate to be used for the reference FX spot rate.
When RateSource(1446) = 3 (ISDA Settlement Rate Option) this contains the value from the scheme that reflects the terms of the Annex A to the ISDA 1998 FX and Currency Option Definitions. See: http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/settlement-rate-option

Field.Name: RestructuringType
Field.Description: A category of CDS credit event in which the underlying bond experiences a restructuring. Used to define a CDS instrument.

Field.Name: Seniority
Field.Description: Specifies which issue (underlying bond) will receive payment priority in the event of a default. Used to define a CDS instrument.
Field.Elaboration: The payment priority is this: Senior Secured (SD), Senior (SR), Senior Non-Preferred (SN), Subordinated (SB), Mezzanine (MZ), Junior (JR).

Field.Name: NotionalPercentageOutstanding
Field.Description: Indicates the notional percentage of the deal that is still outstanding based on the remaining components of the index. Used to calculate the true value of a CDS trade or position.

Field.Name: OriginalNotionalPercentageOutstanding
Field.Description: Used to reflect the Original value prior to the application of a credit event. See NotionalPercentageOutstanding(1451).

Field.Name: UnderlyingRestructuringType
Field.Description: See RestructuringType(1449)

Field.Name: UnderlyingSeniority
Field.Description: See Seniority(1450)

Field.Name: UnderlyingNotionalPercentageOutstanding
Field.Description: See NotionalPercentageOutstanding(1451)

Field.Name: UnderlyingOriginalNotionalPercentageOutstanding
Field.Description: See OriginalNotionalPercentageOutstanding(1452)

Field.Name: AttachmentPoint
Field.Description: Lower bound percentage of the loss that the tranche can endure.

Field.Name: DetachmentPoint
Field.Description: Upper bound percentage of the loss the tranche can endure.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAttachmentPoint
Field.Description: See AttachmentPoint(1457).

Field.Name: UnderlyingDetachmentPoint
Field.Description: See DetachmentPoint(1458).

Field.Name: NoTargetPartyIDs
Field.Description: Identifies the number of target parties identified in a mass action.

Field.Name: TargetPartyID
Field.Description: PartyID value within an target party repeating group.

Field.Name: TargetPartyIDSource
Field.Description: PartyIDSource value within an target party repeating group. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

Field.Name: TargetPartyRole
Field.Description: PartyRole value within an target party repeating group. Same values as PartyRole (452)

Field.Name: SecurityListID
Field.Description: Specifies an identifier for a Security List

Field.Name: SecurityListRefID
Field.Description: Specifies a reference from one Security List to another. Used to support a hierarchy of Security Lists.

Field.Name: SecurityListDesc
Field.Description: Specifies a description or name of a Security List.

Field.Name: EncodedSecurityListDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedSecurityListDesc (tbd) field.

Field.Name: EncodedSecurityListDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the SecurityListDesc (1467) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the SecurityListDesc field.

Field.Name: SecurityListType
Field.Description: Specifies a type of Security List.

Field.Name: SecurityListTypeSource
Field.Description: Specifies a specific source for a SecurityListType. Relevant when a certain type can be provided from various sources.

Field.Name: NewsID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a News message

Field.Name: NewsCategory
Field.Description: Category of news mesage.

Field.Name: LanguageCode
Field.Description: The national language in which the news item is provided.

Field.Name: NoNewsRefIDs
Field.Description: Number of News reference items

Field.Name: NewsRefID
Field.Description: Reference to another News message identified by NewsID(1474).

Field.Name: NewsRefType
Field.Description: Type of reference to another News(35=B) message item.

Field.Name: StrikePriceDeterminationMethod
Field.Description: Specifies how the strike price is determined at the point of option exercise. The strike may be fixed throughout the life of the option, set at expiration to the value of the underlying, set to the average value of the underlying , or set to the optimal value of the underlying.

Field.Name: StrikePriceBoundaryMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the boundary condition to be used for the strike price relative to the underlying price at the point of option exercise.

Field.Name: StrikePriceBoundaryPrecision
Field.Description: Used in combination with StrikePriceBoundaryMethod to specify the percentage of the strike price in relation to the underlying price. The percentage is generally 100 or greater for puts and 100 or less for calls.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPriceDeterminationMethod
Field.Description: Specifies how the underlying price is determined at the point of option exercise. The underlying price may be set to the current settlement price, set to a special reference, set to the optimal value of the underlying during the defined period ("Look-back") or set to the average value of the underlying during the defined period ("Asian option").

Field.Name: OptPayoutType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of valuation method or payout trigger for an in-the-money option.

Field.Name: NoComplexEvents
Field.Description: Number of complex event occurrences.

Field.Name: ComplexEventType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of complex event.

Field.Name: ComplexOptPayoutAmount
Field.Description: Cash amount indicating the pay out associated with an event. For binary options this is a fixed amount.

Field.Name: ComplexEventPrice
Field.Description: Specifies the price at which the complex event takes effect. Impact of the event price is determined by the ComplexEventType(1484).

Field.Name: ComplexEventPriceBoundaryMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the boundary condition to be used for the event price relative to the underlying price at the point the complex event outcome takes effect as determined by the ComplexEventPriceTimeType.

Field.Name: ComplexEventPriceBoundaryPrecision
Field.Description: Used in combination with ComplexEventPriceBoundaryMethod to specify the percentage of the strike price in relation to the underlying price. The percentage is generally 100 or greater for puts and 100 or less for calls.

Field.Name: ComplexEventPriceTimeType
Field.Description: Specifies when the complex event outcome takes effect. The outcome of a complex event is a payout or barrier action as specified by the ComplexEventType(1484).

Field.Name: ComplexEventCondition
Field.Description: Specifies the condition between complex events when more than one event is specified. Multiple barrier events would use an "or" condition since only one can be effective at a given time. A set of digital range events would use an "and" condition since both conditions must be in effect for a payout to result.

Field.Name: NoComplexEventDates
Field.Description: Number of complex event date occurrences for a given complex event.

Field.Name: ComplexEventStartDate
Field.Description: Specifies the start date of the date range on which a complex event is effective. The start date will be set equal to the end date for single day events such as Bermuda options ComplexEventStartDate must always be less than or equal to ComplexEventEndDate.

Field.Name: ComplexEventEndDate
Field.Description: Specifies the end date of the date range on which a complex event is effective. The start date will be set equal to the end date for single day events such as Bermuda options ComplexEventEndDate must always be greater than or equal to ComplexEventStartDate.

Field.Name: NoComplexEventTimes
Field.Description: Number of complex event time occurrences for a given complex event date The default in case of an absence of time fields is 00:00:00-23:59:59.

Field.Name: ComplexEventStartTime
Field.Description: Specifies the start time of the time range on which a complex event date is effective. ComplexEventStartTime must always be less than or equal to ComplexEventEndTime.

Field.Name: ComplexEventEndTime
Field.Description: Specifies the end time of the time range on which a complex event date is effective. ComplexEventEndTime must always be greater than or equal to ComplexEventStartTime.

Field.Name: StreamAsgnReqID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for the stream assignment request provided by the requester.

Field.Name: StreamAsgnReqType
Field.Description: Type of stream assignment request.

Field.Name: NoAsgnReqs
Field.Description: Number of assignment requests.

Field.Name: MDStreamID
Field.Description: The identifier or name of the price stream.

Field.Name: StreamAsgnRptID
Field.Description: Unique identifier of the stream assignment report provided by the respondent.

Field.Name: StreamAsgnRejReason
Field.Description: Reason code for stream assignment request reject.

Field.Name: StreamAsgnAckType
Field.Description: Type of acknowledgement.

Field.Name: StreamAsgnType
Field.Description: The type of assignment being affected in the Stream Assignment Report.

Field.Name: RelSymTransactTime
Field.Description: See TransactTime(60)

Field.Name: FillYieldType
Field.Description: Yield Type, using same values as YieldType (235)

Field.Name: FillYield
Field.Description: Yield Percentage, using same values as Yield (236)

Field.Name: NoMatchInst
Field.Description: Number of Instructions in the <MatchingInstructions> repeating group.

Field.Name: MatchInst
Field.Description: Matching Instruction for the order.

Field.Name: MatchAttribTagID
Field.Description: Existing FIX field to be applied as a matching criteria to the instruction, bilaterally agreed between parties.

Field.Name: MatchAttribValue
Field.Description: Value of MatchAttribTagID(1626) on which to apply the matching instruction.

Field.Name: MatchInstMarketID
Field.Description: Identifies the market to which the matching instruction applies.

Field.Name: TriggerScope
Field.Description: Defines the scope of TriggerAction(1101) when it is set to "cancel" (3).

Field.Name: ExposureDuration
Field.Description: This is the time in seconds of a "Good for Time" (GFT) TimeInForce. Positive integer value which represents the time is seconds in which the new order remains active in the market before it is automatically cancelled (e.g. expired). Bi-lateral agreements will dictate the maximum value of this field. It is assumed that most systems will impose a max limit of 86,400 seconds (i.e. 24 hours). For Quotes: The period of time a quoted price is tradable(i.e. on-the-wire) before it becomes indicative (i.e. off-the-wire).

Field.Name: NoLimitAmts
Field.Description: The number of limit amount entries.

Field.Name: LimitAmtType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of limit amount expressed in LastLimitAmt(1632) and LimitAmtRemaining(1633).

Field.Name: LastLimitAmt
Field.Description: The amount that has been drawn down against the counterparty for a given trade. The type of limit is specified in LimitAmtType(1631). Bilateral agreements dictate the units and maximum value of this field.

Field.Name: LimitAmtRemaining
Field.Description: The remaining limit amount available between the counterparties. The type of limit is specified in LimitAmtType(1631). Bilateral agreements dictate the units and maximum value of this field.

Field.Name: LimitAmtCurrency
Field.Description: Indicates the currency that the limit amount is specified in. See Currency(15) for additional description and valid values.

Field.Name: MarginReqmtInqID
Field.Description: Unique identifier of the MarginRequirementInquiry.

Field.Name: NoMarginReqmtInqQualifier
Field.Description: Number of margin requirement inquiry qualifiers.

Field.Name: MarginReqmtInqQualifier
Field.Description: Qualifier for MarginRequirementInquiry to identify a specific report.

Field.Name: MarginReqmtRptType
Field.Description: Type of MarginRequirementReport.

Field.Name: MarginClass
Field.Description: Identifier for group of instruments with similar risk profile.

Field.Name: MarginReqmtInqStatus
Field.Description: Status of MarginRequirementInquiry.

Field.Name: MarginReqmtInqResult
Field.Description: Result returned in response to MarginRequirementInquiry.

Field.Name: MarginReqmtRptID
Field.Description: Identifier for the MarginRequirementReport message.

Field.Name: NoMarginAmt
Field.Description: Number of margin requirement amounts.

Field.Name: MarginAmtType
Field.Description: Type of margin requirement amount being specified.

Field.Name: MarginAmt
Field.Description: Amount of margin requirement.

Field.Name: MarginAmtCcy
Field.Description: Currency of the MarginAmt(1645).

Field.Name: NoRelatedInstruments
Field.Description: Number of related instruments

Field.Name: RelatedInstrumentType
Field.Description: The type of instrument relationship

Field.Name: RelatedSymbol
Field.Description: Ticker symbol of the related security. Common "human understood" representation of the security.

Field.Name: RelatedSecurityID
Field.Description: Related security identifier value of RelatedSecurityIDSource(1651) type.

Field.Name: RelatedSecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies class or source of the RelatedSecurityID (1650) value.

Field.Name: RelatedSecurityType
Field.Description: Security type of the related instrument.

Field.Name: RelatedMaturityMonthYear
Field.Description: Expiration date for the related instrument contract.

Field.Name: CoveredQty
Field.Description: Used to specify the portion of the short contract quantity that is considered covered (e.g. used for short option position).

Field.Name: MarketMakerActivity
Field.Description: Indicates market maker participation in security.

Field.Name: PartyDetailsListRequestID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for PartyDetailsListRequest.

Field.Name: NoRequestedPartyRoles
Field.Description: Number of requested party roles.

Field.Name: RequestedPartyRole
Field.Description: Identifies the type or role of party that has been requested.

Field.Name: PartyDetailsListReportID
Field.Description: Identifier for the PartyDetailsListReport and the PartyDetailsListUpdateReport.

Field.Name: RequestResult
Field.Description: Result of a request as identified by the appropriate request ID field

Field.Name: TotNoParties
Field.Description: Total number of PartyListGrp returned.

Field.Name: NoPartyRelationships
Field.Description: Number of party relationships.

Field.Name: PartyRelationship
Field.Description: Used to specify the type of the party relationship.

Field.Name: NoPartyDetailAltID
Field.Description: Number of party alternative identifiers.

Field.Name: PartyDetailAltID
Field.Description: An alternate party identifier for the party specified in PartyDetailID(1691)

Field.Name: PartyDetailAltIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source of the PartyDetailAltID(1517) value.

Field.Name: NoPartyDetailAltSubIDs
Field.Description: Number of party detail alternate sub-identifiers.

Field.Name: PartyDetailAltSubID
Field.Description: Sub-identifier for the party specified in PartyDetailAltID(1517).

Field.Name: PartyDetailAltSubIDType
Field.Description: Type of PartyDetailAltSubID(1520) value.

Field.Name: NoRiskLimitTypes
Field.Description: Number of risk limits with associated warning levels.

Field.Name: RiskLimitType
Field.Description: Used to specify the type of risk limit amount or position limit quantity or margin requirement amounts.

Field.Name: RiskLimitAmount
Field.Description: Specifies the risk limit amount.

Field.Name: RiskLimitCurrency
Field.Description: Used to specify the currency of the risk limit amount.

Field.Name: RiskLimitPlatform
Field.Description: The area to which risk limit is applicable. This can be a trading platform or an offering.

Field.Name: NoRiskInstrumentScopes
Field.Description: Number of risk instrument scopes.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeOperator
Field.Description: Operator to perform on the instrument(s) specified

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeSymbol
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified symbol. See Symbol(55) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeSymbolSfx
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified symbol suffix. See SymbolSfx(65) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeSecurityID
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified security identifier. See SecurityID(48) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeSecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified security identifier source. See SecurityIDSource(22) field for description.

Field.Name: NoInstrumentScopeSecurityAltID
Field.Description: Number of alternate security identifier for the specified InstrumentScopeSecurityID(1538).

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeSecurityAltID
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified security alternate identifier. See SecurityAltID(455) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeSecurityAltIDSource
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified security alternate identifier source. See SecurityAltIDSource(456) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeProduct
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified instrument product category. See Product (460) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeProductComplex
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified product complex. See ProductComplex(1227) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeSecurityGroup
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified security group. See SecurityGroup(1151) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeCFICode
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified CFICode. See CFICode(461) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeSecurityType
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified security type. See SecurityType(167) field for description).

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeSecuritySubType
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified security sub-type. See SecuritySubType(762) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeMaturityMonthYear
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified maturity month and year. See MaturityMonthYear(200) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeMaturityTime
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified maturity time. See MaturityTime(1079) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeRestructuringType
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified restructuring type. See RestructuringType(1449) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeSeniority
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified seniority type. See Seniority(1450) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopePutOrCall
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to puts or calls. See PutOrCall(201) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeFlexibleIndicator
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to securities that can be defined using flexible terms or not. See FlexibleIndicator(1244) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeCouponRate
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified coupon rate. See CouponRate(223) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeSecurityDesc
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified security description. See SecurityDesc(107) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeSettlType
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified settlement type. See SettlType(63) field for description.

Field.Name: RiskInstrumentMultiplier
Field.Description: Multiplier applied to the transaction amount for comparison with risk limits. Default if not specified is 1.0.

Field.Name: NoRiskWarningLevels
Field.Description: Number of risk warning levels.

Field.Name: RiskWarningLevelPercent
Field.Description: Percent of risk limit at which a warning is issued.

Field.Name: RiskWarningLevelName
Field.Description: Name or error message associated with the risk warning level.

Field.Name: NoRelatedPartyDetailID
Field.Description: Number of related party detail identifiers.

Field.Name: RelatedPartyDetailID
Field.Description: Party identifier for the party related to the party specified in PartyDetailID(1691).

Field.Name: RelatedPartyDetailIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source of the RelatedPartyDetailID(1563).

Field.Name: RelatedPartyDetailRole
Field.Description: Identifies the type or role of the RelatedPartyDetailID(1563) specified.

Field.Name: NoRelatedPartyDetailSubIDs
Field.Description: Number of related party detail sub-identifiers.

Field.Name: RelatedPartyDetailSubID
Field.Description: Sub-identifier for the party specified in RelatedPartyID(1563).

Field.Name: RelatedPartyDetailSubIDType
Field.Description: Type of RelatedPartyDetailSubID(1567) value.

Field.Name: NoRelatedPartyDetailAltID
Field.Description: Number of related party detail alternate identifiers.

Field.Name: RelatedPartyDetailAltID
Field.Description: An alternate party identifier for the party specified in RelatedPartyID(1563).

Field.Name: RelatedPartyDetailAltIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source of the RelatedPartyDetailAltID(1570) value.

Field.Name: NoRelatedPartyDetailAltSubIDs
Field.Description: Number of related party detail alternate sub-identifiers.

Field.Name: RelatedPartyDetailAltSubID
Field.Description: Sub-identifier for the party specified in RelatedPartyDetailAltID(1570).

Field.Name: RelatedPartyDetailAltSubIDType
Field.Description: Type of RelatedPartyDetailAltSubID(1573) value.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeSecurityExchange
Field.Description: Used to limit instrument scope to specified security exchange. See SecurityExchange(207) field for description.

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeEncodedSecurityDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) InstrumentScopeEncodedSecurityDesc (1621) field

Field.Name: InstrumentScopeEncodedSecurityDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the InstrumentScopeSecurityDesc (1556) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the InstrumentScopeSecurityDesc field.

Field.Name: NoInstrumentScopes
Field.Description: Number of instrument scopes.

Field.Name: NoRequestingPartyIDs
Field.Description: Number of requesting party identifiers.

Field.Name: RequestingPartyID
Field.Description: Party identifier for the requesting party.

Field.Name: RequestingPartyIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source of the RequestingPartyID(1658) value.

Field.Name: RequestingPartyRole
Field.Description: Identifies the type or role of the RequestingPartyID(1658) specified.

Field.Name: NoRequestingPartySubIDs
Field.Description: Number of requesting party sub-identifiers.

Field.Name: RequestingPartySubID
Field.Description: Sub-identifier for the party specified in RequestingPartyID(1658).

Field.Name: RequestingPartySubIDType
Field.Description: Type of RequestingPartySubID(1662) value.

Field.Name: EncodedRejectTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedRejectText(1665) field.

Field.Name: EncodedRejectText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the RejectText(1328) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding(347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the RejectText(1328) field.

Field.Name: RiskLimitRequestID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for the PartyRiskLimitsRequest

Field.Name: RiskLimitReportID
Field.Description: Identifier for the PartyRiskLimitsReport

Field.Name: NoRequestedRiskLimitType
Field.Description: Number of risk limit types requested.

Field.Name: NoRiskLimits
Field.Description: Number of risk limits for different instrument scopes.

Field.Name: RiskLimitID
Field.Description: Unique reference identifier for a specific risk limit defined for the specified party.

Field.Name: NoPartyDetails
Field.Description: Number of party details.

Field.Name: PartyDetailStatus
Field.Description: Indicates the status of the party identified with PartyDetailID(1691).

Field.Name: PartyDetailRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Qualifies the value of PartyDetailRole(1693).

Field.Name: RelatedPartyDetailRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Qualifies the value of RelatedPartyRole(1565)

Field.Name: NoPartyUpdates
Field.Description: Number of party updates.

Field.Name: NoPartyRiskLimits
Field.Description: Number of party risk limits.

Field.Name: PartyDetailID
Field.Description: Party identifier within Parties Reference Data messages.

Field.Name: PartyDetailIDSource
Field.Description: Source of the identifier of the PartyDetailID(1691) specified.

Field.Name: PartyDetailRole
Field.Description: Identifies the type or role of PartyDetailID(1691) specified.

Field.Name: NoPartyDetailSubIDs
Field.Description: Number of party detail sub-identifiers.

Field.Name: PartyDetailSubID
Field.Description: Sub-identifier for the party specified in PartyDetailID(1691).

Field.Name: PartyDetailSubIDType
Field.Description: Type of PartyDetailSubID(1695) value.

Field.Name: SecurityMassTradingStatus
Field.Description: Identifies the trading status applicable to a group of instruments.

Field.Name: SecurityMassTradingEvent
Field.Description: Identifies an event related to the mass trading status.

Field.Name: MassHaltReason
Field.Description: Denotes the reason for the Opening Delay or Trading halt of a group of securities.

Field.Name: MDSecurityTradingStatus
Field.Description: Identifies the trading status applicable to the instrument in the market data message.

Field.Name: MDSubFeedType
Field.Description: Describes a sub-class for a given class of service defined by MDFeedType (1022)

Field.Name: MDHaltReason
Field.Description: Denotes the reason for the Opening Delay or Trading Halt.

Field.Name: SideTradeID
Field.Description: Used to represent the trade ID for each side of the trade assigned by an intermediary.

Field.Name: SideOrigTradeID
Field.Description: Used to capture the original trade id for each side of a trade undergoing novation to a standardized model.

Field.Name: DifferentialPrice
Field.Description: Used to specify the differential price when reporting the individual leg of a spread trade. Both leg price and differential price may be provided on such a report. Note that MultiLegReportingType(442) will be set to 2 (Individual leg of a multi-leg security) in this case.
