Also used in pricing Trade at Settlement (TAS) and Trade At Marker (TAM) contracts for which the value is the negotiated currency offset either at settlement (TAS) or at time specified in the product definition (TAM). The final contract price is specified in LastPx(31).

Field.Name: TrdAckStatus
Field.Description: Used to indicate the status of the trade submission (not the trade report)

Field.Name: PriceQuoteCurrency
Field.Description: Default currency in which the price is quoted. Defined at the instrument level. Used in place of Currency (tag 15) to express the currency of a product when the former is implemented as the FX dealt currency.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPriceQuoteCurrency
Field.Description: Default currency in which the price is quoted. Defined at the instrument level. Used in place of Currency (tag 15) to express the currency of a product when the former is implemented as the FX dealt currency.

Field.Name: LegPriceQuoteCurrency
Field.Description: Default currency in which the price is quoted. Defined at the instrument level. Used in place of Currency (tag 15) to express the currency of a product when the former is implemented as the FX dealt currency.

Field.Name: DerivativePriceQuoteCurrency
Field.Description: Default currency in which the price is quoted. Defined at the instrument level. Used in place of Currency (tag 15) to express the currency of a product when the former is implemented as the FX dealt currency.

Field.Name: NoSecurityClassifications
Field.Description: Number of Security Classifications.

Field.Name: SecurityClassificationReason
Field.Description: Allows classification of instruments according to a set of high level reasons. Classification reasons describe the classes in which the instrument participates.

Field.Name: SecurityClassificationValue
Field.Description: Specifies the product classification value which further details the manner in which the instrument participates in the class.

Field.Name: PosAmtReason
Field.Description: Specifies the reason for an amount type when reported on a position. Useful when multiple instances of the same amount type are reported.

Field.Name: NoLegPosAmt
Field.Description: Number of TrdInstrmtLegPosAmt values.

Field.Name: LegPosAmt
Field.Description: Leg position amount.

Field.Name: LegPosAmtType
Field.Description: Type of leg position amount.

Field.Name: LegPosCurrency
Field.Description: Leg position currency.

Field.Name: LegPosAmtReason
Field.Description: Specifies the reason for an amount type when reported on a position. Useful when multiple instances of the same amount type are reported.

Field.Name: LegQtyType
Field.Description: Type of quantity specified in LegQty field. LegContractMultiplier (614) is required when LegQtyType = 1 (Contracts). LegUnitOfMeasure (tag 999) and LegTimeUnit (tag 1001) are required when LegQtyType = 2 (Units of Measure per Time Unit). LegQtyType can be different for each leg.

Field.Name: DiscountFactor
Field.Description: Used to calculate the present value of an amount to be paid in the future.

Field.Name: ParentAllocID
Field.Description: Contains the IndividualAllocId (tag 467) value of the allocation that is being offset as a result of a new allocation. This would be an optional field that would only be populated in the case of an allocation of an allocation (as well as any subsequent allocations). This wouldnt be populated for an initial allocation since an allocation id is not supplied on default (initial) allocations.

Field.Name: LegSecurityGroup
Field.Description: Represents the product group of a leg.This is useful in conveying multi-leg instruments where the legs may participate in separate security groups.

Field.Name: PositionContingentPrice
Field.Description: Risk adjusted price used to calculate variation margin on a position.

Field.Name: ClearingTradePrice
Field.Description: Alternate clearing price

Field.Name: SideClearingTradePrice
Field.Description: Alternate clearing price for the side being reported.

Field.Name: SideClearingTradePriceType
Field.Description: Indicates to recipient whether trade is clearing at execution prices LastPx(tag 31) or alternate clearing prices SideClearingTradePrice(tag 1597).

Field.Name: SidePriceDifferential
Field.Description: Price Differential between the front and back leg of a spread or complex instrument.

Field.Name: FIXEngineName
Field.Description: Provides the name of the infrastructure component being used for session level communication. Normally this would be the FIX Engine or FIX Gateway product name.

Field.Name: FIXEngineVersion
Field.Description: Provides the version of the infrastructure component.

Field.Name: FIXEngineVendor
Field.Description: Provides the name of the vendor providing the infrastructure component.

Field.Name: ApplicationSystemName
Field.Description: Provides the name of the application system being used to generate FIX application messages. This will normally be a trading system, OMS, or EMS.

Field.Name: ApplicationSystemVersion
Field.Description: Provides the version of the application system being used to initiate FIX application messages.

Field.Name: ApplicationSystemVendor
Field.Description: Provides the vendor of the application system.

Field.Name: NumOfSimpleInstruments
Field.Description: Represents the total number of simple instruments that make up a multi-legged security. Complex spread instruments may be constructed of legs which themselves are multi-leg instruments.

Field.Name: SecurityRejectReason
Field.Description: Identifies the reason a security definition request is being rejected.

Field.Name: InitialDisplayQty
Field.Description: Used to convey the initially requested display quantity specified in DisplayQty(1138) on order entry and modification messages in ExecutionReport message. Applicable only in ExecutionReport message where DisplayQty(1138) is the currently displayed quantity and the requested display quantity of the order also needs to be conveyed. The values of the two fields are different as soon as the order is partially filled and also after a refresh of the order whenever DisplayMethod(1084) is not 1=Initial.

Field.Name: ThrottleStatus
Field.Description: Indicates whether a message was queued as a result of throttling.

Field.Name: NoThrottles
Field.Description: Indicates number of repeating groups to follow.

Field.Name: ThrottleAction
Field.Description: Action to take should throttle limit be exceeded.

Field.Name: ThrottleType
Field.Description: Type of throttle.

Field.Name: ThrottleNoMsgs
Field.Description: Maximum number of messages allowed by the throttle. May be a rate limit or a limit on the number of outstanding requests.

Field.Name: ThrottleTimeInterval
Field.Description: Value of the time interval in which the rate throttle is applied.

Field.Name: ThrottleTimeUnit
Field.Description: Units in which ThrottleTimeInterval is expressed. Uses same enumerations as OrderDelayUnit(1429).

Field.Name: NoThrottleMsgType
Field.Description: Number of ThrottleMsgType fields.

Field.Name: ThrottleMsgType
Field.Description: The MsgType (35) of the FIX message being referenced.

Field.Name: ThrottleInst
Field.Description: Describes action recipient should take if a throttle limit were exceeded.

Field.Name: ThrottleCountIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether a message decrements the number of outstanding requests, e.g. one where ThrottleType = Outstanding Requests.

Field.Name: AccountSummaryReportID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for the AccountSummaryReport(35=CQ).

Field.Name: NoSettlementAmounts
Field.Description: Number of settlement amount entries.

Field.Name: SettlementAmount
Field.Description: The amount of settlement.

Field.Name: SettlementAmountCurrency
Field.Description: The currency of the reported settlement amount.

Field.Name: NoCollateralAmounts
Field.Description: Number of collateral amount entries.

Field.Name: CurrentCollateralAmount
Field.Description: Currency value currently attributed to the collateral.

Field.Name: CollateralCurrency
Field.Description: Currency of the collateral; optional, defaults to the Settlement Currency if not specified.

Field.Name: CollateralType
Field.Description: Type of collateral on deposit being reported.

Field.Name: NoPayCollects
Field.Description: Number of pay collect entries.

Field.Name: PayAmount
Field.Description: Amount to be paid by the clearinghouse to the clearing firm.

Field.Name: CollectAmount
Field.Description: Amount to be collected by the clearinghouse from the clearing firm.

Field.Name: PayCollectType
Field.Description: Category describing the reason for funds paid to, or the funds collected from the clearing firm.

Field.Name: PayCollectCurrency
Field.Description: Currency denomination of value in PayAmount(1710) and CollectAmount(1711). If not specified, default to currency specified in SettlementAmountCurrency(1702).

Field.Name: PayCollectMarketSegmentID
Field.Description: Market segment associated with the pay collect amount.

Field.Name: PayCollectMarketID
Field.Description: Market associated with the pay collect amount.

Field.Name: MarginAmountMarketSegmentID
Field.Description: Market segment associated with the margin amount.

Field.Name: MarginAmountMarketID
Field.Description: Market associated with the margin amount

Field.Name: FirmGroupID
Field.Description: Firm assigned group allocation entity identifier.

Field.Name: FirmMnemonic
Field.Description: Allocation identifier assigned by the Firm submitting the allocation for an individual allocation instruction (as opposed to the overall message level identifier).

Field.Name: AllocGroupID
Field.Description: Intended to be used by a central counterparty to assign an identifier to allocations of trades for the same instrument traded at the same price.

Field.Name: AvgPxGroupID
Field.Description: Used by submitting firm to group trades being allocated into an average price group. The trades in average price group will be used to calculate an average price for the group.

Field.Name: FirmAllocText
Field.Description: Firm reference information, usually internal information, that is part of the initial message. The information would not be carried forward (e.g to Take-up Firm) and preserved with the transaction.

Field.Name: EncodedFirmAllocTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedFirmAllocText(1734) field.

Field.Name: EncodedFirmAllocText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the FirmAllocText(1732) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding(347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) represention should also be specified in FirmAllocText(1732) field.

Field.Name: AllocationRollupInstruction
Field.Description: An indicator to override the normal procedure to roll up allocations for the same take-up firm.

Field.Name: AllocGroupQuantity
Field.Description: Indicates the total quantity of an allocation group. Includes any allocated quantity.

Field.Name: AllocGroupRemainingQuantity
Field.Description: Indicates the remaining quantity of an allocation group that has not yet been allocated.

Field.Name: AllocReversalStatus
Field.Description: Identifies the status of a reversal transaction.

Field.Name: ObligationType
Field.Description: Type of reference obligation for credit derivatives contracts.

Field.Name: TradePriceNegotiationMethod
Field.Description: Method used for negotiation of contract price.

Field.Name: UpfrontPriceType
Field.Description: Type of price used to determine upfront payment for swaps contracts.

Field.Name: UpfrontPrice
Field.Description: Price used to determine upfront payment for swaps contracts.

Field.Name: LastUpfrontPrice
Field.Description: Price used to determine upfront payment for swaps contracts reported for a deal (trade).

Field.Name: ShortSaleRestriction
Field.Description: Indicates whether a restriction applies to short selling a security.

Field.Name: ShortSaleExemptionReason
Field.Description: Indicates the reason a short sale order is exempted from applicable regulation (e.g. Reg SHO addendum (b)(1) in the U.S.).

Field.Name: LegShortSaleExemptionReason
Field.Description: Indicates the reason a short sale is exempted from applicable regulation (e.g. Reg SHO addendum (b)(1) in the U.S.)

Field.Name: SideShortSaleExemptionReason
Field.Description: Indicates the reason a short sale is exempted from applicable regulation (e.g. Reg SHO addendum (b)(1) in the U.S.)

Field.Name: UnitOfMeasureCurrency
Field.Description: Indicates the currency of the unit of measure. Conditionally required when UnitOfMeasure(996) = Ccy

Field.Name: PriceUnitOfMeasureCurrency
Field.Description: Indicates the currency of the price unit of measure. Conditionally required when PriceUnitOfMeasure(1191) = Ccy

Field.Name: UnderlyingUnitOfMeasureCurrency
Field.Description: Indicates the currency of the underlying unit of measure. Conditionally required when UnderlyingUnitOfMeasure(998) = Ccy

Field.Name: UnderlyingPriceUnitOfMeasureCurrency
Field.Description: Indicates the currency of the underlying price unit of measure. Conditionally required when UnderlyingPriceUnitOfMeasure(1424) = Ccy

Field.Name: LegUnitOfMeasureCurrency
Field.Description: Indicates the currency of the unit of measure. Conditionally required when LegUnitOfMeasure(999) = Ccy

Field.Name: LegPriceUnitOfMeasureCurrency
Field.Description: Indicates the currency of the price unit of measure. Conditionally required when LegPriceUnitOfMeasure(1421) = Ccy

Field.Name: DerivativeUnitOfMeasureCurrency
Field.Description: Indicates the currency of the unit of measure. Conditionally required when DerivativeUnitOfMeasure(1269) = Ccy

Field.Name: DerivativePriceUnitOfMeasureCurrency
Field.Description: Indicates the currency of the price unit of measure. Conditionally required when DerivativePriceUnitOfMeasure(1315) = Ccy

Field.Name: ApplLevelRecoveryIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether application level recovery is needed.

Field.Name: BidMDEntryID
Field.Description: The market data entry identifier of the bid side of a quote

Field.Name: OfferMDEntryID
Field.Description: The market data entry identifier of the offer side of a quote.

Field.Name: BidQuoteID
Field.Description: Marketplace assigned quote identifier for the bid side. Can be used to indicate priority.

Field.Name: OfferQuoteID
Field.Description: Marketplace assigned quote identifier for the offer side. Can be used to indicate priority.

Field.Name: TotalBidSize
Field.Description: Specifies the total bid size.

Field.Name: TotalOfferSize
Field.Description: Specifies the total offer size.

Field.Name: SecondaryQuoteID
Field.Description: Assigned by the party which accepts the quote. Can be used to provide the quote identifier assigned by an exchange, marketplace or executing system.

Field.Name: CustodialLotID
Field.Description: An opaque identifier used to communicate the custodians identifier for the lot. It is expected that this information would be provided by the custodian as part of a reconciliation process that occurs before trading.

Field.Name: VersusPurchaseDate
Field.Description: The effective acquisition date of the lot that would be used for gain-loss trade lot reporting. The versus purchase date used to identify the lot in situations where a custodial lot identifier is not available.

Field.Name: VersusPurchasePrice
Field.Description: The versus purchase price used to identify the lot in situations where a custodial lot identifier is not available. The value should be calculated based on current cost basis / quantity held.

Field.Name: CurrentCostBasis
Field.Description: The amount that the current shares are worth. If this lot was liquidated, the total gain/loss for a trade is equal to the trade amount minus the current cost basis.

Field.Name: LegCustodialLotID
Field.Description: An opaque identifier used to communicate the custodians identifier for the lot. It is expected that this information would be provided by the custodian as part of a reconciliation process that occurs before trading.

Field.Name: LegVersusPurchaseDate
Field.Description: The effective acquisition date of the lot that would be used for gain-loss trade lot reporting. The versus purchase date used to identify the lot in situations where a custodial lot identifier is not available.

Field.Name: LegVersusPurchasePrice
Field.Description: The versus purchase price used to identify the lot in situations where a custodial lot identifier is not available.The value should be calculated based on current cost basis / quantity held.

Field.Name: LegCurrentCostBasis
Field.Description: The amount that the current shares are worth. If this lot was liquidated, the total gain/loss for a trade is equal to the trade amount minus the current cost basis.

Field.Name: RiskLimitRequestType
Field.Description: Type of risk limit information.

Field.Name: RiskLimitRequestResult
Field.Description: Result of risk limit definition request.

Field.Name: RiskLimitRequestStatus
Field.Description: Status of risk limit definition request.

Field.Name: RiskLimitStatus
Field.Description: Status of risk limit definition for one party.

Field.Name: RiskLimitResult
Field.Description: Result of risk limit definition for one party.

Field.Name: RiskLimitUtilizationPercent
Field.Description: Percentage of utilization of a party's set risk limit.

Field.Name: RiskLimitUtilizationAmount
Field.Description: Absolute amount of utilization of a party's set risk limit.

Field.Name: RiskLimitAction
Field.Description: Identifies the action to take or risk model to assume should risk limit be exceeded or breached for the specified party.

Field.Name: RiskWarningLevelAmount
Field.Description: Amount at which a warning is issued.

Field.Name: RiskWarningLevelAction
Field.Description: Action to take should warning level be exceeded.

Field.Name: EntitlementRequestID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for PartyEntitlementsRequest(35=CU).

Field.Name: EntitlementReportID
Field.Description: Identifier for the PartyEntitlementsReport(35=CV).

Field.Name: NoPartyEntitlements
Field.Description: Number of party entitlement values.

Field.Name: NoEntitlements
Field.Description: Number of entitlement values.

Field.Name: EntitlementIndicator
Field.Description: Used to indicate if a party is entitled to an entitlement type specified in the EntitlementType(1775) field.

Field.Name: EntitlementType
Field.Description: Type of entitlement.

Field.Name: EntitlementID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a specific NoEntitlements(1773) repeating group instance.

Field.Name: NoEntitlementAttrib
Field.Description: Number of entitlement attributes.

Field.Name: EntitlementAttribType
Field.Description: Name of the entitlement attribute type. A code list of allowed values will be maintained on the FIX Protocol website. Values "4000" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

Field.Name: EntitlementAttribDatatype
Field.Description: Datatype of the entitlement attribute.

Field.Name: EntitlementAttribValue
Field.Description: Value of the entitlement attribute.

Field.Name: EntitlementAttribCurrency
Field.Description: Currency for EntitlementAttribValue(1780). Can be used if these fields represent a price, price offset, or amount.

Field.Name: EntitlementStartDate
Field.Description: Indicates the starting date of the entitlement.

Field.Name: EntitlementEndDate
Field.Description: Indicates the ending date of the entitlement.

Field.Name: EntitlementPlatform
Field.Description: The area to which the entitlement is applicable. This can be a trading platform or an offering.

Field.Name: TradSesControl
Field.Description: Indicates how control of trading session and subsession transitions are performed.

Field.Name: TradeVolType
Field.Description: Define the type of trade volume applicable for the MinTradeVol(562) and MaxTradeVol(1140)

Field.Name: RefTickTableID
Field.Description: Spread table code referred by the security or symbol.

Field.Name: LegID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for the leg within the context of a message (the scope of uniqueness to be defined by counterparty agreement). The LegID(1788) can be referenced using LegRefID(654).

Field.Name: NoTargetMarketSegments
Field.Description: Number of market segments upon which a mass action is to be taken.

Field.Name: TargetMarketSegmentID
Field.Description: Market segment within a target market segment repeating group.

Field.Name: NoAffectedMarketSegments
Field.Description: Number of market segments affected by a mass action.

Field.Name: AffectedMarketSegmentID
Field.Description: Market segment within an affected market repeating segment group.

Field.Name: NoNotAffectedMarketSegments
Field.Description: Number of market segments left unaffected by a mass action.

Field.Name: NotAffectedMarketSegmentID
Field.Description: Market segment within an unaffected market repeating segment group.

Field.Name: NoOrderEvents
Field.Description: Number of order events.

Field.Name: OrderEventType
Field.Description: The type of event affecting an order. The last event type within the OrderEventGrp component indicates the ExecType(150) value resulting from the series of events (ExecType(150) values are shown in brackets).

Field.Name: OrderEventExecID
Field.Description: Refer to ExecID(17). Used when multiple different events are reported in single Execution Report. ExecID(17) and OrderEventExecID(1797) values should not overlap.

Field.Name: OrderEventReason
Field.Description: Action that caused the event to occur.

Field.Name: OrderEventPx
Field.Description: Price associated with the event.

Field.Name: OrderEventQty
Field.Description: Quantity associated with the event.

Field.Name: OrderEventLiquidityIndicator
Field.Description: Indicator to identify whether this fill was a result of a liquidity provider providing or liquidity taker taking the liquidity. Applicable only for OrderEventType(1796) values of 4(Partially Filled) or 5(Filled).

Field.Name: OrderEventText
Field.Description: Additional information about the event.

Field.Name: AuctionType
Field.Description: Type of auction order.

Field.Name: AuctionAllocationPct
Field.Description: Percentage of matched quantity to be allocated to the submitter of the response to an auction order.

Field.Name: AuctionInstruction
Field.Description: Instruction related to system generated auctions, e.g. flash order auctions.

Field.Name: RefClOrdID
Field.Description: Used to reference an order via ClOrdID(11).

Field.Name: LockType
Field.Description: Indicates whether an order is locked and for what reason.

Field.Name: LockedQty
Field.Description: Locked order quantity.

Field.Name: SecondaryLockedQty
Field.Description: Locked order quantity in addition to LockedQty (1808), e.g. to distinguish total locked quantity from currently locked quantity.

Field.Name: ReleaseInstruction
Field.Description: Instruction to define conditions under which to release a locked order or parts of it.

Field.Name: ReleaseQty
Field.Description: Quantity to be made available, i.e. released from a lock.

Field.Name: NoDisclosureInstructions
Field.Description: Number of disclosure instructions.

Field.Name: DisclosureType
Field.Description: Information subject to disclosure.

Field.Name: DisclosureInstruction
Field.Description: Instruction to disclose information or to use default value of the receiver.

Field.Name: TradingCapacity
Field.Description: Designates the capacity in which the order is submitted for trading by the market participant.

Field.Name: ClearingAccountType
Field.Description: Designates the account type to be used for the order when submitted to clearing.

Field.Name: LegClearingAccountType
Field.Description: Designates the capacity in which the order will be submitted to clearing.

Field.Name: TargetPartyRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Qualifies the value of TargetPartyRole (1464).

Field.Name: RelatedHighPrice
Field.Description: Upper boundary for the price of a related entity, e.g. price of the underlying instrument in an Underlying Price Contingency (UPC) order.

Field.Name: RelatedLowPrice
Field.Description: Lower boundary for the price of a related entity, e.g. price of the underlying instrument in an Underlying Price Contingency (UPC) order.

Field.Name: RelatedPriceSource
Field.Description: Source for the price of a related entity, e.g. price of the underlying instrument in an Underlying Price Contingency (UPC) order. Can be used together with RelatedHighPrice (1819) and/or RelatedLowPrice (1820).

Field.Name: MinQtyMethod
Field.Description: Indicates how the minimum quantity should be applied when executing the order.

Field.Name: Triggered
Field.Description: Indicates whether order has been triggered during its lifetime. Applies to cases where original information, e.g. OrdType(40), is modified when the order is triggered.

Field.Name: AffectedOrigClOrdID
Field.Description: OrigClOrdID(41) of an order affected by a mass cancel or mass action request.

Field.Name: NotAffSecondaryOrderID
Field.Description: SecondaryOrderID (198) of an order not affected by a mass cancel or mass action request.

Field.Name: NoCrossLegs
Field.Description: Number of legs in the side of a cross order.

Field.Name: EventTimePeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the event.

Field.Name: EventTimeUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the event.

Field.Name: LastQtyVariance
Field.Description: When LastQty is an estimated value, e.g. for a Repo circled trade, LastQtyVariance specifies the absolute amount that the size may vary up or down when finalized. Omitted when LastQty(32) is already final.

Field.Name: OrderOrigination
Field.Description: Identifies the origin of the order.

Field.Name: OriginatingDeptID
Field.Description: An identifier representing the department or desk within the firm that originated the order.

Field.Name: ReceivingDeptID
Field.Description: An identifier representing the department or desk within the firm that received the order.

Field.Name: InformationBarrierID
Field.Description: The identifier of the information barrier in place for a trading unit that will meet the criteria of the "no-knowledge" exception in FINRA Rule 5320.02.

Field.Name: SettlPriceIncrement
Field.Description: Settlement price increment for stated price range.

Field.Name: SettlPriceSecondaryIncrement
Field.Description: Secondary settlement price increment for stated price range. The meaning of secondary is left to bilateral agreement, e.g. it may refer to final settlement for a contract.

Field.Name: ClearedIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the trade or position being reported was cleared through a clearing organization.

Field.Name: ContractRefPosType
Field.Description: Additional information related to the pricing of a commodity swaps position, specifically an indicator referring to the position type.

Field.Name: PositionCapacity
Field.Description: Used to describe the ownership of the position.

Field.Name: PosQtyUnitOfMeasureCurrency
Field.Description: Indicates the currency of the unit of measure if position quantity is expressed in valuation rather than contracts. Conditionally required when PosQtyUnitOfMeasure(1836)=Ccy.

Field.Name: PosQtyUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Indicates the unit of measure of the position quantity when not expressed in contracts.

Field.Name: UnderlyingContractPriceRefMonth
Field.Description: Reference month if there is no applicable UnderlyingMaturityMonth(313) value for the contract or security.

Field.Name: NoTradePriceConditions
Field.Description: Number of trade price conditions.

Field.Name: TradePriceCondition
Field.Description: Price conditions in effect at the time of the trade. Multiple price conditions can be in effect at the same time. Price conditions are usually required to be reported in markets that have regulations on price execution at a market or national best bid or offer, and the trade price differs from the best bid or offer.

Field.Name: TradeAllocStatus
Field.Description: Identifies the status of an allocation when using a pre-clear workflow.
Field.Elaboration: Note: This is different from the give-up process where a trade is cleared and then given up and goes through the allocation flow.

Field.Name: NoTradeQtys
Field.Description: Number of trade quantities.

Field.Name: TradeQtyType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of trade quantity in TradeQty(1843).

Field.Name: TradeQty
Field.Description: Trade quantity.

Field.Name: NoTradeAllocAmts
Field.Description: Number of trade allocation amount entries.

Field.Name: TradeAllocAmtType
Field.Description: Type of the amount associated with a trade allocation.

Field.Name: TradeAllocAmt
Field.Description: The amount associated with a trade allocation.

Field.Name: TradeAllocCurrency
Field.Description: Currency denomination of the trade allocation amount.

Field.Name: TradeAllocGroupInstruction
Field.Description: Instruction on how to add a trade to an allocation group when it is being given-up.

Field.Name: OffsetInstruction
Field.Description: Indicates the trade is a result of an offset or onset.

Field.Name: TradeAllocAmtReason
Field.Description: Specifies the reason for an amount type when reported on an allocation. Useful when multiple instances of the same amount type are reported.

Field.Name: StrategyLinkID
Field.Description: Identifies the multileg strategy (e.g. spread) to which the trade belongs. This links together trade legs executed as part of a strategy during a single match event.

Field.Name: SideAvgPx
Field.Description: Calculated average price for this side of the trade.

Field.Name: SideAvgPxIndicator
Field.Description: Used to indicate whether a trade or a sub-allocation should be allocated at the trade price (e.g. no average pricing), or whether it should be grouped with other trades/sub-allocations and allocated at the average price of the group.

Field.Name: SideAvgPxGroupID
Field.Description: The identifier for the average price group for the trade side. See also AvgPxGroupID(1731).

Field.Name: NoRelatedTrades
Field.Description: Number of related trades.

Field.Name: RelatedTradeID
Field.Description: Identifier of a related trade.

Field.Name: RelatedTradeIDSource
Field.Description: Describes the source of the identifier that RelatedTradeID(1856) represents.

Field.Name: RelatedTradeDate
Field.Description: Date of a related trade.

Field.Name: RelatedTradeMarketID
Field.Description: Market of execution of related trade.

Field.Name: RelatedTradeQuantity
Field.Description: Quantity of the related trade which can be less than or equal to the actual quantity of the related trade. For example, when one trade offsets another across asset classes.

Field.Name: NoRelatedPositions
Field.Description: Number of related positions.

Field.Name: RelatedPositionID
Field.Description: Identifier of a related position.

Field.Name: RelatedPositionIDSource
Field.Description: Describes the source of the identifier that RelatedPositionID(1862) represents.

Field.Name: RelatedPositionDate
Field.Description: Used to help identify the position when RelatedPositionID(1862) is not unique across multiple days. This date is generally the creation date of the identifier.

Field.Name: QuoteAckStatus
Field.Description: Acknowledgement status of a Quote(35=S) or QuoteCancel(35=Z) message submission.

Field.Name: OfferID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for the ask side of the quote assigned by the quote issuer.

Field.Name: NoValueChecks
Field.Description: Number of value check entries.

Field.Name: ValueCheckType
Field.Description: Type of value to be checked.

Field.Name: ValueCheckAction
Field.Description: Action to be taken for the ValueCheckType(1869).

Field.Name: LegSecurityXMLLen
Field.Description: The length of the LegSecurityXML(1872) data block.

Field.Name: LegSecurityXML
Field.Description: XML definition for the leg security.

Field.Name: LegSecurityXMLSchema
Field.Description: The schema used to validate the contents of LegSecurityXML(1872).

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityXMLLen
Field.Description: The length of the UnderlyingSecurityXML(1875) data block.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityXML
Field.Description: XML definition for the underlying security.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityXMLSchema
Field.Description: The schema used to validate the contents of UnderlyingSecurityXML(1875).

Field.Name: PartyDetailRequestResult
Field.Description: Result party detail definition request.

Field.Name: PartyDetailRequestStatus
Field.Description: Status of party details definition request.

Field.Name: PartyDetailDefinitionStatus
Field.Description: Status of party detail definition for one party.

Field.Name: PartyDetailDefinitionResult
Field.Description: Result of party detail definition for one party.

Field.Name: EntitlementRequestResult
Field.Description: Result of risk limit definition request.

Field.Name: EntitlementRequestStatus
Field.Description: Status of party entitlements definition request.

Field.Name: EntitlementStatus
Field.Description: Status of entitlement definition for one party.

Field.Name: EntitlementResult
Field.Description: Result of entitlement definition for one party.

Field.Name: EntitlementRefID
Field.Description: Reference to an EntitlementID(1776). Used for modification or deletion of an entitlement.

Field.Name: SettlPriceUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Used to express the unit of measure of the settlement price if different from the contract.

Field.Name: SettlPriceUnitOfMeasureCurrency
Field.Description: Indicates the currency of the settlement price unit of measure if expressed in another currency than the base currency. Conditionally required when SettlPriceUnitOfMeasure(1886)=Ccy.

Field.Name: TradeMatchTimestamp
Field.Description: Timestamp of the match event. For off-exchange trades the time at which the deal was matched by the exchange. This timestamp will be the same on all the trades and will not change when a trade is modified.

Field.Name: NoInstrmtMatchSides
Field.Description: Number of instrument match sides.

Field.Name: NoTrdMatchSides
Field.Description: Number of trade match sides.

Field.Name: TrdMatchSubID
Field.Description: Used to identify each price level, step or clip within a match event.
Field.Elaboration: The identifier may represent a grouping of matched resting orders at a given price level that was matched by an aggressor order. For example, an aggressive order sweeping through 2 price levels that included 3 resting orders would have two different TrdMatchSubID(1891) values.

Field.Name: NoLegExecs
Field.Description: Number of instrument leg executions.

Field.Name: LegExecID
Field.Description: The ExecID(17) value corresponding to a trade leg.

Field.Name: LegTradeID
Field.Description: The TradeID(1003) value corresponding to a trade leg.

Field.Name: LegTradeReportID
Field.Description: The TradeReportID(571) value corresponding to a trade leg.

Field.Name: TradeMatchAckStatus
Field.Description: Used to indicate the status of the trade match report submission.

Field.Name: TradeMatchRejectReason
Field.Description: Reason the trade match report submission was rejected.

Field.Name: SideMarketSegmentID
Field.Description: Identifies the market segment of the side.

Field.Name: SideVenueType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of venue where the trade was executed for the side.

Field.Name: SideExecRefID
Field.Description: Used to reference the value from SideExecID(1427).

Field.Name: LegExecRefID
Field.Description: Used to reference the value from LegExecID(1893).

Field.Name: HaircutIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates, if "Y", that a stated valuation includes a haircut, e.g. that the stated value reflects the subtraction of the haircut. Note that a value of "N" does not imply a haircut is not applicable, only that the haircut (if any) is not reflected in the stated valuation.

Field.Name: NumOfCompetitors
Field.Description: The number of competing Respondents (e.g. dealers) to receive a quote request (either via the QuoteRequest(35=R) or via other means).

Field.Name: ResponseTime
Field.Description: The time by which a meaningful response should arrive back (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT").
Field.Elaboration: The meaning of the response time is specific to the context where the field is used. For a QuoteRequest(35=R) message, this is the time by which the Quote(35=S) message should arrive to the initiator of the QuoteRequest(35=R) message.

Field.Name: QuoteDisplayTime
Field.Description: Time by which the quote will be displayed.
Field.Elaboration: For example, the time the execution venue will display dealer(s) submitted quotes to market participant(s).

Field.Name: ExposureDurationUnit
Field.Description: Time unit in which the ExposureDuration(1629) is expressed.

Field.Name: CoverPrice
Field.Description: The best quoted price received among those not traded.

Field.Name: NoClearingAccountTypes
Field.Description: Number of clearing account type entries.

Field.Name: NoPriceMovements
Field.Description: Number of price movement entries.

Field.Name: NoPriceMovementValues
Field.Description: Number of price movement value entries.

Field.Name: PriceMovementValue
Field.Description: Value at specific price movement point.

Field.Name: PriceMovementPoint
Field.Description: Price movement point up (positive integer) or down (negative integer) relative to the underlying price of the instrument.

Field.Name: PriceMovementType
Field.Description: Describes the format of the PriceMovementValue(1921).

Field.Name: EncodedEventTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedEventText(868) fied.

Field.Name: EncodedEventText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the EventText(868) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the EventText(868) field.

Field.Name: RegulatoryTradeID
Field.Description: Trade identifier required by government regulators or other regulatory organizations for regulatory reporting purposes. For example, unique swap identifer (USI) as required by the U.S. Commodity Futures Trading Commission.

Field.Name: RegulatoryTradeIDEvent
Field.Description: Identifies the event which caused origination of the identifier in RegulatoryTradeID(1903). When more than one event is the cause, use the higher enumeration value. For example, if the identifier is originated due to an allocated trade which was cleared and reported, use the enumeration value 2 (Clearing).

Field.Name: RegulatoryTradeIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the reporting entity that originated the value in RegulatoryTradeID(1903). The reporting entitiy identifier may be assigned by a regulator.

Field.Name: RegulatoryTradeIDType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of trade identifier provided in RegulatoryTradeID(1903). Contextual hierarchy of events for the same trade or transaction maybe captured through use of the different RegulatoryTradeIDType(1906) values using multiple instances of the repeating group as needed for regulatory reporting.

Field.Name: NoRegulatoryTradeIDs
Field.Description: Number of regulatory IDs in the repeating group.

Field.Name: NoAllocRegulatoryTradeIDs
Field.Description: Number of regulatory IDs in the repeating group.

Field.Name: AllocRegulatoryTradeID
Field.Description: Trade identifier required by government regulators or other regulatory organizations for regulatory reporting purposes. For example, unique swap identifer (USI) as required by the U.S. Commodity Futures Trading Commission.

Field.Name: AllocRegulatoryTradeIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the reporting entity that originated the value in AllocRegulatoryTradeID(1909). The reporting entity identifier may be assigned by a regulator.

Field.Name: AllocRegulatoryTradeIDEvent
Field.Description: Identifies the event which caused the origination of the identifier in AllocRegulatoryTradeID(1909). When more than one event is the cause, use the higher enumeration value. For example, if the identifier is originated due to an allocated trade which was cleared and reported, use the enumeration value 2(Clearing).

Field.Name: AllocRegulatoryTradeIDType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of trade identifier provided in AllocRegulatoryTradeID(1909), within the context of the hierarchy of trade events.

Field.Name: ClearingIntention
Field.Description: Specifies the party's or parties' intention to clear the trade.

Field.Name: TradeClearingInstruction
Field.Description: Specifies the eligibility of this trade for clearing and central counterparty processing.

Field.Name: BackloadedTradeIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates that the trade being reported occurred in the past and is still in effect or active.

Field.Name: ConfirmationMethod
Field.Description: Specifies how a trade was confirmed.

Field.Name: MandatoryClearingIndicator
Field.Description: An indication that the trade is flagged for mandatory clearing.

Field.Name: MixedSwapIndicator
Field.Description: An indication that the trade is a mixed swap.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of CFTC , a "Mixed swap" is defined in the Commodity Exchange Act (CEA) section 1a(47)(D) as an instrument that is in part a swap subject to the jurisdiction of the CFTC, and in part a security-based swap subject to the jurisdiction of the SEC. When reporting the additional Swap Data Repositories must be identified in the appropriate Parties component with PartyRole(452) = 102 (Data repository), PartyRoleQualifier(2376) = 12 (Additional domestic trade repository) and PartySub-IDType(803) = 70 (Location or jurisdiction).

Field.Name: OffMarketPriceIndicator
Field.Description: An indication that the price is off-market.

Field.Name: VerificationMethod
Field.Description: Indication of how a trade was verified.

Field.Name: ClearingRequirementException
Field.Description: Specifies whether a party to a swap is using an exception to a clearing requirement. In the US, one such clearing requirement is CFTC's rule pursuant to CEA Section 2(h)(1).

Field.Name: IRSDirection
Field.Description: Used to specify whether the principal is paying or receiving the fixed rate in an interest rate swap.

Field.Name: RegulatoryReportType
Field.Description: Type of regulatory report.

Field.Name: VoluntaryRegulatoryReport
Field.Description: Used in conjunction with RegulatoryReportType(1934) to indicate whether the trade report is a voluntary regulatory report. If not specified, the default for a regulatory report is "N". When VoluntaryRegulatoryReport(1935)=Y it is recommended that one of the parties to the trade be identified as the voluntary reporting party through PartySubIDType(803) = 63 (Voluntary reporting entity).

Field.Name: TradeCollateralization
Field.Description: Specifies how the trade is collateralized.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of Dodd-Frank, all values shown except for 4 (Net exposure) apply. In the context of ESMA EU SFTR reporting only the values 1 (Uncollateralized), 3 (Fully collateralized) and 4 (Net exposure) apply.

Field.Name: TradeContinuation
Field.Description: Specifies the post-execution trade continuation or lifecycle event. Additional values may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties.

Field.Name: AssetClass
Field.Description: The broad asset category for assessing risk exposure.

Field.Name: AssetSubClass
Field.Description: The subcategory description of the asset class.

Field.Name: AssetType
Field.Description: Used to provide more specific description of the asset specified in AssetSubClass(1939). See https://www.fixtrading.org/codelists/AssetType for code list of applicable values. ISO 4721 Currency Code values are to be used when specific currency as an asset type is to be expressed. Other values may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of MiFID II's this may indicate the value needed in ESMA RTS 2 Annex IV Table 2 Field 16, or ESMA RTS 23 Annex I Table 2 'Sub product' field.

Field.Name: SwapClass
Field.Description: The classification or type of swap. Additional values may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties.

Field.Name: NthToDefault
Field.Description: The Nth reference obligation to default in a CDS reference basket. If specified without MthToDefault(1943) the default will trigger a CDS payout. If MthToDefault(1943) is also present then payout occurs between the Nth and Mth obligations to default.

Field.Name: MthToDefault
Field.Description: The Mth reference obligation to default in a CDS reference basket. When NthToDefault(1942) and MthToDefault(1943) are represented then the CDS payout occurs between the Nth and Mth obligations to default.

Field.Name: SettledEntityMatrixSource
Field.Description: Relevant settled entity matrix source.

Field.Name: SettledEntityMatrixPublicationDate
Field.Description: The publication date of the applicable version of the matrix. If not specified, the Standard Terms Supplement defines rules for which version of the matrix is applicable.

Field.Name: CouponType
Field.Description: Coupon type of the bond.

Field.Name: TotalIssuedAmount
Field.Description: Specifies the total amount of the issue. Corresponds to the par value multiplied by the number of issued securities.

Field.Name: CouponFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of the bond's coupon payment.

Field.Name: CouponFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the frequency of the bond's coupon payment.

Field.Name: CouponDayCount
Field.Description: The day count convention used in interest calculations for a bond or an interest bearing security. Absence of this field for a bond or an interest bearing security transaction implies a "flat" trade, i.e. no accrued interest determined at time of the transaction.

Field.Name: ConvertibleBondEquityID
Field.Description: Identifies the equity in which a convertible bond can be converted to.

Field.Name: ConvertibleBondEquityIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies class or source of the ConvertibleBondEquityID(1951) value. 100+ are reserved for private security.

Field.Name: ContractPriceRefMonth
Field.Description: Reference month if there is no applicable MaturityMonthYear(200) value for the contract or security.

Field.Name: LienSeniority
Field.Description: Indicates the seniority level of the lien in a loan.

Field.Name: LoanFacility
Field.Description: Specifies the type of loan when the credit default swap's reference obligation is a loan.

Field.Name: ReferenceEntityType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of reference entity for first-to-default CDS basket contracts.

Field.Name: IndexSeries
Field.Description: The series identifier of a credit default swap index.

Field.Name: IndexAnnexVersion
Field.Description: The version of a credit default swap index annex.

Field.Name: IndexAnnexDate
Field.Description: The date of a credit default swap index series annex.

Field.Name: IndexAnnexSource
Field.Description: The source of a credit default swap series annex.

Field.Name: AgreementVersion
Field.Description: The version of the master agreement

Field.Name: MasterConfirmationDesc
Field.Description: The type of master confirmation executed between the parties. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/master-confirmation-type for values.

Field.Name: MasterConfirmationDate
Field.Description: Alternative to broker confirmation. The date of the confirmation executed between the parties and intended to govern all relevant transactions between those parties.

Field.Name: MasterConfirmationAnnexDesc
Field.Description: The type of master confirmation annex executed between the parties. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/master-confirmation-annex-type for values.

Field.Name: MasterConfirmationAnnexDate
Field.Description: The date that an annex to the master confirmation was executed between the parties.

Field.Name: BrokerConfirmationDesc
Field.Description: Describes the type of broker confirmation executed between the parites. Can be used as an alterative to MasterConfirmationDesc(1962). See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/broker-confirmation-type for values.

Field.Name: CreditSupportAgreementDesc
Field.Description: The type of ISDA Credit Support Agreement. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/credit-support-agreement-type for values.

Field.Name: CreditSupportAgreementDate
Field.Description: The date of the ISDA Credit Support Agreement executed between the parties and intended to govern collateral arrangements for all OTC derivatives transactions between those parties.

Field.Name: CreditSupportAgreementID
Field.Description: A common reference or unique identifier to identify the ISDA Credit Support Agreement executed between the parties.

Field.Name: GoverningLaw
Field.Description: Identification of the law governing the transaction. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/governing-law for values.

Field.Name: NoSideRegulatoryTradeIDs
Field.Description: Number of regulatory IDs in the repeating group.

Field.Name: SideRegulatoryTradeID
Field.Description: Trade identifier required by government regulators or other regulatory organziations for regulatory reporting purposes. For example, unique swap identifier (USI) as required by the U.S. Commodity Futures Trading Commission.

Field.Name: SideRegulatoryTradeIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the reporting entity that originated the value in SideRegulatoryTradeID(1972). The reporting entity identifier may be assigned by a regulator.

Field.Name: SideRegulatoryTradeIDEvent
Field.Description: Identifies the event which caused origination of the identifier in SideRegulatoryTradeID(1972). When more than one event is the cause, use the higher enumeration value. For example, if the identifier is originated due to an allocated trade which was cleared and reported, use the enumeration value 2 (Clearing).

Field.Name: SideRegulatoryTradeIDType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of trade identifier provided in SideRegulatoryTradeID(1972), within the context of the hierarchy of trade events.

Field.Name: NoSecondaryAssetClasses
Field.Description: Number of secondary asset classes in the repeating group.

Field.Name: SecondaryAssetClass
Field.Description: The broad asset category for assessing risk exposure for a multi-asset trade.

Field.Name: SecondaryAssetSubClass
Field.Description: An indication of the general description of the asset class.

Field.Name: SecondaryAssetType
Field.Description: Used to provide more specific description of the asset specified in SecondaryAssetSubClass(1978). See https://www.fixtrading.org/codelists/AssetType for code list of applicable values. ISO 4721 Currency Code values are to be used when specific currency as an asset type is to be expressed. Other values may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of MiFID II's this may indicate the value needed in ESMA RTS 2 Annex IV Table 2 Field 16, or ESMA RTS 23 Annex I Table 2 'Sub product' field.

Field.Name: BlockTrdAllocIndicator
Field.Description: Indication that a block trade will be allocated.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingEvents
Field.Description: Number of events in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingEventType
Field.Description: Code to represent the type of event.

Field.Name: UnderlyingEventDate
Field.Description: The date of the event.

Field.Name: UnderlyingEventTime
Field.Description: The time of the event. To be used in combination with UnderlyingEventDate(1983).

Field.Name: UnderlyingEventTimeUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the event.

Field.Name: UnderlyingEventTimePeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the event.

Field.Name: UnderlyingEventPx
Field.Description: Predetermined price of issue at event, if applicable.

Field.Name: UnderlyingConstituentWeight
Field.Description: For a basket, or pool, describes the weight of each of the constituents within the basket. If not provided, it is assumed to be equal weighted.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCouponType
Field.Description: Specifies the coupon type of the underlying bond.

Field.Name: UnderlyingTotalIssuedAmount
Field.Description: Specifies the total amount of the issue. Corresponds to the par value multiplied by the number of issued security.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCouponFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of the bond's coupon payment.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCouponFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the frequency of the bond's coupon payment.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCouponDayCount
Field.Description: The day count convention used in interest calculations for a bond or an interest bearing security.

Field.Name: UnderlyingObligationID
Field.Description: For a CDS basket or pool identifies the reference obligation.
Field.Elaboration: UnderlyingObligationID(1994) is reserved for the reference entity for baskets or pools. In a CDS single name the reference entity is identified in insrument ID and the obligations are identified in UnderlyingObligationID(1994).

Field.Name: UnderlyingObligationIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source scheme of the UnderlyingObligationID(1994).

Field.Name: UnderlyingEquityID
Field.Description: Specifies the equity in which a convertible bond can be converted.

Field.Name: UnderlyingEquityIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source of the UnderlyingEquityID(1996).

Field.Name: UnderlyingLienSeniority
Field.Description: Indicates the seniority level of the lien in a loan.

Field.Name: UnderlyingLoanFacility
Field.Description: Specifies the type of loan when the credit default swap's reference obligation is a loan.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReferenceEntityType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of reference entity for first-to-default CDS basket contracts.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermXIDRef
Field.Description: Reference to the protection terms applicable to this entity or obligation. Contains the same XID named string value of the instance in the ProtectionTerms repeating group that applies to this Underlying.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlTermXIDRef
Field.Description: Reference to the cash or physical settlement terms applicable to this entity or obligation. Contains the same XID named string value of the instance in the appropriate repeating group that applies to this Underlying.

Field.Name: UnderlyingIndexSeries
Field.Description: The series identifier of a credit default swap index.

Field.Name: UnderlyingIndexAnnexVersion
Field.Description: The version identifier of a credit default swap index annex.

Field.Name: UnderlyingIndexAnnexDate
Field.Description: The date of a credit default swap index series annex.

Field.Name: UnderlyingIndexAnnexSource
Field.Description: The source of a credit default swap index series annex.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProductComplex
Field.Description: Identifies an entire suite of products for a given market. In Futures this may be "interest rates", "agricultural", "equity indexes", etc

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityGroup
Field.Description: An exchange specific name assigned to a group of related securities which may be concurrently affected by market events and actions.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettleOnOpenFlag
Field.Description: Indicator to determine if Instrument is Settle on Open.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAssignmentMethod
Field.Description: Method under which assignment was conducted

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityStatus
Field.Description: Gives the current state of the instrument

Field.Name: UnderlyingObligationType
Field.Description: Type of reference obligation for credit derivatives contracts.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAssetClass
Field.Description: The broad asset category for assessing risk exposure.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAssetSubClass
Field.Description: An indication of the general description of the asset class.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAssetType
Field.Description: Used to provide more specific description of the asset specified in UnderlyingAssetSubClass(2082). See https://www.fixtrading.org/codelists/AssetType for code list of applicable values. ISO 4721 Currency Code values are to be used when specific currency as an asset type is to be expressed. Other values may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of MiFID II's this may indicate the value needed in ESMA RTS 2 Annex IV Table 2 Field 16, or ESMA RTS 23 Annex I Table 2 'Sub product' field.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSwapClass
Field.Description: The type or classification of swap. Additional values may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties.

Field.Name: UnderlyingNthToDefault
Field.Description: The Nth reference obligation to default in a CDS reference basket. If specified without UnderlyingMthToDefault(2018) the default will trigger a CDS payout. If UnderlyingMthToDefault(2018) is also present then payout occurs between the Nth and Mth obligations to default.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMthToDefault
Field.Description: The Mth reference obligation to default in a CDS reference basket. When UnderlyingNthToDefault(2017) and UnderlyingMthToDefault(2018) are represented then the CDS payout occurs between the Nth and Mth obligations to default.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettledEntityMatrixSource
Field.Description: Relevant settled entity matrix source.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettledEntityMatrixPublicationDate
Field.Description: Specifies the publication date of the applicable version of the matrix. If not specified, the Standard Terms Supplement defines rules for which version of the matrix is applicable.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStrikeMultiplier
Field.Description: Used for derivatives. Multiplier applied to the strike price for the purpose of calculating the settlement value.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStrikeValue
Field.Description: Used for derivatives. The number of shares/units for the financial instrument involved in the option trade.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStrikePriceDeterminationMethod
Field.Description: Specifies how the strike price is determined at the point of option exercise. The strike may be fixed throughout the life of the option, set at expiration to the value of the underlying, set to the average value of the underlying , or set to the optimal value of the underlying.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStrikePriceBoundaryMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the boundary condition to be used for the strike price relative to the underlying price at the point of option exercise.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStrikePriceBoundaryPrecision
Field.Description: Used in combination with StrikePriceBoundaryMethod(1479) to specify the percentage of the strike price in relation to the underlying price. The percentage is generally 100 or greater for puts and 100 or less for calls.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMinPriceIncrement
Field.Description: Minimum price increment for the instrument. Could also be used to represent tick value.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMinPriceIncrementAmount
Field.Description: Minimum price increment amount associated with the UnderlyingMinPriceIncrement(2026). For listed derivatives, the value can be calculated by multiplying UnderlyingMinPriceIncrement(2026) by UnderlyingContractMultiplier(436).

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptPayoutType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of valuation method or payout trigger for an in-the-money option.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptPayoutAmount
Field.Description: Cash amount indicating the pay out associated with an option. For binary options this is a fixed amount.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPriceQuoteMethod
Field.Description: Method for price quotation.

Field.Name: UnderlyingValuationMethod
Field.Description: Indicates type of valuation method used.

Field.Name: UnderlyingListMethod
Field.Description: Indicates whether the instruments are pre-listed only or can also be defined via user request.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCapPrice
Field.Description: Used to express the ceiling price of a capped call.

Field.Name: UnderlyingFloorPrice
Field.Description: Used to express the floor price of a capped put.

Field.Name: UnderlyingFlexibleIndicator
Field.Description: Used to indicate if a security has been defined as flexible according to "non-standard" means. Analog to CFICode Standard/Non-standard indicator.

Field.Name: UnderlyingFlexProductEligibilityIndicator
Field.Description: Used to indicate if a product or group of product supports the creation of flexible securities.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPositionLimit
Field.Description: Position limit for the instrument.

Field.Name: UnderlyingNTPositionLimit
Field.Description: Position Limit in the near-term contract for a given exchange-traded product.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPool
Field.Description: Identifies the mortgage backed security (MBS) / asset backed security (ABS) pool.

Field.Name: UnderlyingContractSettlMonth
Field.Description: Specifies when the contract (i.e. MBS/TBA) will settle. Must be present for MBS/TBA.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDatedDate
Field.Description: If different from IssueDate()

Field.Name: UnderlyingInterestAccrualDate
Field.Description: If different from IssueDate and DatedDate

Field.Name: UnderlyingShortSaleRestriction
Field.Description: Indicates whether a restriction applies to short selling a security.

Field.Name: UnderlyingRefTickTableID
Field.Description: Spread table code referred by the security or symbol.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingComplexEvents
Field.Description: Number of complex events in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of complex event.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexOptPayoutAmount
Field.Description: Cash amount indicating the pay out associated with an event. For binary options this is a fixed amount.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventPrice
Field.Description: Specifies the price at which the complex event takes effect. Impact of the event price is determined by the UnderlyingComplexEventType(2046).

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventPriceBoundaryMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the boundary condition to be used for the event price relative to the UnderlyingComplexEventPrice(2048) at the point the complex event outcome takes effect as determined by the UnderlyingComplexEventPriceTimeType(2051).

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventPriceBoundaryPrecision
Field.Description: Used in combination with UnderlyingComplexEventPriceBoundaryMethod(2049) to specify the percentage of the strike price in relation to the underlying price. The percentage is generally 100 or greater for puts and 100 or less for calls.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventPriceTimeType
Field.Description: Specifies when the complex event outcome takes effect. The outcome of a complex event is a payout or barrier action as specified by the UnderlyingComplexEventType(2046).

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventCondition
Field.Description:
Specifies the condition between complex events when more than one event is specified.
Multiple barrier events would use an "or" condition since only one can be effective at a given time. A set of digital range events would use an "and" condition since both conditions must be in effect for a payout to result.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingComplexEventDates
Field.Description: Number of underlying complex event dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventStartDate
Field.Description: The start date of the date range on which a complex event is effective. The start date will be set equal to the end date for single day events such as Bermuda options. The start date must always be less than or equal to end date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventEndDate
Field.Description: The end date of the date range on which a complex event is effective. The start date will be set equal to the end date for single day events such as Bermuda options. UnderlyingComplexEventEndDate(2056) must always be greater than or equal to UnderlyingComplexEventStartDate(2055).

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingComplexEventTimes
Field.Description: Number of complex event times in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventStartTime
Field.Description: The start time of the time range on which a complex event date is effective. UnderlyingComplexEventStartTime(2057) must always be less than or equal to UndelryingComplexEventEndTime(2058).

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventEndTime
Field.Description: The end time of the time range on which a complex event date is effective. UnderlyingComplexEventEndTime(2058) must always be greater than or equal to UnderlyingComplexEventStartTime(2057).

Field.Name: NoLegEvents
Field.Description: Number of events in the repeating group

Field.Name: LegEventType
Field.Description: Code to represent the type of event.

Field.Name: LegEventDate
Field.Description: The date of the event.

Field.Name: LegEventTime
Field.Description: Specific time of event. To be used in combination with LegEventDate(2061).

Field.Name: LegEventTimeUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the event.

Field.Name: LegEventTimePeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the event.

Field.Name: LegEventPx
Field.Description: Predetermined price of issue at event, if applicable.

Field.Name: LegEventText
Field.Description: Free form text to specify additional information or enumeration description when a standard value does not apply.

Field.Name: LegAssetClass
Field.Description: The broad asset category for assessing risk exposure.

Field.Name: LegAssetSubClass
Field.Description: The general subcategory description of the asset class.

Field.Name: LegAssetType
Field.Description: Used to provide more specific description of the asset specified in LegAssetSubClass(2068). See https://www.fixtrading.org/codelists/AssetType for code list of applicable values. ISO 4721 Currency Code values are to be used when specific currency as an asset type is to be expressed. Other values may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of MiFID II's this may indicate the value needed in ESMA RTS 2 Annex IV Table 2 Field 16, or ESMA RTS 23 Annex I Table 2 'Sub product' field.

Field.Name: LegSwapClass
Field.Description: Swap type.

Field.Name: UnderlyingEventText
Field.Description: Free form text to specify comments related to the event.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingEventTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingEventText(2073) field.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingEventText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingEventText(2071) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingEventText(2071) field.

Field.Name: EncodedLegEventTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedLegEventText(2075) field.

Field.Name: EncodedLegEventText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the LegEventText(2066) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the LegEventText(2066) field.

Field.Name: NoLegSecondaryAssetClasses
Field.Description: Number of secondary asset classes in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegSecondaryAssetClass
Field.Description: The broad asset category for assessing risk exposure for a multi-asset trade.

Field.Name: LegSecondaryAssetSubClass
Field.Description: An indication of the general description of the asset class.

Field.Name: LegSecondaryAssetType
Field.Description: Used to provide more specific description of the asset specified in LegSecondaryAssetSubClass(2078). See https://www.fixtrading.org/codelists/AssetType for code list of applicable values. ISO 4721 Currency Code values are to be used when specific currency as an asset type is to be expressed. Other values may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of MiFID II's this may indicate the value needed in ESMA RTS 2 Annex IV Table 2 Field 16, or ESMA RTS 23 Annex I Table 2 'Sub product' field.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingSecondaryAssetClasses
Field.Description: Number of secondary asset classes in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecondaryAssetClass
Field.Description: The broad asset category for assessing risk exposure for a multi-asset trade.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecondaryAssetSubClass
Field.Description: An indication of the general description of the asset class.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecondaryAssetType
Field.Description: Used to provide more specific description of the asset specified in UnderlyingSecondaryAssetSubClass(2082). See https://www.fixtrading.org/codelists/AssetType for code list of applicable values. ISO 4721 Currency Code values are to be used when specific currency as an asset type is to be expressed. Other values may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of MiFID II's this may indicate the value needed in ESMA RTS 2 Annex IV Table 2 Field 16, or ESMA RTS 23 Annex I Table 2 'Sub product' field.

Field.Name: NoAdditionalTermBondRefs
Field.Description: Number of bonds in the repeating group.

Field.Name: AdditionalTermBondSecurityID
Field.Description: Security identifier of the bond.

Field.Name: AdditionalTermBondSecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source scheme of the AdditionalTermBondSecurityID(40001) value.

Field.Name: AdditionalTermBondDesc
Field.Description: Description of the bond.

Field.Name: EncodedAdditionalTermBondDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedAdditionalTermBondDesc(40005) field.

Field.Name: EncodedAdditionalTermBondDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the AdditionalTermBondDesc(40003) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the AdditionalTermBondDesc(40003) field.

Field.Name: AdditionalTermBondCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency the bond value is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: AdditionalTermBondIssuer
Field.Description: Issuer of the bond.

Field.Name: EncodedAdditionalTermBondIssuerLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedAdditionalTermBondIssuer(40009) field.

Field.Name: EncodedAdditionalTermBondIssuer
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the AdditionalTermBondIssuer(40007) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the AdditionalTermBondIssuer(40007) field.

Field.Name: AdditionalTermBondSeniority
Field.Description: Specifies the bond's payment priority in the event of a default.

Field.Name: AdditionalTermBondCouponType
Field.Description: Coupon type of the bond.

Field.Name: AdditionalTermBondCouponRate
Field.Description: Coupon rate of the bond. See also CouponRate(223).

Field.Name: AdditionalTermBondMaturityDate
Field.Description: The maturity date of the bond.

Field.Name: AdditionalTermBondParValue
Field.Description: The par value of the bond.

Field.Name: AdditionalTermBondCurrentTotalIssuedAmount
Field.Description: Total issued amount of the bond.

Field.Name: AdditionalTermBondCouponFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of the bond's coupon payment.

Field.Name: AdditionalTermBondCouponFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the frequency of the bond's coupon payment.

Field.Name: AdditionalTermBondDayCount
Field.Description: The day count convention used in interest calculations for a bond or an interest bearing security.

Field.Name: NoAdditionalTerms
Field.Description: Number of additional terms in the repeating group.

Field.Name: AdditionalTermConditionPrecedentBondIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the condition precedent bond is applicable. The swap contract is only valid if the bond is issued and if there is any dispute over the terms of fixed stream then the bond terms would be used.

Field.Name: AdditionalTermDiscrepancyClauseIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the discrepancy clause is applicable.

Field.Name: NoCashSettlTerms
Field.Description: Number of elements in the repeating group.

Field.Name: CashSettlCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency the CashSettlAmount(40034) is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: CashSettlValuationFirstBusinessDayOffset
Field.Description: The number of business days after settlement conditions have been satisfied, when the calculation agent is to obtain a price quotation on the reference obligation for the purpose of cash settlement.
Field.Elaboration: Associated with ISDA 2003 Term: Valuation Date.

Field.Name: CashSettlValuationSubsequentBusinessDaysOffset
Field.Description: The number of business days between successive valuation dates when multiple valuation dates are applicable for cash settlement.
Field.Elaboration: Associated with ISDA 2003 Term: Valuation Date

Field.Name: CashSettlNumOfValuationDates
Field.Description: Where multiple valuation dates are specified as being applicable for cash settlement, this specifies the number of applicable valuation dates.
Field.Elaboration: Associated with ISDA 2003 Term: Valuation Date

Field.Name: CashSettlValuationTime
Field.Description: The time of valuation.

Field.Name: CashSettlBusinessCenter
Field.Description: Identifies the business center calendar used at valuation time for cash settlement purposes e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: CashSettlQuoteMethod
Field.Description: The type of quote used to determine the cash settlement price.

Field.Name: CashSettlQuoteAmount
Field.Description: When determining the cash settlement amount, if weighted average price quotes are to be obtained for the reference obligation, this is the upper limit to the outstanding principal balance of the reference obligation for which the quote should be obtained. If not specifed, the ISDA definitions provide for a fallback amount equal to floating rate payer calculation amount.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Quotation Amount.

Field.Name: CashSettlQuoteCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency the CashSettlQuoteAmount(40028) is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 Currency Code.

Field.Name: CashSettlMinimumQuoteAmount
Field.Description: When determining the cash settlement amount, if weighted average price quotes are to be obtained for the reference obligation, this is the minimum intended threshold amount of outstanding principal balance of the reference obligation for which the quote should be obtained. If not specified, the ISDA definitions provide for a fallback amount of the lower of either USD1,000,000 (or its equivalent in the relevent obligation currency) or the (minimum) quoted amount.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Minimum Quotation Amount.

Field.Name: CashSettlMinimumQuoteCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency the CashSettlMinimumQuoteAmount(40030) is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 Currency Code.

Field.Name: CashSettlDealer
Field.Description: Identifies the dealer from whom price quotations for the reference obligation are obtained for the purpose of cash settlement valuation calculation.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Dealer.

Field.Name: CashSettlBusinessDays
Field.Description: The number of business days used in the determination of the cash settlement payment date.
Field.Elaboration: If a cash settlement amount is specified, the cash settlement payment date will be this number of business days following the calculation of the final price. If a cash settlement amount is not specified, the cash settlement payment date will be this number of business days after all conditions to settlement are satisfied. ISDA 2003 Term: Cash Settlement Date.

Field.Name: CashSettlAmount
Field.Description: The amount paid between the trade parties, seller to the buyer, for cash settlement on the cash settlement date.
Field.Elaboration: If not specified this is not to be included in the message and the parties to the trade are expected to calculate the value. The value is the greater of (a) floating rate payer calculation amount x (reference price - final price) or (b) zero. Price values are all expressed as a percentage. ISDA 2003 Term: Cash Settlement Amount

Field.Name: CashSettlRecoveryFactor
Field.Description: Used for fixed recovery, this specifies the recovery level as determined at contract inception, to be applied in the event of a default. The factor is used to calculate the amount paid by the seller to the buyer for cash settlement on the cash settlement date. The amount calculated is (1 - CashSettlRecoveryFactor(40035)) x floating rate payer calculation amount. The currency is derived from the floating rate payer calculation amount.

Field.Name: CashSettlFixedTermIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether fixed settlement is applicable or not applicable in a recovery lock.

Field.Name: CashSettlAccruedInterestIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether accrued interest is included or not in the value provided in CashSettlAmount(40034). For cash settlement this specifies whether quotations should be obtained inclusive or not of accrued interest. For physical settlement this specifies whether the buyer should deliver the obligation with an outstanding principal balance that includes or excludes accrued interest.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Include/Exclude Accrued Interest.

Field.Name: CashSettlValuationMethod
Field.Description: The ISDA defined methodology for determining the final price of the reference obligation for purposes of cash settlement.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Valuation Method

Field.Name: CashSettlTermXID
Field.Description: A named string value referenced by UnderlyingSettlTermXIDRef(41315).

Field.Name: NoContractualDefinitions
Field.Description: Number of financing definitions in the repeating group.

Field.Name: ContractualDefinition
Field.Description: Specifies which contract definition, such as those published by ISDA, will apply for the terms of the trade. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/contractual-definitions for values.

Field.Name: NoContractualMatrices
Field.Description: Number of contractual matrices in the repeating group.

Field.Name: ContractualMatrixSource
Field.Description: Identifies the applicable contract matrix. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/matrix-type-1-0.xml for values.

Field.Name: ContractualMatrixDate
Field.Description: The publication date of the applicable version of the contract matrix. If not specified, the ISDA Standard Terms Supplement defines rules for which version of the matrix is applicable.

Field.Name: ContractualMatrixTerm
Field.Description: Specifies the applicable key into the relevent contract matrix. In the case of 2000 ISDA Definitions Settlement Matrix for Early Termination and Swaptions, the ContractualMatrixTerm(40045) is not applicable and is to be omitted. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/credit-matrix-transaction-type for values.

Field.Name: NoFinancingTermSupplements
Field.Description: Number of financing terms supplements in the repeating group.

Field.Name: FinancingTermSupplementDesc
Field.Description: Identifies the applicable contractual supplement. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/contractual-supplement for values.

Field.Name: FinancingTermSupplementDate
Field.Description: The publication date of the applicable version of the contractual supplement.

Field.Name: NoStreams
