Field.Description: Specifies the positive tolerance value. The value may be an absolute quantity or a percentage, as specified in DeliveryScheduleToleranceType(41046). Value may exceed agreed upon value. Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%).

Field.Name: DeliveryScheduleToleranceUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the tolerance value's unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: DeliveryScheduleToleranceType
Field.Description: Specifies the tolerance value type.

Field.Name: DeliveryScheduleSettlCountry
Field.Description: Specifies the country where delivery takes place. Uses ISO 3166 2-character country code.

Field.Name: DeliveryScheduleSettlTimeZone
Field.Description: Delivery timezone specified as "prevailing" rather than "standard" or "daylight". See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Prevailing_Timezones for code list of applicable prevailing timezones.

Field.Name: DeliveryScheduleSettlFlowType
Field.Description: Specifies the commodity delivery flow type.

Field.Name: DeliveryScheduleSettlHolidaysProcessingInstruction
Field.Description: Indicates whether holidays are included in the settlement periods. Required for electricity contracts.

Field.Name: NoDeliveryScheduleSettlDays
Field.Description: Number of delivery schedules in the repeating group.

Field.Name: DeliveryScheduleSettlDay
Field.Description: Specifies the day or group of days for delivery.

Field.Name: DeliveryScheduleSettlTotalHours
Field.Description: The sum of the total hours specified in the DeliveryScheduleSettlTimeGrp component.

Field.Name: NoDeliveryScheduleSettlTimes
Field.Description: Number of hour ranges in the repeating group.

Field.Name: DeliveryScheduleSettlStart
Field.Description: The scheduled start time for the delivery of the commodity where delivery occurs over specified times. The format of the time value is specified in DeliveryScheduleSettlTimeType(41057).

Field.Name: DeliveryScheduleSettlEnd
Field.Description: The scheduled end time for the delivery of the commodity where delivery occurs over specified times. The format of the time value is specified in DeliveryScheduleSettlTimeType(41057).

Field.Name: DeliveryScheduleSettlTimeType
Field.Description: Specifies the format of the delivery start and end time values.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of delivery stream.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamPipeline
Field.Description: The name of the oil delivery pipeline.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamEntryPoint
Field.Description: The point at which the commodity will enter the delivery mechanism or pipeline.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamWithdrawalPoint
Field.Description: The point at which the commodity product will be withdrawn prior to delivery.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamDeliveryPoint
Field.Description: The point at which the commodity product will be delivered and received. Value specified should follow market convention appropriate for the commodity product. For bullion, see http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/bullion-delivery-location for values.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamDeliveryRestriction
Field.Description: Specifies under what conditions the buyer and seller should be excused of their delivery obligations.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamDeliveryContingency
Field.Description: Specifies the electricity delivery contingency. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/electricity-transmission-contingency for values.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamDeliveryContingentPartySide
Field.Description: The trade side value of the party responsible for electricity delivery contingency.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamDeliverAtSourceIndicator
Field.Description: When this element is specified and set to 'Y', delivery of the coal product is to be at its source.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamRiskApportionment
Field.Description: Specifies how the parties to the trade apportion responsibility for the delivery of the commodity product. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Risk_Apportionment for the details of the external code list.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamRiskApportionmentSource
Field.Description: Specifies the source or legal framework for the risk apportionment. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Risk_Apportionment_Source for the details of the external code list.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamTitleTransferLocation
Field.Description: Specifies the title transfer location.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamTitleTransferCondition
Field.Description: Specifies the condition of title transfer.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamImporterOfRecord
Field.Description: A party, not necessarily of the trade, who is the Importer of Record for the purposes of paying customs duties and applicable taxes or costs related to importation.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamNegativeTolerance
Field.Description: Specifies the negative tolerance value. The value may be an absolute quantity or a percentage, as specified in DeliveryStreamToleranceType(41074). Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%).

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamPositiveTolerance
Field.Description: Specifies the positive tolerance value. The value may be an absolute quantity or a percentage, as specified in DeliveryStreamToleranceType(41074). Value may exceed agreed upon value. Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%).

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamToleranceUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the tolerance value's unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamToleranceType
Field.Description: Specifies the tolerance value type.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamToleranceOptionSide
Field.Description: Indicates whether the tolerance is at the seller's or buyer's option.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamTotalPositiveTolerance
Field.Description: The positive percent tolerance which applies to the total quantity delivered over all shipment periods. Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%.).

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamTotalNegativeTolerance
Field.Description: The negative percent tolerance which applies to the total quantity delivered over all shipment periods. Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%.).

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamNotionalConversionFactor
Field.Description: If the notional quantity is specified in a unit that does not match the unit in which the commodity reference price is quoted, the scaling or conversion factor used to convert the commodity reference price unit into the notional quantity unit should be stated here. If there is no conversion, this field is not intended to be used.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamTransportEquipment
Field.Description: The transportation equipment with which the commodity product will be delivered and received.
Field.Elaboration: Examples of transportation equipment or mode are barge, truck, railcar, etc.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamElectingPartySide
Field.Description: A reference to the party able to choose whether the gas is delivered for a particular period as found in a swing or interruptible contract.

Field.Name: NoDeliveryStreamCycles
Field.Description: Number of delivery cycles in the repeating group.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamCycleDesc
Field.Description: The delivery cycles during which the oil product will be transported in the pipeline.

Field.Name: EncodedDeliveryStreamCycleDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedDeliveryStreamCycleDesc(41084) field.

Field.Name: EncodedDeliveryStreamCycleDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the DeliveryStreamCycleDesc(41082) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the DeliveryStreamCycleDesc(41082) field.

Field.Name: NoDeliveryStreamCommoditySources
Field.Description: Number of commodity sources in the repeating group.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamCommoditySource
Field.Description: The SCoTA coal cargo origin, mining region, mine(s), mining complex(es), loadout(s) or river dock(s) or other point(s) of origin that seller and buyer agree are acceptable origins for the coal product. For international coal transactions, this is the origin of the coal product. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-coal-product-source for values.

Field.Name: DocumentationText
Field.Description: A sentence or phrase pertenant to the trade, not a reference to an external document. E.g. "To be registered with the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency, Acid Rain Division, SO2 Allowance Tracking System"

Field.Name: EncodedDocumentationTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedDocumentationText(1527) field.

Field.Name: EncodedDocumentationText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the DocumentationText(1513) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the DocumentationText(1513) field.

Field.Name: SwapSubClass
Field.Description: The sub-classification or notional schedule type of the swap.

Field.Name: SettlRateIndex
Field.Description: In an outright or forward commodity trade that is cash settled this is the index used to determine the cash payment.

Field.Name: SettlRateIndexLocation
Field.Description: This is an optional qualifying attribute of SettlRateIndex(1577) such as the delivery zone for an electricity contract.

Field.Name: OptionExpirationDesc
Field.Description: Description of the option expiration.

Field.Name: EncodedOptionExpirationDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedOptionExpirationDesc(1697) field.

Field.Name: EncodedOptionExpirationDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the OptionExpirationDesc(1581) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the OptionExpirationDesc(1581).

Field.Name: StrikeUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Used to express the unit of measure (UOM) of the price if different from the contract.

Field.Name: StrikeIndex
Field.Description: Specifies the index used to calculate the strike price.

Field.Name: StrikeIndexSpread
Field.Description: Specifies the strike price offset from the named index.

Field.Name: ValuationSource
Field.Description: Specifies the source of trade valuation data.

Field.Name: ValuationReferenceModel
Field.Description: Specifies the methodology and/or assumptions used to generate the trade value.

Field.Name: StrategyType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of trade strategy.

Field.Name: CommonPricingIndicator
Field.Description: When this element is specified and set to 'Y', it indicates that common pricing applies. Common pricing may be relevant for a transaction that references more than one commodity reference price.

Field.Name: SettlDisruptionProvision
Field.Description: Specifies the consequences of bullion settlement disruption events.

Field.Name: InstrumentRoundingDirection
Field.Description: Specifies the rounding direction if not overridden elsewhere.

Field.Name: InstrumentRoundingPrecision
Field.Description: Specifies the rounding precision in terms of a number of decimal places. Note how a percentage rate rounding of 5 decimal places is expressed as a rounding precision of 7.

Field.Name: LegSettleOnOpenFlag
Field.Description: Indicator to determine if the instrument is to settle on open.

Field.Name: LegInstrmtAssignmentMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the method under which assignment was conducted.

Field.Name: LegSecurityStatus
Field.Description: Used for derivatives. Denotes the current state of the InstrumentLeg.

Field.Name: LegRestructuringType
Field.Description: A category of CDS credit event in which the underlying bond experiences a restructuring. Used to define a CDS instrument.

Field.Name: LegSeniority
Field.Description: Specifies which issue (underlying bond) will receive payment priority in the event of a default. Used to define a CDS instrument.

Field.Name: LegNotionalPercentageOutstanding
Field.Description: Indicates the notional percentage of the deal that is still outstanding based on the remaining components of the index. Used to calculate the true value of a CDS trade or position.

Field.Name: LegOriginalNotionalPercentageOutstanding
Field.Description: Used to reflect the Original value prior to the application of a credit event. See LegNotionalPercentageOutstanding(2151).

Field.Name: LegAttachmentPoint
Field.Description: Lower bound percentage of the loss that the tranche can endure.

Field.Name: LegDetachmentPoint
Field.Description: Upper bound percentage of the loss the tranche can endure.

Field.Name: LegObligationType
Field.Description: Type of reference obligation for credit derivatives contracts.

Field.Name: LegSwapSubClass
Field.Description: The sub-classification or notional schedule type of the swap.

Field.Name: LegNthToDefault
Field.Description: The Nth reference obligation in a CDS reference basket. If specified without LegMthToDefault(2158) the default will trigger a CDS payout. If LegMthToDefault(2158) is also present then payout occurs between the Nth and Mth obligations to default.

Field.Name: LegMthToDefault
Field.Description: The Mth reference obligation to default in a CDS reference basket. When an NthToDefault(2157) to MthToDefault(2158) are represented then the CDS payout occurs between the Nth and Mth obligations to default.

Field.Name: LegSettledEntityMatrixSource
Field.Description: Relevant settled entity matrix source.

Field.Name: LegSettledEntityMatrixPublicationDate
Field.Description: The publication date of the applicable version of the matrix. When this element is omitted, the Standard Terms Supplement defines rules for which version of the matrix is applicable.

Field.Name: LegCouponType
Field.Description: Specifies the coupon type of the bond.

Field.Name: LegTotalIssuedAmount
Field.Description: Specifies the total amount of the issue. Corresponds to the par value multiplied by the number of issued security.

Field.Name: LegCouponFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of the bond's coupon payment.

Field.Name: LegCouponFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the frequency of the bond's coupon payment.

Field.Name: LegCouponDayCount
Field.Description: The day count convention used in interest calculations for a bond or an interest bearing security.

Field.Name: LegConvertibleBondEquityID
Field.Description: Identifies the equity in which a convertible bond can be converted to.

Field.Name: LegConvertibleBondEquityIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies class or source of the LegConvertibleBondEquitySecurityID(2166) value.

Field.Name: LegContractPriceRefMonth
Field.Description: Reference month if there is no applicable LegMaturityMonthYear(610) value for the contract or security.

Field.Name: LegLienSeniority
Field.Description: Indicates the seniority level of the lien in a loan.

Field.Name: LegLoanFacility
Field.Description: Specifies the type of loan when the credit default swap's reference obligation is a loan.

Field.Name: LegReferenceEntityType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of reference entity for first-to-default CDS basket contracts.

Field.Name: LegIndexSeries
Field.Description: The series identifier of a credit default swap index.

Field.Name: LegIndexAnnexVersion
Field.Description: The version of a credit default swap index annex.

Field.Name: LegIndexAnnexDate
Field.Description: The date of a credit default swap index series annex.

Field.Name: LegIndexAnnexSource
Field.Description: The source of a credit default swap series annex.

Field.Name: LegSettlRateIndex
Field.Description: In an outright or forward commodity trade that is cash settled this is the index used to determine the cash payment.

Field.Name: LegSettlRateIndexLocation
Field.Description: This is an optional qualifying attribute of LegSettlementRateIndex(2176) such as the delivery zone for an electricity contract.

Field.Name: LegOptionExpirationDesc
Field.Description: Description of the option expiration.

Field.Name: EncodedLegOptionExpirationDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedLegOptionExpirationDesc(2180) field.

Field.Name: EncodedLegOptionExpirationDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the LegOptionExpirationDesc(2178) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the LegOptionExpirationDesc(2178).

Field.Name: LegStrikeMultiplier
Field.Description: Used for derivatives. Multiplier applied to the strike price for the purpose of calculating the settlement value.

Field.Name: LegStrikeValue
Field.Description: The number of shares/units for the financial instrument involved in the option trade. Used for derivatives.

Field.Name: LegStrikeUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Used to express the unit of measure (UOM) of the price if different from the contract.

Field.Name: LegStrikeIndex
Field.Description: Specifies the index used to calculate the strike price.

Field.Name: LegStrikeIndexSpread
Field.Description: Specifies the strike price offset from the named index.

Field.Name: LegStrikePriceDeterminationMethod
Field.Description: Specifies how the strike price is determined at the point of option exercise. The strike may be fixed throughout the life of the option, set at expiration to the value of the underlying, set to the average value of the underlying , or set to the optimal value of the underlying.

Field.Name: LegStrikePriceBoundaryMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the boundary condition to be used for the strike price relative to the underlying price at the point of option exercise.

Field.Name: LegStrikePriceBoundaryPrecision
Field.Description: Used in combination with StrikePriceBoundaryMethod(2187) to specify the percentage of the strike price in relation to the underlying price. The percentage is generally 100 or greater for puts and 100 or less for calls.

Field.Name: LegUnderlyingPriceDeterminationMethod
Field.Description: Specifies how the underlying price is determined at the point of option exercise. The underlying price may be set to the current settlement price, set to a special reference, set to the optimal value of the underlying during the defined period ("Look-back") or set to the average value of the underlying during the defined period ("Asian option").

Field.Name: LegMinPriceIncrement
Field.Description: Minimum price increment for a given exchange-traded instrument. Could also be used to represent tick value.

Field.Name: LegMinPriceIncrementAmount
Field.Description: Minimum price increment amount associated with the LegMinPriceIncrement(2190). For listed derivatives, the value can be calculated by multiplying LegMinPriceIncrement(2190) by LegContractMultiplier(614).

Field.Name: LegSettlMethod
Field.Description: Settlement method for a contract or instrument. Additional values may be used with bilateral agreement.

Field.Name: LegOptPayoutType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of valuation method or trigger payout for an in-the-money option.

Field.Name: LegOptPayoutAmount
Field.Description: Cash amount indicating the pay out associated with an option. For binary options this is a fixed amount.

Field.Name: LegPriceQuoteMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the method for price quotation.

Field.Name: LegValuationMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the type of valuation method applied.

Field.Name: LegValuationSource
Field.Description: Specifies the source of trade valuation data.

Field.Name: LegValuationReferenceModel
Field.Description: Specifies the methodology and/or assumptions used to generate the trade value.

Field.Name: LegListMethod
Field.Description: Indicates whether instruments are pre-listed only or can also be defined via user request.

Field.Name: LegCapPrice
Field.Description: Used to express the ceiling price of a capped call.

Field.Name: LegFloorPrice
Field.Description: Used to express the floor price of a capped put.

Field.Name: LegFlexibleIndicator
Field.Description: Used to indicate a derivatives security that can be defined using flexible terms. The terms commonly permitted to be defined by market participants are expiration date and strike price. FlexibleIndicator is an alternative to LegCFICode(608) Standard/Non-standard attribute.

Field.Name: LegFlexProductEligibilityIndicator
Field.Description: Used to indicate if a product or group of product supports the creation of flexible securities.

Field.Name: LegPositionLimit
Field.Description: Position Limit for a given exchange-traded product.

Field.Name: LegNTPositionLimit
Field.Description: Position limit in the near-term contract for a given exchange-traded product.

Field.Name: LegCPProgram
Field.Description: The program under which a commercial paper is issued.

Field.Name: LegCPRegType
Field.Description: The registration type of a commercial paper issuance.

Field.Name: LegShortSaleRestriction
Field.Description: Indicates whether a restriction applies to short selling a security.

Field.Name: LegStrategyType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of trade strategy.

Field.Name: LegCommonPricingIndicator
Field.Description: When this element is specified and set to 'Y', it indicates that common pricing applies. Common pricing may be relevant for a transaction that references more than one commodity reference price.

Field.Name: LegSettlDisruptionProvision
Field.Description: Specifies the consequences of bullion settlement disruption events.

Field.Name: LegInstrumentRoundingDirection
Field.Description: Specifies the rounding direction if not overridden elsewhere.
Field.Elaboration: Applicable for complex FX option strategies.

Field.Name: LegInstrumentRoundingPrecision
Field.Description: Specifies the rounding precision in terms of a number of decimal places. Note how a percentage rate rounding of 5 decimal places is expressed as a rounding precision of 7.

Field.Name: MarketDisruptionProvision
Field.Description: The consequences of market disruption events.

Field.Name: MarketDisruptionFallbackProvision
Field.Description: Specifies the location of the fallback provision documentation.

Field.Name: MarketDisruptionMaximumDays
Field.Description: Specifies the maximum number of market disruption days (commodity or bullion business days) in a contract or confirmation. If none are specified, the maximum number of market disruption days is five (5).
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2005 Commodity Definition.

Field.Name: MarketDisruptionMaterialityPercentage
Field.Description: Used when a price materiality percentage applies to the price source disruption event and this event has been specified.
Field.Elaboration: Applicable to 2005 Commodity Definitions only.

Field.Name: MarketDisruptionMinimumFuturesContracts
Field.Description: Specifies the minimum futures contracts level that dictates whether or not a 'De Minimis Trading' event has occurred.
Field.Elaboration: Applicable to 1993 Commodity Definitions only.

Field.Name: NoMarketDisruptionEvents
Field.Description: Number of disruption events in the repeating group.

Field.Name: MarketDisruptionEvent
Field.Description: Specifies the market disruption event. For commodities see http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-market-disruption for values. For foreign exchange, see http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Market_Disruption_Event for code list of applicable event types.

Field.Name: NoMarketDisruptionFallbacks
Field.Description: Number of fallbacks in the repeating group.

Field.Name: MarketDisruptionFallbackType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of disruption fallback. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-market-disruption-fallback for values.

Field.Name: NoMarketDisruptionFallbackReferencePrices
Field.Description: Number of fallback reference securities in the repeating group.

Field.Name: MarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierType
Field.Description: The type of reference price underlier.

Field.Name: MarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityID
Field.Description: Specifies the identifier value of the security.

Field.Name: MarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Specifies the class or source scheme of the security identifier.

Field.Name: MarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDesc
Field.Description: Specifies the description of the underlying security.

Field.Name: EncodedMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDesc(41102) field.

Field.Name: EncodedMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the MarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDesc(41100) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the MarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDesc(41100) field.

Field.Name: MarketDisruptionFallbackOpenUnits
Field.Description: If there are multiple underlying assets, this specifies the number of units (index or securities) that constitute the underlier of the swap. In the case of a basket swap, this is used to reference both the number of basket units, and the number of each asset components of the basket when these are expressed in absolute terms.

Field.Name: MarketDisruptionFallbackBasketCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency if the underlier is a basket. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: MarketDisruptionFallbackBasketDivisor
Field.Description: Specifies the basket divisor amount. This value is normally used to adjust the constituent weight for pricing or to adjust for dividends, or other corporate actions.

Field.Name: MiscFeeRate
Field.Description: The fee rate when MiscFeeAmt(137) is a percentage of trade quantity.

Field.Name: MiscFeeAmountDue
Field.Description: The fee amount due if different from MiscFeeAmt(137).

Field.Name: ExerciseDesc
Field.Description: A description of the option exercise.

Field.Name: EncodedExerciseDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedExerciseDesc(41102) field.

Field.Name: EncodedExerciseDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ExerciseDesc(41106) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ExerciseDesc(41106) field.

Field.Name: AutomaticExerciseIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates (when 'Y') that exercise is automatic when the strike price is crossed or the underlying trade is in the money.

Field.Name: AutomaticExerciseThresholdRate
Field.Description: The threshold rate for triggering automatic exercise.

Field.Name: ExerciseConfirmationMethod
Field.Description: Indicates whether follow-up confirmation of exercise (written or electronic) is required following telephonic notice by the buyer to the seller or seller's agent.

Field.Name: ManualNoticeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: Identifies the business center used for adjusting the time for manual exercise notice. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: FallbackExerciseIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the notional amount of the underlying swap, not previously exercised under the option, will be automatically exercised at the expiration time on the expiration date if at such time the buyer is in-the-money, provided that the difference between the settlement rate and the fixed rate under the relevant underlying swap is not less than one tenth of a percentage point (0.10% or 0.001).

Field.Name: LimitedRightToConfirmIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the Seller may request the Buyer to confirm its intent to exercise if not done on or before the expiration time on the expiration date. If true ("Y") specific rules will apply in relation to the settlement mode.

Field.Name: ExerciseSplitTicketIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates in physical settlement of bond and convertible bond options whether the party required to deliver the bonds will divide those to be delivered as notifying party desires to facilitate delivery obligations.

Field.Name: NoOptionExerciseBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the option exercise dates, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the option exercise dates. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the DateAdjustment component within the Instrument component.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseEarliestDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative earliest option exercise date offset.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseEarliestDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative earliest exercise date offset.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseEarliestDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative earliest exercise date offset.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of exercise dates.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the frequency of exercise dates.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseStartDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted start date for calculating periodic exercise dates.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseStartDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the option exercise start date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseStartDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative exercise start date offset.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseStartDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative exercise start date offset.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseStartDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative option exercise start date offset.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseStartDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted start date for calculating periodic exercise dates.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseSkip
Field.Description: The number of periods in the referenced date schedule that are between each date in the relative date schedule. Thus a skip of 2 would mean that dates are relative to every second date in the referenced schedule. If present this should have a value greater than 1.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseNominationDeadline
Field.Description: Last date (adjusted) for establishing the option exercise terms.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseFirstDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted first exercise date.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseLastDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted last exercise date.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseEarliestTime
Field.Description: The earliest time at which notice of exercise can be given by the buyer to the seller (or seller's agent) (i) on the expriation date, in the case of a European style option, (ii) on each Bermuda option exercise date and the expiration date, in the case of a Bermuda style option, (iii) the commencement date to, and including, the expiration date, in the case of an American option.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseLatestTime
Field.Description: The latest exercise time. See also OptionExerciseEarliestTime(41134).

Field.Name: OptionExerciseTimeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center used to determine the locale for option exercise time, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values

Field.Name: NoOptionExerciseDates
Field.Description: Number of dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseDate
Field.Description: The option exercise fixed date, unadjusted or adjusted depending on OptionExerciseDateType(41139).

Field.Name: OptionExerciseDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of date. When specified it applies not only to the current date but to all subsequent dates in the group until overridden with a new type.

Field.Name: NoOptionExerciseExpirationDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseExpirationDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the option exercise expiration dates, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseExpirationDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the option exercise expiration dates. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the DateAdjustment component within the Instrument component.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseExpirationDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the option exercise expiration date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseExpirationDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative exercise expiration date offset.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseExpirationDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative exercise expiration date offset.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseExpirationFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of exercise expiration dates.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseExpirationFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the frequency of exercise expiration dates.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseExpirationRollConvention
Field.Description: The convention for determining the sequence of exercise expiration dates. It is used in conjunction with a specified frequency. Used only to override the roll convention defined in the DateAdjustment component in Instrument.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseExpirationDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative option exercise expiration date offset.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseExpirationTime
Field.Description: The option exercise expiration time.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseExpirationTimeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center used to determine the locale for option exercise expiration time, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoOptionExerciseExpirationDates
Field.Description: Number of fixed exercise expiration dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseExpirationDate
Field.Description: An adjusted or unadjusted fixed option exercise expiration date.

Field.Name: OptionExerciseExpirationDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of option exercise expiration date. When specified it applies not only to the current date but to all subsequent dates in the group until overridden with a new type.

Field.Name: PaymentUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Used to express the unit of measure (UOM) of the payment amount if not in the currency of the trade.

Field.Name: PaymentDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the payment date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: PaymentDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative payment date offset.

Field.Name: PaymentDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative payment date offset.

Field.Name: PaymentDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative payment date offset.

Field.Name: PaymentForwardStartType
Field.Description: Forward start premium type.

Field.Name: NoPaymentScheduleFixingDays
Field.Description: Number of fixing days in the repeating group.

Field.Name: PaymentScheduleFixingDayOfWeek
Field.Description: The day of the week on which fixing will take place.

Field.Name: PaymentScheduleFixingDayNumber
Field.Description: The occurrence of the day of week on which fixing takes place.
Field.Elaboration: For example, a fixing of the 3rd Friday would be DayOfWk=5 DayNum=3. If omitted every day of the week is a fixing day.

Field.Name: PaymentScheduleXID
Field.Description: Identifier of this PaymentSchedule for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: PaymentScheduleXIDRef
Field.Description: Reference to payment schedule elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: PaymentScheduleRateCurrency
Field.Description: The currency of the schedule rate. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: PaymentScheduleRateUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The schedule rate unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: PaymentScheduleRateConversionFactor
Field.Description: The number to be multiplied by the derived floating rate of the payment schedule in order to arrive at the payment rate. If omitted, the schedule rate conversion factor is 1.

Field.Name: PaymentScheduleRateSpreadType
Field.Description: Identifies whether the rate spread is an absolute value to be added to the index rate or a percentage of the index rate.

Field.Name: PaymentScheduleSettlPeriodPrice
Field.Description: The schedule settlement period price.

Field.Name: PaymentScheduleSettlPeriodPriceCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of the schedule settlement period price. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: PaymentScheduleSettlPeriodPriceUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The settlement period price unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: PaymentScheduleStepUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The schedule step unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: PaymentScheduleFixingDayDistribution
Field.Description: The distribution of fixing days.

Field.Name: PaymentScheduleFixingDayCount
Field.Description: The number of days over which fixing should take place.

Field.Name: PaymentScheduleFixingLagPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the fixing lag duration.

Field.Name: PaymentScheduleFixingLagUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the fixing lag duration.

Field.Name: PaymentScheduleFixingFirstObservationDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative first observation date offset.
Field.Elaboration: If the first observation offset is specified, the observation period will start the specified interval prior to each calculation period - i.e. if the first observation offset is 4 months and the lag duration is 3 months, observations will be taken in months 4, 3 and 2 (but not 1) prior to each calculation period. If no first observation offset is specified, the observation period will end immediately preceding each calculation period.

Field.Name: PaymentScheduleFixingFirstObservationDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative first observation date offset.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamFlatRateIndicator
Field.Description: When this element is specified and set to 'Y', the Flat Rate is the New Worldwide Tanker Nominal Freight Scale for the Freight Index Route taken at the Trade Date of the transaction Fixed. If 'N' it is taken on each Pricing Date Floating.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamFlatRateAmount
Field.Description: Specifies the actual monetary value of the flat rate when PaymentStreamFlatRateIndicator(41180) = 'Y'.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamFlatRateCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of the actual flat rate. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamMaximumPaymentAmount
Field.Description: Specifies the limit on the total payment amount.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamMaximumPaymentCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of total payment amount limit. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamMaximumTransactionAmount
Field.Description: Specifies the limit on the payment amount that goes out in any particular calculation period.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamMaximumTransactionCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of the period payment amount limit. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamFixedAmountUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the fixed payment amount unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: PaymentStreamTotalFixedAmount
Field.Description: Specifies the total fixed payment amount.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamWorldScaleRate
Field.Description: The number of Worldscale points for purposes of the calculation of a fixed amount for a wet voyage charter commodity swap.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamContractPrice
Field.Description: The price per relevant unit for purposes of the calculation of a fixed amount for a dry voyage charter or time charter commodity swap.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamContractPriceCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of PaymentStreamContractPrice(41190). Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: NoPaymentStreamPricingBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamPricingBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the payment stream's pricing dates, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamRateIndex2CurvePeriod
Field.Description: Secondary time unit multiplier for the payment stream's floating rate index curve.
Field.Elaboration: May be used for a Forward Rate Agreement (FRA) with an average rate between two curve points.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamRateIndex2CurveUnit
Field.Description: Secondary time unit associated with the payment stream's floating rate index curve.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamRateIndexLocation
Field.Description: Specifies the location of the floating rate index.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamRateIndexLevel
Field.Description: This is the weather Cooling Degree Days (CDD), Heating Degree Days (HDD) or HDD index level specified as the number of (amount of) weather index units specified by the parties in the related confirmation.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamRateIndexUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The unit of measure (UOM) of the rate index level.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamSettlLevel
Field.Description: Specifies how weather index units are to be calculated.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamReferenceLevel
Field.Description: This is the weather Cooling Degree Days (CDD), Heating Degree Days (HDD) or HDD reference level specified as the number of (amount of) weather index units specified by the parties in the related confirmation.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamReferenceLevelUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The unit of measure (UOM) of the rate reference level.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamReferenceLevelEqualsZeroIndicator
Field.Description: When set to 'Y', it indicates the weather reference level equals zero.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamRateSpreadCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of the floating rate spread. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamRateSpreadUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Species the unit of measure (UOM) of the floating rate spread.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamRateConversionFactor
Field.Description: The number to be multiplied by the derived floating rate of the payment stream in order to arrive at the payment rate. If omitted, the floating rate conversion factor is 1.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamRateSpreadType
Field.Description: Identifies whether the rate spread is an absolute value to be added to the index rate or a percentage of the index rate.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamLastResetRate
Field.Description: The floating rate determined at the most recent reset. The rate is expressed in decimal form, e.g. 5% is represented as 0.05.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamFinalRate
Field.Description: The floating rate determined at the final reset. The rate is expressed in decimal form, e.g. 5% is represented as 0.05.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamCalculationLagPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the calculation lag duration.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamCalculationLagUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the calculation lag duration.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamFirstObservationDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative first observation date offset.
Field.Elaboration: If the first observation offset is specified, the observation period will start the specified interval prior to each calculation period - i.e. if the first observation offset is 4 months and the lag duration is 3 months, observations will be taken in months 4, 3 and 2 (but not 1) prior to each calculation period. If no first observation offset is specified, the observation period will end immediately preceding each calculation period.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamFirstObservationDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative first observation date offset.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamPricingDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the commodity pricing day type.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamPricingDayDistribution
Field.Description: The distribution of pricing days.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamPricingDayCount
Field.Description: The number of days over which pricing should take place.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamPricingBusinessCalendar
Field.Description: Specifies the business calendar to use for pricing. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-business-calendar for values.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamPricingBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the payent stream's pricing dates. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the DateAdjustment component within the Instrument component.

Field.Name: NoPaymentStreamPaymentDates
Field.Description: Number of payment dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamPaymentDate
Field.Description: The adjusted or unadjusted fixed stream payment date.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamPaymentDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of payment date. When specified it applies not only to the current date but to all subsequent dates in the group until overridden with a new type.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamMasterAgreementPaymentDatesIndicator
Field.Description: When set to 'Y', it indicates that payment dates are specified in the relevant master agreement.

Field.Name: NoPaymentStreamPricingDates
Field.Description: Number of pricing dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamPricingDate
Field.Description: The adjusted or unadjusted fixed stream pricing date.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamPricingDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of pricing date. When specified it applies not only to the current date but to all subsequent dates in the group until overridden with a new type.

Field.Name: NoPaymentStreamPricingDays
Field.Description: Number of pricing days in the repeating group.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamPricingDayOfWeek
Field.Description: The day of the week on which pricing takes place.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamPricingDayNumber
Field.Description: The occurrence of the day of week on which pricing takes place.
Field.Elaboration: For example a pricing day of the 3rd Friday would be DayOfWk=5 DayNum=3.

Field.Name: NoPricingDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: PricingDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust pricing or fixing dates, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: PricingDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted pricing or fixing date.

Field.Name: PricingDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust pricing or fixing dates. Used only to override the business day convention defined in the DateAdjustment component within the Instrument component.

Field.Name: PricingDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted pricing or fixing date.

Field.Name: PricingTime
Field.Description: Specifies the local market time of the pricing or fixing.

Field.Name: PricingTimeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: Specifies the business center for determining the pricing or fixing time. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoStreamAssetAttributes
Field.Description: Number of asset attribute entries in the group.

Field.Name: StreamAssetAttributeType
Field.Description: Specifies the name of the attribute. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Asset_Attribute_Types for code list of applicable asset attribute types.

Field.Name: StreamAssetAttributeValue
Field.Description: Specifies the value of the attribute.

Field.Name: StreamAssetAttributeLimit
Field.Description: Limit or lower acceptable value of the attribute.

Field.Name: NoStreamCalculationPeriodDates
Field.Description: Number of calculation period dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: StreamCalculationPeriodDate
Field.Description: The adjusted or unadjusted fixed calculation period date.

Field.Name: StreamCalculationPeriodDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of fixed calculation period date. When specified it applies not only to the current date but to all subsequent dates in the group until overridden with a new type.

Field.Name: StreamCalculationPeriodDatesXID
Field.Description: Identifier of this calculation period for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: StreamCalculationPeriodDatesXIDRef
Field.Description: Cross reference to another calculation period for duplicating its properties.

Field.Name: StreamCalculationBalanceOfFirstPeriod
Field.Description: When specified and set to 'Y', it indicates that the first calculation period should run from the effective date to the end of the calendar period in which the effective date falls (e.g. Jan 15 - Jan 31 if the calculation periods are one month long and effective date is Jan 15.). If 'N' or not specified, it indicates that the first calculation period should run from the effective date for one whole period (e.g. Jan 15 to Feb 14 if the calculation periods are one month long and the effective date is Jan 15.).

Field.Name: StreamCalculationCorrectionPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the length of time after the publication of the data when corrections can be made.

Field.Name: StreamCalculationCorrectionUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the length of time after the publication of the data when corrections can be made.

Field.Name: NoStreamCommoditySettlBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the commodity delivery date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityBase
Field.Description: Specifies the general base type of the commodity traded. Where possible, this should follow the naming convention used in the 2005 ISDA Commodity Definitions.
Field.Elaboration: Examples of general commodity base types include: Metal, Bullion, Oil, Natural Gas, Coal, Electricity, Inter-Energy, Grains, Oils Seeds, Dairy, Livestock, Forestry, Softs, Weather, Emissions.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of commodity product. For coal see http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-coal-product-type for values. For metals see http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-metal-product-type for values. For bullion see http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Bullion_Types for the external code list of bullion types.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySecurityID
Field.Description: Specifies the market identifier for the commodity.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the class or source of the StreamCommoditySecurityIDSource(41253) value.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityDesc
Field.Description: Description of the commodity asset.

Field.Name: EncodedStreamCommodityDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedStreamCommodityDesc(41257) field.

Field.Name: EncodedStreamCommodityDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the StreamCommodityDesc(41255) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the StreamCommodityDesc(41255) field.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The unit of measure (UOM) of the commodity asset.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityCurrency
Field.Description: Identifies the currency of the commodity asset. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityExchange
Field.Description: Identifies the exchange where the commodity is traded.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityRateSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source of rate information used for commodities. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Commodity_Rate_Source for code list of applicable sources.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityRateReferencePage
Field.Description: Identifies the reference "page" from the rate source.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityRateReferencePageHeading
Field.Description: Identifies the page heading from the rate source.

Field.Name: StreamDataProvider
Field.Description: Specifies the commodity data or information provider. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-information-provider for values.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityPricingType
Field.Description: Specifies how the pricing or rate setting of the trade is to be determined or based upon. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Commodity_Rate_Pricing_Type for code list of applicable commodity pricing types.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityNearbySettlDayPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the nearby settlement day.
Field.Elaboration: When the commodity transaction references a futures contract, the delivery or settlement dates are a nearby month or week. For example, for eighth nearby month use Period=8 and Unit=Mo.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityNearbySettlDayUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the nearby settlement day.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted commodity delivery date.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the commodity delivery date. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the DateAdjustment component within the Instrument component.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted commodity delivery date.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlMonth
Field.Description: Specifies a fixed single month for commodity delivery.
Field.Elaboration: Use "1" for January, "2" for February, etc.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlDateRollPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the commodity delivery date roll.
Field.Elaboration: For a commodity transaction that references a listed future via the delivery dates, this is the day offset on which the specified future will roll to the next nearby month when the referenced future expires.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlDateRollUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the commodity delivery date roll.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the commodity delivery roll day type.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityXID
Field.Description: Identifier of this stream commodity for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityXIDRef
Field.Description: Reference to a stream commodity elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: NoStreamCommodityAltIDs
Field.Description: Number of alternate security identifers.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityAltID
Field.Description: Alternate security identifier value for the commodity.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityAltIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the class or source of the alternate commodity security identifier.

Field.Name: NoStreamCommodityDataSources
Field.Description: Number of data sources in the repeating group. The order of entry determines priority first is the main source, second is fallback, third is second fallback.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityDataSourceID
Field.Description: Data source identifier.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityDataSourceIDType
Field.Description: Type of data source identifier.

Field.Name: NoStreamCommoditySettlDays
Field.Description: Number of days in the repeating group.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlDay
Field.Description: Specifies the day or group of days for delivery.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlTotalHours
Field.Description: Sum of the hours specified in StreamCommoditySettlTimeGrp.

Field.Name: NoStreamCommoditySettlTimes
Field.Description: Number of hour ranges in the repeating group.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlStart
Field.Description: The start time for commodities settlement where delivery occurs over time. The time format is specified by the settlement time type.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlEnd
Field.Description: The end time for commodities settlement where delivery occurs over time. The time format is specified by the settlement time type.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlTimeType
Field.Description: Specifies the format of the commodities settlement start and end times.

Field.Name: NoStreamCommoditySettlPeriods
Field.Description: Number of commodity settlement periods in the repeating group.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlCountry
Field.Description: Specifies the country where delivery takes place. Uses ISO 3166 2-character country code.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlTimeZone
Field.Description: Commodity delivery timezone specified as "prevailing" rather than "standard" or "daylight". See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Prevailing_Timezones for code list of applicable prevailing timezones.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlFlowType
Field.Description: Specifies the commodity delivery flow type.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlPeriodNotional
Field.Description: Specifies the delivery quantity associated with this settlement period.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlPeriodNotionalUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the unit of measure (UOM) of the delivery quantity associated with this settlement period.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlPeriodFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the settlement period frequency.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlPeriodFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the settlement period frequency.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlPeriodPrice
Field.Description: The settlement period price.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlPeriodPriceUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the settlement period price unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlPeriodPriceCurrency
Field.Description: The currency of the settlement period price. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlHolidaysProcessingInstruction
Field.Description: Indicates whether holidays are included in the settlement periods. Required for electricity contracts.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlPeriodXID
Field.Description: Identifier of this settlement period for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: StreamCommoditySettlPeriodXIDRef
Field.Description: Cross reference to another settlement period for duplicating its properties.

Field.Name: StreamXID
Field.Description: Identifier of this Stream for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: StreamNotionalXIDRef
Field.Description: Cross reference to another Stream notional for duplicating its properties.

Field.Name: StreamNotionalFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the swap stream's notional frequency.

Field.Name: StreamNotionalFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the swap stream's notional frequency.

Field.Name: StreamNotionalCommodityFrequency
Field.Description: The commodity's notional or quantity delivery frequency.

Field.Name: StreamNotionalUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the delivery stream quantity unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: StreamTotalNotional
Field.Description: Total notional or delivery quantity over the term of the contract.

Field.Name: StreamTotalNotionalUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the unit of measure (UOM) for the total notional or delivery quantity over the term of the contract.

Field.Name: NoMandatoryClearingJurisdictions
Field.Description: Number of mandatory clearing jurisdictions.

Field.Name: MandatoryClearingJurisdiction
Field.Description: Identifier of the regulatory jurisdiction requiring the trade to be cleared.

Field.Name: LastQtyChanged
Field.Description: The positive or negative change in quantity when this report is a trade correction or continuation.

Field.Name: TradeVersion
Field.Description: Specifies the version of a trade or contract. This is used by systems or trading platforms in conjunction with TradeID(1003) to uniquely identify the version of a trade or contract. If used the conditions for a change of version are subject to bilateral agreement. It is recommended to change the version only for significant updates to the business entity rather than for minor changes to trade details or systematic distribution of reports. Examples where the version would change are trade quantity modification, customer account assignment or trade novation.

Field.Name: HistoricalReportIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates that the trade or event being reported occurred in the past and the trade is terminated or no longer active.

Field.Name: NoLegAdditionalTermBondRefs
Field.Description: Number of bonds in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegAdditionalTermBondSecurityID
Field.Description: Security identifier of the bond.

Field.Name: LegAdditionalTermBondSecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source scheme of the LegAdditionalTermBondSecurityID(41317) value.

Field.Name: LegAdditionalTermBondDesc
Field.Description: Description of the bond.

Field.Name: EncodedLegAdditionalTermBondDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedLegAdditionalTermBondDesc(41321) field.

Field.Name: EncodedLegAdditionalTermBondDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the LegAdditionalTermBondDesc(41319) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the LegAdditionalTermBondDesc(41319) field.

Field.Name: LegAdditionalTermBondCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency the bond value is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: LegAdditionalTermBondIssuer
Field.Description: Issuer of the bond.

Field.Name: EncodedLegAdditionalTermBondIssuerLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedLegAdditionalTermBondIssuer(41325) field.

Field.Name: EncodedLegAdditionalTermBondIssuer
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the LegAdditionalTermBondIssuer(41323) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the LegAdditionalTermBondIssuer(41323) field.

Field.Name: LegAdditionalTermBondSeniority
Field.Description: Specifies the bond's payment priority in the event of a default.

Field.Name: LegAdditionalTermBondCouponType
Field.Description: Specifies the coupon type of the bond.

Field.Name: LegAdditionalTermBondCouponRate
Field.Description: Coupon rate of the bond. See also CouponRate(223).

Field.Name: LegAdditionalTermBondMaturityDate
Field.Description: The maturity date of the bond.

Field.Name: LegAdditionalTermBondParValue
Field.Description: The par value of the bond.

Field.Name: LegAdditionalTermBondCurrentTotalIssuedAmount
Field.Description: Total issued amount of the bond.

Field.Name: LegAdditionalTermBondCouponFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of the bond's coupon payment.

Field.Name: LegAdditionalTermBondCouponFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the frequency of the bond's coupon payment.

Field.Name: LegAdditionalTermBondDayCount
Field.Description: The day count convention used in interest calculations for a bond or an interest bearing security.

Field.Name: NoLegAdditionalTerms
Field.Description: Number of additional terms in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegAdditionalTermConditionPrecedentBondIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the condition precedent bond is applicable. The swap contract is only valid if the bond is issued and if there is any dispute over the terms of fixed stream then the bond terms would be used.

Field.Name: LegAdditionalTermDiscrepancyClauseIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the discrepancy clause is applicable.

Field.Name: NoLegAssetAttributes
Field.Description: Number of asset attribute entries in the group.

Field.Name: LegAssetAttributeType
Field.Description: Specifies the name of the attribute. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Asset_Attribute_Types for code list of applicable asset attribute types.

Field.Name: LegAssetAttributeValue
Field.Description: Specifies the value of the attribute.

Field.Name: LegAssetAttributeLimit
Field.Description: Limit or lower acceptable value of the attribute.

Field.Name: NoLegCashSettlDealers
Field.Description: Number of dealers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlDealer
Field.Description: Identifies the dealer from whom price quotations for the reference obligation are obtained for the purpose of cash settlement valuation calculation.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Dealer

Field.Name: NoLegCashSettlTerms
Field.Description: Number of elements in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency the LegCashSettlAmount(41357) is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: LegCasSettlValuationFirstBusinessDayOffset
Field.Description: The number of business days after settlement conditions have been satisfied, when the calculation agent is to obtain a price quotation on the reference obligation for purposes of cash settlement.
Field.Elaboration: Associated with ISDA 2003 Term: Valuation Date.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlValuationSubsequentBusinessDaysOffset
Field.Description: The number of business days between successive valuation dates when multiple valuation dates are applicable for cash settlement.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlNumOfValuationDates
Field.Description: Where multiple valuation dates are specified as being applicable for cash settlement, this element specifies the number of applicable valuation dates.
Field.Elaboration: Associated with ISDA 2003 Term: Valuation Date

Field.Name: LegCashSettlValuationTime
Field.Description: Time of valuation.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlBusinessCenter
Field.Description: Identifies the business center calendar used at valuation time for cash settlement purposes e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlQuoteMethod
Field.Description: The type of quote used to determine the cash settlement price.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlQuoteAmount
Field.Description: When determining the cash settlement amount, if weighted average price quotes are to be obtained for the reference obligation, this is the upper limit to the outstanding principal balance of the reference obligation for which the quote should be obtained. If not specifed, the ISDA definitions provide for a fallback amount equal to floating rate payer calculation amount.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Quotation Amount.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlQuoteCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency the LegCashSettlQuoteAmount(41352) is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 Currency Code.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlMinimumQuoteAmount
Field.Description: When determining the cash settlement amount, if weighted average price quotes are to be obtained for the reference obligation, this is the minimum intended threshold amount of outstanding principal balance of the reference obligation for which the quote should be obtained. If not specified, the ISDA definitions provide for a fallback amount of the lower of either USD1,000,000 (or its equivalent in the relevent obligation currency) or the (minimum) quoted amount.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Minimum Quotation Amount.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlMinimumQuoteCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency the LegCashSettlQuoteMinimumAmount(41354) is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 Currency Code.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlBusinessDays
Field.Description: The number of business days used in the determination of the cash settlement payment date.
Field.Elaboration: If a cash settlement amount is specified, the cash settlement payment date will be this number of business days following the calculation of the final price. If a cash settlement amount is not specified, the cash settlement payment date will be this number of business days after all conditions to settlement are satisfied. ISDA 2003 Term: Cash Settlement Date.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlAmount
Field.Description: The amount paid between the trade parties, seller to the buyer, for cash settlement on the cash settlement date.
Field.Elaboration: If not specified this would typically be calculated as ((100 or the reference price) - reference obligation price) x floating rate payer calculation amount. Price values are all expressed as a percentage. ISDA 2003 Term: Cash Settlement Amount.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlRecoveryFactor
Field.Description: Used for fixed recovery, this specifies the recovery level as determined at contract inception, to be applied in the event of a default. The factor is used to calculate the amount paid by the seller to the buyer for cash settlement on the cash settlement date. The amount calculated is (1 - LegCashSettlRecoveryFactor(41358)) x floating rate payer calculation amount. The currency is derived from the floating rate payer calculation amount.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlFixedTermIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether fixed settlement is applicable or not applicable in a recovery lock.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlAccruedInterestIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether accrued interest is included or not in the value provided in LegCashSettlAmount(41357). For cash settlement this specifies whether quotations should be obtained inclusive or not of accrued interest. For physical settlement this specifies whether the buyer should deliver the obligation with an outstanding principal balance that includes or excludes accrued interest.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Include/Exclude Accrued Interest.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlValuationMethod
Field.Description: The ISDA defined methodology for determining the final price of the reference obligation for purposes of cash settlement.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Valuation Method.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlTermXID
Field.Description: A named string value referenced by UnderlyingSettlTermXIDRef(41315).

Field.Name: NoLegComplexEventAveragingObservations
Field.Description: The number of averaging observations in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventAveragingObservationNumber
Field.Description: Cross reference to the ordinal observation as specified either in the LegComplexEventScheduleGrp or LegComplexEventPeriodDateGrp components.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventAveragingWeight
Field.Description: The weight factor to be applied to the observation.

Field.Name: NoLegComplexEventCreditEvents
Field.Description: The number of credit events specified in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventCreditEventType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of credit event. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Credit_Event_Types for code list of applicable event types.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventCreditEventValue
Field.Description: The credit event value appropriate to LegComplexEventCreditEventType(41367). See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Credit_Event_Types for applicable event type values.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventCreditEventCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the applicable currency when LegComplexEventCreditEventCurrency(41368) is an amount. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventCreditEventPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for complex credit events.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventCreditEventUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with complex credit events.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventCreditEventDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type for the complex credit events.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventCreditEventRateSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source of rate information used for credit events. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Credit_Event_Rate_Source for code list of applicable sources.

Field.Name: NoLegComplexEventCreditEventQualifiers
Field.Description: Number of qualifiers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventCreditEventQualifier
Field.Description: Specifies a complex event qualifier. Used to further qualify LegComplexEventCreditEventType(41367).

Field.Name: NoLegComplexEventPeriodDateTimes
Field.Description: Number of entries in the date-time repeating group.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventPeriodDate
Field.Description: Averaging date for an Asian option. Trigger date for a Barrier or Knock option.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventPeriodTime
Field.Description: Averaging time for an Asian option.

Field.Name: NoLegComplexEventPeriods
Field.Description: Number of periods in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventPeriodType
Field.Description: Specifies the period type.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center for adjusting dates and times in the schedule or date-time group. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoLegComplexEventRateSources
Field.Description: Number of rate sources in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventRateSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source of rate information. For FX, the reference source to be used for the FX spot rate.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventRateSourceType
Field.Description: Indicates whether the rate source specified is a primary or secondary source.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventReferencePage
Field.Description: Identifies the reference page from the rate source. For FX, the reference page to the spot rate is to be used for the reference FX spot rate. When LegComplexEventRateSource(41383) = 3 (ISDA Settlement Rate Option) this contains the value from the scheme that reflects the terms of the Annex A to the ISDA 1998 FX and Currency Option Definitions. See: http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/settlement-rate-option.

Field.Name: LegComplexEvenReferencePageHeading
Field.Description: Identifies the reference page heading from the rate source.

Field.Name: NoLegComplexEventDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the event date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted complex event date.
Field.Elaboration: For example the second expiration date for a calendar spread option strategy.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the complex event date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative date offset.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative date offset.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative date offset.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the event date. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the LegDateAdjustment component within the InstrumentLeg component.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted complex event date.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventFixingTime
Field.Description: The local market fixing time.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventFixingTimeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center for determining the actual fixing times. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoLegComplexEventCreditEventSources
Field.Description: Number of event sources in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventCreditEventSource
Field.Description: A newspaper or electronic news service that may publish relevant information used in the determination of whether or not a credit event has occurred.

Field.Name: NoLegComplexEvents
Field.Description: Number of complex events in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of complex event.

Field.Name: LegComplexOptPayoutPaySide
Field.Description: Trade side of payout payer.

Field.Name: LegComplexOptPayoutReceiveSide
Field.Description: Trade side of payout receiver.

Field.Name: LegComplexOptPayoutUnderlier
Field.Description: Reference to the underlier whose payments are being passed through.

Field.Name: LegComplexOptPayoutAmount
Field.Description: Cash amount indicating the pay out associated with an event. For binary options this is a fixed amount.

Field.Name: LegComplexOptPayoutPercentage
Field.Description: Percentage of observed price for calculating the payout associated with the event.

Field.Name: LegComplexOptPayoutTime
Field.Description: Specifies when the payout is to occur.

Field.Name: LegComplexOptPayoutCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of the payout amount. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventPrice
Field.Description: Specifies the price at which the complex event takes effect. Impact of the event price is determined by the LegComplexEventType(2219).

Field.Name: LegComplexEventPricePercentage
Field.Description: Specifies the price percentage at which the complex event takes effect. Impact of the event price is determined by the LegComplexEventType(2219).

Field.Name: LegComplexEventPriceBoundaryMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the boundary condition to be used for the event price relative to the complex event price at the point the complex event outcome takes effect as determined by the LegComplexEventPriceTimeType(2231).

Field.Name: LegComplexEventPriceBoundaryPrecision
