Field.Description: Used in combination with LegComplexEventPriceBoundaryMethod(2229) to specify the percentage of the strike price in relation to the underlying price. The percentage is generally 100 or greater for puts and 100 or less for calls.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventPriceTimeType
Field.Description: Specifies when the complex event outcome takes effect. The outcome of a complex event is a payout or barrier action as specified by the LegComplexEventType(2219).

Field.Name: LegComplexEventCondition
Field.Description: Specifies the condition between complex events when more than one event is specified. Multiple barrier events would use an "or" condition since only one can be effective at a given time. A set of digital range events would use an "and" condition since both conditions must be in effect for a payout to result.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventCurrencyOne
Field.Description: Specifies the first or only reference currency of the trade. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.
Field.Elaboration: Applicable for complex FX option strategies.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventCurrencyTwo
Field.Description: Specifies the second reference currency of the trade. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.
Field.Elaboration: Applicable for complex FX option strategies.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventQuoteBasis
Field.Description: For foreign exchange Quanto option feature.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventFixedFXRate
Field.Description: Specifies the fixed FX rate alternative for FX Quantro options.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventDeterminationMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the method according to which an amount or a date is determined. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/determination-method for values.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventCalculationAgent
Field.Description: Used to identify the calculation agent.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventStrikePrice
Field.Description: Upper strike price for Asian option feature. Strike percentage for a Strike Spread.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventStrikeFactor
Field.Description: Strike factor for Asian option feature. Upper strike percentage for a Strike Spread.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventStrikeNumberOfOptions
Field.Description: Upper string number of options for a Strike Spread.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventCreditEventsXIDRef
Field.Description: Reference to credit event table elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventCreditEventNotifyingParty
Field.Description: The notifying party is the party that notifies the other party when a credit event has occurred by means of a credit event notice. If more than one party is referenced as being the notifying party then either party may notify the other of a credit event occurring.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventCreditEventBusinessCenter
Field.Description: Specifies the local business center for which the credit event is to be determined. The inclusion of this business center implies that Greenwich Mean Time in Section 3.3 of the 2003 ISDA Credit Derivatives Definitions is replaced by the local time of the specified business center. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventCreditEventStandardSources
Field.Description: When this element is specified and set to 'Y', indicates that ISDA defined Standard Public Sources are applicable.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventCreditEventMinimumSources
Field.Description: The minimum number of the specified public information sources that must publish information that reasonably confirms that a credit event has occurred. The market convention is two.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Specified Number.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventXID
Field.Description: Identifier of this complex event for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventXIDRef
Field.Description: Reference to a complex event elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: NoLegComplexEventDates
Field.Description: Number of complex event dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventStartDate
Field.Description: The start date of the date range on which a complex event is effective. The start date will be set equal to the end date for single day events such as Bermuda options. The start date must always be less than or equal to end date.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventEndDate
Field.Description: The end date of the date range on which a complex event is effective. The start date will be set equal to the end date for single day events such as Bermuda options. The end date must always be greater than or equal to start date.

Field.Name: NoLegComplexEventTimes
Field.Description: Number of complex event times in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventStartTime
Field.Description: The start time of the time range on which a complex event date is effective. The start time must always be less than or equal to the end time.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventEndTime
Field.Description: The end time of the time range on which a complex event date is effective. The end time must always be greater than or equal to the start time.

Field.Name: NoLegComplexEventSchedules
Field.Description: Number of schedules in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventScheduleStartDate
Field.Description: The start date of the schedule.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventScheduleEndDate
Field.Description: The end date of the schedule.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventScheduleFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the schedule date frequency.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventScheduleFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the schedule date frequency.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventScheduleRollConvention
Field.Description: The convention for determining the sequence of dates. It is used in conjunction with a specified frequency. Used only to override the roll convention defined in the LegDateAdjustment component in InstrumentLeg.

Field.Name: NoLegDeliverySchedules
Field.Description: Number of delivery schedules in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryScheduleType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of delivery schedule.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryScheduleXID
Field.Description: Identifier for this instance of delivery schedule for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryScheduleNotional
Field.Description: Physical delivery quantity.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryScheduleNotionalUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the delivery quantity unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: LegDeliveryScheduleNotionalCommodityFrequency
Field.Description: The frequency of notional delivery.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryScheduleNegativeTolerance
Field.Description: Specifies the negative tolerance value. The value may be an absolute quantity or a percentage, as specified in LegDeliveryScheduleToleranceType(41417). Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%).

Field.Name: LegDeliverySchedulePositiveTolerance
Field.Description: Specifies the positive tolerance value. The value may be an absolute quantity or a percentage, as specified in LegDeliveryScheduleToleranceType(41417). Value may exceed agreed upon value. Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%).

Field.Name: LegDeliveryScheduleToleranceUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the tolerance value's unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: LegDeliveryScheduleToleranceType
Field.Description: Specifies the tolerance value type.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryScheduleSettlCountry
Field.Description: Specifies the country where delivery takes place. Uses ISO 3166 2-character country code.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryScheduleSettlTimeZone
Field.Description: Delivery timezone specified as "prevailing" rather than "standard" or "daylight". See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Prevailing_Timezones for code list of applicable prevailing timezones.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryScheduleSettlFlowType
Field.Description: Specifies the delivery flow type.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryScheduleSettlHolidaysProcessingInstruction
Field.Description: Indicates whether holidays are included in the settlement periods. Required for electricity contracts.

Field.Name: NoLegDeliveryScheduleSettlDays
Field.Description: Number of delivery schedules in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryScheduleSettlDay
Field.Description: Specifies the day or group of days for delivery.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryScheduleSettlTotalHours
Field.Description: The sum of the total hours specified in the LegDeliveryScheduleSettlTimeGrp component.

Field.Name: NoLegDeliveryScheduleSettlTimes
Field.Description: Number of hour ranges in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryScheduleSettlStart
Field.Description: The scheduled start time for the delivery of the commodity where delivery occurs over specified times. The format of the time value is specified in LegDeliveryScheduleSettlTimeType(41428).

Field.Name: LegDeliveryScheduleSettlEnd
Field.Description: The scheduled end time for the delivery of the commodity where delivery occurs over specified times. The format of the time value is specified in LegDeliveryScheduleSettlTimeType(41428).

Field.Name: LegDeliveryScheduleSettlTimeType
Field.Description: Specifies the format of the delivery start and end time values.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of delivery stream.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamPipeline
Field.Description: The name of the oil delivery pipeline.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamEntryPoint
Field.Description: The point at which the commodity will enter the delivery mechanism or pipeline.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamWithdrawalPoint
Field.Description: The point at which the commodity product will be withdrawn prior to delivery.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamDeliveryPoint
Field.Description: The point at which the commodity product will be delivered and received. Value specified should follow market convention appropriate for the commodity product. For bullion, see http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/bullion-delivery-location for values.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamDeliveryRestriction
Field.Description: Specifies under what conditions the buyer and seller should be excused of their delivery obligations.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamDeliveryContingency
Field.Description: Specifies the electricity delivery contingency. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/electricity-transmission-contingency for values.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamDeliveryContingentPartySide
Field.Description: The trade side value of the party responsible for electricity delivery contingency.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamDeliverAtSourceIndicator
Field.Description: When this element is specified and set to 'Y', delivery of the coal product is to be at its source.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamRiskApportionment
Field.Description: Specifies how the parties to the trade apportion responsibility for the delivery of the commodity product. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Risk_Apportionment for the details of the external code list.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamRiskApportionmentSource
Field.Description: Specifies the source or legal framework for the risk apportionment. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Risk_Apportionment_Source for the details of the external code list.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamTitleTransferLocation
Field.Description: Specifies the title transfer location.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamTitleTransferCondition
Field.Description: Specifies the condition of title transfer.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamImporterOfRecord
Field.Description: A party, not necessarily of the trade, who is the Importer of Record for the purposes of paying customs duties and applicable taxes or costs related to importation.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamNegativeTolerance
Field.Description: Specifies the negative tolerance value. The value may be an absolute quantity or a percentage, as specified in LegDeliveryStreamToleranceType(41445). Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%).

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamPositiveTolerance
Field.Description: Specifies the positive tolerance value. The value may be an absolute quantity or a percentage, as specified in LegDeliveryStreamToleranceType(41445). Value may exceed agreed upon value. Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%).

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamToleranceUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the tolerance value's unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamToleranceType
Field.Description: Specifies the tolerance value type.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamToleranceOptionSide
Field.Description: Indicates whether the tolerance is at the seller's or buyer's option.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamTotalPositiveTolerance
Field.Description: The positive percent tolerance which applies to the total quantity delivered over all shipment periods. Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%.).

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamTotalNegativeTolerance
Field.Description: The negative percent tolerance which applies to the total quantity delivered over all shipment periods. Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%.).

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamNotionalConversionFactor
Field.Description: If the notional quantity is specified in a unit that does not match the unit in which the commodity reference price is quoted, the scaling or conversion factor used to convert the commodity reference price unit into the notional quantity unit should be stated here. If there is no conversion, this field is not intended to be used.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamTransportEquipment
Field.Description: The transportation equipment with which the commodity product will be delivered and received.
Field.Elaboration: Examples of transportation equipment or mode are barge, truck, railcar, etc.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamElectingPartySide
Field.Description: A reference to the party able to choose whether the gas is delivered for a particular period e.g. a swing or interruptible contract.

Field.Name: NoLegStreamAssetAttributes
Field.Description: Number of asset attribute entries in the group.

Field.Name: LegStreamAssetAttributeType
Field.Description: Specifies the name of the attribute. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Asset_Attribute_Types for code list of applicable asset attribute types.

Field.Name: LegStreamAssetAttributeValue
Field.Description: Specifies the value of the attribute.

Field.Name: LegStreamAssetAttributeLimit
Field.Description: Limit or lower acceptable value of the attribute.

Field.Name: NoLegDeliveryStreamCycles
Field.Description: Number of commodity sources in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamCycleDesc
Field.Description: The delivery cycles during which the oil product will be transported in the pipeline.

Field.Name: EncodedLegDeliveryStreamCycleDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedLegDeliveryStreamCycleDesc(41459) field.

Field.Name: EncodedLegDeliveryStreamCycleDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the LegDeliveryStreamCycleDesc(41457) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the LegLeg DeliveryStream(41457) field.

Field.Name: NoLegDeliveryStreamCommoditySources
Field.Description: Number of commodity sources in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamCommoditySource
Field.Description: The SCoTA coal cargo origin, mining region, mine(s), mining complex(es), loadout(s) or river dock(s) or other point(s) of origin that seller and buyer agree are acceptable origins for the coal product. For international coal transactions, this is the origin of the coal product. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-coal-product-source for values.

Field.Name: NoLegInstrumentParties
Field.Description: Number of parties in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegInstrumentPartyID
Field.Description: Used to identify party id related to instrument.

Field.Name: LegInstrumentPartyIDSource
Field.Description: Used to identify source of instrument party id.

Field.Name: LegInstrumentPartyRole
Field.Description: Used to identify the role of instrument party id.

Field.Name: NoLegInstrumentPartySubIDs
Field.Description: Number of parties sub-IDs in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegInstrumentPartySubID
Field.Description: PartySubID value within an instrument party repeating group.

Field.Name: LegInstrumentPartySubIDType
Field.Description: Type of LegInstrumentPartySubID (2259) value.

Field.Name: LegMarketDisruptionProvision
Field.Description: The consequences of market disruption events.

Field.Name: LegMarketDisruptionFallbackProvision
Field.Description: Specifies the location of the fallback provision documentation.

Field.Name: LegMarketDisruptionMaximumDays
Field.Description: Specifies the maximum number of market disruption days (commodity or bullion business days) in a contract or confirmation. If none are specified, the maximum number of market disruption days is five (5).
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2005 Commodity Definition.

Field.Name: LegMarketDisruptionMaterialityPercentage
Field.Description: Used when a price materiality percentage applies to the price source disruption event and this event has been specified.
Field.Elaboration: Applicable to 2005 Commodity Definitions only.

Field.Name: LegMarketDisruptionMinimumFuturesContracts
Field.Description: Specifies the minimum futures contracts level that dictates whether or not a 'De Minimis Trading' event has occurred.
Field.Elaboration: Applicable to 1993 Commodity Definitions only.

Field.Name: NoLegMarketDisruptionEvents
Field.Description: Number of disruption events in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegMarketDisruptionEvent
Field.Description: Specifies the market disruption event. For commodities see http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-market-disruption for values. For foreign exchange, see http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Market_Disruption_Event for code list of applicable event types.

Field.Name: NoLegMarketDisruptionFallbacks
Field.Description: Number of fallbacks in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegMarketDisruptionFallbackType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of disruption fallback. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-market-disruption-fallback for values.

Field.Name: NoLegMarketDisruptionFallbackReferencePrices
Field.Description: Number of fallback reference securities in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierType
Field.Description: The type of reference price underlier.

Field.Name: LegMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityID
Field.Description: Specifies the identifier value of the security.

Field.Name: LegMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Specifies the class or source scheme of the security identifier.

Field.Name: LegMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDesc
Field.Description: Specifies the description of the underlying security.

Field.Name: EncodedLegMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedLegMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDesc (41477) field.

Field.Name: EncodedLegMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the LegMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDesc(41475) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the LegMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDesc(41475) field.

Field.Name: LegMarketDisruptionFallbackOpenUnits
Field.Description: If there are multiple underlying assets, this specifies the number of units (index or securities) that constitute the underlier of the swap. In the case of a basket swap, this is used to reference both the number of basket units, and the number of each asset components of the basket when these are expressed in absolute terms.

Field.Name: LegMarketDisruptionFallbackBasketCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency if the underlier is a basket. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: LegMarketDisruptionFallbackBasketDivisor
Field.Description: Specifies the basket divisor amount. This value is normally used to adjust the constituent weight for pricing or to adjust for dividends, or other corporate actions.

Field.Name: LegExerciseDesc
Field.Description: A description of the option exercise.

Field.Name: EncodedLegExerciseDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedLegExerciseDesc(41483) field.

Field.Name: EncodedLegExerciseDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the LegExerciseDesc(41481) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the LegExerciseDesc(41481) field.

Field.Name: LegAutomaticExerciseIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates (when 'Y') that exercise is automatic when the strike price is crossed or the underlying trade is in the money.

Field.Name: LegAutomaticExerciseThresholdRate
Field.Description: The threshold rate for triggering automatic exercise.

Field.Name: LegExerciseConfirmationMethod
Field.Description: Indicates whether follow-up confirmation of exercise (written or electronic) is required following telephonic notice by the buyer to the seller or seller's agent.

Field.Name: LegManualNoticeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: Identifies the business center used for adjusting the time for manual exercise notice. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: LegFallbackExerciseIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the notional amount of the underlying swap, not previously exercised under the option, will be automatically exercised at the expiration time on the expiration date if at such time the buyer is in-the-money, provided that the difference between the settlement rate and the fixed rate under the relevant underlying swap is not less than one tenth of a percentage point (0.10% or 0.001).

Field.Name: LegLimitRightToConfirmIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the Seller may request the Buyer to confirm its intent to exercise if not done on or before the expiration time on the expiration date. If true ("Y") specific rules will apply in relation to the settlement mode.

Field.Name: LegExerciseSplitTicketIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates in physical settlement of bond and convertible bond options whether the party required to deliver the bonds will divide those to be delivered as notifying party desires to facilitate delivery obligations.

Field.Name: NoLegOptionExerciseBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the option exercise dates, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the option exercise dates. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the LegDateAdjustment component within the InstrumentLeg component.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseEarliestDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative earliest exercise date offset.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseEarliestDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative earliest exercise date offset.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseEarliestDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative earliest exercise date offset.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of exercise dates.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the frequency of exercise dates.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseStartDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted start date for calculating periodic exercise dates.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseStartDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the option exercise start date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseStartDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative exercise start date offset.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseStartDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative exercise start date offset.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseStartDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative option exercise start date offset.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseStartDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted start date for calculating periodic exercise dates.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseSkip
Field.Description: The number of periods in the referenced date schedule that are between each date in the relative date schedule. Thus a skip of 2 would mean that dates are relative to every second date in the referenced schedule. If present this should have a value greater than 1.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseNominationDeadline
Field.Description: The last date (adjusted) for establishing the option exercise terms.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseFirstDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted first exercise date.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseLastDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted last exercise date.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseEarliestTime
Field.Description: The earliest time at which notice of exercise can be given by the buyer to the seller (or seller's agent) (i) on the expriation date, in the case of a European style option, (ii) on each Bermuda option exercise date and the expiration date, in the case of a Bermuda style option, (iii) the commencement date to, and including, the expiration date, in the case of an American option.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseLatestTime
Field.Description: The latest exercise time. See also LegOptionExerciseEarliestTime(41509).

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseTimeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center used to determine the locale for option exercise time, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoLegOptionExerciseDates
Field.Description: Number of dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseDate
Field.Description: The adjusted or unadjusted option exercise fixed date.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of option exercise date. When specified it applies not only to the current date but to all subsequent dates in the group until overridden with a new type.

Field.Name: NoLegOptionExerciseExpirationDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseExpirationDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the option exercise expiration dates, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseExpirationDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the option exercise expiration dates. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the LegDateAdjustment component within the InstrumentLeg component.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseExpirationDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the option exercise expiration date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseExpirationDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative exercise expiration date offset.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseExpirationDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative exercise expiration date offset.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseExpirationFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of exercise expiration dates.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseExpirationFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the frequency of exercise expiration dates.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseExpirationRollConvention
Field.Description: The convention for determining the sequence of exercise expiration dates. It is used in conjunction with a specified frequency. Used only to override the roll convention defined in the LegDateAdjustment component in InstrumentLeg.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseExpirationDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative option exercise expiration date offset.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseExpirationTime
Field.Description: The option exercise expiration time.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseExpirationTimeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center used to determine the locale for option exercise expiration time, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoLegOptionExerciseExpirationDates
Field.Description: Number of fixed exercise expiration dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseExpirationDate
Field.Description: The adjusted or unadjusted option exercise expiration fixed date.

Field.Name: LegOptionExerciseExpirationDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of option exercise expiration date. When specified it applies not only to the current date but to all subsequent dates in the group until overridden with a new type.

Field.Name: NoLegPaymentScheduleFixingDays
Field.Description: Number of fixing days in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegPaymentScheduleFixingDayOfWeek
Field.Description: The day of the week on which fixing takes place.

Field.Name: LegPaymentScheduleFixingDayNumber
Field.Description: The occurrence of the day of week on which fixing takes place.
Field.Elaboration: For example, a fixing of the 3rd Friday would be DayOfWk=5 DayNum=3. If omitted every day of the week is a fixing day.

Field.Name: LegPaymentScheduleXID
Field.Description: Identifier of this LegPaymentSchedule for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: LegPaymentScheduleXIDRef
Field.Description: Reference to payment schedule elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: LegPaymentScheduleRateCurrency
Field.Description: The currency of the schedule rate. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: LegPaymentScheduleRateUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The schedule rate unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: LegPaymentScheduleRateConversionFactor
Field.Description: The number multipled by the derived floating rate of the leg's payment schedule in order to arrive at the payment rate. If omitted, the schedule rate conversion factor is 1.

Field.Name: LegPaymentScheduleRateSpreadType
Field.Description: Identifies whether the rate spread is an absolute value to be added to the index rate or a percentage of the index rate.

Field.Name: LegPaymentScheduleSettlPeriodPrice
Field.Description: The schedule settlement period price.

Field.Name: LegPaymentScheduleSettlPeriodPriceCurrency
Field.Description: The currency of the schedule settlement period price. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: LegPaymentScheduleSettlPeriodPriceUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The settlement period price unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: LegPaymentScheduleStepUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The schedule step unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: LegPaymentScheduleFixingDayDistribution
Field.Description: The distribution of fixing days.

Field.Name: LegPaymentScheduleFixingDayCount
Field.Description: The number of days over which fixing should take place.

Field.Name: LegPaymentScheduleFixingLagPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the fixing lag duration.

Field.Name: LegPaymentScheduleFixingLagUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the fixing lag duration.

Field.Name: LegPaymentScheduleFixingFirstObservationDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative first observation date offset.
Field.Elaboration: If the first observation offset is specified, the observation period will start the specified interval prior to each calculation period - i.e. if the first observation offset is 4 months and the lag duration is 3 months, observations will be taken in months 4, 3 and 2 (but not 1) prior to each calculation period. If no first observation offset is specified, the observation period will end immediately preceding each calculation period.

Field.Name: LegPaymentScheduleFixingFirstObservationDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative first observation date offset.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamFlatRateIndicator
Field.Description: When this element is specified and set to 'Y', the Flat Rate is the New Worldwide Tanker Nominal Freight Scale for the Freight Index Route taken at the trade date of the transaction "Fixed". If 'N' it is taken on each pricing date "Floating".

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamFlatRateAmount
Field.Description: Specifies the actual monetary value of the flat rate when LegPaymentStreamFlatRateIndicator(41549) = 'Y'.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamFlatRateCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of the actual flat rate. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: LegStreamMaximumPaymentAmount
Field.Description: Specifies the limit on the total payment amount.

Field.Name: LegStreamMaximumPaymentCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of total payment amount limit. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: LegStreamMaximumTransactionAmount
Field.Description: Specifies the limit on the payment amount that goes out in any particular calculation period.

Field.Name: LegStreamMaximumTransactionCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of the period payment amount limit. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamFixedAmountUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The fixed payment amount unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamTotalFixedAmount
Field.Description: Specifies the total fixed payment amount.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamWorldScaleRate
Field.Description: The number of Worldscale points for purposes of the calculation of a fixed amount for a wet voyage charter commodity swap.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamContractPrice
Field.Description: The price per relevant unit for purposes of the calculation of a fixed amount for a dry voyage charter or time charter commodity swap.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamContractPriceCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of LegPaymentStreamContractPrice(41559). Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: NoLegPaymentStreamPricingBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamPricingBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the pricing dates, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamRateIndex2CurveUnit
Field.Description: Secondary time unit associated with the payment stream's floating rate index curve.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamRateIndex2CurvePeriod
Field.Description: Secondary time unit multiplier for the payment stream's floating rate index curve.
Field.Elaboration: May be used for a Forward Rate Agreement (FRA) with an average rate between two curve points.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamRateIndexLocation
Field.Description: Specifies the location of the floating rate index.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamRateIndexLevel
Field.Description: This is the weather Cooling Degree Days (CDD), Heating Degree Days (HDD) or HDD index level specified as the number of (amount of) weather index units specified by the parties in the related confirmation.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamRateIndexUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The unit of measure (UOM) of the rate index level.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamSettlLevel
Field.Description: Specifies how weather index units are to be calculated.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamReferenceLevel
Field.Description: This is the weather Cooling Degree Days (CDD), Heating Degree Days (HDD) or HDD reference level specified as the number of (amount of) weather index units specified by the parties in the related confirmation.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamReferenceLevelUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The unit of measure (UOM) of the rate reference level.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamReferenceLevelEqualsZeroIndicator
Field.Description: When set to 'Y', it indicates that the weather reference level equals zero.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamRateSpreadCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of the floating rate spread. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamRateSpreadUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the unit of measure (UOM) of the floating rate spread.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamRateConversionFactor
Field.Description: The number to be multiplied by the derived floating rate of the leg's payment stream in order to arrive at the payment rate. If omitted, the floating rate conversion factor is 1.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamRateSpreadType
Field.Description: Identifies whether the rate spread is an absolute value to be added to the index rate or a percentage of the index rate.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamLastResetRate
Field.Description: The floating rate determined at the most recent reset. The rate is expressed in decimal form, e.g. 5% is represented as 0.05.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamFinalRate
Field.Description: The floating rate determined at the final reset. The rate is expressed in decimal form, e.g. 5% is represented as 0.05.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamCalculationLagPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the calculation lag duration.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamCalculationLagUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the calculation lag duration.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamFirstObservationDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative first observation date offset.
Field.Elaboration: If the first observation offset is specified, the observation period will start the specified interval prior to each calculation period - i.e. if the first observation offset is 4 months and the lag duration is 3 months, observations will be taken in months 4, 3 and 2 (but not 1) prior to each calculation period. If no first observation offset is specified, the observation period will end immediately preceding each calculation period.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamFirstObservationDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative first observation date offset.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamPricingDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the commodity pricing day type.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamPricingDayDistribution
Field.Description: The distribution of pricing days.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamPricingDayCount
Field.Description: The number of days over which pricing should take place.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamPricingBusinessCalendar
Field.Description: Specifies the business calendar to use for pricing. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-business-calendar for values.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamPricingBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the payment stream's pricing dates. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the LegDateAdjustment component within the InstrumentLeg component.

Field.Name: NoLegPaymentStreamPaymentDates
Field.Description: Number of payment dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamPaymentDate
Field.Description: The adjusted or unadjusted fixed stream payment date.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamPaymentDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of payment date. When specified it applies not only to the current date but to all subsequent dates in the group until overridden with a new type.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamMasterAgreementPaymentDatesIndicator
Field.Description: When set to 'Y', it indicates that payment dates are specified in the relevant master agreement.

Field.Name: NoLegPaymentStreamPricingDates
Field.Description: Number of pricing dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamPricingDate
Field.Description: The adjusted or unadusted fixed stream pricing date.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamPricingDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of pricing date. When specified it applies not only to the current date but to all subsequent dates in the group until overridden with a new type.

Field.Name: NoLegPaymentStreamPricingDays
Field.Description: Number of pricing days in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamPricingDayOfWeek
Field.Description: The day of the week on which pricing takes place..

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamPricingDayNumber
Field.Description: The occurrence of the day of week on which pricing takes place.
Field.Elaboration: For example a pricing day of the 3rd Friday would be DayOfWk=5 DayNum=3.

Field.Name: NoLegPhysicalSettlTerms
Field.Description: Number of entries in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegPhysicalSettlTermXID
Field.Description: A named string value referenced by UnderlyingSettlTermXIDRef(41315).

Field.Name: LegPhysicalSettlCurency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of physical settlement. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: LegPhysicalSettlBusinessDays
Field.Description: The number of business days used in the determination of physical settlement. Its precise meaning is dependant on the context in which this is used.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Business Day.

Field.Name: LegPhysicalSettlMaximumBusinessDays
Field.Description: A maximum number of business days. Its precise meaning is dependant on the context in which this element is used. Intended to be used to limit a particular ISDA fallback provision.

Field.Name: NoLegPhysicalSettlDeliverableObligations
Field.Description: Number of entries in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegPhysicalSettlDeliverableObligationType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of delivery obligation applicable for physical settlement. See http://www.fixptradingcommunity.org/codelists#Deliverable_Obligation_Types for code list for applicable deliverable obligation types.

Field.Name: LegPhysicalSettlDeliverableObligationValue
Field.Description: Physical settlement delivery obligation value appropriate to LegPhysicalSettlDeliverableObligationType(41605). See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Deliverable_Obligation_Types for code list for applicable deliverable obligation types.

Field.Name: NoLegPricingDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegPricingDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the pricing or fixing date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: LegPricingDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted pricing or fixing date.

Field.Name: LegPricingDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the pricing or fixing date. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the LegDateAdjustment component within the InstrumentLeg component.

Field.Name: LegPricingDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted pricing or fixing date.

Field.Name: LegPricingTime
Field.Description: The local market pricing or fixing time.

Field.Name: LegPricingTimeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: Specifies the business center for determining the pricing or fixing time. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoLegProtectionTermEventNewsSources
Field.Description: Number of event sources in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermEventNewsSource
Field.Description: A newspaper or electronic news service that may publish relevant information used in the determination of whether or not a credit event has occurred.

Field.Name: NoLegProtectionTerms
Field.Description: Number of protection terms in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermXID
Field.Description: A named string value referenced from UnderlyingLegProtectionTermXIDRef(41314).

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermNotional
Field.Description: The notional amount of protection coverage.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Floating Rate Payer Calculation Amount.

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermCurrency
Field.Description: The currency of LegProtectionTermNotional(41618). Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermSellerNotifies
Field.Description: The notifying party is the party that notifies the other party when a credit event has occurred by means of a credit event notice. If more than one party is referenced as being the notifying party then either party may notify the other of a credit event occurring. LegProtectionTermSellerNotifies(41620)=Y indicates that the seller notifies.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Notifying Party.

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermBuyerNotifies
Field.Description: The notifying party is the party that notifies the other party when a credit event has occurred by means of a credit event notice. If more than one party is referenced as being the notifying party then either party may notify the other of a credit event occurring. LegProtectionTermBuyerNotifies(41621)=Y indicates that the buyer notifies.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Notifying Party.

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermEventBusinessCenter
Field.Description: When used, the business center indicates the local time of the business center that replaces the Greenwich Mean Time in Section 3.3 of the 2003 ISDA Credit Derivatives Definitions. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermStandardSources
Field.Description: Indicates whether ISDA defined Standard Public Sources are applicable (LegProtectionTermStandardSources(41623)=Y) or not.

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermEventMinimumSources
Field.Description: The minimum number of the specified public information sources that must publish information that reasonably confirms that a credit event has occurred. The market convention is two.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Specified Number.

Field.Name: NoLegProtectionTermEvents
Field.Description: Number of protection term events in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermEventType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of credit event applicable to the protection terms. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Protection_Term_Event_Types for code list of applicable event types.

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermEventValue
Field.Description: Specifies the protection term event value appropriate to LegProtectionTermEventType(41626). See http:///www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Protection_Term_Event_Types for applicable event type values.

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermEventCurrency
Field.Description: Applicable currency if the event value is an amount. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermEventPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for protection term events.

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermEventUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with protection term events.

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermEventDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type for protection term events.

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermEventRateSource
Field.Description: Rate source for events that specify a rate source, e.g. floating rate interest shortfall.

Field.Name: NoLegProtectionTermEventQualifiers
Field.Description: Number of qualifiers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermEventQualifier
Field.Description: Specifies the protection term event qualifier. Used to further qualify LegProtectionTermEventType(41626).

Field.Name: NoLegProtectionTermObligations
Field.Description: Number of obligations in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermObligationType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of obligation applicable to the protection terms. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Protection_Term_Obligation_Types for code list of applicable obligation types.

Field.Name: LegProtectionTermObligationValue
Field.Description: The value associated with the protection term obligation specified in LegProtectionTermObligationType(41636). See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Protection_Term_Obligation_Types for applicable obligation type values.

Field.Name: NoLegStreamCalculationPeriodDates
Field.Description: Number of calculation period dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegStreamCalculationPeriodDate
Field.Description: The adjusted or unadjusted fixed calculation period date.

Field.Name: LegStreamCalculationPeriodDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of fixed calculation period date. When specified it applies not only to the current date but to all subsequent dates in the group until overridden with a new type.

Field.Name: LegStreamCalculationPeriodDatesXID
Field.Description: Identifier of this calculation period for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: LegStreamCalculationPeriodDatesXIDRef
Field.Description: Cross reference to another calculation period for duplicating its properties.

Field.Name: LegStreamCalculationBalanceOfFirstPeriod
Field.Description: When specified and set to 'Y', it indicates that the first calculation period should run from the effective date to the end of the calendar period in which the effective date falls (e.g. Jan 15 - Jan 31 if the calculation periods are one month long and effective date is Jan 15.). If 'N' or not specified, it indicates that the first calculation period should run from the effective date for one whole period (e.g. Jan 15 to Feb 14 if the calculation periods are one month long and the effective date is Jan 15.).

Field.Name: LegStreamCalculationCorrectionPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the length of time after the publication of the data when corrections can be made.

Field.Name: LegStreamCalculationCorrectionUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the length of time after the publication of the data when corrections can be made.

Field.Name: NoLegStreamCommoditySettlBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the commodity delivery date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityBase
Field.Description: Specifies the general base type of the commodity traded. Where possible, this should follow the naming convention used in the 2005 ISDA Commodity Definitions.
Field.Elaboration: Examples of general commodity base types include: Metal, Bullion, Oil, Natural Gas, Coal, Electricity, Inter-Energy, Grains, Oils Seeds, Dairy, Livestock, Forestry, Softs, Weather, Emissions.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of commodity product. For coal see http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-coal-product-type for values. For metals see http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-metal-product-type for values. For bullion see http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Bullion_Types for the external code list of bullion types.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySecurityID
Field.Description: Specifies the market identifier for the commodity.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the class or source of the LegStreamCommoditySecurityIDSource(41650) value.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityDesc
Field.Description: Description of the commodity asset.

Field.Name: EncodedLegStreamCommodityDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedLegStreamCommodityDesc(41654) field.

Field.Name: EncodedLegStreamCommodityDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the LegStreamCommodityDesc(41652) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the LegStreamCommodityDesc(41652) field.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The unit of measure (UOM) of the commodity asset.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityCurrency
Field.Description: Identifies the currency of the commodity asset. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityExchange
Field.Description: Identifies the exchange where the commodity is traded.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityRateSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source of rate information used for commodities. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Commodity_Rate_Source for code list of applicable sources.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityRateReferencePage
Field.Description: Identifies the reference "page" from the rate source.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityRateReferencePageHeading
Field.Description: Identifies the page heading from the rate source.

Field.Name: LegStreamDataProvider
Field.Description: Specifies the commodity data or information provider. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-information-provider for values.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityPricingType
Field.Description: Specifies how the pricing or rate setting of the trade is to be determined or based upon. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Commodity_Rate_Pricing_Type for code list of applicable commodity pricing types.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityNearbySettlDayPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the nearby settlement day.
Field.Elaboration: When the commodity transaction references a futures contract, the delivery or settlement dates are a nearby month or week. For example, for eighth nearby month use Period=8 and Unit=Mo.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityNearbySettlDayUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the nearby settlement day.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted commodity delivery date.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the commodity delivery date. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the LegDateAdjustment component within the InstrumentLeg component.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted commodity delivery date.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlMonth
Field.Description: Specifies a fixed single month for commodity delivery.
Field.Elaboration: Use "1" for January, "2" for February, etc.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlDateRollPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the commodity delivery date roll.
Field.Elaboration: For a commodity transaction that references a listed future via the delivery dates, this is the day offset on which the specified future will roll to the next nearby month when the referenced future expires.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlDateRollUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the commodity delivery date roll.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the commodity delivery roll day type.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityXID
Field.Description: Identifier of this stream commodity for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityXIDRef
Field.Description: Reference to a stream commodity elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: NoLegStreamCommodityAltIDs
Field.Description: Number of alternate security identifers.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityAltID
Field.Description: Alternate security identifier value for the commodity.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityAltIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the class or source of the alternate commodity security identifier.

Field.Name: NoLegStreamCommodityDataSources
Field.Description: Number of data sources in the repeating group. The order of entry determines priority first is the main source, second is fallback, third is second fallback.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityDataSourceID
Field.Description: Specifies the data source identifier.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityDataSourceIDType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of data source identifier.

Field.Name: NoLegStreamCommoditySettlDays
Field.Description: Number of days in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlDay
Field.Description: Specifies the day or group of days for delivery.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlTotalHours
Field.Description: Sum of the hours specified in LegStreamCommoditySettlTimeGrp.

Field.Name: NoLegStreamCommoditySettlTimes
Field.Description: Number of hour ranges in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlStart
Field.Description: The start time for commodity settlement where delivery occurs over time. The time format is specified by the settlement time type.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlEnd
Field.Description: The end time for commodity settlement where delivery occurs over time. The time format is specified by the settlement time type.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlTimeType
Field.Description: Specifies the format of the commodity settlement start and end times.

Field.Name: NoLegStreamCommoditySettlPeriods
Field.Description: Number of commodity settlement periods in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlCountry
Field.Description: Specifies the country where delivery takes place. Uses ISO 3166 2-character country code.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlTimeZone
Field.Description: Commodity delivery timezone specified as "prevailing" rather than "standard" or "daylight". See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Prevailing_Timezones for code list of applicable prevailing timezones.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlFlowType
Field.Description: Specifies the commodity delivery flow type.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlPeriodNotional
Field.Description: Delivery quantity associated with this settlement period.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlPeriodNotionalUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the unit of measure (UOM) of the delivery quantity associated with this settlement period.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlPeriodFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the settlement period frequency.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlPeriodFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the settlement period frequency.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlPeriodPrice
Field.Description: The settlement period price.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlPeriodPriceUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The settlement period price unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlPeriodPriceCurrency
Field.Description: The currency of the settlement period price. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlHolidaysProcessingInstruction
Field.Description: Indicates whether holidays are included in the settlement periods. Required for electricity contracts.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlPeriodXID
Field.Description: Identifier of this settlement period for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommoditySettlPeriodXIDRef
Field.Description: Cross reference to another settlement period for duplicating its properties.

Field.Name: LegStreamXID
Field.Description: Identifier of this LegStream for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: LegStreamNotionalXIDRef
Field.Description: Cross reference to another LegStream notional for duplicating its properties.

Field.Name: LegStreamNotionalFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the swap stream's notional frequency.

Field.Name: LegStreamNotionalFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the swap stream's notional frequency.

Field.Name: LegStreamNotionalCommodityFrequency
Field.Description: The commodity's notional or quantity delivery frequency.

Field.Name: LegStreamNotionalUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the delivery quantity unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: LegStreamTotalNotional
Field.Description: Specifies the total notional or delivery quantity over the term of the contract.

Field.Name: LegStreamTotalNotionalUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the unit of measure (UOM) for the total notional or delivery quantity over the term of the contract.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingAssetAttributes
Field.Description: Number of asset attribute entries in the group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAssetAttributeType
Field.Description: Specifies the name of the attribute. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Asset_Attribute_Types for code list of applicable asset attribute types.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAssetAttributeValue
Field.Description: Specifies the value of the attribute.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAssetAttributeLimit
Field.Description: Limit or lower acceptable value of the attribute.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingComplexEventAveragingObservations
Field.Description: The number of averaging observations in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventAveragingObservationNumber
Field.Description: Cross reference to the ordinal observation as specified either in the UnderlyingComplexEventScheduleGrp or UnderlyingComplexEventPeriodDateGrp components.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventAveragingWeight
Field.Description: The weight factor to be applied to the observation.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingComplexEventCreditEvents
Field.Description: The number of credit events specified in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of credit event. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Credit_Event_Types for code list of applicable event types.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventValue
Field.Description: The credit event value appropriate to UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventType(41717). See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Credit_Event_Types for applicable event type values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the applicable currency when UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventValue(41718) is an amount. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for complex credit events.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with complex credit events.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type for the complex credit events.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventRateSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source of rate information used for credit events. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Credit_Event_Rate_Source for code list of applicable sources.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventQualifiers
Field.Description: Number of qualifiers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventQualifier
Field.Description: Specifies a complex event qualifier. Used to further qualify UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventType(41717).

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingComplexEventPeriodDateTimes
Field.Description: Number of entries in the date-time repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventPeriodDate
Field.Description: The averaging date for an Asian option. The trigger date for a Barrier or Knock option.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventPeriodTime
Field.Description: The averaging time for an Asian option.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingComplexEventPeriods
Field.Description: Number of periods in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventPeriodType
Field.Description: Specifies the period type.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center for adjusting dates and times in the schedule or date-time group. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingComplexEventRateSources
Field.Description: Number of rate sources in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventRateSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source of rate information.
Field.Elaboration: For FX, the reference source to be used for the FX spot rate.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventRateSourceType
Field.Description: Indicates whether the rate source specified is a primary or secondary source.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventReferencePage
Field.Description: Identifies the reference page from the rate source. For FX, the reference page to the spot rate is to be used for the reference FX spot rate. When UnderlyingComplexEventRateSource(41733) = 3 (ISDA Settlement Rate Option) this contains the value from the scheme that reflects the terms of the Annex A to the ISDA 1998 FX and Currency Option Definitions. See: http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/settlement-rate-option.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventReferencePageHeading
Field.Description: Identifies the reference page heading from the rate source.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingComplexEventDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar is used to adjust the event date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted complex event date.
Field.Elaboration: For example the second expiration date for a calendar spread option strategy.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the complex event date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the event date. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the UnderlyingDateAdjustment component within the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted complex event date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventFixingTime
Field.Description: The local market fixing time.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventFixingTimeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center for determining the actual fixing times. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventSources
Field.Description: Number of event sources in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventSource
Field.Description: A newspaper or electronic news service that may publish relevant information used in the determination of whether or not a credit event has occurred.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexOptPayoutPaySide
Field.Description: Trade side of payout payer.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexOptPayoutReceiveSide
Field.Description: Trade side of payout receiver.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexOptPayoutUnderlier
Field.Description: Reference to the underlier whose payments are being passed through.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexOptPayoutPercentage
Field.Description: Percentage of observed price for calculating the payout associated with the event.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexOptPayoutTime
Field.Description: The time when the payout is to occur.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexOptPayoutCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of the payout amount. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventPricePercentage
Field.Description: Specifies the price percentage at which the complex event takes effect. Impact of the event price is determined by the UnderlyingComplexEventType(2046).

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventCurrencyOne
Field.Description: Specifies the first or only reference currency of the trade. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.
Field.Elaboration: Applicable for complex FX option strategies.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventCurrencyTwo
Field.Description: Specifies the second reference currency of the trade. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.
Field.Elaboration: Applicable for complex FX option strategies.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventQuoteBasis
Field.Description: Specifies the currency pairing for the quote.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventFixedFXRate
Field.Description: Specifies the fixed FX rate alternative for FX Quantro options.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventDeterminationMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the method according to which an amount or a date is determined. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/determination-method for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventCalculationAgent
Field.Description: Used to identify the calculation agent.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventStrikePrice
Field.Description: Upper strike price for Asian option feature. Strike percentage for a Strike Spread.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventStrikeFactor
Field.Description: Strike factor for Asian option feature. Upper strike percentage for a Strike Spread.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventStrikeNumberOfOptions
Field.Description: Upper string number of options for a Strike Spread.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventsXIDRef
Field.Description: Reference to credit event table elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventNotifyingParty
Field.Description: The notifying party is the party that notifies the other party when a credit event has occurred by means of a credit event notice. If more than one party is referenced as being the notifying party then either party may notify the other of a credit event occurring.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventBusinessCenter
Field.Description: Specifies the local business center for which the credit event is to be determined. The inclusion of this business center implies that Greenwich Mean Time in Section 3.3 of the 2003 ISDA Credit Derivatives Definitions is replaced by the local time of the specified business center. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventStandardSources
Field.Description: When this element is specified and set to 'Y', indicates that ISDA defined Standard Public Sources are applicable.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventCreditEventMinimumSources
Field.Description: The minimum number of the specified public information sources that must publish information that reasonably confirms that a credit event has occurred. The market convention is two.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Specified Number.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventXID
Field.Description: Identifier of this complex event for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventXIDRef
Field.Description: Reference to a complex event elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingComplexEventSchedules
Field.Description: Number of schedules in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventScheduleStartDate
Field.Description: The start date of the schedule.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventScheduleEndDate
Field.Description: The end date of the schedule.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventScheduleFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the schedule date frequency.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventScheduleFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the schedule date frequency.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventScheduleRollConvention
Field.Description: The convention for determining the sequence of dates. It is used in conjunction with a specified frequency. Used only to override the roll convention defined in the UnderlyingDateAdjustment component in UnderlyingInstrument.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingDeliverySchedules
Field.Description: Number of delivery schedules in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of delivery schedule.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleXID
Field.Description: Identifier for this instance of delivery schedule for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleNotional
Field.Description: Physical delivery quantity.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleNotionalUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the delivery quantity unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleNotionalCommodityFrequency
Field.Description: The frequency of notional delivery.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleNegativeTolerance
Field.Description: Specifies the negative tolerance value. The value may be an absolute quantity or a percentage, as specified in UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleToleranceType(41765). Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%).

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliverySchedulePositiveTolerance
Field.Description: Specifies the positive tolerance value. The value may be an absolute quantity or a percentage, as specified in UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleToleranceType(41765). Value may exceed agreed upon value. Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%).

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleToleranceUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the tolerance value's unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleToleranceType
Field.Description: Specifies the tolerance value type.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleSettlCountry
Field.Description: Specifies the country where delivery takes place. Uses ISO 3166 2-character country code.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleSettlTimeZone
Field.Description: Delivery timezone specified as "prevailing" rather than "standard" or "daylight". See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Prevailing_Timezones for code list of applicable prevailing timezones.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleSettlFlowType
Field.Description: Specifies the delivery flow type.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleSettlHolidaysProcessingInstruction
Field.Description: Indicates whether holidays are included in the settlement periods. Required for electricity contracts.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingDeliveryScheduleSettlDays
Field.Description: Number of delivery schedules in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleSettlDay
Field.Description: Specifies the day or group of days for delivery.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleSettlTotalHours
Field.Description: The sum of the total hours specified in the UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleSettlTimeGrp component.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingDeliveryScheduleSettlTimes
Field.Description: Number of hour ranges in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleSettlStart
Field.Description: The scheduled start time for the delivery of the commodity where delivery occurs over specified times. The format of the time value is specified in UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleSettlTimeType(41776).

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleSettlEnd
Field.Description: The scheduled end time for the delivery of the commodity where delivery occurs over specified times. The format of the time value is specified in UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleSettlTimeType(41776).

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryScheduleSettlTimeType
Field.Description: Specifies the format of the delivery start and end time values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of delivery stream.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamPipeline
Field.Description: The name of the oil delivery pipeline.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamEntryPoint
Field.Description: The point at which the commodity will enter the delivery mechanism or pipeline.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamWithdrawalPoint
Field.Description: The point at which the commodity product will be withdrawn prior to delivery.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamDeliveryPoint
Field.Description: The point at which the commodity product will be delivered and received. Value specified should follow market convention appropriate for the commodity product. For bullion see http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/bullion-delivery-location for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamDeliveryRestriction
Field.Description: Specifies under what conditions the buyer and seller should be excused of their delivery obligations.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamDeliveryContingency
Field.Description: Specifies the electricity delivery contingency. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/electricity-transmission-contingency for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamDeliveryContingentPartySide
Field.Description: The trade side value of the party responsible for electricity delivery contingency.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamDeliverAtSourceIndicator
Field.Description: When this element is specified and set to 'Y', delivery of the coal product is to be at its source.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamRiskApportionment
Field.Description: Specifies how the parties to the trade apportion responsibility for the delivery of the commodity product. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Risk_Apportionment for the details of the external code list.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamRiskApportionmentSource
Field.Description: Specifies the source or legal framework for the risk apportionment. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Risk_Apportionment_Source for the details of the external code list.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamTitleTransferLocation
Field.Description: Specifies the title transfer location.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamTitleTransferCondition
Field.Description: Specifies the title transfer condition.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamImporterOfRecord
Field.Description: A party, not necessarily of the trade, who is the Importer of Record for the purposes of paying customs duties and applicable taxes or costs related to importation.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamNegativeTolerance
Field.Description: Specifies the negative tolerance value. The value may be an absolute quantity or a percentage, as specified in UnderlyingDeliveryStreamToleranceType(41793). Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%).

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamPositiveTolerance
Field.Description: Specifies the positive tolerance value. The value may be an absolute quantity or a percentage, as specified in UnderlyingDeliveryStreamToleranceType(41793).
