Value may exceed agreed upon value. Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%).

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamToleranceUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the tolerance value's unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamToleranceType
Field.Description: Specifies the tolerance value type.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamToleranceOptionSide
Field.Description: Indicates whether the tolerance is at the seller's or buyer's option.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamTotalPositiveTolerance
Field.Description: The positive percent tolerance which applies to the total quantity delivered over all shipment periods. Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%.).

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamTotalNegativeTolerance
Field.Description: The negative percent tolerance which applies to the total quantity delivered over all shipment periods. Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%.).

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamNotionalConversionFactor
Field.Description: If the notional quantity is specified in a unit that does not match the unit in which the commodity reference price is quoted, the scaling or conversion factor used to convert the commodity reference price unit into the notional quantity unit should be stated here. If there is no conversion, this field is not intended to be used.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamTransportEquipment
Field.Description: The transportation equipment with which the commodity product will be delivered and received.
Field.Elaboration: Examples of transportation equipment or mode are barge, truck, railcar, etc.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamElectingPartySide
Field.Description: A reference to the party able to choose whether the gas is delivered for a particular period e.g. a swing or interruptible contract.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingStreamAssetAttributes
Field.Description: Number of asset attribute entries in the group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamAssetAttributeType
Field.Description: Specifies the name of the attribute. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Asset_Attribute_Types for code list of applicable asset attribute types.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamAssetAttributeValue
Field.Description: Specifies the value of the attribute.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamAssetAttributeLimit
Field.Description: The limit or lower acceptable value of the attribute.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingDeliveryStreamCycles
Field.Description: Number of delivery cycles in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamCycleDesc
Field.Description: The delivery cycles during which the oil product will be transported in the pipeline.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingDeliveryStreamCycleDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingDeliveryStreamCycleDesc(41807) field.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingDeliveryStreamCycleDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingDeliveryStreamCycleDesc(41805) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingDeliveryStreamCycleDesc(41805) field.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingDeliveryStreamCommoditySources
Field.Description: Number of commodity sources in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamCommoditySource
Field.Description: The SCoTA coal cargo origin, mining region, mine(s), mining complex(es), loadout(s) or river dock(s) or other point(s) of origin that seller and buyer agree are acceptable origins for the coal product. For international coal transactions, this is the origin of the coal product. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-coal-product-source for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingExerciseDesc
Field.Description: A description of the option exercise.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingExerciseDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingExerciseDesc(41812) field.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingExerciseDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingExerciseDesc(41810) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingExerciseDesc(41810) field.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAutomaticExerciseIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates (when 'Y') that exercise is automatic when the strike price is crossed or the underlying trade is in the money.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAutomaticExerciseThresholdRate
Field.Description: The threshold rate for triggering automatic exercise.

Field.Name: UnderlyingExerciseConfirmationMethod
Field.Description: Indicates whether follow-up confirmation of exercise (written or electronic) is required following telephonic notice by the buyer to the seller or seller's agent.

Field.Name: UnderlyingManualNoticeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: Identifies the business center used for adjusting the time for manual exercise notice. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingFallbackExerciseIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the notional amount of the underlying swap, not previously exercised under the option, will be automatically exercised at the expiration time on the expiration date if at such time the buyer is in-the-money, provided that the difference between the settlement rate and the fixed rate under the relevant underlying swap is not less than one tenth of a percentage point (0.10% or 0.001).

Field.Name: UnderlyingLimitedRightToConfirmIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the Seller may request the Buyer to confirm its intent to exercise if not done on or before the expiration time on the Expiration date. If true ("Y") specific rules will apply in relation to the settlement mode.

Field.Name: UnderlyingExerciseSplitTicketIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates in physical settlement of bond and convertible bond options whether the party required to deliver the bonds will divide those to be delivered as notifying party desires to facilitate delivery obligations.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingOptionExerciseBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the option exercise dates, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the option exercise dates. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the UnderlyingDateAdjustment component within the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseEarliestDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative earliest exercise date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseEarliestDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative earliest exercise date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseEarliestDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative earliest exercise date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of exercise dates.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the frequency of exercise dates.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseStartDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted start date for calculating periodic exercise dates.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseStartDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the option exercise start date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseStartDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative exercise start date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseStartDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative exercise start date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseStartDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative option exercise start date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseStartDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted start date for calculating periodic exercise dates.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseSkip
Field.Description: The number of periods in the referenced date schedule that are between each date in the relative date schedule. Thus a skip of 2 would mean that dates are relative to every second date in the referenced schedule. If present this should have a value greater than 1.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseNominationDeadline
Field.Description: The last date (adjusted) for establishing the option exercise terms.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseFirstDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted first exercise date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseLastDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted last exercise date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseEarliestTime
Field.Description: The earliest time at which notice of exercise can be given by the buyer to the seller (or seller's agent) (i) on the expriation date, in the case of a European style option, (ii) on each Bermuda option exercise date and the expiration date, in the case of a Bermuda style option, (iii) the commencement date to, and including, the expiration date, in the case of an American option.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseLatestTime
Field.Description: Latest exercise time. See also UnderlyingOptionExerciseEarliestTime(41838).

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseTimeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center used to determine the locale for option exercise time, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingOptionExerciseDates
Field.Description: Number of dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseDate
Field.Description: The adjusted or unadjusted option exercise fixed date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of option exercise date. When specified it applies not only to the current date but to all subsequent dates in the group until overridden with a new type.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingOptionExerciseExpirationDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseExpirationDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the option exercise expiration dates, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseExpirationDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the option exercise expiration dates. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the UnderlyingDateAdjustment component within the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseExpirationDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the option exercise expiration date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseExpirationDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative exercise expiration date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseExpirationDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative exercise expiration date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseExpirationFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of exercise expiration dates.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseExpirationFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the frequency of exercise expiration dates.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseExpirationRollConvention
Field.Description: The convention for determining the sequence of exercise expiration dates. It is used in conjunction with a specified frequency. Used only to override the roll convention defined in the UnderlyingDateAdjustment component in UnderlyingInstrument.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseExpirationDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative option exercise expiration date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseExpirationTime
Field.Description: The option exercise expiration time.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseExpirationTimeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center used to determine the locale for option exercise expiration time, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingOptionExerciseExpirationDates
Field.Description: Number of fixed exercise expiration dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseExpirationDate
Field.Description: The adjusted or unadjusted option exercise expiration fixed date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExerciseExpirationDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of option exercise expiration date. When specified it applies not only to the current date but to all subsequent dates in the group until overridden with a new type.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlRateIndex
Field.Description: In an outright or forward commodity trade that is cash settled this is the index used to determine the cash payment.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlRateIndexLocation
Field.Description: This is an optional qualifying attribute of UnderlyingSettlementRateIndex(2284) such as the delivery zone for an electricity contract.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionExpirationDesc
Field.Description: Description of the option expiration.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingOptionExpirationDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingOptionExpirationDesc(2288) field.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingOptionExpirationDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingOptionExpirationDesc(2286) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingOptionExpirationDesc(2286).

Field.Name: UnderlyingSwapSubClass
Field.Description: The sub-classification or notional schedule type of the swap.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStrikeUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Used to express the unit of measure (UOM) of the price if different from the contract.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStrikeIndex
Field.Description: Specifies the index used to calculate the strike price.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStrikeIndexSpread
Field.Description: Specifies the strike price offset from the named index.

Field.Name: UnderlyingValuationSource
Field.Description: Specifies the source of trade valuation data.

Field.Name: UnderlyingValuationReferenceModel
Field.Description: Specifies the methodology and/or assumptions used to generate the trade value.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStrategyType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of trade strategy.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCommonPricingIndicator
Field.Description: When this element is specified and set to 'Y', it indicates that common pricing applies. Common pricing may be relevant for a transaction that references more than one commodity reference price.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlDisruptionProvision
Field.Description: Specifies the consequences of settlement disruption events.

Field.Name: UnderlyingInstrumentRoundingDirection
Field.Description: Specifies the rounding direction if not overridden elsewhere.

Field.Name: UnderlyingInstrumentRoundingPrecision
Field.Description: Specifies the rounding precision in terms of a number of decimal places. Note how a percentage rate rounding of 5 decimal places is expressed as a rounding precision of 7.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMarketDisruptionProvision
Field.Description: The consequences of market disruption events.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackProvision
Field.Description: Specifies the location of the fallback provision documentation.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMarketDisruptionMaximumDays
Field.Description: Specifies the maximum number of market disruption days (commodity or bullion business days) in a contract or confirmation. If none are specified, the maximum number of market disruption days is five (5).
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2005 Commodity Definition.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMarketDisruptionMaterialityPercentage
Field.Description: Used when a price materiality percentage applies to the price source disruption event and this event has been specified.
Field.Elaboration: Applicable to 2005 Commodity Definitions only.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMarketDisruptionMinimumFuturesContracts
Field.Description: Specifies the minimum futures contracts level that dictates whether or not a 'De Minimis Trading' event has occurred.
Field.Elaboration: Applicable to 1993 Commodity Definitions only.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingMarketDisruptionEvents
Field.Description: Number of disruption events in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMarketDisruptionEvent
Field.Description: Specifies the market disruption event. For commodities see http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-market-disruption for values. For foreign exchange, see http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Market_Disruption_Event for code list of applicable event types.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbacks
Field.Description: Number of fallbacks in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of disruption fallback. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-market-disruption-fallback for values.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackReferencePrices
Field.Description: Number of fallback reference securities in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierType
Field.Description: The type of reference price underlier.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityID
Field.Description: Specifies the identifier value of the security.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Specifies the class or source scheme of the security identifier.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDesc
Field.Description: Specifies the description of underlying security.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDesc(41874) field.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDesc(41872) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackUnderlierSecurityDesc(41872).

Field.Name: UnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackOpenUnits
Field.Description: If there are multiple underlying assets, this specifies the number of units (index or securities) that constitute the underlier of the swap. In the case of a basket swap, this is used to reference both the number of basket units, and the number of each asset components of the basket when these are expressed in absolute terms.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackBasketCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency if the underlier is a basket. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackBasketDivisor
Field.Description: Specifies the basket divisor amount. This value is normally used to adjust the constituent weight for pricing or to adjust for dividends, or other corporate actions.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingPaymentScheduleFixingDays
Field.Description: Number of fixing days in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentScheduleFixingDayOfWeek
Field.Description: The day of the week on which fixing takes place.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentScheduleFixingDayNumber
Field.Description: The occurrence of the day of week on which fixing takes place.
Field.Elaboration: For example, a fixing of the 3rd Friday would be DayOfWk=5 DayNum=3. If omitted every day of the week is a fixing day.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentScheduleXID
Field.Description: Identifier of this UnderlyingPaymentSchedule for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentScheduleXIDRef
Field.Description: Reference to payment schedule elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentScheduleRateCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of the schedule rate. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentScheduleRateUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The schedule rate unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentScheduleRateConversionFactor
Field.Description: The number to be multiplied by the derived floating rate of the underlying's payment schedule in order to arrive at the payment rate. If ommitted, the schedule rate conversion factor is 1.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentScheduleRateSpreadType
Field.Description: Specifies whether the rate spread is an absolute value to be added to the index rate or a percentage of the index rate.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentScheduleSettlPeriodPrice
Field.Description: The schedule settlement period price.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentScheduleSettlPeriodPriceCurrency
Field.Description: The currency of the schedule settlement period price. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentScheduleSettlPeriodPriceUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The settlement period price unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentScheduleStepUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The schedule step unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentScheduleFixingDayDistribution
Field.Description: The distribution of fixing days.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentScheduleFixingDayCount
Field.Description: The number of days over which fixing should take place.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentScheduleFixingLagPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the fixing lag duration.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentScheduleFixingLagUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the fixing lag duration.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentScheduleFixingFirstObservationDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative first observation date offset.
Field.Elaboration: If the first observation offset is specified, the observation period will start the specified interval prior to each calculation period - i.e. if the first observation offset is 4 months and the lag duration is 3 months, observations will be taken in months 4, 3 and 2 (but not 1) prior to each calculation period. If no first observation offset is specified, the observation period will end immediately preceding each calculation period.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentScheduleFixingFirstObservationDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative first observation date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFlatRateIndicator
Field.Description: When this element is specified and set to 'Y', the Flat Rate is the New Worldwide Tanker Nominal Freight Scale for the Freight Index Route taken at the Trade Date of the transaction "Fixed". If 'N' it is taken on each Pricing Date "Floating".

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFlatRateAmount
Field.Description: Specifies the actual monetary value of the flat rate when UnderlyingPaymentStreamFlatRateIndicator(41897) = 'Y'.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFlatRateCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of the actual flat rate. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamMaximumPaymentAmount
Field.Description: Specifies the limit on the total payment amount.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamMaximumPaymentCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of total payment amount limit. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamMaximumTransactionAmount
Field.Description: Specifies the limit on the payment amount that goes out in any particular calculation period.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamMaximumTransactionCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of the period payment amount limit. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFixedAmountUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Fixed payment amount unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamTotalFixedAmount
Field.Description: Specifies the total fixed payment amount.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamWorldScaleRate
Field.Description: The number of Worldscale points for purposes of the calculation of a fixed amount for a wet voyage charter commodity swap.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamContractPrice
Field.Description: The price per relevant unit for purposes of the calculation of a fixed amount for a dry voyage charter or time charter commodity swap.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamContractPriceCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of UnderlyingPaymentStreamContractPrice(41907). Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingPaymentStreamPricingBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamPricingBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the payment stream's pricing dates, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamRateIndex2CurveUnit
Field.Description: Secondary time unit associated with the payment streams floating rate index curve.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamRateIndex2CurvePeriod
Field.Description: Secondary time unit multiplier for the payment streams floating rate index curve.
Field.Elaboration: May be used for a Forward Rate Agreement (FRA) with an average rate between two curve points.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamRateIndexLocation
Field.Description: Specifies the location of the floating rate index.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamRateIndexLevel
Field.Description: This is the weather Cooling Degree Days (CDD), Heating Degree Days (HDD) or HDD index level specified as the number of (amount of) weather index units specified by the parties in the related confirmation.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamRateIndexUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The unit of measure (UOM) of the rate index level.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamSettlLevel
Field.Description: Specifies how weather index units are to be calculated.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamReferenceLevel
Field.Description: This is the weather Cooling Degree Days (CDD), Heating Degree Days (HDD) or HDD reference level specified as the number of (amount of) weather index units specified by the parties in the related confirmation.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamReferenceLevelUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The unit of measure (UOM) of the rate reference level.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamReferenceLevelEqualsZeroIndicator
Field.Description: When set to 'Y', it indicates that the weather reference level equals zero.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamRateSpreadCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of the floating rate spread. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamRateSpreadUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the unit of measure (UOM) of the floating rate spread.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamRateConversionFactor
Field.Description: The number to be multiplied by the derived floating rate of the underlying's payment stream in order to arrive at the payment rate. If omitted, the floating rate conversion factor is 1.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamRateSpreadType
Field.Description: Identifies whether the rate spread is an absolute value to be added to the index rate or a percentage of the index rate.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamLastResetRate
Field.Description: The floating rate determined at the most recent reset. The rate is expressed in decimal form, e.g. 5% is represented as 0.05.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFinalRate
Field.Description: The floating rate determined at the final reset. The rate is expressed in decimal form, e.g. 5% is represented as 0.05.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCalculationLagPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the calculation lag duration.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCalculationLagUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the calculation lag duration.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFirstObservationDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative first observation date offset.
Field.Elaboration: If the first observation offset is specified, the observation period will start the specified interval prior to each calculation period - i.e. if the first observation offset is 4 months and the lag duration is 3 months, observations will be taken in months 4, 3 and 2 (but not 1) prior to each calculation period. If no first observation offset is specified, the observation period will end immediately preceding each calculation period.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFirstObservationDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative first observation date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamPricingDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the commodity pricing day type.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamPricingDayDistribution
Field.Description: The distribution of pricing days.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamPricingDayCount
Field.Description: The number of days over which pricing should take place.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamPricingBusinessCalendar
Field.Description: Specifies the business calendar to use for pricing. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-business-calendar for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamPricingBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the payment stream's pricing dates. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the UnderlyingDateAdjustment component within the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingPaymentStreamPaymentDates
Field.Description: Number of payment dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamPaymentDate
Field.Description: The adjusted or unadjusted fixed stream payment date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamPaymentDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of payment date. When specified it applies not only to the current date but to all subsequent dates in the group until overridden with a new type.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamMasterAgreementPaymentDatesIndicator
Field.Description: When set to 'Y', it indicates that payment dates are specified in the relevant master agreement.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingPaymentStreamPricingDates
Field.Description: Number of pricing dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamPricingDate
Field.Description: An adjusted or unadjusted fixed pricing date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamPricingDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of pricing date. When specified it applies not only to the current date but to all subsequent dates in the group until overridden with a new type.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingPaymentStreamPricingDays
Field.Description: Number of pricing days in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamPricingDayOfWeek
Field.Description: The day of the week on which pricing takes place.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamPricingDayNumber
Field.Description: The occurrence of the day of week on which pricing takes place.
Field.Elaboration: For example a pricing day of the 3rd Friday would be DayOfWk=5 DayNum=3.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingPricingDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPricingDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the pricing or fixing date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPricingDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted pricing or fixing date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPricingDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the pricing or fixing date. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the UnderlyingDateAdjustment component within the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPricingDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted pricing or fixing date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPricingTime
Field.Description: The local market pricing or fixing time.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPricingTimeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: Specifies the business center for determining the pricing or fixing time. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingStreamCalculationPeriodDates
Field.Description: Number of calculation period dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCalculationPeriodDate
Field.Description: The adjusted or unadjusted fixed calculation period date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCalculationPeriodDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of fixed calculation period date. When specified it applies not only to the current date but to all subsequent dates in the group until overridden with a new type.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCalculationPeriodDatesXID
Field.Description: Identifier of this calculation period for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCalculationPeriodDatesXIDRef
Field.Description: Cross reference to another calculation period for duplicating its properties.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCalculationBalanceOfFirstPeriod
Field.Description: When specified and set to 'Y', it indicates that the first calculation period should run from the effective date to the end of the calendar period in which the effective date falls (e.g. Jan 15 - Jan 31 if the calculation periods are one month long and effective date is Jan 15.). If 'N' or not specified, it indicates that the first calculation period should run from the effective date for one whole period (e.g. Jan 15 to Feb 14 if the calculation periods are one month long and the effective date is Jan 15.).

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCalculationCorrectionPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the length of time after the publication of the data when corrections can be made.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCalculationCorrectionUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the length of time after the publication of the data when corrections can be made.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the commodity delivery date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityBase
Field.Description: Specifies the general base type of the commodity traded. Where possible, this should follow the naming convention used in the 2005 ISDA Commodity Definitions.
Field.Elaboration: Examples of general commodity base types include:Metal, Bullion, Oil, Natural Gas, Coal, Electricity, Inter-Energy, Grains, Oils Seeds, Dairy, Livestock, Forestry, Softs, Weather, Emissions.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of commodity product. For coal see http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-coal-product-type for values. For metals see http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-metal-product-type for values. For bullion see http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Bullion_Types for the external code list of bullion types.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySecurityID
Field.Description: Specifies the market identifier for the commodity.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the class or source of the UnderlyingStreamCommoditySecurityIDSource(41966) value.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityDesc
Field.Description: Description of the commodity asset.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingStreamCommodityDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingStreamCommodityDesc(41970) field.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingStreamCommodityDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingStreamCommodityDesc(41968) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingStreamCommodityDesc(41968) field.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The unit of measure (UOM) of the commodity asset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityCurrency
Field.Description: Identifies the currency of the commodity asset. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityExchange
Field.Description: Identifies the exchange where the commodity is traded.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityRateSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source of rate information used for commodities. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Commodity_Rate_Source for code list of applicable sources.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityRateReferencePage
Field.Description: Identifies the reference "page" from the rate source.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityRateReferencePageHeading
Field.Description: Identifies the page heading from the rate source.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamDataProvider
Field.Description: Specifies the commodity data or information provider. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-information-provider for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityPricingType
Field.Description: Specifies how the pricing or rate setting of the trade is to be determined or based upon. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Commodity_Rate_Pricing_Type for code list of applicable commodity pricing types.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityNearbySettlDayPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the nearby settlement day.
Field.Elaboration: When the commodity transaction references a futures contract, the delivery or settlement dates are a nearby month or week. For example, for eighth nearby month use Period=8 and Unit=Mo.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityNearbySettlDayUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the nearby settlement day.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted commodity delivery date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the commodity delivery date. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the UnderlyingDateAdjustment component within the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted commodity delivery date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlMonth
Field.Description: Specifies a fixed single month for commodity delivery.
Field.Elaboration: Use "1" for January, "2" for February, etc.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlDateRollPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the commodity delivery date roll.
Field.Elaboration: For a commodity transaction that references a listed future via the delivery dates, this is the day offset on which the specified future will roll to the next nearby month when the referenced future expires.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlDateRollUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the commodity delivery date roll.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the commodity delivery roll day type.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityXID
Field.Description: Identifier of this stream commodity for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityXIDRef
Field.Description: Reference to a stream commodity elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingStreamCommodityAltIDs
Field.Description: Number of alternate security identifers.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityAltID
Field.Description: Alternate security identifier value for the commodity.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityAltIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the class or source of the alternate commodity security identifier.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingStreamCommodityDataSources
Field.Description: Number of commodity data sources in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityDataSourceID
Field.Description: Data source identifier.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityDataSourceIDType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of data source identifier.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlDays
Field.Description: Number of days in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlDay
Field.Description: Specifies the day or group of days for delivery.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlTotalHours
Field.Description: Sum of the hours specified in UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlTimeGrp.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlTimes
Field.Description: Number of hour ranges in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlStart
Field.Description: The start time for commodity settlement where delivery occurs over time. The time format is specified by the settlement time type.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlEnd
Field.Description: The end time for commodity settlement where delivery occurs over time. The time format is specified by the settlement time type.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlTimeType
Field.Description: Specifies the format of the commodity settlement start and end times.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlPeriods
Field.Description: Number of commodity settlement periods in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlCountry
Field.Description: Specifies the country where delivery takes place. Uses ISO 3166 2-character country code.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlTimeZone
Field.Description: Commodity delivery timezone specified as "prevailing" rather than "standard" or "daylight". See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Prevailing_Timezones for code list of applicable prevailing timezones.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlFlowType
Field.Description: Specifies the commodity delivery flow type.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlPeriodNotional
Field.Description: Specifies the delivery quantity associated with this settlement period.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlPeriodNotionalUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the unit of measure (UOM) of the delivery quantity associated with this settlement period.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlPeriodFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the settlement period frequency.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlPeriodFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the settlement period frequency.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlPeriodPrice
Field.Description: The settlement period price.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlPeriodPriceUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the settlement period price unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlPeriodPriceCurrency
Field.Description: The currency of the settlement period price. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlHolidaysProcessingInstruction
Field.Description: Indicates whether holidays are included in the settlement periods. Required for electricity contracts.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlPeriodXID
Field.Description: Identifier of this settlement period for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommoditySettlPeriodXIDRef
Field.Description: Cross reference to another settlement period for duplicating its properties.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamXID
Field.Description: Identifier of this UnderlyingStream for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamNotionalXIDRef
Field.Description: Cross reference to another UnderlyingStream notional for duplicating its properties.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamNotionalFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the swap stream's notional frequency.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamNotionalFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the swap stream's notional frequency.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamNotionalCommodityFrequency
Field.Description: The commodity's notional or quantity delivery frequency.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamNotionalUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the delivery quantity unit of measure (UOM).

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamTotalNotional
Field.Description: Specifies the total notional or delivery quantity over the term of the contract.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamTotalNotionalUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: Specifies the unit of measure (UOM) for the total notional or delivery quantity over the term of the contract.

Field.Name: AllocGrossTradeAmt
Field.Description: Total amount traded for this account (i.e. quantity * price) expressed in units of currency.

Field.Name: RiskLimitReportStatus
Field.Description: Status of risk limit report.

Field.Name: RiskLimitReportRejectReason
Field.Description: The reason for rejecting the PartyRiskLimitsReport(35=CM) or PartyRiskLimitsUpdateReport(35=CR).

Field.Name: RiskLimitCheckRequestID
Field.Description: The unique identifier of the PartyRiskLimitCheckRequest(35=DF) message.

Field.Name: RiskLimitCheckID
Field.Description: The unique and static identifier, at the business entity level, of a risk limit check request.

Field.Name: RiskLimitCheckTransType
Field.Description: Specifies the transaction type of the risk limit check request.

Field.Name: RiskLimitCheckType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of limit check message.

Field.Name: RiskLimitCheckRequestRefID
Field.Description: Specifies the message reference identifier of the risk limit check request message.

Field.Name: RiskLimitCheckRequestType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of limit amount check being requested.

Field.Name: RiskLimitCheckAmount
Field.Description: Specifies the amount being requested for approval.

Field.Name: RiskLimitCheckRequestStatus
Field.Description: Indicates the status of the risk limit check request.

Field.Name: RiskLimitCheckRequestResult
Field.Description: Result of the credit limit check request.

Field.Name: RiskLimitApprovedAmount
Field.Description: The credit/risk limit amount approved.

Field.Name: PartyActionRequestID
Field.Description: The unique identifier of the PartyActionRequest(35=DH) message.

Field.Name: PartyActionType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of action to take or was taken for a given party.

Field.Name: ApplTestMessageIndicator
Field.Description: Used to indicate whether the message being sent is to test the receiving application's availability to process the message. When set to "Y" the message is a test message. If not specified, the message is by default not a test message.

Field.Name: PartyActionReportID
Field.Description: The unique identifier of the PartyActionReport(35=DI) message as assigned by the message sender.

Field.Name: PartyActionResponse
Field.Description: Specifies the action taken as a result of the PartyActionType(2239) of the PartyActionRequest(35=DH) message.

Field.Name: PartyActionRejectReason
Field.Description: Specifies the reason the PartyActionRequest(35=DH) was rejected.

Field.Name: RefRiskLimitCheckID
Field.Description: The reference identifier of the PartyRiskLimitCheckRequest(35=DF) message, or a similar out of band message, that contained the approval for the risk/credit limit check request.

Field.Name: RefRiskLimitCheckIDType
Field.Description: Specifies which type of identifier is specified in RefRiskLimitCheckID(2334) field.

Field.Name: RiskLimitVelocityPeriod
Field.Description: The time interval for which the clip size limit applies. The velocity time unit is expressed in RiskLimitVelocityUnit(2337).

Field.Name: RiskLimitVelocityUnit
Field.Description: Unit of time in which RiskLimitVelocityPeriod(2336) is expressed.

Field.Name: RequestingPartyRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Qualifies the value of RequestingPartyRole(1660).

Field.Name: RiskLimitCheckModelType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of credit limit check model workflow to apply for the specified party

Field.Name: RiskLimitCheckStatus
Field.Description: Indicates the status of the risk limit check performed on a trade.

Field.Name: SideRiskLimitCheckStatus
Field.Description: Indicates the status of the risk limit check performed on the side of a trade.

Field.Name: NoEntitlementTypes
Field.Description: Number of entitlement types in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegMidPx
Field.Description: Leg Mid price/rate. For OTC swaps, this is the mid-market mark (for example, as defined by CFTC). For uncleared OTC swaps, LegMidPx(2346) and the MidPx(631) fields are mutually exclusive.

Field.Name: RegulatoryTransactionType
Field.Description: Specifies the regulatory mandate or rule that the transaction complies with.

Field.Name: BatchID
Field.Description: Unique Identifier for a batch of messages.

Field.Name: BatchTotalMessages
Field.Description: Total # of messages contained within batch.

Field.Name: BatchProcessMode
Field.Description: Indicates the processing mode for a batch of messages.

Field.Name: CollateralPortfolioID
Field.Description: Identifier of the collateral portfolio when reporting on a portfolio basis.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamDeliveryPointSource
Field.Description: Identifies the class or source of DeliveryStreamDeliveryPoint(41062).

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamDeliveryPointDesc
Field.Description: Description of the delivery point identified in DeliveryStreamDeliveryPoint(41062).

Field.Name: TradingUnitPeriodMultiplier
Field.Description: Indicates the number of contract periods associated with the minimum trading unit for a given contract duration resulting in the number of total traded contracts.
Field.Elaboration: As an example, 456 is the number of off-peak periods for a product with a minimum trading unit of 5 MWh resulting in 2280 total traded contracts.

Field.Name: LegTradingUnitPeriodMultiplier
Field.Description: Indicates the number of contract periods associated with the minimum trading unit for a given contract duration resulting in the number of total traded contracts.
Field.Elaboration: As an example, 456 is the number of off-peak periods for a product with a minimum trading unit of 5 MWh resulting in 2280 total traded contracts.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamDeliveryPointDesc
Field.Description: Description of the delivery point identified in LegDeliveryStreamDeliveryPoint(41433).

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamDeliveryPointSource
Field.Description: Identifies the class or source of LegDeliveryStreamDeliveryPoint(41433).

Field.Name: LegTotalTradeQty
Field.Description: Expresses the total quantity traded over the life of the contract when LegLastQty(1418) is to be repeated periodically over the term of the contract. The value is the product of LegLastQty(1418) and LegTradingUnitPeriodMultiplier(2353).

Field.Name: LegLastMultipliedQty
Field.Description: Expresses the quantity bought/sold when LastQty is expressed in contracts. Used in addition to LegLastQty(1418), it is the product of LegLastQty(1418) and LegContractMultiplier(614).

Field.Name: LegTotalGrossTradeAmt
Field.Description: Expresses the full total monetary value of the traded contract. The value is the product of LegLastPx(637) and LegTotalTradeQty(2357) or LegTotalTradeMultipliedQty(2360), if priced in units instead of contracts.

Field.Name: LegTotalTradeMultipliedQty
Field.Description: Expresses the total trade quantity in units where LegContractMultiplier(614) is not 1. The value is the product of LegTotalTradeQty(2357) and LegContractMultiplier(614).

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamDeliveryPointDesc
Field.Description: Description of the delivery point identified in UnderlyingDeliveryStreamDeliveryPoint(41781).

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamDeliveryPointSource
Field.Description: Identifies the class or source of UnderlyingDeliveryStreamDeliveryPoint(41781).

Field.Name: UnderlyingTradingUnitPeriodMultiplier
Field.Description: Indicates the number of contract periods associated with the minimum trading unit for a given contract duration resulting in the number of total traded contracts.
Field.Elaboration: As an example, 456 is the number of off-peak periods for a product with a minimum trading unit of 5 MWh resulting in 2280 total traded contracts.

Field.Name: PosReportAction
Field.Description: Indicates action that triggered the Position Report.

Field.Name: SettlForwardPoints
Field.Description: FX forward points added to SettlPrice(730). The value is expressed in decimal form and may be a negative.
Field.Elaboration: As an example, 61.99 points is expressed as 0.006199.

Field.Name: SettlPriceFxRateCalc
Field.Description: Specifies whether LastPx(31) [TradeCaptureReport] or SettlPrice(730) [PositionReport] should be multiplied or divided.

Field.Name: TotalTradeQty
Field.Description: Expresses the total quantity traded over the life of the contract when LastQty(32) is repeated periodically over the term of the contract. The value is the product of LastQty(32) and TradingUnitPeriodMultiplier(2353).

Field.Name: LastMultipliedQty
Field.Description: Expresses the quantity bought or sold when LastQty(32) is expressed in number of contracts. Used in addition to LastQty(32). It is the product of LastQty(32) and ContractMultiplier(231).

Field.Name: TotalGrossTradeAmt
Field.Description: Expresses the full total monetary value of the traded contract. The value is the product of LastPx(31) and TotalTradeQty(2367) or TotalTradeMultipliedQty(2370), if priced in units instead of contracts.

Field.Name: TotalTradeMultipliedQty
Field.Description: Expresses the total trade quantity in units where ContractMultiplier(231) is not 1. The value is the product of TotalTradeQty(2367) and ContractMultiplier(231).

Field.Name: EncodedTradeContinuationText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the TradeContinuationText(2374) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding(347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the TradeContinuationText(2374) field.

Field.Name: EncodedTradeContinuationTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedTradeContinuationText(2371) field.

Field.Name: IntraFirmTradeIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the trade or position was entered into as an intra-group transaction, i.e. between two units of the same parent entity having majority ownership interest in both counterparties.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of EMIR this refers to Regulation (EU) 648/2012 Article 3 "intragroup transactions" section 1 which states: "In relation to a non-financial counterparty, an intragroup transaction is an OTC derivative contract entered into with another counterparty which is part of the same group provided that both counterparties are included in the same consolidation on a full basis and they are subject to an appropriate centralised risk evaluation, measurement and control procedures and that counterparty is established in the Union or, if it is established in a third country, the Commission has adopted an implementing act under Article 13(2) in respect of that third country. Canada's similar requirement is under Appendix A to OSC Rule 91-507."

Field.Name: TradeContinuationText
Field.Description: Elaboration of the purpose or action of the regulatory report when TradeContinuation(1937)=99 (Other).

Field.Name: TaxonomyType
Field.Description: The type of identification taxonomy used to identify the security.

Field.Name: PartyRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Used to further qualify the value of PartyRole(452).

Field.Name: DerivativeInstrumentPartyRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Used to further qualify the value of DerivativeInstrumentPartyRole(1295).

Field.Name: InstrumentPartyRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Used to further qualify the value of InstrumentPartyRole(1051).

Field.Name: LegInstrumentPartyRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Used to further qualify the value of LegInstrumentPartyRole(2257).

Field.Name: LegProvisionPartyRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Used to further qualify the value of LegProvisionPartyRole(40536).

Field.Name: Nested2PartyRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Used to further qualify the value of Nested2PartyRole(759).

Field.Name: Nested3PartyRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Used to further qualify the value of Nested3PartyRole(951).

Field.Name: Nested4PartyRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Used to further qualify the value of Nested4PartyRole(1417).

Field.Name: NestedPartyRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Used to further qualify the value of NestedPartyRole(538).

Field.Name: ProvisionPartyRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Used to further qualify the value of ProvisionPartyRole(40177).

Field.Name: RequestedPartyRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Used to further qualify the value of RequestedPartyRole(1509).

Field.Name: RootPartyRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Used to further qualify the value of RootPartyRole(1119).

Field.Name: SettlPartyRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Used to further qualify the value of SettlPartyRole(784).

Field.Name: UnderlyingInstrumentPartyRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Used to further qualify the value of UnderlyingInstrumentPartyRole(1061).

Field.Name: AllocRefRiskLimitCheckID
Field.Description: The reference identifier to the PartyRiskLimitCheckRequest(35=DF), or a similar out of band message, message that contained the approval or rejection for risk/credit limit check for this allocation.

Field.Name: AllocRefRiskLimitCheckIDType
Field.Description: Specifies which type of identifier is specified in AllocRefRiskLimitCheckID(2392) field.

Field.Name: LimitUtilizationAmt
Field.Description: The total amount of the limit that has been drawn down against the counterparty. This includes the amount for prior trades. It may or may not include the amount for the given trade, specified in LastLimitAmt(1632), depending upon whether the given trade is considered pending.

Field.Name: LimitAmt
Field.Description: The limit for the counterparty. This represents the total limit amount, independent of any amount already utilized.

Field.Name: LimitRole
Field.Description: Indicates the scope of the limit by role.
Field.Elaboration: Used to indicate whether this is a customer account limit, a clearing firm limit, etc.

Field.Name: RegulatoryTradeIDScope
Field.Description: Specifies the scope to which the RegulatoryTradeID(1903) applies. Used when a trade must be assigned more than one identifier, e.g. one for the clearing member and another for the client on a cleared trade as with the principal model in Europe.

Field.Name: SideRegulatoryTradeIDScope
Field.Description: Specifies the scope to which the SideRegulatoryTradeID(1972) applies. Used when a trade must be assigned more than one identifier, e.g. one for the clearing member and another for the client on a cleared trade as with the principal model in Europe.

Field.Name: AllocRegulatoryTradeIDScope
Field.Description: Specifies the scope to which the AllocRegulatoryTradeID(1909) applies. Used when a trade must be assigned more than one identifier, e.g. one for the clearing member and another for the client on a cleared trade as with the principal model in Europe.

Field.Name: AllocRegulatoryLegRefID
Field.Description: Identifies the leg of the trade the entry applies to by referencing the leg's LegID(1788).

Field.Name: RegulatoryLegRefID
Field.Description: Identifies the leg of the trade the entry applies to by referencing the leg's LegID(1788).

Field.Name: SideRegulatoryLegRefID
Field.Description: Identifies the leg of the trade the entry applies to by referencing the leg's LegID(1788).

Field.Name: EffectiveBusinessDate
Field.Description: Specifies an explicit business date for associated reference data or transaction. Used when an implicit date is not sufficiently specific.

Field.Name: ListManualOrderIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates if the list of orders was initially received manually (as opposed to electronically) or if it was entered manually (as opposed to entered by automated trading software).

Field.Name: EntitlementSubType
Field.Description: Subtype of an entitlement specified in EntitlementType(1775).

Field.Name: QuoteModelType
Field.Description: Quote model type

Field.Name: ComplianceText
Field.Description: Free text for compliance information required for regulatory reporting.

Field.Name: EncodedComplianceTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedComplianceText(2352) field.

Field.Name: EncodedComplianceText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ComplianceText(2404) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ComplianceText(2404) field.

Field.Name: ExecMethod
Field.Description: Specifies how the transaction was executed, e.g. via an automated execution platform or other method.

Field.Name: PricePrecision
Field.Description: Specifies the price decimal precision of the instrument.
Field.Elaboration: For FX, this specifies the pip size in which forward points are calculated. Point (pip) size varies by currency pair. Major currencies are all traded in points of 0.0001, with the exception of JPY which has a point size of 0.01.

Field.Name: TradeContingency
Field.Description: Indicates the contingency attribute for a trade in an asset class that may be contingent on the clearing of a corresponding paired trade (for example Exchange for Physical (EFP), Exchange for Swap (EFS), Exchange for Related (EFR) or Exchange for Option (EFO), collectively called EFRPs). Once the paired trade clears or fails to clear, the related trade (the trade which carries this attribute) ceases to exist.

Field.Name: ComplexEventSpotRate
Field.Description: FX spot rate.

Field.Name: ComplexEventForwardPoints
Field.Description: FX forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventSpotRate
Field.Description: FX spot rate.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventForwardPoints
Field.Description: FX forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: RateSourceReferemcePageHeading
Field.Description: Identifies the page heading from the rate source.

Field.Name: RelatedToSecurityID
Field.Description: The security identifier of the instrument, instrument leg or underlying instrument with which the related instrument has correlation.

Field.Name: RelatedToSecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies class or source of the RelatedToSecurityID(2413) value.

Field.Name: RelatedToStreamXIDRef
Field.Description: StreamXID(41303), LegStreamXID(41700) or UnderlyingStreamXID(42016) of the stream with which the related instrument has correlation.

Field.Name: FirmTradeEventID
Field.Description: An identifier created by the trading party for the life cycle event associated with this report.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventSpotRate
Field.Description: FX spot rate.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventForwardPoints
Field.Description: FX forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: LegMarketDisruptionValue
Field.Description: Applicable value for LegMarketDisruptionEvent(41468).

Field.Name: LegMarketDisruptionFallbackValue
Field.Description: Applicable value for LegMarketDisruptionFallbackType(41470).

Field.Name: MarketDisruptionValue
Field.Description: Applicable value for MarketDisruptionEvent(41093).

Field.Name: MarketDisruptionFallbackValue
Field.Description: Applicable value for MarketDisruptionFallbackType(41095).

Field.Name: PaymentSubType
Field.Description: Used to further clarify the value of PaymentType(40213).

Field.Name: PaymentLegRefID
Field.Description: Identifies the instrument leg in which this payment applies to by referencing the leg's LegID(1788).

Field.Name: UnderlyingMarketDisruptionValue
Field.Description: Applicable value for UnderlyingMarketDisruptionEvent(41865).

Field.Name: UnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackValue
Field.Description: Applicable value for UnderlyingMarketDisruptionFallbackType(41867).

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingAdditionalTermBondRefs
Field.Description: Number of bonds in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondSecurityID
Field.Description: Security identifier of the bond.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondSecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source scheme of the UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondSecurityID(41341) value.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondDesc
Field.Description: Description of the bond.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingAdditionalTermBondDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingAdditionalTermBondDesc(41711) field.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingAdditionalTermBondDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondDesc(41709) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondDesc(41709) field.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency the bond value is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondIssuer
Field.Description: Issuer of the bond.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingAdditionalTermBondIssuerLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingAdditionalTermBondIssuer(42026) field.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingAdditionalTermBondIssuer
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondIssuer(42017) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondIssuer(42017) field.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondSeniority
Field.Description: Specifies the bond's payment priority in the event of a default.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondCouponType
Field.Description: Coupon type of the bond.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondCouponRate
Field.Description: Coupon rate of the bond. See also CouponRate(223).

Field.Name: UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondMaturityDate
Field.Description: The maturity date of the bond.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondParValue
Field.Description: The par value of the bond.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondCurrentTotalIssuedAmount
Field.Description: Total issued amount of the bond.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondCouponFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of the bond's coupon payment.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondCouponFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the frequency of the bond's coupon payment.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAdditionalTermBondDayCount
Field.Description: The day count convention used in interest calculations for a bond or an interest bearing security.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingAdditionalTerms
Field.Description: Number of additional terms in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAdditionalTermConditionPrecedentBondIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the condition precedent bond is applicable. The swap contract is only valid if the bond is issued and if there is any dispute over the terms of fixed stream then the bond terms would be used.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAdditionalTermDiscrepancyClauseIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the discrepancy clause is applicable.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingCashSettlDealers
Field.Description: Number of dealers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlDealer
Field.Description: Identifies the dealer from whom price quotations for the reference obligation are obtained for the purpose of cash settlement valuation calculation.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Dealer

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingCashSettlTerms
Field.Description: Number of elements in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency the UnderlyingCashSettlAmount(42054) is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlValuationFirstBusinessDayOffset
Field.Description: The number of business days after settlement conditions have been satisfied, when the calculation agent is to obtain a price quotation on the reference obligation for purposes of cash settlement.
Field.Elaboration: Associated with ISDA 2003 Term: Valuation Date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlValuationSubsequentBusinessDaysOffset
Field.Description: The number of business days between successive valuation dates when multiple valuation dates are applicable for cash settlement.
Field.Elaboration: Associated with ISDA 2003 Term: Valuation Date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlNumOfValuationDates
Field.Description: Where multiple valuation dates are specified as being applicable for cash settlement, this element specifies the number of applicable valuation dates.
Field.Elaboration: Associated with ISDA 2003 Term: Valuation Date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlValuationTime
Field.Description: Time of valuation.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlBusinessCenter
Field.Description: Identifies the business center calendar used at valuation time for cash settlement purposes e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlQuoteMethod
Field.Description: The type of quote used to determine the cash settlement price.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlQuoteAmount
Field.Description: When determining the cash settlement amount, if weighted average price quotes are to be obtained for the reference obligation, this is the upper limit to the outstanding principal balance of the reference obligation for which the quote should be obtained. If not specifed, the ISDA definitions provide for a fallback amount equal to floating rate payer calculation amount.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Quotation Amount.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlQuoteCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency the UnderlyingCashSettlQuoteAmount(42049) is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlMinimumQuoteAmount
Field.Description: When determining the cash settlement amount, if weighted average price quotes are to be obtained for the reference obligation, this is the minimum intended threshold amount of outstanding principal balance of the reference obligation for which the quote should be obtained. If not specified, the ISDA definitions provide for a fallback amount of the lower of either USD1,000,000 (or its equivalent in the relevent obligation currency) or the (minimum) quoted amount.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Minimum Quotation Amount.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlMinimumQuoteCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency the UnderlyingCashSettlQuoteAmount(42049) is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlBusinessDays
Field.Description: The number of business days used in the determination of the cash settlement payment date.
Field.Elaboration: If a cash settlement amount is specified, the cash settlement payment date will be this number of business days following the calculation of the final price. If a cash settlement amount is not specified, the cash settlement payment date will be this number of business days after all conditions to settlement are satisfied. ISDA 2003 Term: Cash Settlement Date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlAmount
Field.Description: The amount paid between the trade parties, seller to the buyer, for cash settlement on the cash settlement date.
Field.Elaboration: If not specified this would typically be calculated as ((100 or the reference price) - reference obligation price) x floating rate payer calculation amount. Price values are all expressed as a percentage. ISDA 2003 Term: Cash Settlement Amount.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlRecoveryFactor
Field.Description: Used for fixed recovery, this specifies the recovery level as determined at contract inception, to be applied in the event of a default. The factor is used to calculate the amount paid by the seller to the buyer for cash settlement on the cash settlement date. The amount is calculated is (1 - UnderlyingCashSettlRecoveryFactor(42055)) x floating rate payer calculation amount. The currency is derived from the floating rate payer calculation amount.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlFixedTermIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether fixed settlement is applicable or not applicable in a recovery lock.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlAccruedInterestIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether accrued interest is included or not in the value provided in UnderlyingCashSettlAmount(42054). For cash settlement this specifies whether quotations should be obtained inclusive or not of accrued interest. For physical settlement this specifies whether the buyer should deliver the obligation with an outstanding principal balance that includes or excludes accrued interest.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Include/Exclude Accrued Interest.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlValuationMethod
Field.Description: The ISDA defined methodology for determining the final price of the reference obligation for purposes of cash settlement.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Valuation Method

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlTermXID
Field.Description: Name referenced from UnderlyingSettlementTermXIDRef(41315).

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingPhysicalSettlTerms
Field.Description: Number of entries in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPhysicalSettlCurrency
Field.Description: Currency of physical settlement. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPhysicalSettlBusinessDays
Field.Description: A number of business days. Its precise meaning is dependent on the context in which this element is used.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Business Day.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPhysicalSettlMaximumBusinessDays
Field.Description: A maximum number of business days. Its precise meaning is dependent on the context in which this element is used. Intended to be used to limit a particular ISDA fallback provision.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPhysicalSettlTermXID
Field.Description: A named string value referenced by UnderlyingSettlementTermXIDRef(41315).

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingPhysicalSettlDeliverableObligations
Field.Description: Number of entries in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPhysicalSettlDeliverableObligationType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of delivery obligation applicable for physical settlement. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Deliverable_Obligation_Types for code list for applicable deliverable obligation types.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPhysicalSettlDeliverableObligationValue
Field.Description: Physical settlement delivery obligation value appropriate to UnderlyingPhysicalSettlDeliverableObligationType(42066). See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Deliverable_Obligation_Types for applicable obligation type values.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingProtectionTerms
Field.Description: Number of protection terms in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermNotional
Field.Description: The notional amount of protection coverage for a floating rate.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Floating Rate Payer Calculation Amount.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermCurrency
Field.Description: The currency of UnderlyingProtectionTermNotional(42069). Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermSellerNotifies
Field.Description: The notifying party is the party that notifies the other party when a credit event has occurred by means of a credit event notice. If more than one party is referenced as being the notifying party then either party may notify the other of a credit event occurring. UnderlyingProtectionTermSellerNotifies(42071)=Y indicates that the seller notifies.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Notifying Party.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermBuyerNotifies
Field.Description: The notifying party is the party that notifies the other party when a credit event has occurred by means of a credit event notice. If more than one party is referenced as being the notifying party then either party may notify the other of a credit event occurring. UnderlyingProtectionTermBuyerNotifies(42072)=Y indicates that the buyer notifies.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Notifying Party.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermEventBusinessCenter
Field.Description: When used, the business center indicates the local time of the business center that replaces the Greenwich Mean Time in Section 3.3 of the 2003 ISDA Credit Derivatives Definitions. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermStandardSources
Field.Description: Indicates whether ISDA defined Standard Public Sources are applicable (UnderlyingProtectionTermStandardSources(42074)=Y) or not.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermEventMinimumSources
Field.Description: The minimum number of the specified public information sources that must publish information that reasonably confirms that a credit event has occurred. The market convention is two.
Field.Elaboration: ISDA 2003 Term: Specified Number.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermXID
Field.Description: A named string value referenced by UnderlyingProtectionTermXIDRef(41314).

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingProtectionTermEvents
Field.Description: Number of protection term events in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermEventType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of credit event applicable to the protection terms. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Protection_Term_Event_Types for code list of applicable event types.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermEventValue
Field.Description: Protection term event value appropriate to UnderlyingProtectionTermEventType(42078). See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Protection_Term_Event_Types for applicable event type values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermEventCurrency
Field.Description: Applicable currency if UnderlyingProtectionTermEventValue(42079) is an amount. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermEventPeriod
