Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for protection term events.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermEventUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with protection term events.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermEventDayType
Field.Description: Day type for events that specify a period and unit.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermEventRateSource
Field.Description: Rate source for events that specify a rate source, e.g. Floating rate interest shortfall.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingProtectionTermEventQualifiers
Field.Description: Number of qualifiers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermEventQualifier
Field.Description: Protection term event qualifier. Used to further qualify UnderlyingProtectionTermEventType(43078).

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingProtectionTermObligations
Field.Description: Number of obligations in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermObligationType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of obligation applicable to the protection terms. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Protection_Term_Obligation_Types for code list of applicable obligation types.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermObligationValue
Field.Description: Protection term obligation value appropriate to UnderlyingProtectionTermObligationType(42088). See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Protection_Term_Obligation_Types for applicable obligation type values.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingProtectionTermEventNewsSources
Field.Description: Number of event news sources in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProtectionTermEventNewsSource
Field.Description: Newspaper or electronic news service or source that may publish relevant information used in the determination of whether or not a credit event has occurred.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlPaymentDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the provisional cash settlement payment's termination, or relative termination, date. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the UnderlyingDateAdjustment component within the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlPaymentDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the cash settlement payment date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlPaymentDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative cash settlement payment date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlPaymentDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative cash settlement payment date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlPaymentDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the provision's relative cash settlement payment date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlPaymentDateRangeFirst
Field.Description: First date in range when a settlement date range is provided.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlPaymentDateRangeLast
Field.Description: Last date in range when a settlement date range is provided.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingProvisionCashSettlPaymentDates
Field.Description: Number of UnderlyingProvision cash settlement payment dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlPaymentDate
Field.Description: The cash settlement payment date, unadjusted or adjusted depending on UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlPaymentDateType(42101).

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlPaymentDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of date (e.g. adjusted for holidays).

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlQuoteSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source of quote information.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlQuoteReferencePage
Field.Description: Identifies the reference "page" from the quote source.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlValueTime
Field.Description: A time specified in 24-hour format, e.g. 11am would be represented as 11:00:00. The time of the cash settlement valuation date when the cash settlement amount will be determined according to the cash settlement method if the parties have not otherwise been able to agree to the cash settlement amount.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlValueTimeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: Identifies the business center calendar used with the provision's cash settlement valuation time. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlValueDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the cash settlement valuation date. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the UnderlyingDateAdjustment component within the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlValueDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the cash settlement value date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlValueDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative cash settlement value date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlValueDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative cash settlement value date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlValueDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the provision's relative cash settlement value date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlValueDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted cash settlement value date.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseFixedDates
Field.Description: Number of UnderlyingProvision option exercise fixed dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseFixedDate
Field.Description: A predetermined option exercise date, unadjusted or adjusted depending on UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseFixedDateType(42114).

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseFixedDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of date (e.g. adjusted for holidays).

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the underlying instrument's provision's option exercise date. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the UnderlyingDateAdjustment component within the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseEarliestDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the interval to the first (and possibly only) exercise date in the exercise period.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseEarliestDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the interval to the first (and possibly only) exercise date in the exercise period.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of subsequent exercise dates in the exercise period following the earliest exercise date. An interval of 1 day should be used to indicate an American style exercise frequency.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the frequency of subsequent exercise dates in the exercise period following the earliest exercise date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseStartDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted first day of the exercise period for an American style option.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseStartDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the option exercise start date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseStartDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative option exercise start date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseStartDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative option exercise start date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseStartDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the provision's relative option exercise start date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseStartDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted first day of the exercise period for an American style option.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExercisePeriodSkip
Field.Description: The number of periods in the referenced date schedule that are between each date in the relative date schedule. Thus a skip of 2 would mean that dates are relative to every second date in the referenced schedule. If present this should have a value greater than 1.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseBoundsFirstDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted first date of a schedule. This can be used to restrict the range of exercise dates when they are relative.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseBoundsLastDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted last date of a schedule. This can be used to restrict the range of exercise dates when they are relative.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseEarliestTime
Field.Description: The earliest time at which notice of exercise can be given by the buyer to the seller (or seller's agent) i) on the expriation date, in the case of a European style option, (ii) on each bermuda option exercise date and the expiration date, in the case of a Bermuda style option the commencement date to, and including, the expiration date, in the case of an American option.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseEarliestTimeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: Identifies the business center calendar used with the provision's earliest time for notice of exercise. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseLatestTime
Field.Description: For a Bermuda or American style option, the latest time on an exercise business day (excluding the expiration date) within the exercise period that notice can be given by the buyer to the seller or seller's agent. Notice of exercise given after this time will be deemed to have been given on the next exercise business day.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseLatestTimeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: Identifies the business center calendar used with the provision's latest time for notice of exercise. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExpirationDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted last day within an exercise period for an American style option. For a European style option it is the only day within the exercise period.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExpirationDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the underlying instrument's provision's option expiration date. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the UnderlyingDateAdjustment component within the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExpirationDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the option expiration date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExpirationDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative option expiration date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExpirationDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative option expiration date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExpirationDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the provision's relative option expiration date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExpirationDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted last date within an exercise period for an American style option. For a European style option it is the only date within the exercise period.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExpirationTime
Field.Description: The latest time for exercise on the expiration date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExpirationTimeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: Identifies the business center calendar used with the provision's latest exercise time on expiration date. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionRelevantUnderlyingDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted date on the underlying set by the exercise of an option. What this date is depends on the option (e.g. in a swaption it is the swap effective date, in an extendible/cancelable provision it is the swap termination date).

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionRelevantUnderlyingDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convnetion used to adjust the underlying instrument provision's option underlying date. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the UnderlyingDateAdjustment component within the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionRelevantUnderlyingDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the date relevant to the underlying trade on exercise is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionRelevantUnderlyingDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative option relevant underlying date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionRelevantUnderlyingDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative option relevant underlying date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionRelevantUnderlyingDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the provision's relative option relevant underlying date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionRelevantUnderlyingDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted date on the underlying set by the exercise of an option. What this date is depends on the option (e.g. in a swaption it is the swap effective date, in an extendible/cancelable provision it is the swap termination date).

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingProvisions
Field.Description: Number of provisions in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionType
Field.Description: Type of provision.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted date of the provision.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the underlying instrument's provision's date. Used only to override the business day convention specified in the UnderlyingDateAdjustment component within the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted date of the provision.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionDateTenorPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the provision's tenor period.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionDateTenorUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the provision's tenor period.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCalculationAgent
Field.Description: Used to identify the calculation agent. The calculation agent may be identified in UnderlyingProvisionCalculationAgent(42156) or in the underlying provision parties component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionSinglePartyBuyerSide
Field.Description: If optional early termination is not available to both parties then this component identifies the buyer of the option through its side of the trade.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionSinglePartySellerSide
Field.Description: If optional early termination is not available to both parties then this component identifies the seller of the option through its side of the trade.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseStyle
Field.Description: The instrument provision's exercise style.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseMultipleNotional
Field.Description: A notional amount which restricts the amount of notional that can be exercised when partial exercise or multiple exercise is applicable. The integral multiple amount defines a lower limit of notional that can be exercised and also defines a unit multiple of notional that can be exercised, i.e. only integer multiples of this amount can be exercised.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseMinimumNotional
Field.Description: The minimum notional amount that can be exercised on a given exercise date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseMaximumNotional
Field.Description: The maximum notional amount that can be exercised on a given exercise date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionMinimumNumber
Field.Description: The minimum number of options that can be exercised on a given exercise date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionMaximumNumber
Field.Description: The maximum number of options that can be exercised on a given exercise date. If the number is not specified, it means that the maximum number of options corresponds to the remaining unexercised options.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseConfirmation
Field.Description: Used to indicate whether follow-up confirmation of exercise (written or electronic) is required following telephonic notice by the buyer to the seller or seller's agent.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlMethod
Field.Description: An ISDA defined cash settlement method used for the determination of the applicable cash settlement amount. The method is defined in the 2006 ISDA Definitions, Section 18.3. Cash Settlement Methods, paragraph (e).

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of settlement. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlCurrency2
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of settlement for a cross-currency provision. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlQuoteType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of quote to be used.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionText
Field.Description: Free form text to specify additional information or enumeration description when a standard value does not apply.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingProvisionTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingProvisionText(42712) field.

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingProvisionText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingProvisionText(42170) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingProvisionText(42170) field.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingProvisionPartyIDs
Field.Description: Number of parties identified in the contract provision.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionPartyID
Field.Description: The party identifier for the payment settlement party.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionPartyIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the class or source of the UnderlyingProvisionPartyID(42174) value.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionPartyRole
Field.Description: Identifies the type or role of UnderlyingProvisionPartyID(42174) specified.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionPartyRoleQualifier
Field.Description: Used to further qualify the value of UnderlyingProvisionPartyRole(42176).

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingProvisionPartySubIDs
Field.Description: Number of sub-party IDs to be reported for the party.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionPartySubID
Field.Description: Underlying provision party sub-identifier, if applicable for UnderlyingProvisionPartyID(42174).

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionPartySubIDType
Field.Description: The type of UnderlyingProvisionPartySubID(42178).

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingProvisionCashSettlPaymentDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlPaymentDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the provision's cash settlement payment's termination, or relative termination, date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingProvisionCashSettlValueDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionCashSettlValueDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the cash settlement valuation date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExerciseBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the underlying instrument's provision's option exercise date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingProvisionOptionExpirationDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionExpirationDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the underlying instrument's provision's option expiration date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingProvisionOptionRelevantUnderlyingDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionOptionRelevantUnderlyingDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the underlying instrument's provision's option underlying date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingProvisionDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used to adjust the underlying instrument's provision's date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: FillRefID
Field.Description: A reference to either the value of the FillExecID(1363) or an implicit position of a fills instance in the FillsGrp component.

Field.Name: OrderRequestID
Field.Description: Unique message identifier for an order request as assigned by the submitter of the request.

Field.Name: MassOrderRequestID
Field.Description: Unique message identifier for a mass order request as assigned by the submitter of the orders.

Field.Name: MassOrderReportID
Field.Description: Unique message identifier for a mass order request as assigned by the receiver of the orders.

Field.Name: MassOrderRequestStatus
Field.Description: Status of mass order request.

Field.Name: MassOrderRequestResult
Field.Description: Request result of mass order request.

Field.Name: OrderResponseLevel
Field.Description: The level of response requested from receiver of mass order messages. A default value should be bilaterally agreed.

Field.Name: NoOrderEntries
Field.Description: Number of order entries.

Field.Name: OrderEntryAction
Field.Description: Specifies the action to be taken for the given order.

Field.Name: OrderEntryID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for an order within a single MassOrder(35=DJ) message that can be used as a reference in the MassOrderAck(35=DK) message.

Field.Name: ExecTypeReason
Field.Description: The initiating event when an ExecutionReport(35=8) is sent.

Field.Name: TotNoOrderEntries
Field.Description: Totals number of orders for a mass order or its acknowledgment being fragmented across multiple messages.

Field.Name: NoTargetPartySubIDs
Field.Description: Number of target party sub IDs in the repeating group.

Field.Name: TargetPartySubID
Field.Description: Party sub-identifier value within a target party repeating group.

Field.Name: TargetPartySubIDType
Field.Description: Type of TargetPartySubID(2434) value.

Field.Name: TransferInstructionID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for the transfer instruction assigned by the submitter.

Field.Name: TransferID
Field.Description: The unique identifier assigned to the transfer entity once it is received, for example, by the CCP or the party governing the transfer process. Generally this same identifier for the transfer is used by all parties involved.

Field.Name: TransferReportID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for the transfer report message.

Field.Name: TransferTransType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of transfer transaction.

Field.Name: TransferType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of transfer request.

Field.Name: TransferScope
Field.Description: Indicates the type of transfer.

Field.Name: TransferStatus
Field.Description: Status of the transfer.

Field.Name: TransferRejectReason
Field.Description: Reason the transfer instruction was rejected.

Field.Name: TransferReportType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of transfer report.

Field.Name: AggressorTime
Field.Description: Timestamp of aggressive order or quote resulting in match event.

Field.Name: AggressorSide
Field.Description: Side of aggressive order or quote resulting in match event.

Field.Name: FastMarketIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates if the instrument is in "fast market" state.
Field.Elaboration: A "fast market" is a state in which market rules are applied to instrument(s) or entire trading session when market events causes significant price movements due to public information.

Field.Name: LinkageHandlingIndicator
Field.Description: Indicate whether linkage handling is in effect for an instrument or not.

Field.Name: NumberOfBuyOrders
Field.Description: Number of buy orders involved in a trade.

Field.Name: NumberOfSellOrders
Field.Description: Number of sell orders involved in a trade.

Field.Name: SettlPriceDeterminationMethod
Field.Description: Calculation method used to determine settlement price.

Field.Name: MDStatisticReqID
Field.Description: Message identifier for a statistics request.

Field.Name: MDStatisticRptID
Field.Description: Message identifier for a statistics report.

Field.Name: MDStatisticName
Field.Description: The short name or acronym for a set of statistic parameters.

Field.Name: MDStatisticDesc
Field.Description: Can be used to provide an optional textual description for a statistic.

Field.Name: MDStatisticType
Field.Description: Type of statistic value.

Field.Name: MDStatisticScope
Field.Description: Entities used as basis for the statistics.

Field.Name: MDStatisticSubScope
Field.Description: Sub-scope of the statistics to further reduce the entities used as basis for the statistics.

Field.Name: MDStatisticScopeType
Field.Description: Scope details of the statistics to reduce the number of events being used as basis for the statistics.

Field.Name: MDStatisticFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Dissemination frequency of statistics. Special meaning for a value of zero which represents an event-driven dissemination in real time (e.g. as soon as a new trade occurs).

Field.Name: MDStatisticFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit for MDStatisticFrequencyPeriod(2460).

Field.Name: MDStatisticDelayPeriod
Field.Description: Number of time units between the calculation of the statistic and its dissemination. Can be used to defer or delay publication.

Field.Name: MDStatisticDelayUnit
Field.Description: Time unit for MDStatisticDelayPeriod(2462).

Field.Name: MDStatisticIntervalType
Field.Description: Type of interval over which statistic is calculated.

Field.Name: MDStatisticIntervalTypeUnit
Field.Description: Time unit for MDStatisticIntervalType(2464).

Field.Name: MDStatisticIntervalPeriod
Field.Description: Length of time over which the statistic is calculated. Special meaning for a value of zero to express that there is no aggregation over time. Can be used with other interval types expressing relative date and time ranges to combine them with sliding window peaks, e.g. highest volume across 1 minute intervals of the previous day.

Field.Name: MDStatisticIntervalUnit
Field.Description: Time unit for MDStatisticIntervalPeriod(2466).

Field.Name: MDStatisticStartDate
Field.Description: First day of range for which statistical data is collected.

Field.Name: MDStatisticEndDate
Field.Description: Last day of range for which statistical data is collected.

Field.Name: MDStatisticStartTime
Field.Description: Start time of the time range for which statistical data is collected.

Field.Name: MDStatisticEndTime
Field.Description: End time of the time range for which statistical data is collected.

Field.Name: MDStatisticRatioType
Field.Description: Ratios between various entities.

Field.Name: MDStatisticRequestResult
Field.Description: Result returned in response to MarketDataStatisticsRequest (35=DO).

Field.Name: NoMDStatistics
Field.Description: Number of market data statistics.

Field.Name: MDStatisticID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a statistic.

Field.Name: MDStatisticTime
Field.Description: Time of calculation of a statistic.

Field.Name: MDStatisticStatus
Field.Description: Status for a statistic to indicate its availability.

Field.Name: MDStatisticValue
Field.Description: Statistical value.

Field.Name: MDStatisticValueType
Field.Description: Type of statistical value.

Field.Name: MDStatisticValueUnit
Field.Description: Unit of time for statistical value.

Field.Name: EncodedMDStatisticDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedMDStatisticDesc(2482) field.

Field.Name: EncodedMDStatisticDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the MDStatisticDesc(2455) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the MDStatisticDesc(2455) field.

Field.Name: AllocRiskLimitCheckStatus
Field.Description: Indicates the status of the risk limit check performed on a trade for this allocation instance.

Field.Name: AssetGroup
Field.Description: Indicates the broad product or asset classification. May be used to provide grouping for the product taxonomy (Product(460), SecurityType(167), etc.) and/or the risk taxonomy (AssetClass(1938), AssetSubClass(1939), AssetType(1940), etc.).

Field.Name: LegAssetGroup
Field.Description: Indicates the broad product or asset classification. May be used to provide grouping for the product taxonomy (Product(460), SecurityType(167), etc.) and/or the risk taxonomy (AssetClass(1938), AssetSubClass(1939), AssetType(1940), etc.).

Field.Name: LegContractualDefinition
Field.Description: Specifies which contract definition, such as those published by ISDA, will apply for the terms of the trade. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/contractual-definitions for values.

Field.Name: NoLegContractualDefinitions
Field.Description: Number of financing definitions in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegContractualMatrixDate
Field.Description: Specifies the publication date of the applicable version of the contract matrix. If not specified, the ISDA Standard Terms Supplement defines rules for which version of the matrix is applicable.

Field.Name: LegContractualMatrixSource
Field.Description: Identifies the applicable contract matrix. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/matrix-type-1-0.xml for values.

Field.Name: LegContractualMatrixTerm
Field.Description: Specifies the applicable key into the relevent contract matrix. In the case of 2000 ISDA Definitions Settlement Matrix for Early Termination and Swaptions, the LegContractualMatrixTerm(42206) is not applicable and is to be omitted. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/credit-matrix-transaction-type for values.

Field.Name: NoLegContractualMatrices
Field.Description: Number of contractual matrices in the repeating group.

Field.Name: EncodedLegDocumentationText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the LegDocumentationText(2505) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding(347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the LegDocumentationText(2505) field.

Field.Name: EncodedLegDocumentationTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedLegDocumentationText(2493) field.

Field.Name: LegAgreementCurrency
Field.Description: Contractual currency forming the basis of a financing agreement and associated transactions. Usually, but not always, the same as the trade currency.

Field.Name: LegAgreementDate
Field.Description: A reference to the date the underlying agreement specified by LegAgreementID(2498) and LegAgreementDesc(2497) was executed.

Field.Name: LegAgreementDesc
Field.Description: The full name of the base standard agreement, annexes and amendments in place between the principals applicable to a financing transaction. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/master-agreement-type for derivative values.

Field.Name: LegAgreementID
Field.Description: A common reference to the applicable standing agreement between the counterparties to a financing transaction.

Field.Name: LegAgreementVersion
Field.Description: The version of the master agreement.

Field.Name: LegBrokerConfirmationDesc
Field.Description: Describes the type of broker confirmation executed between the parties. Can be used as an alternative to MasterConfirmationDesc(1962). See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/broker-confirmation-type for values.

Field.Name: LegCreditSupportAgreementDate
Field.Description: The date of the ISDA Credit Support Agreement executed between the parties and intended to govern collateral arrangements for all OTC derivatives transactions between those parties.

Field.Name: LegCreditSupportAgreementDesc
Field.Description: The type of ISDA Credit Support Agreement. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/credit-support-agreement-type for values.

Field.Name: LegCreditSupportAgreementID
Field.Description: A common reference or unique identifier to identify the ISDA Credit Support Agreement executed between the parties.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryType
Field.Description: Identifies type of settlement.

Field.Name: LegDocumentationText
Field.Description: A sentence or phrase pertinent to the trade, not a reference to an external document. E.g. "To be registered with the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency, Acid Rain Division, SO2 Allowance Tracking System".

Field.Name: LegEndDate
Field.Description: End date of a financing deal, i.e. the date the seller reimburses the buyer and takes back control of the collateral.

Field.Name: LegGoverningLaw
Field.Description: Identification of the law governing the transaction. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/governing-law for values.

Field.Name: LegMarginRatio
Field.Description: The fraction of the cash consideration that must be collateralized, expressed as a percent. A MarginRatio of 2% indicates that the value of the collateral (after deducting for "haircut") must exceed the cash consideration by 2%.

Field.Name: LegMasterConfirmationAnnexDate
Field.Description: The date that an annexation to the master confirmation was executed between the parties.

Field.Name: LegMasterConfirmationDate
Field.Description: Alternative to broker confirmation. The date of the confirmation executed between the parties and intended to govern all relevant transactions between those parties.

Field.Name: LegMasterConfirmationDesc
Field.Description: The type of master confirmation executed between the parties. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/master-confirmation-type for values.

Field.Name: LegMasterConfirmationAnnexDesc
Field.Description: The type of master confirmation annexation executed between the parties. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/master-confirmation-annex-type for values.

Field.Name: LegStartDate
Field.Description: Start date of a financing deal, i.e. the date the buyer pays the seller cash and takes control of the collateral.

Field.Name: LegTerminationType
Field.Description: Type of financing termination.

Field.Name: LegFinancingTermSupplementDate
Field.Description: Specifies the publication date of the applicable version of the contractual supplement.

Field.Name: LegFinancingTermSupplementDesc
Field.Description: Identifies the applicable contractual supplement. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/contractual-supplement for values.

Field.Name: NoLegFinancingTermSupplements
Field.Description: Number of financing terms supplements in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAssetGroup
Field.Description: Indicates the broad product or asset classification. May be used to provide grouping for the product taxonomy (Product(460), SecurityType(167), etc.) and/or the risk taxonomy (AssetClass(1938), AssetSubClass(1939), AssetType(1940), etc.).

Field.Name: FirmTransactionID
Field.Description: The unique transaction entity identifier assigned by the firm.

Field.Name: TransactionID
Field.Description: The unique transaction entity identifier.

Field.Name: WireReference
Field.Description: The reference to a wire transfer associated with the transaction. Wire references done via wire services such as Fedwire Output Message Accountabilitty Data "OMAD" or SWIFT Output Sequence Number "OSN".

Field.Name: CollRptRejectReason
Field.Description: Reject reason code for rejecting the collateral report.

Field.Name: CollRptStatus
Field.Description: The status of the collateral report.

Field.Name: PackageID
Field.Description: Identifier assigned to a collection of trades so that they can be analyzed as one atomic unit for risk assessment and clearing.

Field.Name: TradeNumber
Field.Description: Ordinal number of the trade within a series of related trades.

Field.Name: AllocCalculatedCcyQty
Field.Description: Used for the calculated quantity of the other side of the currency trade applicable to the allocation instance.

Field.Name: CollateralRequestInstruction
Field.Description: An encoded collateral request processing instruction to the receiver.

Field.Name: CollateralRequestLinkID
Field.Description: A unique identifier to link together a set or group of requests.

Field.Name: CollateralRequestNumber
Field.Description: Ordinal number of the request within a set or group of requests.

Field.Name: TotNumCollateralRequests
Field.Description: Total number of request messages within a set or group of requests.

Field.Name: WarningText
Field.Description: Communicates the underlying condition when the request response indicates "warning".

Field.Name: EncodedWarningText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the WarningText(2520) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding(347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the WarningText(2520) field.

Field.Name: EncodedWarningTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedWarningtText(2521) field.

Field.Name: LegStreamCommodityDeliveryPricingRegion
Field.Description: The delivery or pricing region associated with the commodity swap. See http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?SID=660d6a40f836aa6ddf213cba080c5b22&node=ap17.2.43_17.e&rgn=div9 for the external code list.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of CFTC Part 43 Appendix E requirement this represents the specific delivery point or pricing point associated with publically reportable commodity swap transactions.

Field.Name: StreamCommodityDeliveryPricingRegion
Field.Description: The delivery or pricing region associated with the commodity swap. See http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?SID=660d6a40f836aa6ddf213cba080c5b22&node=ap17.2.43_17.e&rgn=div9 for the external code list.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of CFTC Part 43 Appendix E requirement this represents the specific delivery point or pricing point associated with publicly reportable commodity swap transactions.

Field.Name: AffiliatedFirmsTradeIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the transaction or position was entered into between two affiliated firms. I.e. one counterparty has an ownership interest in the other counterparty but less than the majority interest.
Field.Elaboration: This trade attribute was identified under and applies to the Canadian CSA trade reporting regulations.

Field.Name: InternationalSwapIndicator
Field.Description: Identifies the swap trade as an "international" transaction.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of CFTC Regulation 45.3(h), an international swap is required by U.S. law and the law of another jurisdiction to be reported both to a US Swaps Data Repository and to a different trade repository registered within the other jurisdiction. The additional SDRs must be identified in the appropriate Parties component with PartyRole(452) = 102 (Data repository), PartyRoleQualifier(2376) = 11 (Additional international trade repository) and PartySubIDType(803) = 70 (Location or jurisdiction).

Field.Name: MultiAssetSwapIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates a swap that does not have one easily identifiable primary underlying asset, but instead involves multiple underlying assets within one trade repository's jurisdiction that belong to different asset classes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamCommodityDeliveryPricingRegion
Field.Description: The delivery or pricing region associated with the commodity swap. See http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?SID=660d6a40f836aa6ddf213cba080c5b22&node=ap17.2.43_17.e&rgn=div9 for the external code list.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of CFTC Part 43 Appendix E requirement this represents the specific delivery point or pricing point associated with publically reportable commodity swap transactions.

Field.Name: NoRelativeValues
Field.Description: Number of relative value metrics entries in the repeating group.

Field.Name: RelativeValueType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of relative value measurement being specified.

Field.Name: RelativeValue
Field.Description: The valuation of an instrument relative to a base measurement specified in RelativeValueType(2530). This value can be negative.

Field.Name: RelativeValueSide
Field.Description: Specifies the side of the relative value.

Field.Name: BidSpread
Field.Description: Basis points relative to a benchmark curve on the bid side, such as LIBOR, or a known security, such as 10Y US Treasury bond. The benchmark security or curve name is specified in the SpreadOrBenchmarkCurveData component.

Field.Name: OfferSpread
Field.Description: Basis points relative to a benchmark curve on the offer side, such as LIBOR, or a known security, such as 10Y US Treasury bond. The benchmark security or curve name is specified in the SpreadOrBenchmarkCurveData component.

Field.Name: ClearingSettlPrice
Field.Description: Clearing settlement price.

Field.Name: MDReportEvent
Field.Description: Technical event within market data feed.

Field.Name: MDReportCount
Field.Description: Number of reference and market data messages in-between two MarketDataReport(35=DR) messages.

Field.Name: TotNoMarketSegmentReports
Field.Description: Total number of reports related to market segments.

Field.Name: TotNoInstrumentReports
Field.Description: Total number of reports related to instruments.

Field.Name: TotNoPartyDetailReports
Field.Description: Total number of reports related to party detail information.

Field.Name: TotNoEntitlementReports
Field.Description: Total number of reports related to party entitlement information.

Field.Name: TotNoRiskLimitReports
Field.Description: Total number of reports related to party risk limit information.

Field.Name: MarketSegmentStatus
Field.Description: Status of market segment.

Field.Name: MarketSegmentType
Field.Description: Used to classify the type of market segment.

Field.Name: MarketSegmentSubType
Field.Description: Used to further categorize market segments within a MarketSegmentType(2543).

Field.Name: NoRelatedMarketSegments
Field.Description: Number of related market segments.

Field.Name: RelatedMarketSegmentID
Field.Description: Identifies a related market segment.

Field.Name: MarketSegmentRelationship
Field.Description: Type of relationship between two or more market segments.

Field.Name: NoAuctionTypeRules
Field.Description: Number of auction order types.

Field.Name: AuctionTypeProductComplex
Field.Description: Identifies an entire suite of products for which the auction order type rule applies.

Field.Name: NoPriceRangeRules
Field.Description: Number of rules related to price ranges.

Field.Name: StartPriceRange
Field.Description: Lower boundary for price range.

Field.Name: EndPriceRange
Field.Description: Upper boundary for price range.

Field.Name: PriceRangeValue
Field.Description: Maximum range expressed as absolute value.

Field.Name: PriceRangePercentage
Field.Description: Maximum range expressed as percentage.

Field.Name: PriceRangeProductComplex
Field.Description: Identifies an entire suite of products in the context of trading rules related to price ranges.

Field.Name: PriceRangeRuleID
Field.Description: Identifier for a price range rule.

Field.Name: FastMarketPercentage
Field.Description: The percentage factor to be applied to trading rule parameters (e.g. price ranges, size ranges, etc.) when fast market conditions are applicable.

Field.Name: NoQuoteSizeRules
Field.Description: Number of rules related to quote sizes.

Field.Name: QuoteSideIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether single sided quotes are allowed.

Field.Name: NoFlexProductEligibilities
Field.Description: Number of eligibility indicators for the creation of flexible securities.

Field.Name: FlexProductEligibilityComplex
Field.Description: Identifies an entire suite of products which are eligible for the creation of flexible securities.

Field.Name: NumOfComplexInstruments
Field.Description: Represents the total number of multileg securities or user defined securities that make up the security.

Field.Name: MarketDepthTimeInterval
Field.Description: Specifies the time interval used for netting market data in a price depth feed.

Field.Name: MarketDepthTimeIntervalUnit
Field.Description: The time unit associated with the time interval of the netting of market data in a price depth feed.

Field.Name: MDRecoveryTimeInterval
Field.Description: Specifies the time interval between two repetitions of the same market data for cyclic recovery feeds.

Field.Name: MDRecoveryTimeIntervalUnit
Field.Description: The time unit associated with the time interval between two cycles of the same market data in cyclic data recovery feeds.

Field.Name: PrimaryServiceLocationID
Field.Description: Primary service location identifier.

Field.Name: SecondaryServiceLocationID
Field.Description: Secondary or alternate service location identifier.

Field.Name: MatchRuleProductComplex
Field.Description: Identifies an entire suite of products for which the matching rule applies.

Field.Name: CustomerPriority
Field.Description: Specifies the kind of priority given to customers.

Field.Name: TickRuleProductComplex
Field.Description: Identifies an entire suite of products for which the price tick rule applies.

Field.Name: PreviousAdjustedOpenInterest
Field.Description: Previous day's adjusted open interest.

Field.Name: PreviousUnadjustedOpenInterest
Field.Description: Previous day's unadjusted open interest.

Field.Name: LowExercisePriceOptionIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates if a given option instrument permits low exercise prices (LEPO).

Field.Name: BlockTradeEligibilityIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates if a given instrument is eligible for block trading.

Field.Name: InstrumentPricePrecision
Field.Description: Specifies the number of decimal places for instrument prices.

Field.Name: StrikePricePrecision
Field.Description: Specifies the number of decimal places for exercise price.

Field.Name: OrigStrikePrice
Field.Description: Original exercise price, e.g. after corporate action requiring changes.

Field.Name: SettlSubMethod
Field.Description: Specifies a suitable settlement sub-method for a given settlement method.

Field.Name: NoClearingPriceParameters
Field.Description: Number of parameter sets for clearing prices.

Field.Name: BusinessDayType
Field.Description: Relative identification of a business day.

Field.Name: ClearingPriceOffset
Field.Description: Constant value required for the calculation of the clearing price, e.g. for variance futures.

Field.Name: VegaMultiplier
Field.Description: Constant value required for the calculation of the clearing quantity, e.g. for variance futures.

Field.Name: AnnualTradingBusinessDays
Field.Description: Number of trading business days in a year.

Field.Name: TotalTradingBusinessDays
Field.Description: Number of trading business days over the lifetime of an instrument.

Field.Name: TradingBusinessDays
Field.Description: Number of actual trading business days of an instrument.

Field.Name: RealizedVariance
Field.Description: Actual or realized variance of an instrument used to calculate settlement prices, e.g. for variance futures.

Field.Name: StandardVariance
Field.Description: Standard variance (over the lifetime of an instrument) or initial variance used to calculate settlement prices, e.g. for variance futures.

Field.Name: RelatedClosePrice
Field.Description: Closing price of the underlying required to calculate the RealizedVariance(2587).

Field.Name: OvernightInterestRate
Field.Description: Overnight interest rate.

Field.Name: AccumulatedReturnModifiedVariationMargin
Field.Description: The economic cost of the variation margin from one trading day to the next.

Field.Name: CalculationMethod
Field.Description: Specifies how the calculation will be made.

Field.Name: NoMiscFeeSubTypes
Field.Description: Specifies the number of miscellaneous fee sub-types.

Field.Name: MiscFeeSubType
Field.Description: Used to provide more granular fee types related to a value of MiscFeeType(139). See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Misc_Fee_Sub_Types for code list of applicable fees. Other fee sub-types may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties.
Field.Elaboration: Fee sub-types may include market or country specific fee.

Field.Name: MiscFeeSubTypeAmt
Field.Description: The amount of the specified MiscFeeSubType(2634).

Field.Name: MiscFeeSubTypeDesc
Field.Description: Can be used to provide an optional textual description of the fee sub-type.

Field.Name: EncodedMiscFeeSubTypeDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedMiscFeeSubTypeDesc(2638) field.

Field.Name: EncodedMiscFeeSubTypeDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the MiscFeeSubTypeDesc(2636) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the MiscFeeSubTypeDesc(2636) field.

Field.Name: CollateralAmountType
Field.Description: The type of value in CurrentCollateralAmount(1704).

Field.Name: PositionID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a position entity. Refer to PosMaintRptID(721) for a unique identifier of a position report message.

Field.Name: PaymentDesc
Field.Description: A short descriptive name given to the payment, e.g. Premium, Upfront, etc. The description has no intrinsic meaning but should be arbitrarily chosen by the remitter as reference.

Field.Name: NoCommissions
Field.Description: Number of commissions in the repeating group.

Field.Name: CommissionAmount
Field.Description: The commission amount.

Field.Name: CommissionAmountType
Field.Description: Indicates what type of commission is being expressed in CommissionAmount(2640).

Field.Name: CommissionBasis
Field.Description: Specifies the basis or unit used to calculate the commission.

Field.Name: CommissionCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency denomination of the commission amount if different from the trade's currency. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: CommissionUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The commission rate unit of measure.

Field.Name: CommissionUnitOfMeasureCurrency
Field.Description: Indicates the currency of the unit of measure. Conditionally required when CommissionUnitOfMeasure(2644) = Ccy (Amount of currency).

Field.Name: CommissionRate
Field.Description: The commission rate when CommissionAmount(2640) is based on a percentage of quantity, amount per unit or a factor of "unit of measure". If the rate is a percentage or expressed in basis points, use the decimalized form, e.g. "0.05" for a 5% commission or "0.005" for 50 basis points.

Field.Name: CommissionSharedIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the amount in CommissionAmount(2640) is to be shared with a third party, e.g. as part of a directed brokerage commission sharing arrangement.

Field.Name: CommissionAmountShared
Field.Description: Commission amount to be shared with a third party, e.g. as part of a directed brokerage commission sharing arrangement. If specified, this amount should not exceed the amount in CommissionAmount(2640).

Field.Name: CommissionLegRefID
Field.Description: Identifies the leg of the trade the entry applies to by referencing the leg's LegID(1788).

Field.Name: CommissionDesc
Field.Description: Description of the commission.

Field.Name: EncodedCommissionDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of the encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedCommissionDesc(2652) field.

Field.Name: EncodedCommissionDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the CommissionDesc(2650) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding(347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the CommissionDesc(2650) field.

Field.Name: NoAllocCommissions
Field.Description: Number of commissions in the repeating group.

Field.Name: AllocCommissionAmount
Field.Description: The commission amount.

Field.Name: AllocCommissionAmountType
Field.Description: Indicates what type of commission is being expressed in AllocCommissionAmount(2654).

Field.Name: AllocCommissionBasis
Field.Description: Specifies the basis or unit used to calculate the commission.

Field.Name: AllocCommissionCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency denomination of the commission amount if different from the trade's currency. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: AllocCommissionUnitOfMeasure
Field.Description: The commission rate unit of measure.

Field.Name: AllocCommissionUnitOfMeasureCurrency
Field.Description: Indicates the currency of the unit of measure. Conditionally required when AllocCommissionUnitOfMeasure(2658) = Ccy (Currency).

Field.Name: AllocCommissionRate
Field.Description: The commission rate when AllocCommissionAmount(2654) is based on a percentage of quantity, amount per unit or a factor of "unit of measure". If the rate is a percentage or expressed in basis points, use the decimalized form, e.g. "0.05" for a 5% commission or "0.005" for 50 basis points.

Field.Name: AllocCommissionSharedIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the amount in AllocCommissionAmount(2654) is to be shared with a third party, e.g. as part of a directed brokerage commission sharing arrangement.

Field.Name: AllocCommissionAmountShared
Field.Description: Commission amount to be shared with a third party, e.g. as part of a directed brokerage commission sharing arrangement. If specified, this amount should not exceed the amount in AllocCommissionAmount(2654).

Field.Name: AllocCommissionLegRefID
Field.Description: Identifies the leg of the trade the entry applies to by referencing the leg's LegID(1788).

Field.Name: AllocCommissionDesc
Field.Description: Description of the commission.

Field.Name: EncodedAllocCommissionDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of the encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedAllocCommissionDesc(2666) field.

Field.Name: EncodedAllocCommissionDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the AllocCommissionDesc(2664) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding(347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the AllocCommissionDesc(2664) field.

Field.Name: DeltaCrossed
Field.Description: Indicates that the party has taken a position on both a put and a call on the same underlying asset.

Field.Name: CashSettlDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted cash settlement date.

Field.Name: CashSettlDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the cash settlement provision's date. Used only to override the business day convention defined in the Instrument component.

Field.Name: CashSettlDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the cash settlement date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: CashSettlDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative cash settlement date offset.

Field.Name: CashSettlDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative cash settlement date offset.

Field.Name: CashSettlDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative cash settlement date offset.

Field.Name: CashSettlDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted cash settlement date.

Field.Name: NoCashSettlDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: CashSettlDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the cash settlement unadjusted or relative date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: CashSettlPriceSource
Field.Description: The source from which the settlement price is to be obtained. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/settlement-price-source for values.

Field.Name: CashSettlPriceDefault
Field.Description: The default election for determining settlement price.

Field.Name: ComplexEventFuturesPriceValuation
Field.Description: Indicates whether the official settlement price as announced by the related exchange is applicable, in accordance with the ISDA 2002 definitions. Applicable only to futures contracts.

Field.Name: ComplexEventOptionsPriceValuation
Field.Description: Indicates whether the official settlement price as announced by the related exchange is applicable, in accordance with the ISDA 2002 definitions. Applicable only to options contracts.

Field.Name: ComplexEventPVFinalPriceElectionFallback
Field.Description: Specifies the fallback provisions for the hedging party in the determination of the final settlement price.

Field.Name: DividendFloatingRateIndex
Field.Description: The dividend accrual floating rate index.

Field.Name: DividendFloatingRateIndexCurvePeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the dividend accrual floating rate index curve.

Field.Name: DividendFloatingRateIndexCurveUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the dividend accrual floating rate index curve period.

Field.Name: DividendFloatingRateMultiplier
Field.Description: A rate multiplier to apply to the floating rate. The multiplier can be less than or greater than 1 (one). This should only be included if the multiplier is not equal to 1 (one) for the term of the contract.

Field.Name: DividendFloatingRateSpread
Field.Description: The basis points spread from the index specified in DividendFloatingRateIndex(42218).

Field.Name: DividendFloatingRateSpreadPositionType
Field.Description: Identifies whether the rate spread is applied to a long or short position.

Field.Name: DividendFloatingRateTreatment
Field.Description: Specifies the yield calculation treatment for the index.

Field.Name: DividendCapRate
Field.Description: The cap rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate. It is only required where the floating rate is capped at a certain level. The cap rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A cap rate of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

Field.Name: DividendCapRateBuySide
Field.Description: Reference to the buyer of the cap rate option through its trade side.

Field.Name: DividendCapRateSellSide
Field.Description: Reference to the seller of the cap rate option through its trade side.

Field.Name: DividendFloorRate
Field.Description: The floor rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate. The floor rate (strike) is only required where the floating rate is floored at a certain strike level. The floor rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate. The rate is expressed as a decimal, e.g. 5% is represented as "0.05".

Field.Name: DividendFloorRateBuySide
Field.Description: Reference to the buyer of the floor rate option through its trade side.

Field.Name: DividendFloorRateSellSide
Field.Description: Reference to the seller of the floor rate option through its trade side.

Field.Name: DividendInitialRate
Field.Description: The initial floating rate reset agreed between the principal parties involved in the trade. This is assumed to be the first required reset rate for the first regular calculation period. It should only be included when the rate is not equal to the rate published on the source implied by the floating rate index. The initial rate is expressed in decimal form, e.g. 5% is represented as "0.05".

Field.Name: DividendFinalRateRoundingDirection
Field.Description: Specifies the rounding direction of the final rate.

Field.Name: DividendFinalRatePrecision
Field.Description: Specifies the rounding precision of the final rate in terms of a number of decimal places. Note how a percentage rate rounding of 5 decimal places is expressed as a rounding precision of 7.

Field.Name: DividendAveragingMethod
Field.Description: When averaging is applicable, used to specify whether a weighted or unweighted average method of calculation is to be used.

Field.Name: DividendNegativeRateTreatment
Field.Description: The specification of any provisions for calculating payment obligations when a floating rate is negative (either due to a quoted negative floating rate or by operation of a spread that is subtracted from the floating rate).

Field.Name: NoDividendAccrualPaymentDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of entries in the DividendAccrualPaymentDateBusinessCenterGrp.

Field.Name: DividendAccrualPaymentDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the instrument's dividend accrual payment date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: DividendAccrualPaymentDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the accrual payment date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: DividendAccrualPaymentDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative accrual payment date offset.

Field.Name: DividendAccrualPaymentDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative accrual payment date offset.

Field.Name: DividendAccrualPaymentDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative accrual payment date offset.

Field.Name: DividendAccrualPaymentDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted accrual payment date.

Field.Name: DividendAccrualPaymeentDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: Accrual payment date adjustment business day convention.

Field.Name: DividendAccrualPaymentDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted accrual payment date.

Field.Name: DividendReinvestmentIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the dividend will be reinvested.

Field.Name: DividendEntitlementEvent
Field.Description: Defines the contract event which the receiver of the derivative is entitled to the dividend.

Field.Name: DividendAmountType
Field.Description: Indicates how the gross cash dividend amount per share is determined.

Field.Name: DividendUnderlierRefID
Field.Description: References the dividend underlier through the instrument's UnderlyingSecurityID(309) which must be fully specified in an instance of the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: ExtraordinaryDividendPartySide
Field.Description: Reference to the party through its side in the trade who makes the determination whether dividends are extraordinary in relation to normal levels.

Field.Name: ExtraordinaryDividendAmountType
Field.Description: Indicates how the extraordinary gross cash dividend per share is determined.

Field.Name: ExtraordinaryDividendCurrency
Field.Description: The currency in which the excess dividend is denominated. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: ExtraordinaryDividendDeterminationMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the method in which the excess amount is determined. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/determination-method for values.

Field.Name: DividendAccrualFixedRate
Field.Description: The dividend accrual fixed rate per annum expressed as a decimal. A value of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

Field.Name: DividendCompoundingMethod
Field.Description: The compounding method to be used when more than one dividend period contributes to a single payment.

Field.Name: DividendNumOfIndexUnits
Field.Description: The number of index units applicable to dividends.

Field.Name: DividendCashPercentage
Field.Description: Declared cash dividend percentage. A value of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

Field.Name: DividendCashEquivalentPercentage
Field.Description: Declared cash-equivalent dividend percentage. A value of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

Field.Name: NonCashDividendTreatment
Field.Description: Defines the treatment of non-cash dividends.

Field.Name: DividendComposition
Field.Description: Defines how the composition of dividends is to be determined.

Field.Name: SpecialDividendsIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether special dividends are applicable.

Field.Name: MaterialDividendsIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether material non-cash dividends are applicable.

Field.Name: OptionsExchangeDividendsIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether option exchange dividends are applicable.

Field.Name: AdditionalDividendsIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether additional dividends are applicable.

Field.Name: AllDividendsIndicator
Field.Description: Represents the European Master Confirmation value of 'All Dividends' which, when applicable, signifies that, for a given Ex-Date, the daily observed share price for that day is adjusted (reduced) by the cash dividend and/or the cash value of any non-cash dividend per share (including extraordinary dividends) declared by the issuer.

Field.Name: DividendFXTriggerDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the FX trigger date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: DividendFXTriggerDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative FX trigger date offset.

Field.Name: DividendFXTriggerDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative FX trigger date offset.

Field.Name: DividendFXTriggerDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative FX trigger date offset.

Field.Name: DividendFXTriggerDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted FX trigger date.

Field.Name: DividendFXTriggerDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used for the FX trigger date adjustment.

Field.Name: DividendFXTriggerDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted FX trigger date.

Field.Name: NoDividendFXTriggerDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of entries in the DividendFXTriggerDateBusinessCenterGrp.

Field.Name: DividendFXTriggerDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the instrument's FX trigger date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoDividendPeriods
Field.Description: Number of entries in the DividendPeriodGrp component.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodSequence
Field.Description: Defines the ordinal dividend period. E.g. 1 = First period, 2 = Second period, etc.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodStartDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted date on which the dividend period will begin.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodEndDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted date on which the dividend period will end.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodUnderlierRefID
Field.Description: References the dividend underlier through the instrument's UnderlyingSecurityID(309) which must be fully specified in an instance of the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodStrikePrice
Field.Description: Specifies the fixed strike price of the dividend period.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The dividend period dates business day convention.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodValuationDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted dividend period valuation date.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodValuationDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the dividend period valuation date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodValuationDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative dividend period valuation date offset.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodValuationDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative dividend period valuation date offset.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodValuationDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative dividend period valuation date offset.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodValuationDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted dividend period valuation date.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodPaymentDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted dividend period payment date.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodPaymentDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the dividend period payment date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodPaymentDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative dividend period payment date offset.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodPaymentDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative dividend period payment date offset.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodPaymentDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative dividend period payment date offset.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodPaymentDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted dividend period payment date.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodXID
Field.Description: Identifier for linking this stream dividend period to an underlier through an instance of RelatedInstrumentGrp.

Field.Name: NoDividendPeriodBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of entries in the DividendPeriodBusinessCenterGrp.

Field.Name: DividendPeriodBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the instrument's dividend period date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoExtraordinaryEvents
Field.Description: Number of extraordinary events in the repeating group.

Field.Name: ExtraordinaryEventType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of extraordinary or disruptive event applicable to the reference entity. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Extraordinary_Event_Type for code list of extraordinary event types and values.

Field.Name: ExtraordinaryEventValue
Field.Description: The extraordinary or disruptive event value appropriate to ExtraordinaryEventType(42297). See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Extraordinary_Event_Type for code list of extraordinary event types and values.

Field.Name: StrikeIndexCurvePoint
Field.Description: The point on the floating rate index curve. Sample values: M = combination of a number between 1-12 and an "M" for month, e.g. 3M Y = combination of number between 1-100 and a "Y" for year, e.g. 10Y 10Y-OLD = see above, then add "-OLD" when appropriate INTERPOLATED = the point is mathematically derived 2/2031 5 3/8 = the point is stated via a combination of maturity month / year and coupon.

Field.Name: StrikeIndexQuote
Field.Description: The quote side from which the index price is to be determined.

Field.Name: ExtraordinaryEventAdjustmentMethod
Field.Description: Defines how adjustments will be made to the contract should one or more of the extraordinary events occur.

Field.Name: ExchangeLookAlike
Field.Description: For a share option trade, indicates whether the instrument is to be treated as an 'exchange look-alike'.
Field.Elaboration: This designation has significance for how share adjustments (arising from corporate actions) will be determined for the instrument. For an 'exchange look-alike' instrument the relevant share adjustments will follow that for a corresponding designated contract listed on the related exchange (referred to as Options Exchange Adjustment (ISDA defined term)), otherwise the share adjustments will be determined by the calculation agent (referred to as Calculation Agent Adjustment (ISDA defined term)).

Field.Name: LegStrikeIndexCurvePoint
Field.Description: The point on the floating rate index curve. Sample values: M = combination of a number between 1-12 and an "M" for month, e.g. 3M Y = combination of number between 1-100 and a "Y" for year, e.g. 10Y 10Y-OLD = see above, then add "-OLD" when appropriate INTERPOLATED = the point is mathematically derived 2/2031 5 3/8 = the point is stated via a combination of maturity month / year and coupon.

Field.Name: LegStrikeIndexQuote
Field.Description: The quote side from which the index price is to be determined.

Field.Name: LegExtraordinaryEventAdjustmentMethod
Field.Description: Defines how adjustments will be made to the contract should one or more of the extraordinary events occur.

Field.Name: LegExchangeLookAlike
Field.Description: For a share option trade, indicates whether the instrument is to be treated as an 'exchange look-alike'.
Field.Elaboration: This designation has significance for how share adjustments (arising from corporate actions) will be determined for the instrument. For an 'exchange look-alike' instrument the relevant share adjustments will follow that for a corresponding designated contract listed on the related exchange (referred to as Options Exchange Adjustment (ISDA defined term)), otherwise the share adjustments will be determined by the calculation agent (referred to as Calculation Agent Adjustment (ISDA defined term)).

Field.Name: LegCashSettlDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted cash settlement date.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the cash settlement provision's date. Used only to override the business day convention defined in the InstrumentLeg component.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the cash settlement date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative cash settlement date offset.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative cash settlement date offset.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative cash settlement date offset.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted cash settlement date.

Field.Name: NoLegCashSettlDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the cash settlement unadjusted or relative date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlPriceSource
Field.Description: The source from which the settlement price is to be obtained. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/settlement-price-source for values.

Field.Name: LegCashSettlPriceDefault
Field.Description: The default election for determining settlement price.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventFuturesPriceValuation
Field.Description: Indicates whether the official settlement price as announced by the related exchange is applicable, in accordance with the ISDA 2002 definitions. Applicable only to futures contracts.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventOptionsPriceValuation
Field.Description: Indicates whether the official settlement price as announced by the related exchange is applicable, in accordance with the ISDA 2002 definitions. Applicable only to options contracts.

Field.Name: LegComplexEventPVFinalPriceElectionFallback
Field.Description: Specifies the fallback provisions for the hedging party in the determination of the final settlement price

Field.Name: NoLegDividendAccrualPaymentDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of entries in the LegDividendAccrualPaymentDateBusinessCenterGrp.

Field.Name: LegDividendAccrualPaymentDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the instrument's dividend accrual payment date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: LegDividendFloatingRateIndex
Field.Description: The dividend accrual floating rate index.

Field.Name: LegDividendFloatingRateIndexCurvePeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the dividend accrual floating rate index curve.

Field.Name: LegDividendFloatingRateIndexCurveUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the dividend accrual floating rate index curve period.

Field.Name: LegDividendFloatingRateMultiplier
Field.Description: A rate multiplier to apply to the floating rate. The multiplier can be less than or greater than 1 (one). This should only be included if the multiplier is not equal to 1 (one) for the term of the contract.

Field.Name: LegDividendFloatingRateSpread
Field.Description: The basis points spread from the index specified in LegDividendFloatingRateIndex(42312).

Field.Name: LegDividendFloatingRateSpreadPositionType
Field.Description: Identifies whether the rate spread is applied to a long or short position.

Field.Name: LegDividendFloatingRateTreatment
Field.Description: Specifies the yield calculation treatment for the index.

Field.Name: LegDividendCapRate
Field.Description: The cap rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate. It is only required where the floating rate is capped at a certain level. The cap rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A cap rate of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

Field.Name: LegDividendCapRateBuySide
Field.Description: Reference to the buyer of the cap rate option through its trade side.

Field.Name: LegDividendCapRateSellSide
