Field.Name: StreamVersionEffectiveDate
Field.Description: The effective date of the StreamVersion(42784).

Field.Name: StreamNotionalDeterminationMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the method for determining the floating notional value for equity swaps. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/determination-method for values.

Field.Name: StreamNotionalAdjustments
Field.Description: For equity swaps this specifies the conditions that govern the adjustment to the number of units of the swap.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingCashSettlDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the cash settlement unadjusted or relative date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted cash settlement date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used to adjust the cash settlement provision's date. Used only to override the business day convention defined in the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the cash settlement date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative cash settlement date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative cash settlement date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative cash settlement date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted cash settlement date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlPriceSource
Field.Description: The source from which the settlement price is to be obtained. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/settlement-price-source for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingCashSettlPriceDefault
Field.Description: The default election for determining settlement price.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventFuturesPriceValuation
Field.Description: Indicates whether the official settlement price as announced by the related exchange is applicable, in accordance with the ISDA 2002 definitions. Applicable only to futures contracts.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventOptionsPriceValuation
Field.Description: Indicates whether the official settlement price as announced by the related exchange is applicable, in accordance with the ISDA 2002 definitions. Applicable only to options contracts.

Field.Name: UnderlyingComplexEventPVFinalPriceElectionFallback
Field.Description: Specifies the fallback provisions for the hedging party in the determination of the final settlement price

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingDividendAccrualPaymentDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of entries in the UnderlyingDividendAccrualPaymentDateBusinessCenterGrp.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendAccrualPaymentDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the instrument's dividend accrual payment date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFloatingRateIndex
Field.Description: The dividend accrual floating rate index.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFloatingRateIndexCurvePeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the dividend accrual floating rate index curve.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFloatingRateIndexCurveUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the dividend accrual floating rate index curve period.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFloatingRateMultiplier
Field.Description: A rate multiplier to apply to the floating rate. The multiplier can be less than or greater than 1 (one). This should only be included if the multiplier is not equal to 1 (one) for the term of the contract.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFloatingRateSpread
Field.Description: The basis points spread from the index specified in UnderlyingDividendFloatingRateIndex(42801).

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFloatingRateSpreadPositionType
Field.Description: Identifies whether the rate spread is applied to a long or short position.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFloatingRateTreatment
Field.Description: Specifies the yield calculation treatment for the index.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendCapRate
Field.Description: The cap rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate. It is only required where the floating rate is capped at a certain level. The cap rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A cap rate of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendCapRateBuySide
Field.Description: Reference to the buyer of the cap rate option through its trade side.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendCapRateSellSide
Field.Description: Reference to the seller of the cap rate option through its trade side.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFloorRate
Field.Description: The floor rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate. The floor rate (strike) is only required where the floating rate is floored at a certain strike level. The floor rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate. The rate is expressed as a decimal, e.g. 5% is represented as "0.05".

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFloorRateBuySide
Field.Description: Reference to the buyer of the floor rate option through its trade side.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFloorRateSellSide
Field.Description: Reference to the seller of the floor rate option through its trade side.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendInitialRate
Field.Description: The initial floating rate reset agreed between the principal parties involved in the trade. This is assumed to be the first required reset rate for the first regular calculation period. It should only be included when the rate is not equal to the rate published on the source implied by the floating rate index. The initial rate is expressed in decimal form, e.g. 5% is represented as "0.05".

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFinalRateRoundingDirection
Field.Description: Specifies the rounding direction of the final rate.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFinalRatePrecision
Field.Description: Specifies the rounding precision of the final rate in terms of a number of decimal places. Note how a percentage rate rounding of 5 decimal places is expressed as a rounding precision of 7.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendAveragingMethod
Field.Description: When averaging is applicable, used to specify whether a weighted or unweighted average method of calculation is to be used.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendNegativeRateTreatment
Field.Description: The specification of any provisions for calculating payment obligations when a floating rate is negative (either due to a quoted negative floating rate or by operation of a spread that is subtracted from the floating rate).

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendAccrualPaymentDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the accrual payment date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendAccrualPaymentDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative accrual payment date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendAccrualPaymentDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative accrual payment date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendAccrualPaymentDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative accrual payment date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendAccrualPaymentDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted accrual payment date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendAccrualPaymentDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: Accrual payment date adjustment business day convention.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendAccrualPaymentDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted accrual payment date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendReinvestmentIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the dividend will be reinvested.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendEntitlementEvent
Field.Description: Defines the contract event which the receiver of the derivative is entitled to the dividend.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendAmountType
Field.Description: Indicates how the gross cash dividend amount per share is determined.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendUnderlierRefID
Field.Description: References the dividend underlier through the instrument's UnderlyingSecurityID(309) which must be fully specified in a separate instance of the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingExtraordinaryDividendPartySide
Field.Description: Reference to the party through its side in the trade who makes the determination whether dividends are extraordinary in relation to normal levels.

Field.Name: UnderlyingExtraordinaryDividendAmountType
Field.Description: Indicates how the extraordinary gross cash dividend per share is determined.

Field.Name: UnderlyingExtraordinaryDividendCurrency
Field.Description: The currency in which the excess dividend is denominated. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingExtraordinaryDividendDeterminationMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the method in which the excess amount is determined. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/determination-method for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendAccrualFixedRate
Field.Description: The dividend accrual fixed rate per annum expressed as a decimal. A value of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendCompoundingMethod
Field.Description: The compounding method to be used when more than one dividend period contributes to a single payment.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendNumOfIndexUnits
Field.Description: The number of index units applicable to dividends.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendCashPercentage
Field.Description: Declared cash dividend percentage. A value of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendCashEquivalentPercentage
Field.Description: Declared cash-equivalent dividend percentage. A value of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

Field.Name: UnderlyingNonCashDividendTreatment
Field.Description: Defines the treatment of non-cash dividends.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendComposition
Field.Description: Defines how the composition of dividends is to be determined.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSpecialDividendsIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether special dividends are applicable.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMaterialDividendsIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether material non-cash dividends are applicable.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOptionsExchangeDividendsIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether option exchange dividends are applicable.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAdditionalDividendsIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether additional dividends are applicable.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAllDividendsIndicator
Field.Description: Represents the European Master Confirmation value of 'All Dividends' which, when applicable, signifies that, for a given Ex-Date, the daily observed share price for that day is adjusted (reduced) by the cash dividend and/or the cash value of any non-cash dividend per share (including extraordinary dividends) declared by the issuer.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFXTriggerDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the FX trigger date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFXTriggerDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative FX trigger date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFXTriggerDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative FX trigger date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFXTriggerDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative FX trigger date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFXTriggerDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted FX trigger date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFXTriggerDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The business day convention used for the FX trigger date adjustment.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFXTriggerDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted FX trigger date.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingDividendFXTriggerDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of entries in the UnderlyingDividendFXTriggerDateBusinessCenterGrp.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendFXTriggerDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the instrument's FX trigger date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingDividendPayments
Field.Description: Number of entries in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPaymentDate
Field.Description: Specifies the date that the dividend or coupon payment is due.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPaymentAmount
Field.Description: The amount of the dividend or coupon payment.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPaymentCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency the UnderlyingDividendPaymentAmount(42857) is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendAccruedInterest
Field.Description: Accrued interest on the dividend or coupon payment.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPayoutRatio
Field.Description: Specifies the actual dividend payout ratio associated with the equity or bond underlier.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPayoutConditions
Field.Description: Specifies the dividend payout conditions that will be applied in the case where the actual ratio is not known, typically because of regulatory or legal uncertainties.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingDividendPeriods
Field.Description: Number of entries in the UnderlyingDividendPeriodGrp component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodSequence
Field.Description: Defines the ordinal dividend period. E.g. 1 = First period, 2 = Second period, etc.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodStartDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted date on which the dividend period will begin.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodEndDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted date on which the dividend period will end.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodUnderlierRefID
Field.Description: References the dividend underlier through the instrument's UnderlyingSecurityID(309) which must be fully specified in an instance of the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodStrikePrice
Field.Description: Specifies the fixed strike price of the dividend period.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The dividend period dates business day convention.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodValuationDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted dividend period valuation date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodValuationDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the dividend period valuation date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodValuationDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative dividend period valuation date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodValuationDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative dividend period valuation date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodValuationDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative dividend period valuation date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodValuationDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted dividend period valuation date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodPaymentDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted dividend period payment date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodPaymentDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the dividend period payment date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodPaymentDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative dividend period payment date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodPaymentDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative dividend period payment date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodPaymentDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative dividend period payment date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodPaymentDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted dividend period payment date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodXID
Field.Description: Identifier for linking this stream dividend period to an underlier through an instance of RelatedInstrumentGrp.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingDividendPeriodBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of entries in UnderlyingDividendPeriodBusinessCenterGrp.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDividendPeriodBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the instrument's dividend period date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingExtraordinaryEvents
Field.Description: Number of extraordinary events in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingExtraordinaryEventType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of extraordinary or disruptive event applicable to UnderlyingExtraordinaryEventType(42885). See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Extraordinary_Event_Type for code list of extraordinary event types and values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingExtraordinaryEventValue
Field.Description: The extraordinary or disruptive event value appropriate to UnderlyingExtraordinaryEventType(42885). See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Extraordinary_Event_Type for code list of extraordinary event types and values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingNotional
Field.Description: Notional value for the equity or bond underlier.

Field.Name: UnderlyingNotionalCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency denomination of the notional value. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingNotionalDeterminationMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the method of determining the notional amount. See: http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/determination-method for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingNotionalAdjustments
Field.Description: Specifies the conditions that govern the adjustment to the number of units of the return swap.

Field.Name: UnderlyingNotionalXIDRef
Field.Description: Cross reference to another notional amount for duplicating its properties.

Field.Name: UnderlyingFutureID
Field.Description: In the case of an index underlier specifies the unique identifier for the referenced futures contract.

Field.Name: UnderlyingFutureIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source of the UnderlyingFutureID(2620).

Field.Name: UnderlyingStrikeIndexCurvePoint
Field.Description: The point on the floating rate index curve. Sample values: M = combination of a number between 1-12 and an "M" for month, e.g. 3M Y = combination of number between 1-100 and a "Y" for year, e.g. 10Y 10Y-OLD = see above, then add "-OLD" when appropriate INTERPOLATED = the point is mathematically derived 2/2031 5 3/8 = the point is stated via a combination of maturity month / year and coupon.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStrikeIndexQuote
Field.Description: The quote side from which the index price is to be determined.

Field.Name: UnderlyingExtraordinaryEventAdjustmentMethod
Field.Description: Defines how adjustments will be made to the contract should one or more of the extraordinary events occur.

Field.Name: UnderlyingExchangeLookAlike
Field.Description: For a share option trade, indicates whether the instrument is to be treated as an 'exchange look-alike'.
Field.Elaboration: This designation has significance for how share adjustments (arising from corporate actions) will be determined for the instrument. For an 'exchange look-alike' instrument the relevant share adjustments will follow that for a corresponding designated contract listed on the related exchange (referred to as Options Exchange Adjustment (ISDA defined term)), otherwise the share adjustments will be determined by the calculation agent (referred to as Calculation Agent Adjustment (ISDA defined term)).

Field.Name: UnderlyingAverageVolumeLimitationPercentage
Field.Description: The limit of average percentage of individual securities traded in a day or a number of days.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAverageVolumeLimitationPeriodDays
Field.Description: Specifies the limitation period for average daily trading volume in number of days.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDepositoryReceiptIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the underlier is a depository receipt.
Field.Elaboration: A depository receipt is a negotiable certificate issued by a trust company or security depository.

Field.Name: UnderlyingOpenUnits
Field.Description: The number of units (units of the index or number of securities, par amount of a bond) that constitute the underlier. In the case of a basket swap, this is used to reference both the number of basket units, and the number of each asset components of the basket when these are expressed in absolute terms.

Field.Name: UnderlyingBasketDivisor
Field.Description: Specifies the basket divisor amount. This value is normally used to adjust the constituent weight for pricing or to adjust for dividends, or other corporate actions.

Field.Name: UnderlyingInstrumentXID
Field.Description: Identifier for referencing this UnderlyingInstrument from a parent instrument or a convertible instrument.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlMethodElectingPartySide
Field.Description: Side value of the party electing the settlement method.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMakeWholeDate
Field.Description: The date through which the option cannot be exercised without penalty.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMakeWholeAmount
Field.Description: Amount to be paid by the buyer of the option if the option is exercised prior to the UnderlyingMakeWholeDate(42888).

Field.Name: UnderlyingMakeWholeBenchmarkCurveName
Field.Description: Identifies the benchmark floating rate index.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMakeWholeBenchmarkCurvePoint
Field.Description: The point on the floating rate index curve. Sample values: M = combination of a number between 1-12 and an "M" for month, e.g. 3M Y = combination of number between 1-100 and a "Y" for year, e.g. 10Y 10Y-OLD = see above, then add "-OLD" when appropriate INTERPOLATED = the point is mathematically derived 2/2031 5 3/8 = the point is stated via a combination of maturity month / year and coupon.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMakeWholeRecallSpread
Field.Description: Spread over the floating rate index.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMakeWholeBenchmarkQuote
Field.Description: The quote side of the benchmark to be used for calculating the "make whole" amount.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMakeWholeInterpolationMethod
Field.Description: The method used when calculating the "make whole" amount. The most common is linear method.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCashSettlIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether cash settlement is applicable.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingXIDRef
Field.Description: Reference to the stream which details the compounding fixed or floating rate.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingSpread
Field.Description: The spread to be used for compounding. Used in scenarios where the interest payment is based on a compounding formula that uses a compounding spread in addition to the regular spread.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamInterpolationMethod
Field.Description: The method used when calculating the index rate from multiple points on the curve. The most common is linear method.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamInterpolationPeriod
Field.Description: Defines applicable periods for interpolation.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingFixedRate
Field.Description: The compounding fixed rate applicable to the payment stream.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingDates
Field.Description: Number of dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingDate
Field.Description: The compounding date. Type of date is specified in UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingDateType(42903).

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of payment compounding date (e.g. adjusted for holidays).

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingDatesBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The compounding dates business day convention.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingDatesRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the compounding dates are relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingDatesOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative compounding date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingDatesOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative compounding date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingDatesOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative compounding date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingPeriodSkip
Field.Description: The number of periods in the "RelativeTo" schedule that are between each date in the compounding schedule. A skip of 2 would mean that compounding dates are relative to every second date in the "RelativeTo" schedule. If present this should have a value greater than 1.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency at which compounding dates occur.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the frequency at which compounding dates occur.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingRollConvention
Field.Description: The convention for determining the sequence of compounding dates. It is used in conjunction with a specified frequency.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamBoundsFirstDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted first date of the compounding schedule. This can be used to restrict the range of dates when they are relative.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamBoundsLastDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted last date of the compounding schedule. This can be used to restrict the range of dates when they are relative.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingDatesBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingDatesBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the payment stream compounding dates, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingEndDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted compounding end date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingEndDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the compounding end date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingEndDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative compounding end date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingEndDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative compounding end date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingEndDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative compounding end date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingEndDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted compounding end date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingRateIndex
Field.Description: The payment stream's compounding floating rate index.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingRateIndexCurvePeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the payment stream's compounding floating rate index curve period.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingRateIndexCurveUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the payment stream's compounding floating rate index curve period.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingRateMultiplier
Field.Description: A rate multiplier to apply to the compounding floating rate. The multiplier can be less than or greater than 1 (one). This should only be included if the multiplier is not equal to 1 (one) for the term of the stream.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingRateSpread
Field.Description: The basis points spread from the index specified in UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingRateIndex(42923).

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingRateSpreadPositionType
Field.Description: Identifies whether the rate spread is applied to a long or short position.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingRateTreatment
Field.Description: Specifies the yield calculation treatment for the index.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingCapRate
Field.Description: The cap rate, if any, which applies to the compounding floating rate. It is only required where the compounding floating rate on a swap stream is capped at a certain level. The cap rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A cap rate of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingCapRateBuySide
Field.Description: Reference to the buyer of the compounding cap rate option through its trade side.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingCapRateSellSide
Field.Description: Reference to the seller of the compounding cap rate option through its trade side.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingFloorRate
Field.Description: The floor rate, if any, which applies to the compounding floating rate. The floor rate (strike) is only required where the compounding floating rate on a swap stream is floored at a certain strike level. The floor rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate. The rate is expressed as a decimal, e.g. 5% is represented as "0.05".

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingFloorRateBuySide
Field.Description: Reference to the buyer of the compounding floor rate option through its trade side.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingFloorRateSellSide
Field.Description: Reference to the seller of the floor rate option through its trade side.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingInitialRate
Field.Description: The initial compounding floating rate reset agreed between the principal parties involved in the trade. It should only be included when the rate is not equal to the rate published on the source implied by the floating rate index. The initial rate is expressed in decimal form, e.g. 5% is represented as "0.05".

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingFinalRateRoundingDirection
Field.Description: Specifies the rounding direction for the compounding floating rate.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingFinalRatePrecision
Field.Description: Specifies the compounding floating rate rounding precision in terms of a number of decimal places. Note how a percentage rate rounding of 5 decimal places is expressed as a rounding precision of 7.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingAveragingMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the averaging method when compounding floating rate averaging is applicable (e.g. weighted or unweighted).

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingNegativeRateTreatment
Field.Description: Specifies the method for calculating payment obligations when a compounding floating rate is negative (either due to a quoted negative floating rate or by operation of a spread that is subtracted from the floating rate).

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingStartDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted compounding start date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingStartDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the compounding start date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingStartDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative compounding start date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingStartDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative compounding start date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingStartDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative compounding start date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamCompoundingStartDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted compounding start date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFormulaImageLength
Field.Description: Length in bytes of the UnderlyingPaymentStreamFormulaImage(42948) field.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFormulaImage
Field.Description: Image of the formula image when represented through an encoded clip in base64Binary.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFinalPricePaymentDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted final price payment date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFinalPricePaymentDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the final price payment date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFinalPricePaymentDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative final price payment date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFinalPricePaymentDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative final price payment date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFinalPricePaymentDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative final price payment date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFinalPricePaymentDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted final price payment date.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingPaymentStreamFixingDates
Field.Description: Number of fixing dates in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFixingDate
Field.Description: The fixing date. Type of date is specified in UnderlyingPaymentStreamFixingDateType(42957).

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFixingDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of fixing date (e.g. adjusted for holidays).

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFirstObservationDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted initial price observation date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFirstObservationDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the initial price observation date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFirstObservationDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the initial price observation date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFirstObservationDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted initial price observation date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamUnderlierRefID
Field.Description: References the dividend underlier through the instrument's UnderlyingSecurityID(309) which must be fully specified in an instance of the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateNotionalReset
Field.Description: Indicates whether the term "Equity Notional Reset" as defined in the ISDA 2002 Equity Derivatives Definitions is applicable ("Y") or not.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamLinkInitialLevel
Field.Description: Price level at which the correlation or variance swap contract will strike.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamLinkClosingLevelIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the correlation or variance swap contract will ("Y") strike off the closing level of the default exchange traded contract or not.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamLinkExpiringLevelIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the correlation or variance swap contract will ("Y") strike off the expiring level of the default exchange traded contract or not.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamLinkEstimatedTradingDays
Field.Description: The expected number of trading days in the variance or correlation swap stream.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamLinkStrikePrice
Field.Description: The strike price of a correlation or variance swap stream.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamLinkStrikePriceType
Field.Description: For a variance swap specifies how UnderlyingPaymentStreamLinkStrikePrice(42968) is expressed.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamLinkMaximumBoundary
Field.Description: Specifies the maximum or upper boundary for variance or strike determination. For a variation swap stream all observations above this price level will be excluded from the variance calculation. For a correlation swap stream the maximum boundary is a percentage of the strike price.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamLinkMinimumBoundary
Field.Description: Specifies the minimum or lower boundary for variance or strike determination. For a variation swap stream all observations below this price level will be excluded from the variance calculation. For a correlation swap stream the minimum boundary is a percentage of the strike price.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamLinkNumberOfDataSeries
Field.Description: Number of data series for a correlation swap. Normal market practice is that correlation data sets are drawn from geographic market areas, such as America, Europe and Asia Pacific. Each of these geographic areas will have its own data series to avoid contagion.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamVarianceUnadjustedCap
Field.Description: Indicates the scaling factor to be multiplied by the variance strike price thereby making variance cap applicable.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamRealizedVarianceMethod
Field.Description: Indicates which price to use to satisfy the boundary condition.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamDaysAdjustmentIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the contract specifies that the notional should be scaled by the number of days in range divided by the estimate trading days or not. The number of "days in range" refers to the number of returns that contribute to the realized volatility.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamNearestExchangeContractRefID
Field.Description: References a contract listed on an exchange through the instrument's UnderlyingSecurityID(309) which must be fully specified in an instance of the UnderlyingInstrument component.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamVegaNotionalAmount
Field.Description: Vega Notional represents the approximate gain/loss at maturity for a 1% difference between RVol (realised volatility) and KVol (strike volatility). It does not necessarily represent the Vega risk of the trade.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFormulaCurrency
Field.Description: The currency in which the formula amount is denominated. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFormulaCurrencyDeterminationMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the method according to which the formula amount currency is determined. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/determination-method for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFormulaReferenceAmount
Field.Description: Specifies the reference amount when this term either corresponds to the standard ISDA Definition (either the 2002 Equity Definition for the Equity Amount, or the 2000 Definition for the Interest Amount), or refers to a term defined elsewhere in the swap document. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Payment_Amount_Relative_To for code list of reference amounts.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingPaymentStreamFormulas
Field.Description: Number of formulas in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFormula
Field.Description: Contains an XML representation of the formula. Defined for flexibility in choice of language (MathML, OpenMath or text).

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamFormulaDesc
Field.Description: A description of the math formula in UnderlyingPaymentStreamFormula(42982).

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStubEndDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted stub end date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStubEndDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The stub end date business day convention.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStubEndDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the stub end date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStubEndDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative stub end date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStubEndDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative stub end date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStubEndDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative stub end date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStubEndDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted stub end date.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingPaymentStubEndDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStubEndDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the payment stub end date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStubStartDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted stub start date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStubStartDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The stub start date business day convention.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStubStartDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the stub start date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStubStartDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative stub start date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStubStartDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative stub start date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStubStartDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative stub start date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStubStartDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted stub start date.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingPaymentStubStartDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStubStartDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the payment stub start date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionBreakFeeElection
Field.Description: Type of fee elected for the break provision.

Field.Name: UnderlyingProvisionBreakFeeRate
Field.Description: Break fee election rate when the break fee is proportional to the notional. A fee rate of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

Field.Name: UnderlyingRateSpreadInitialValue
Field.Description: Specifies the initial rate spread for a basket underlier.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingRateSpreadSteps
Field.Description: Number of entries in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingRateSpreadStepDate
Field.Description: The date that the rate spread step takes affect.

Field.Name: UnderlyingRateSpreadStepValue
Field.Description: The the value of the new rate spread as of the UnderlyingRateSpreadStepDate(43006).

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingReturnRateDates
Field.Description: Number of iterations in the return rate date repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateDateMode
Field.Description: Specifies the valuation type applicable to the return rate date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the return rate valuation dates are relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative return rate valuation date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative return rate valuation date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative return rate valuation date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationStartDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted start date for return rate valuation. This can be used to restrict the range of dates when they are relative.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationStartDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the return rate valuation start date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationStartDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative return rate valuation start date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationStartDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative return rate valuation start date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationStartDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative return rate valuation start date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationStartDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted start date for return rate valuation. This can be used to restrict the range of dates when they are relative.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationEndDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted end date for return rate valuation. This can be used to restrict the range of dates when they are relative.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationEndDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the return rate valuation end date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationEndDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative return rate valuation end date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationEndDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative return rate valuation end date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationEndDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative return rate valuation end date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationEndDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted end date for return rate valuation. This can be used to restrict the range of dates when they are relative.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency at which return rate valuation dates occur.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the frequency at which return rate valuation dates occur.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationFrequencyRollConvention
Field.Description: The convention for determining the sequence of return rate valuation dates. It is used in conjunction with a specified frequency.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The return rate valuation dates business day convention.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingReturnRateFXConversions
Field.Description: Number of iterations in the return rate FX conversion repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateFXCurrencySymbol
Field.Description: Specifies the currency pair for the FX conversion expressed using the CCY1/CCY2 convention. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateFXRate
Field.Description: The rate of exchange between the two currencies specified in UnderlyingReturnRateFXCurrencySymbol(43031).

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateFXRateCalc
Field.Description: Specifies whether UnderlyingReturnRateFXRate(43032) should be multiplied or divided.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingReturnRates
Field.Description: Number of iterations in the return rate repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRatePriceSequence
Field.Description: Specifies the type of price sequence of the return rate.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateCommissionBasis
Field.Description: Specifies the basis or unit used to calculate the commission.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateCommissionAmount
Field.Description: The commission amount.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateCommissionCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency the commission amount is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateTotalCommissionPerTrade
Field.Description: The total commission per trade.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateDeterminationMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the method by which the underlier prices are determined. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/determination-method for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateAmountRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the reference amount when the return rate amount is relative to another amount in the trade. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Payment_Amount_Relative_To for code list of relative amounts.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateQuoteMeasureType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of the measure applied to the return rate's asset, e.g. valuation, sensitivity risk. This could be an NPV, a cash flow, a clean price, etc. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/asset-measure for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateQuoteUnits
Field.Description: Specifies the units that the measure is expressed in. If not specified, the default is a price/value in currency units. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/price-quote-units for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateQuoteMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the type of quote used to determine the return rate of the swap.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateQuoteCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency the return rate quote is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 Currency Code.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateQuoteCurrencyType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of currency, e.g. settlement currency, base currency, etc., that the quote is reported in. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/reporting-currency-type for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateQuoteTimeType
Field.Description: Specifies how or the timing when the quote is to be obtained.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateQuoteTime
Field.Description: The time when the quote is to be generated.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateQuoteDate
Field.Description: The date when the quote is to be generated.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateQuoteExpirationTime
Field.Description: The time when the quote ceases to be valid.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateQuoteBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used for adjustments associated with UnderlyingReturnRateQuoteTimeType(43047) or UnderlyingReturnRateQuoteTime(43048) and UnderlyingReturnRateQuoteDate(43049), e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateQuoteExchange
Field.Description: Specifies the exchange (e.g. stock or listed futures/options exchange) from which the quote is obtained.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateQuotePricingModel
Field.Description: Specifies the pricing model used to evaluate the underlying asset price. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/pricing-model for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateCashFlowType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of cash flows, e.g. coupon payment, premium fee, settlement fee, etc. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/cashflow-type for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationTimeType
Field.Description: Specifies the timing at which the calculation agent values the underlying.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationTime
Field.Description: The time at which the calculation agent values the underlying asset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationTimeBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used for adjustments associated with UnderlyingReturnRateValuationTimeType(43055) or UnderlyingReturnRateValuationTime(43056) , e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationPriceOption
Field.Description: Indicates whether an ISDA price option applies, and if applicable which type of price.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateFinalPriceFallback
Field.Description: Specifies the fallback provision for the hedging party in the determination of the final price.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingReturnRateInformationSources
Field.Description: Number of iterations in the return rate information source repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateInformationSource
Field.Description: Identifies the source of rate information. For FX the references source to be used for the FX spot rate.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateReferencePage
Field.Description: Identifies the reference "page" from the rate source. For FX, the reference page to the spot rate to be used for the reference FX spot rate. When UnderlyingReturnRateInformationSource(43061) = 3 (ISDA Settlement Rate Option) this contains the value from the scheme that reflects the terms of the Annex A to the ISDA 1998 FX and Currency Option Definitions. See: http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/settlement-rate-option

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateReferencePageHeading
Field.Description: Identifies the page heading from the rate source.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingReturnRatePrices
Field.Description: Number of iterations in the return rate price repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRatePriceBasis
Field.Description: The basis of the return price.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRatePrice
Field.Description: Specifies the price of the underlying swap asset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRatePriceCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of the price of the underlying swap asset. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRatePriceType
Field.Description: Specifies whether the UnderlyingReturnRatePrice(43066) is expressed in absolute or relative terms.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingReturnRateValuationDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of iterations in the return rate valuation date business center repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the return rate valuation unadjusted or relative dates, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingReturnRateValuationDates
Field.Description: Number of iterations in the return rate valuation date repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationDate
Field.Description: The return rate valuation date. Type of date is specified in UnderlyingReturnRateValuationDateType(43073).

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnRateValuationDateType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of return rate valuation date (e.g. adjusted for holidays).

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingSettlMethodElectionDateBusinessCenters
Field.Description: Number of business centers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlMethodElectionDateBusinessCenter
Field.Description: The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the settlement method election unadjusted or relative date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlMethodElectionDateUnadjusted
Field.Description: The unadjusted settlement method election date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlMethodElectionDateBusinessDayConvention
Field.Description: The settlement method election date adjustment business day convention.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlMethodElectionDateRelativeTo
Field.Description: Specifies the anchor date when the settlement method election date is relative to an anchor date. See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlMethodElectionDateOffsetPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the relative settlement method election date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlMethodElectionDateOffsetUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the relative settlement method election date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlMethodElectionDateOffsetDayType
Field.Description: Specifies the day type of the relative settlement method election date offset.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSettlMethodElectionDateAdjusted
Field.Description: The adjusted settlement method election date.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamVersion
Field.Description: The stream version identifier when there have been modifications to the contract over time. Helps signal when there are embedded changes.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamVersionEffectiveDate
Field.Description: The effective date of the UnderlyingStreamVersion(43083).

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamNotionalDeterminationMethod
Field.Description: Specifies the method for determining the floating notional value for equity swaps. See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/determination-method for values.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStreamNotionalAdjustments
Field.Description: For equity swaps this specifies the conditions that govern the adjustment to the number of units of the swap.

Field.Name: RemunerationIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the trade price was adjusted for compensation (i.e. includes a mark-up, mark-down or commission) in the price paid.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of MSRB and FINRA TRACE reporting requirements, this is used among firms to indicate trade remuneration.

Field.Name: CompressionGroupID
Field.Description: Use to identify a netting or compression group where trades in the group were netted or compressed. This includes both terminating trades and any remnant trades that result from the operation.

Field.Name: SelfMatchPreventionID
Field.Description: Identifies an order or trade that should not be matched to an opposite order or trade if both buy and sell orders for the same asset contain the same SelfMatchPreventionID(2362) and submitted by the same firm.

Field.Name: PartyRiskLimitStatus
Field.Description: The status of risk limits for a party.

Field.Name: TradeConfirmationReferenceID
Field.Description: A reference or control identifier or number used as a trade confirmation key.
Field.Elaboration: An example of a control identifier is the DTC ID Control Number.

Field.Name: AlgorithmicTradeIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates that the order or trade originates from a computer program or algorithm requiring little-to-no human intervention.

Field.Name: NoTrdRegPublications
Field.Description: Number of regulatory publication rules in repeating group.

Field.Name: TrdRegPublicationType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of regulatory trade publication. Additional reasons for the publication type may be specified in TrdRegPublicationReason(2670).

Field.Name: TrdRegPublicationReason
Field.Description: Additional reason for trade publication type specified in TrdRegPublicationType(2669). Reasons may be specific to regulatory trade publication rules.

Field.Name: LegDifferentialPrice
Field.Description: Used in pricing a group of individual Trade at Settlement (TAS) and Trade At Marker (TAM) contracts as an atomic unit. The value is the negotiated currency offset either at settlement (TAS) or at the time specified in the product definition (TAM). The final contract price is reported in LegLastPx(637).

Field.Name: CrossedIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether the order or quote was crossed with another order or quote having the same context, e.g. having accounts with a common ownership.

Field.Name: NoOrderAttributes
Field.Description: Number of order attribute entries.

Field.Name: OrderAttributeType
Field.Description: The type of order attribute.

Field.Name: OrderAttributeValue
Field.Description: The value associated with the order attribute type specified in OrderAttributeType(2594).

Field.Name: TradeReportingIndicator
Field.Description: Used between parties to convey trade reporting status.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of regulatory reporting, this field may be used by the reporting party (e.g. party obligated to report to regulators) to inform their trading counterparty or other interested parties the trade reporting status.

Field.Name: SideTradeReportingIndicator
Field.Description: Used between parties to convey trade reporting status.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of regulatory reporting, this field may be used by the reporting party (e.g. party obligated to report to regulators) to inform their trading counterparty or other interested parties the trade reporting status.

Field.Name: CrossRequestID
Field.Description: Unique message identifier for a cross request as assigned by the submitter of the request.

Field.Name: FillMatchID
Field.Description: Identifier assigned by a matching system to a match event containing multiple executions.

Field.Name: FillMatchSubID
Field.Description: Identifier assigned by a matching system to a price level (e.g. match step, clip) within a match event containing multiple executions.

Field.Name: MassActionReason
Field.Description: Reason for submission of mass action.

Field.Name: MaximumPricePercentage
Field.Description: Maximum deviation, in percentage terms, of an execution price from a reference price, e.g. the initial price of a match event.

Field.Name: NotAffectedReason
Field.Description: Reason for order being unaffected by mass action even though it belongs to the orders covered by MassActionScope(1374).

Field.Name: TotalNotAffectedOrders
Field.Description: Total number of orders unaffected by either the OrderMassActionRequest(35=CA) or OrderMassCancelRequest(35=Q).

Field.Name: OrderOwnershipIndicator
Field.Description: Change of ownership of an order to a specific party.

Field.Name: LegAccount
Field.Description: Account mnemonic as agreed between buy and sell sides, e.g. broker and institution or investor/intermediary and fund manager.

Field.Name: InTheMoneyCondition
Field.Description: Specifies an option instrument's "in the money" condition.

Field.Name: LegInTheMoneyCondition
Field.Description: Specifies an option instrument's "in the money" condition in general terms.

Field.Name: UnderlyingInTheMoneyCondition
Field.Description: Specifies an option instrument's "in the money" condition in general terms.

Field.Name: DerivativeInTheMoneyCondition
Field.Description: Specifies an option instrument's "in the money" condition in general terms.

Field.Name: ContraryInstructionEligibilityIndicator
Field.Description: Identifies whether the option instrument is eligible for contrary instructions at the time of exercise. The contrariness of an instruction will be determined in the context of InTheMoneyCondition(2681). When not specified, the eligibility is undefined or not applicable.

Field.Name: LegContraryInstructionEligibilityIndicator
Field.Description: Identifies whether the option instrument is eligible for contrary instructions at the time of exercise. The contrariness of an instruction will be determined in the context of LegInTheMoneyCondition(2682). When not specified, the eligibility is undefined or not applicable.

Field.Name: UnderlyingContraryInstructionEligibilityIndicator
Field.Description: Identifies whether the option instrument is eligible for contrary instructions at the time of exercise. The contrariness of an instruction will be determined in the context of UnderlyingInTheMoneyCondition(2683). When not specified, the eligibility is undefined or not applicable.

Field.Name: DerivativeContraryInstructionEligibilityIndicator
Field.Description: Identifies whether the option instrument is eligible for contrary instructions at the time of exercise. The contrariness of an instruction will be determined in the context of DerivativeInTheMoneyCondition(2684). When not specified, the eligibility is undefined or not applicable.

Field.Name: CollateralMarketPrice
Field.Description: Market price of the collateral, either from market sources or pre-agreed by the counterparties.

Field.Name: CollateralPercentOverage
Field.Description: Percentage of over-collateralization particularly when CollateralAmountType(2632) = 4 (Additional collateral value)

Field.Name: NoSideCollateralAmounts
Field.Description: Number of side collateral amount entries.

Field.Name: SideCollateralAmountMarketID
Field.Description: Market associated with the collateral amount.

Field.Name: SideCollateralAmountMarketSegmentID
Field.Description: Market segment associated with the collateral amount.

Field.Name: SideCollateralAmountType
Field.Description: The type of value in CurrentCollateralAmount(1704).

Field.Name: SideCollateralCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency of the collateral; optional, defaults to the settlement currency if not specified. Uses ISO 4217 Currency Code.

Field.Name: SideCollateralFXRate
Field.Description: Foreign exchange rate used to compute the SideCurrentCollateralAmount(2702) from the SideCollateralCurrency(2695) and the Currency(15).

Field.Name: SideCollateralFXRateCalc
Field.Description: Specifies whether or not SideCollateralFXRate(2696) should be multiplied or divided.

Field.Name: SideCollateralMarketPrice
Field.Description: Market price of the collateral, either from market sources or pre-agreed by the counterparties.

Field.Name: SideCollateralPercentOverage
Field.Description: Percentage of over-collateralization particularly when SideCollateralAmountType(2694) = 4 (Additional collateral value).

Field.Name: SideCollateralPortfolioID
Field.Description: Identifier of the collateral portfolio when reporting on a portfolio basis.

Field.Name: SideCollateralType
Field.Description: Type of collateral on deposit being reported.

Field.Name: SideCurrentCollateralAmount
Field.Description: Currency value currently attributed to the collateral.

Field.Name: SideHaircutIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates, if "Y", that a stated valuation includes a haircut, e.g. that the stated value reflects the subtraction of the haircut. Note that a value of "N" does not imply a haircut is not applicable, only that the haircut (if any) is not reflected in the stated valuation.

Field.Name: ExDestinationType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of execution destination for the order.

Field.Name: MarketCondition
Field.Description: Market condition. In the context of ESMA RTS 8 it is important that trading venues communicate the condition of the market, particularly "stressed" and "exceptional", in order to provide incentives for firms contributing to liquidity.

Field.Name: NoQuoteAttributes
Field.Description: Number of quote attributes entries.

Field.Name: QuoteAttributeType
Field.Description: The type of attribute for the quote.

Field.Name: QuoteAttributeValue
Field.Description: The value associated with the quote attribute type specified in QuoteAttributeType(2707).

Field.Name: NoPriceQualifiers
Field.Description: Number of price qualifiers in the repeating group.

Field.Name: PriceQualifier
Field.Description: Qualifier for price. May be used when the price needs to be explicitly qualified.

Field.Name: MDValueTier
Field.Description: Describes the reporting ranges for executed transactions.
Field.Elaboration: In context of ESMA RTS 27 Article 9, the execution venue is required to report on transactions within several size ranges (in terms of a value and currency). The thresholds for these ranges are dependent on the type of financial instrument.

Field.Name: MiscFeeQualifier
Field.Description: Identifies whether the current entry contributes to the trade or transaction economics, i.e. affects NetMoney(118).

Field.Name: MiscFeeDesc
Field.Description: Can be used to provide a textual description of the fee type.

Field.Name: FinancialInstrumentFullName
Field.Description: The full normative name of the financial instrument.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of ESMA reference data, this is used to provide the full name of the instrument as defined by the Derivatives Service Bureau (DSB).

Field.Name: EncodedFinancialInstrumentFullNameLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedFinancialInstrumentFullName(2716) field.

Field.Name: EncodedFinancialInstrumentFullName
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the FinancialInstrumentFullName(2714) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding(347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the FinancialInstrumentFullName(2714) field.

Field.Name: LegFinancialInstrumentFullName
Field.Description: The full normative name of the multileg's financial instrument.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of ESMA reference data, this is used to provide the full name of the instrument as defined by the Derivatives Service Bureau (DSB).

Field.Name: EncodedLegFinancialInstrumentFullNameLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) individual multileg instrument's EncodedLegFinancialInstrumentFullName(2719).

Field.Name: EncodedLegFinancialInstrumentFullName
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the LegFinancialInstrumentFullName(2717) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding(347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the LegFinancialInstrumentFullName(2717) field.

Field.Name: UnderlyingFinancialInstrumentFullName
Field.Description: The full normative name of the underlying financial instrument.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of ESMA reference data, this is used to provide the full name of the instrument as defined by the Derivatives Service Bureau (DSB).

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingFinancialInstrumentFullNameLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) underlying instrument's EncodedUnderlyingFinancialInstrumentFullName(2722).

Field.Name: EncodedUnderlyingFinancialInstrumentFullName
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingFinancialInstrumentFullName(2720) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding(347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingFinancialInstrumentFullName(2720) field.

Field.Name: UnderlyingIndexCurveUnit
Field.Description: Curve time unit associated with the underlying index.

Field.Name: UnderlyingIndexCurvePeriod
Field.Description: Curve time multiplier for the underlying index.

Field.Name: CommissionAmountSubType
Field.Description: Further sub classification of the CommissionAmountType(2641).

Field.Name: AllocCommissionAmountSubType
Field.Description: Further sub classification of the AllocCommissionAmountType(2655).

Field.Name: AllocLegRefID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a specific leg (uniqueness not defined as part of the FIX specification). AllocLegRefID(2727tbd) references the value from LegID(1788) in the current multileg order or trade message specifying to which leg the allocation instance applies.

Field.Name: FloatingRateIndexCurvePeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the floating rate index identified in FloatingRateIndexID(2731).

Field.Name: FloatingRateIndexCurveSpread
Field.Description: Spread from the floating rate index.

Field.Name: FloatingRateIndexCurveUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the floating rate index identified in FloatingRateIndexID(2731).

Field.Name: FloatingRateIndexID
Field.Description: Security identifier of the floating rate index.

Field.Name: FloatingRateIndexIDSource
Field.Description: Source for the floating rate index identified in FloatingRateIndexID(2731).

Field.Name: IndexRollMonth
Field.Description: Month identified in the index roll.
Field.Elaboration: Use "1" for January, "2" for February, etc.

Field.Name: NoIndexRollMonths
Field.Description: Number of instances of the index roll month.

Field.Name: AssetSubType
Field.Description: Used to provide a more specific description of the asset specified in AssetType(1940). See https://www.fixtrading.org/codelists/AssetSubType for code list of applicable values.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of MiFID II, ESMA RTS 23 Annex I Table 2, this may indicate the 'Further sub product' or equity 'Parameter' fields.

Field.Name: CommodityFinalPriceType
Field.Description: Final price type of the commodity as specified by the trading venue.

Field.Name: FinancialInstrumentShortName
Field.Description: Short name of the financial instrument. Uses ISO 18774 (FINS) values.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of MiFID II this maps to ESMA RTS 23 Annex I Table 3 Field 7 and may be used in other RTS that requires a similar field.

Field.Name: NextIndexRollDate
Field.Description: Next index roll date.

Field.Name: LegAssetSubType
Field.Description: Used to provide a more specific description of the asset specified in LegAssetType(2069). See https://www.fixtrading.org/codelists/AssetSubType for code list of applicable values.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of MiFID II, ESMA RTS 23 Annex I Table 2, this may indicate the 'Further sub product' or equity 'Parameter' fields.

Field.Name: LegFinancialInstrumentShortName
Field.Description: Short name of the financial instrument. Uses ISO 18774 (FISN) values.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of MiFID II this maps to ESMA RTS 23 Annex I Table 3 Field 7 and may be used in other RTS that requires a similar field.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamRateIndexID
Field.Description: Security identifier of the floating rate index.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamRateIndexIDSource
Field.Description: Source for the floating rate index identified in LegPaymentStreamRateIndexID(43088).

Field.Name: LegSecondaryAssetSubType
Field.Description: Used to provide a more specific description of the asset specified in LegSecondaryAssetType(2079). See https://www.fixtrading.org/codelists/AssetSubType for code list of applicable values.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of MiFID II RTS 23 Annex I Table 2, this may indicate the 'Further sub product' or equity 'Parameter' fields.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamRateIndexID
Field.Description: Security identifier of the floating rate index.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamRateIndexIDSource
Field.Description: Source for the floating rate index identified in PaymentStreamRateIndexID(43090).

Field.Name: NoReferenceDataDates
Field.Description: Number of instances of reference data dates.

Field.Name: ReferenceDataDate
Field.Description: Reference data entry's date-time of the type specified in ReferenceDataDateType(2748).

Field.Name: ReferenceDataDateType
Field.Description: Reference data entry's date-time type.

Field.Name: SecondaryAssetSubType
Field.Description: Used to provide a more specific description of the asset specified in SecondaryAssetType(1979). See https://www.fixtrading.org/codelists/AssetSubType for code list of applicable values.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of MiFID II, ESMA RTS 23 Annex I Table 2, this may indicate the 'Further sub product' or equity 'Parameter' fields.

Field.Name: UnderlyingFinancialInstrumentShortName
Field.Description: Short name of the financial instrument. Uses ISO 18774 (FINS) values.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of MiFID II this maps to ESMA RTS 23 Annex I Table 3 Field 7 and may be used in other RTS that requires a similar field.

Field.Name: UnderlyingAssetSubType
Field.Description: Used to provide a more specific description of the asset specified in UnderlyingAssetType(2015). See https://www.fixtrading.org/codelists/AssetSubType for code list of applicable values.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of MiFID II, ESMA RTS 23 Annex I Table 2, this may indicate the 'Further sub product' or equity 'Parameter' fields.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamRateIndexID
Field.Description: Security identifier of the floating rate index.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamRateIndexIDSource
Field.Description: Source for the floating rate index identified in UnderlyingPaymentStreamRateIndexID(43092).

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecondaryAssetSubType
Field.Description: May be used to provide a more specific description of the asset specified in UnderlyingSecondaryAssetType(2083). See https://www.fixtrading.org/codelists/AssetSubType for code list of applicable values.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of MiFID II, ESMA RTS 23 Annex I Table 2, this may indicate the 'Further sub product' or equity 'Parameter' fields.

Field.Name: DeliveryStreamRouteOrCharter
Field.Description: Specific delivery route or time charter average. Applicable to commodity freight swaps.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryStreamRouteOrCharter
Field.Description: Specific delivery route or time charter average. Applicable to commodity freight swaps.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryStreamRouteOrCharter
Field.Description: Specific delivery route or time charter average. Applicable to commodity freight swaps.

Field.Name: ExecutionTimestamp
Field.Description: Time of the individual execution.

Field.Name: ReportingPx
Field.Description: Represents the reportable price on fill when an instance of the Parties component with PartyRole(452) = 73 (Execution Venue) is present to prevent having to compute running totals.

Field.Name: ReportingQty
Field.Description: Represents the reportable quantity on fill when an instance of the Parties component with PartyRole(452) = 73 (Execution Venue) is present to prevent having to compute running totals.

Field.Name: DeliveryRouteOrCharter
Field.Description: Specific delivery route or time charter average. Applicable to commodity freight contracts.

Field.Name: ReturnTrigger
Field.Description: Indicates the type of return or payout trigger for the swap or forward.

Field.Name: LegDeliveryRouteOrCharter
Field.Description: Specific delivery route or time charter average. Applicable to commodity freight contracts.

Field.Name: LegReturnTrigger
Field.Description: Indicates the type of return or payout trigger for the swap or forward.

Field.Name: UnderlyingDeliveryRouteOrCharter
Field.Description: Specific delivery route or time charter average. Applicable to commodity freight contracts.

Field.Name: UnderlyingReturnTrigger
Field.Description: Indicates the type of return or payout trigger for the swap or forward.

Field.Name: AllocRequestID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for the request message.

Field.Name: GroupAmount
Field.Description: Indicates the total notional units or amount of an allocation group. Includes any allocated units or amount.
