Field.Elaboration: Whether notional units or amount is used depends on the type of listed derivative contract and the clearinghouse. A notional unit is (price x quantity) without the derivative's contract value factor.

Field.Name: GroupRemainingAmount
Field.Description: Indicates the remaining notional units or amount of an allocation group that has not yet been allocated.
Field.Elaboration: Whether notional units or amount is used depends on the type of listed derivative contract and the clearinghouse. A notional unit is (price x quantity) without the derivative's contract value factor.

Field.Name: AllocGroupAmount
Field.Description: Indicates the notional units or amount being allocated.
Field.Elaboration: Whether notional units or amount is used depends on the type of listed derivative contract and the clearinghouse. A notional unit is (price x quantity) without the derivative's contract value factor.

Field.Name: PriceMarkup
Field.Description: Price offset of the markup denominated in the price type of the trade.
Field.Elaboration: The field is expressed in a value that can simply be added to or subtracted from the (clean) price to reach the marked- up price. E.g., a percent of par price of 98 marked up to 98.5 should be 0.5, an FX rate of 1.17936 marked up to 1.19 should be 0.01064, a stock price of 22.75 marked up to 22.9 should be 0.15, etc.

Field.Name: AveragePriceType
Field.Description: The average pricing model used for block trades.

Field.Name: AveragePriceStartTime
Field.Description: Start of the time period during which price averaging occurred.

Field.Name: AveragePriceEndTime
Field.Description: End of the time period during which price averaging occurred.

Field.Name: OrderPercentOfTotalVolume
Field.Description: For Percent-of-volume (POV) average pricing this is the target percentage this order quantity represents of the total trading volume of an instrument during the specified time period. This provides the data needed to ensure that the average price is fair based on the total sum of grouped POV trades.
Field.Elaboration: For example, if during the POV time period there are 5 trades including this one with a total volume of 5000 and this trade has a quantity of 1000 then the OrderPercentOfTotalVolume(2766) of this trade is 20 percent expressed as "0.20".

Field.Name: AllocGroupStatus
Field.Description: Status of the trade give-up relative to the group identified in AllocGroupID(1730).

Field.Name: AllocRequestStatus
Field.Description: Status of the AllocationInstructionAlertRequest(35=DU).

Field.Name: AllocAvgPxIndicator
Field.Description: Average pricing indicator at the allocation level.

Field.Name: AllocAvgPxGroupID
Field.Description: Used by submitting firm to group trades being sub-allocated into an average price group. The trades in the average price group will be used to calculate an average price for the group.

Field.Name: PreviousAllocGroupID
Field.Description: When reporting a group change by the central counterparty to allocations of trades for the same instrument traded at the same price this identifies the previous group identifier.

Field.Name: NoMatchExceptions
Field.Description: Number of match exceptions in the repeating group.

Field.Name: MatchExceptionType
Field.Description: Type of matching exception.

Field.Name: MatchExceptionElementType
Field.Description: Identifies the data point used in the matching operation which resulted in an exception.

Field.Name: MatchExceptionElementName
Field.Description: The matching exception data point name, for example: "Trade currency". This may be used for display purposes, providing a corresponding description for the value in MatchExceptionElementType(2774).

Field.Name: MatchExceptionAllocValue
Field.Description: The allocating party's data value used in the match operation.

Field.Name: MatchExceptionConfirmValue
Field.Description: The confirming party's data value used in the match operation.

Field.Name: MatchExceptionToleranceValue
Field.Description: The data element's tolerance value. Omitted if no tolerance is allowed or not applicable.

Field.Name: MatchExceptionToleranceValueType
Field.Description: The type of value in MatchExceptionToleranceValue(2778). Omitted if no tolerance is allowed or not applicable.
Field.Elaboration: For example, if the tolerance for accrued interest is 0.01% of total accrued interest then MatchExceptionElementType(2774)=1 (Accrued interest), MatchExceptionToleranceValueType(2779)=2 (Percentage) and MatchExcecptionToleranceValue(2778)=0.0001. If tolerance for the exchange rate of an FX trade is "0.001" then MatchExceptionElementType(2774)=2 (Deal pPrice), MatchExceptionToleranceValueType(2779)=1 (Fixed amount) and MatchExcecptionToleranceValue(2778)=0.001.

Field.Name: MatchExceptionText
Field.Description: Description of the exception.

Field.Name: NoMatchingDataPoints
Field.Description: Number of matching data points in the repeating group.

Field.Name: MatchingDataPointIndicator
Field.Description: Data point's matching type.

Field.Name: MatchingDataPointValue
Field.Description: Value of the matching data point.

Field.Name: MatchingDataPointType
Field.Description: Identifies the data point used in the matching operation.
Field.Elaboration: Values may not have applicable tolerance values, in this case this means the data point was used for matching but did not match.

Field.Name: MatchingDataPointName
Field.Description: The matching data point name, for example: "Trade currency". This may be used for display purposes, providing a corresponding description for the value in MatchingDataPointType(2784).

Field.Name: EncodedMatchExceptionTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedMatchExceptionText(2798) field.

Field.Name: EncodedMatchExecptionText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the MatchExceptionText(2780) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding(347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the MatchExceptionText(2780) field.

Field.Name: TradeAggregationRequestID
Field.Description: The message identifier for the trade aggregation request.

Field.Name: TradeAggregationRequestRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier to a previously sent trade aggregation message being cancelled or replaced.

Field.Name: TradeAggregationTransType
Field.Description: Identifies the trade aggregation transaction type.

Field.Name: AggregatedQty
Field.Description: Total quantity of orders or fills quantity aggregated.

Field.Name: TradeAggregationRequestStatus
Field.Description: Status of the trade aggregation request.

Field.Name: TradeAggregationRejectReason
Field.Description: Reason for trade aggregation request being rejected.

Field.Name: TradeAggregationReportID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for the TradeAggregationReport(35=DX).

Field.Name: AvgSpotRate
Field.Description: The average FX spot rate.

Field.Name: AvgForwardPoints
Field.Description: The average forward points. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: OffshoreIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates the type of the currency rate being used. This is relevant for currencies that have offshore rate that different from onshore rate.

Field.Name: FXBenchmarkRateFix
Field.Description: Specifies the foreign exchange benchmark rate fixing to be used in valuing the transaction. For example "London 4 p.m." or "Tokyo 3 p.m."

Field.Name: PayReportID
Field.Description: Unique ID of the PayManagementReport(35=EA) message.

Field.Name: PayDisputeReason
Field.Description: Used to provide the reason for disputing a request or report. See https://www.fixtrading.org/packages/PayDisputeReason for the list of applicable values.

Field.Name: EncodedReplaceText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ReplaceText(2805) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding(347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ReplaceText(2805) field.

Field.Name: EncodedReplaceTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedReplaceText(2801) field.

Field.Name: PayReportRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier of the PayManagementReport(35=EA). To be used with PayReportTransType(2804)=1 (Replace).

Field.Name: PayReportTransType
Field.Description: Identifies the message transaction type.

Field.Name: ReplaceText
Field.Description: Identifies the reason for amendment.

Field.Name: PayReportStatus
Field.Description: Identifies status of the payment report.

Field.Name: CancelText
Field.Description: Identifies the reason for cancelation.

Field.Name: EncodedCancelText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the CancelText(2807) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding(347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the CancelText(2807) field.

Field.Name: EncodedCancelTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedCancelText(2808) field.

Field.Name: PayRequestRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier of the PayManagementRequest(35=DY). To be used with PayRequestTransType(2811)=1 (Cancel).

Field.Name: PayRequestTransType
Field.Description: Identifies the message transaction type.

Field.Name: PayRequestID
Field.Description: Unique ID of the PayManagementRequest(35=DY) message.

Field.Name: PayRequestStatus
Field.Description: Identifies status of the request being responded to.

Field.Name: EncodedPostTradePaymentDesc
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the PostTradePaymentDesc(2820) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding(347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the PostTradePaymentDesc(2820) field.

Field.Name: EncodedPostTradePaymentDescLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedPostTradePaymentDesc(2814) field.

Field.Name: PostTradePaymentAccount
Field.Description: The cash account on the books of the receiver of the request or the sender of the report to be debited or credited.

Field.Name: PostTradePaymentAmount
Field.Description: The payment amount for the specified PostTradePaymentType(2824).

Field.Name: PostTradePaymentCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies the currency in which PostTradePaymentAmount(2817) is denominated. Uses ISO 4271 currency codes.

Field.Name: PostTradePaymentDebitOrCredit
Field.Description: Payment side of this individual payment from the requesting firm's perspective.

Field.Name: PostTradePaymentDesc
Field.Description: A short descriptive name given to the payment, e.g. Premium, Upfront, etc. The description may be used as reference.

Field.Name: PostTradePaymentID
Field.Description: The identifier for the individual payment.

Field.Name: PostTradePaymentLinkID
Field.Description: Used to link a group of payments together, e.g. cross-currency payments associated with a swap.

Field.Name: PostTradePaymentStatus
Field.Description: Used to indicate the status of a post-trade payment.

Field.Name: PostTradePaymentType
Field.Description: Type of post-trade payment. See ISITC "Payments Cash Purpose Codes" for list of payment type codes to use available at https://isitc.org/market-practices/reference-data-and-standards-market-practice and select "ISITC Classification Code List".

Field.Name: PostTradePaymentCalculationDate
Field.Description: The (actual) date the periodic payments calculations are made.

Field.Name: PostTradePaymentValueDate
Field.Description: The adjusted (for holidays and other non-business days) payment date on which the payment is expected to settle.

Field.Name: PostTradePaymentFinalValueDate
Field.Description: The actual or final payment date on which the payment was made.

Field.Name: CurrentDisplayPrice
Field.Description: Price at which the order is currently displayed to the market. Can be used on order messages, e.g. NewOrderSingle(35=D), to provide the current displayed price of a parent order when splitting it into smaller child orders.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of US CAT this is used when reporting new child orders.

Field.Name: DuplicateClOrdIDIndicator
Field.Description: Used to indicate that a ClOrdID(11) value is an intentional duplicate of a previously sent value. Allows to avoid the rejection of an order with OrdRejReason(103) = 6 (Duplicate Order).
Field.Elaboration: In the context of US CAT this can be used when the recipient of a previously routed order requires the same identifier to be re-used for a new route.

Field.Name: EventInitiatorType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of entity who initiated an event, e.g. modification or cancellation of an order or quote.

Field.Name: NBBOEntryType
Field.Description: Type of NBBO information.

Field.Name: NBBOPrice
Field.Description: Price related to NBBO. NBBOEntryType(2831) may be used to indicate entry type, e.g. bid or offer.

Field.Name: NBBOQty
Field.Description: Quantity related to NBBO. NBBOEntryType(2831) may be used to indicte entry type, e.g. bid or offer.

Field.Name: NBBOSource
Field.Description: Source of NBBO information.

Field.Name: OrderOriginationFirmID
Field.Description: Identifier for the original owner of an order as part of the OrderAggregationGrp component. Use the Parties component with PartyRole(452) = 13 (Order Origination Firm) to identify the original owner of an individual order outside of an aggregation.

Field.Name: OrderTime
Field.Description: Timestamp for the assignment of a (unique) identifier to an order.

Field.Name: SingleQuoteIndicator
Field.Description: Used to indicate whether the quoting system allows only one quote to be active at a time for the quote issuer or market maker.

Field.Name: CurrentWorkingPrice
Field.Description: Current working price of the order relative to the state of the order.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of US CAT this can be used for the current price of the parent order when reporting a split into new (child) orders.

Field.Name: TrdRegTimestampManualIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether a given timestamp was manually captured.

Field.Name: CollateralReinvestmentRate
Field.Description: Interest rate received for collateral reinvestment.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of EU SFTR this is the reinvestment interest rate received from cash collateral made by the lender. If there are multiple reinvestment types, this is an average rate.

Field.Name: UnderlyingRefID
Field.Description: Identifies the underlying instrument the entity applies to by referencing the underlying instrument's UnderlyingID(2874).

Field.Name: CollateralReinvestmentAmount
Field.Description: The cash amount of the specified re-investment type.

Field.Name: CollateralReinvestmentCurrency
Field.Description: The currency denomination of the re-invested cash amount. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: CollateralReinvestmentType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of investment the cash collateral is re-invested in.

Field.Name: NoCollateralReinvestments
Field.Description: Number of instances of CollateralReinvestmentType(2844) in the repeating group.

Field.Name: FundingSource
Field.Description: Specifies the funding source used to finance margin or collateralized loan.

Field.Name: FundingSourceCurrency
Field.Description: Currency denomination of the market value of the funding source. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: FundingSourceMarketValue
Field.Description: Market value of the funding source.

Field.Name: NoFundingSources
Field.Description: Number of instances of FundingSource(2846) in the repeating group.

Field.Name: LegPaymentStreamOtherDayCount
Field.Description: The industry name of the day count convention not listed in LegPaymentStreamDayCount(40283).

Field.Name: MarginDirection
Field.Description: Indicates whether the margin described is posted or received.

Field.Name: PaymentFixedRate
Field.Description: The rate applicable to the fixed rate payment.

Field.Name: PaymentFloatingRateIndex
Field.Description: The payment floating rate index. See SpreadOrBenchmarkCurveData(221) for suggested values.

Field.Name: PaymentFloatingRateIndexCurvePeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the floating rate index.

Field.Name: PaymentFloatingRateIndexCurveUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the floating rate index.

Field.Name: PaymentFloatingRateSpread
Field.Description: Spread from floating rate index.

Field.Name: PaymentFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the payment frequency.

Field.Name: PaymentFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the payment frequency.

Field.Name: PaymentRateResetFrequencyPeriod
Field.Description: Time unit multiplier for the floating rate reset frequency.

Field.Name: PaymentRateResetFrequencyUnit
Field.Description: Time unit associated with the floating rate reset frequency.

Field.Name: PaymentStreamOtherDayCount
Field.Description: The industry name of the day count convention not listed in PaymentStreamDayCount(40742).

Field.Name: SideCollateralReinvestmentRate
Field.Description: Interest rate received for collateral reinvestment.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of EU SFTR this is the reinvestment interest rate received from cash collateral made by the lender. If there are multiple reinvestment types, this is an average rate.

Field.Name: SideUnderlyingRefID
Field.Description: Identifies the underlying instrument the entity applies to by referencing the underlying instrument's UnderlyingID(2874).

Field.Name: NoSideCollateralReinvestments
Field.Description: Number of instances of SideCollateralReinvestmentType(2867) in the repeating group.

Field.Name: SideCollateralReinvestmentAmount
Field.Description: The cash amount of the specified re-investment type.

Field.Name: SideCollateralReinvestmentCurrency
Field.Description: The currency denomination of the re-invested cash amount. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Field.Name: SideCollateralReinvestmentType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of investment the cash collateral is re-invested in.

Field.Name: CollateralizationValueDate
Field.Description: Date when the collateral is to be assessed or assigned.

Field.Name: RegulatoryReportTypeBusinessDate
Field.Description: The business date on which the event identified in RegulatoryReportType(1934) took place.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of EU SFTR reports with a RegulatoryReportType(1934) value 7 (Post-trade valuation), 31 (Collateral update) or 32 (Margin update), the business date on which the business event took place, which results in the information contained in the report.

Field.Name: ClearingPortfolioID
Field.Description: When the transaction is cleared and included in a portfolio of transactions this identifies the portfolio by its unique identifier.
Field.Elaboration: In the context of EU SFTR reporting this applies to cleared transactions grouped in a portfolio for which margins are exchanged.

Field.Name: NoTransactionAttributes
Field.Description: Number of instances of TransactionAttributeType(2872) in the repeating group.

Field.Name: TransactionAttributeType
Field.Description: Type of attribute(s) or characteristic(s) associated with the transaction.

Field.Name: TransactionAttributeValue
Field.Description: Value associated with the specificed TransactionAttributeType(2872).

Field.Name: UnderlyingID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for the underlying instrument within the context of a message.
Field.Elaboration: The UnderlyingID(2874) can be referenced by other fields, for example UnderlyingRefID(tbd2841) and SideUnderlyingRefID(2863), from other components . The scope of uniqueness is agreed upon between counterparties.

Field.Name: UnderlyingPaymentStreamOtherDayCount
Field.Description: The industry name of the day count convention not listed in UnderlyingPaymentStreamDayCount(40572).

Field.Name: PosAmtPrice
Field.Description: The price used to calculate the PosAmt(708).
Field.Elaboration: This may be used for certain PosAmtType(707) values where the PosAmt(708) is based on the current price of the position's security. In the context of EU SFTR reporting, this is the price used to calculate the loan value for securities loan and borrowing, and buy-sell back. The price may be expressed in units or percentage of the underlying security, yield or an absolute amount that ignores netting. For Buy/Sellback it expresses the initial spot price.

Field.Name: PosAmtPriceType
Field.Description: Specifies the type of price for PosAmtPrice(2876).

Field.Name: TerminationDate
Field.Description: The date of a contract's early termination or other post-trade event when the event is prior to the contract natural end or maturity not defined as part of the security's reference data or contractual terms/agreement.

Field.Name: CouponOtherDayCount
Field.Description: The industry name of the day count convention not listed in CouponDayCount(1950).

Field.Name: LegCouponOtherDayCount
Field.Description: The industry name of the day count convention not listed in LegCouponDayCount(2165).

Field.Name: UnderlyingCouponOtherDayCount
Field.Description: The industry name of the day count convention not listed in UnderlyingCouponDayCount(1993).
